)@@G@@ODE OF SYMBOLS    @G@@@[ REPRESENTATING IMMEDIATE DATA WHICH ARE USED BEUJ
)@@G@@FORE THE APPEARANCE     @G@@@[ OF THEIR DEFINING  EQUF  STATEMENTS.  'D'UK
)@@G@@-FLAGS MAY ALSO BE CAUSED     @F@@@[ BY THE PRESENCE OF EXTRA STATEMENTSUL
)@@G@@ WITHIN A BLOCK, E.G., TWO    @F@@@[ 'ELSE' STATEMENTS IN AN 'IF' BLOCK,UM
)@@G@@ OR EXTRA 'END' STATEMENTS OF @F@@@[ SOME KIND.  'D'-FLAGS OCCUR AT THE UN

)@@G@@RILY THE POINT AT WHICH THE   @F@@@[ ERROR WAS MADE, A 'D'-FLAG MAY MEANUP

)@@G@@     SYNTAX ERRORS ON THE DEFINING STATEMENTS OF A CONTROL  @F@@@[ STRUCUR
)@@G@@TURE ARE INDICATED BY 'E'-FLAGS. SUCH FLAGS MAY BE CAUSED BY@G@@@[ AN UNUS
)@@G@@RECOGNIZEABLE KEYWORD OR BY THE OMISSION OF A REQUIRED FIELD.     @F@@@[UT

)@@G@@SSES TO THEM, AND @^@@@[ IN WHICH THEY EXIT.    @#@@@[2PROGRAM TYPES    BC
)@@G@@@F@@@[     A MAINPROGRAM IS DEFINED AS A PROGRAM MODULE WHICH RECEIVES  BD
)@@G@@@F@@@[ CONTROL DIRECTLY FROM THE OPERATING SYSTEM, AND EXITS BACK TO IT.BE
)@@G@@@F@@@[ IT MAY BE THE DRIVING MODULE OF A PROGRAM, OR MAY BE A SEPERATE  BF
)@@G@@@F@@@[ ACTIVITY ACTIVATED VIA AN ER FORK$ FROM ANOTHER ACTIVITY OF THE  BG
)@@G@@@G@@@[ SAME PROGRAM.  ITS EXECUTION IS ASYNCHRONOUS WITH THE MODULE WHICBH
)@@G@@H     @G@@@[ INITIATES IT.  TERMINATION OF THE BLOCK OCCURS AT EXECUTIONBI
)@@G@@ OF THE     @F@@@[ 'ENDBEG' STATEMENT. NORMAL TERMINATION IS A RETURN TOBJ
)@@G@@ THE SYSTEM @F@@@[ VIA THE EXIT$ REQUEST.  IF SIGNALLING IS SPECIFIED, RBK
)@@G@@ETURN TO THE@F@@@[ SYSTEM CAN BE BY EXIT$, ERR$, EABT$, OR ABORT$, DEPENBL
)@@G@@DING ON THE @A@@@[ SIGNAL INDEX VALUE (SEE BELOW).    @]@@@[SPACE 1     BM
)@@G@@@F@@@[     A CONTINGENCY ROUTINE IS A MODULE WHICH RECEIVES CONTROL FROMBN
)@@G@@@F@@@[ THE OPERATING SYSTEM BY MEANS OF AN INTERRUPT WITHIN SOME OTHER  BO
)@@G@@@F@@@[ PORTION OF THE USER PROGRAM.  ITS EXECUTION IS ALWAYS SYNCHRONOUSBP
)@@G@@@F@@@[ WITH THE INTERRUPTED PROGRAM MODULE.  THE 'CONTINGENCY PACKET' ISBQ
)@@G@@@F@@@[ ASSOCIATED WITH THE BEGIN STATEMENT, AND MAY BE REFERENCED BY THEBR
)@@G@@@F@@@[ LABEL ASSOCIATED WITH IT.  CONTINGENCY ROUTINES DIFFER FROM MAIN BS
)@@G@@@F@@@[ PROGRAMS IN THAT THEY CAN RELINQUISH CONTROL EITHER BY RESUMING  BT
)@@G@@@G@@@[ THE INTERRUPTED PROGRAM OR BY RETURNING TO THE OPERATING SYSTEM. BU
)@@G@@A     @F@@@[ 'NORMAL' EXIT (NO SIGNALLING SPECIFIED) RESUMES THE INTERRUBV
)@@G@@PTED  @F@@@[ PROGRAM AT THE LOCATION WHOSE ADDRESS IS SPECIFIED IN THE LBW

)@@G@@AS BEEN     @F@@@[ SPECIFIED, RETURN CAN BE EITHER TO THE INTERRUPTED PRBY
)@@G@@OGRAM MODULE@F@@@[ OR THE SYSTEM.  IN THIS CASE, THE FIRST WORD OF THE CBZ
)@@G@@ONTINGENCY  @G@@@[ PACKET (OR THE SIGNAL WORD, IF ONE WAS SPECIFIED) IS CA

)@@G@@E INTERRUPTED     @F@@@[ PROGRAM IS RESUMED AT THE ADDRESS SPECIFIED BY CC

)@@G@@@]@@@[SPACE 1     @F@@@[      THE EXECSUB BLOCK TYPE IS DESIGNED FOR CODCJ
)@@G@@E WHICH WILL BE   @F@@@[ IMBEDDED IN THE EXEC8 OPERATING SYSTEM ITSELF. CK

)@@G@@IVALENT.    @#@@@[3TABLE SEARCHING  @F@@@[     A SPECIAL FORM OF CONDITIMK
)@@G@@ON TEST IS AVAILABLE TO DETERMINE   @F@@@[ WHETHER A SPECIFIED VALUE APPML

)@@G@@NSTRUCTIONS TO EXAMINE THE CONTENTS @F@@@[ OF THE SPECIFIED TABLE. THE TMO

)@@G@@COUNT OF TOTAL NO BLOX (ALL KINDS EXCEPT BEGIN) @A@@@[.       2 = GLOBALKP

)@@G@@ASS THIS IS @[@@@[.     @G@@@[G$CTR*(6) EQU 1-G$CTR(6)            . SET KW
)@@G@@FLAG: ON IF ASSEMBLER PASS 1  @D@@@[G$CTR*(7) EQU      1-G$CTR(6)       KX
)@@G@@. ON IF PASS 2    @G@@@[ DO G$CTR(7) , BRIEF                  . ON PASS KY

)@@G@@-------     @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @H@@@[G$AMPR*    EQU      &(5)=-2   LB

)@@G@@LER HAS BRIEF DIRECTIVE @F@@@[          RES       FIXUP-$           . MALI

)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @G@@@[          END                         . END DEFN OF MALN
)@@G@@STER MAGIC PROC   @ @@@[/. ***** DIAGNOSTICS *****    @[@@@[.     @[@@@[LO
)@@G@@.     @A@@@[. FIELDS IN ERROR MESSAGE FORM ARE: @C@@@[.    FIELD 1: TYPELP
)@@G@@ OF CURRENTLY ACTIVE BLOCK    @E@@@[.             TYPES ARE 1=>BEGIN, 2=LQ
)@@G@@>IF, 3=>CASE, 4=>REPEAT @A@@@[.          2: CURRENT NESTING DEPTH @F@@@[LR

)@@G@@.          4: ERROR TYPE@ @@@[.          5: ERROR SUBTYPE   @[@@@[.     LT
)@@G@@@F@@@[. LOCATION COUNTER ERRORS (MESSAGE CLASS=0) ARE SIGNALLED WHEN    LU
)@@G@@@E@@@[. SOME CODE PREVIOUS TO THE POINT OF THE MESSAGE GENERATES  @F@@@[LV
)@@G@@. A DIFFERENT NUMBER OF INSTRUCTIONS ON ASSEMBLER PASSES ONE AND  @F@@@[LW
)@@G@@. TWO (ASSEMBLER D-FLAG). AT THE POINT OF DETECTION, STRUC$ WILL  @F@@@[LX
)@@G@@. ATTEMPT TO FORESTALL SPURIOUS ERRORS OF THIS TYPE IN THE CODE   @G@@@[LY
)@@G@@. WHICH FOLLOWS BY FORCING THE LOCATION COUNTER TO WHAT IT BELIEVES     LZ
)@@G@@@F@@@[. THE CORRECT VALUE SHOULD BE. THE ERROR TYPE AND SUBTYPE FIELDS  MA
)@@G@@@F@@@[. ARE INTERNAL SERIAL NUMBERS, AND HAVE NO SPECIAL SIGNIFICANCE.  MB
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @G@@@[. FOR SYNTAX ERRORS (MESSAGE CLASS=1), ERROR TYPES ANDMC
)@@G@@ SUBTYPES ARE:    @[@@@[.     @B@@@[.    1,X => ERROR IN SPECIFICATION OMD
)@@G@@F TEST@C@@@[.     ,01      UNRECOGNIZEABLE TYPE OF TEST     @B@@@[.     ME
)@@G@@,02      UNRECOGNIZEABLE KEYWORD    @B@@@[.    2,X => ERROR IN <VARY> SPMF
)@@G@@ECIFICATION @C@@@[.     ,01      OFFSET REQUIRES IMMEDIATE 'BY'   @E@@@[MG
)@@G@@.     ,02      LOOKFOR FORMAT REQUIRES 'BY' SPECIFICATION   @D@@@[.     MH
)@@G@@,03      REQUIRED FROM, TO, OR BY SPEC MISSING  @E@@@[.     ,04      LOOMI
)@@G@@P CONTROL VARIABLE PASSES THROUGH ZERO    @E@@@[.     ,05      SIGN OF BMJ
)@@G@@Y CONFLICTS WITH SIGN OF TO-FROM    @F@@@[.     ,06      EXPLICIT SENSE MK
)@@G@@(UP/DOWN) CONFLICTS WITH BY, TO-FROM@D@@@[.     ,07      REQUIRED 'BY' SML
)@@G@@PECIFICATION NOT GIVEN  @C@@@[.     ,010     BAD KEYWORD FOLLOWING 'LOOKMM
)@@G@@FOR'  @ @@@[.    3,X => PARAMETER ERROR   @D@@@[.     ,01      CASEREGISMN
)@@G@@TER NOT OVERLAPPED (A0-A3)    @D@@@[.     ,02      REQUIRED REGISTER SPEMO
)@@G@@CIFICATION MISSING@D@@@[.     ,03      INCORRECT NUMBER OF FIELDS ON 'IFMP
)@@G@@'     @D@@@[.     ,04      MISSING 'WHEN' ON ESCAPE STATEMENT     @F@@@[MQ
)@@G@@.     ,05      MINIMUM SPECIFIED CASE NOT ZERO (CALLING OPTION)   @F@@@[MR
)@@G@@.     ,06      ALL CASE VALUES NOT SPECIFIED (CALLING OPTION)     @[@@@[MS
)@@G@@.     @F@@@[. FOR STRUCTURE ERRORS (MESSAGE CLASS=2) , TYPES AND SUBTYPEMT
)@@G@@S ARE:@[@@@[.     @ @@@[.    1,X => NESTING ERROR     @F@@@[.     ,01   MU
)@@G@@   TOO MANY OR TOO FEW END STATMENTS IN PREVIOUS BLOCK@F@@@[.     ,02   MV
)@@G@@   MISSING END IN PREVIOUS BLOCK MAY CAUSE D-FLAGS    @E@@@[.     ,03   MW
)@@G@@   STATEMENT CANNOT APPEAR IN CURRENT BLOCK TYPE@F@@@[.              EITMX
)@@G@@HER THE END STATEMENT FOR THE PREVIOUS BLOCK OR @G@@@[.              THEMY
)@@G@@ START STATEMENT FOR THE CURRENT BLOCK IS MISSING     @D@@@[.    2,X => MZ
)@@G@@INCONSISTENT LOGIC (STATEMENTS OR FIELDS) @G@@@[.     ,01      ESCAPE INNA
)@@G@@VALID IF BOTH WHILE/LOOKFOR AND UNTIL ARE GIVEN @E@@@[.     ,02      OTHNB
)@@G@@ERWISE STMNT MEANINGLESS, NO ESCAPE GIVEN @F@@@[.     ,03      ATEND UNRNC
)@@G@@EACHABLE, NO TESTS APPEARED ON REPEAT     @F@@@[.     ,05      NOFIND COND
)@@G@@DE ILLEGAL WITH CALLING OPTION (CASE)     @ @@@[.    3,X => MISCELLANEOUNE
)@@G@@S     @E@@@[.     ,01      ATTEMPT TO CHANGE LOCATION COUNTERS WITHIN   NF
)@@G@@@F@@@[.              A BLOCK. BLOCKS MUST BE WHOLLY CONTAINED WITHIN    NG
)@@G@@@F@@@[.              A SINGLE BANK. SWITCHING BETWEEN BANKS MUST BE     NH
)@@G@@@D@@@[.              ACCOMPLISHED VIA A SUBROUTINE CALL     @[@@@[.     NI
)@@G@@@#@@@[          DEF     @H@@@[G$ERFO    FORM      3,6,3,12,12     . A DINJ
)@@G@@STINCTIVE FORM FOR ERROR MESSAGES   @#@@@[P       PROC   *2 @[@@@[.     NK
)@@G@@@^@@@[G$$GFL*   NAME      2   @[@@@[.     @D@@@[. FORCE DEFINITION OF PRNL
)@@G@@OC NEEDED TO FORCE G-FLAGS    @[@@@[.     @#@@@[          PROC    @#@@@[NM
)@@G@@G$$FRG**  NAME    @]@@@[ GO G$$DIA  @#@@@[          END     @[@@@[.     NN
)@@G@@@C@@@[. NOW G-FLAG GENERATOR ACTUALLY DOES ITS THING  @[@@@[.     @F@@@[NO
)@@G@@ GO G$$FRG          . LEAP TO OTHER PROC, WHICH LEAPS TO G$$DIA   @[@@@[NP
)@@G@@.     @[@@@[.     @I@@@[G$$IFL*  NAME       3                 . THIS ENTNQ
)@@G@@RY FOR TRULY INVALID INSTRUCTION    @H@@@[          RES       1         NR
)@@G@@        . WHICH ACTUALLY TAKES SPACE IN THE CODE@C@@@[ GO G$$DIA        NS
)@@G@@  . GO DISPLAY THE MESSAGE    @[@@@[.     @E@@@[G$$EFL*  NAME       1   NT
)@@G@@              . GENERATE AN E-FLAG  @#@@@[A       EQU    +) @]@@@[ GO G$NU
)@@G@@$DIA  @[@@@[.     @^@@@[G$$DFL*  NAME       0   @E@@@[G$DFLG****        NV
)@@G@@              . GENERATE A GLOBAL D-FLAG  @G@@@[ DO P(1)>0 , RES P(1,1)-NW
)@@G@@$             . THEN FORCE LC BACK INTO PHASE   @]@@@[ GO G$$DIA  @[@@@[NX
)@@G@@.     @E@@@[G$$TFL*  NAME       4                 . GENERATE A T-FLAG   NY
)@@G@@@A@@@[A       EQU    + (I$ 0,0,0,0,077,0) @[@@@[.     @F@@@[. NOW WE GENNZ
)@@G@@ERATE THE MESSAGES. TO AVOID EXTRANEOUS D-FLAGS ON    @E@@@[. THE USER'SOA
)@@G@@ LISTING, NEGATIVE RES'S ARE USED TO INSURE THAT@F@@@[. THE MESSAGES DO OB
)@@G@@NOT OCCUPY ANY SPACE IN THE PROGRAM'S ADDRESS   @F@@@[. SPACE. TO INSUREOC
)@@G@@ THAT THE MESSAGE DOES NOT GO UNNOTICED, WE     @G@@@[. TRASH ON THE LASOD
)@@G@@T WORD OF GENERATED USER CODE, MAKING IT AN IOPR.     @[@@@[.     @E@@@[OE
)@@G@@. TO AVOID SURPRESSION IF BRIEF MODE IS ON, THE DIAGNOSTIC  @D@@@[. MESSOF
)@@G@@AGE SENTINAL WORD IS THE 1ST ONE GENERATED.     @[@@@[.     @G@@@[G$$DIAOG
)@@G@@*   NAME                        . DIAGNOSTIC PRINTOUT STARTS HERE @H@@@[OH
)@@G@@          RES       -1                . GET RID OF USER'S LAST INSTRUCTIOI
)@@G@@ON    @F@@@[K         EQU       1+(P(0,0)=0)      . SPEC TO FIND FLAGS IOJ
)@@G@@N     @F@@@[M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . CURRENT NESTING LEVEOK
)@@G@@L     @D@@@[          G$ERFO    G$TYPE(M),M,P(0,0),P(K,1),P(K,2)  @#@@@[OL
)@@G@@          UNLIST  @F@@@[          G$$IFLAG                    . MARK THIOM
)@@G@@S ELEMENT IN ERROR@G@@@[          RES       -2                . PURGE SEON
)@@G@@NTINAL AND IFLAG WORD   @H@@@[          +0                          . FOOO
)@@G@@RCE PROG TO IOPR IF ITS EXECUTED    @#@@@[          LIST    @E@@@[      OP
)@@G@@    END                         . OF DIAGNOSTIC PROCS @C@@@[/.    ******OQ
)@@G@@** PROGRAM DEFINITION GROUP ********@[@@@[.     @ @@@[. ARRAY USAGE BY BOR
)@@G@@EGIN BLOCKS:@[@@@[.     @F@@@[.    G$LABL(K,1) ENTRY POINT TO BLOCK (=PKOS
)@@G@@T ADDR IF CONTINGENCY)  @B@@@[.             2) EXIT POINT FROM BLOCK    OT
)@@G@@@E@@@[.             3) ADDR OF GENERATED REG SAVE AREA (IF ANY)   @C@@@[OU
)@@G@@.             4) ADDR OF SIGNAL CELL, IF ANY    @[@@@[.     @E@@@[.    GOV
)@@G@@$FLAG(K,1) XREG USED FOR SIGNALLING, ZERO IF NONE     @B@@@[.           OW
)@@G@@  2) NUMBER OF SAVED REGISTERS@C@@@[.             2,N) AXR$ VALUE OF N'TOX
)@@G@@H SAVED REG @C@@@[.             3) BLOCK TYPE (MAINPROG, ETC.)    @[@@@[OY
)@@G@@.     @C@@@[.               ******************************* @C@@@[.     OZ
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@[.               *       PA
)@@G@@    BEGIN             * @C@@@[.               *                         PB
)@@G@@    * @C@@@[.               ******************************* @[@@@[.     PC
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @#@@@[           DEF    @H@@@[F          FUNC   PD
)@@G@@                    . ----- UTILITY FUNC USED IN SORTING    @#@@@[G$$INCPE
)@@G@@*    NAME   @D@@@[III*(1)    EQU              III(1)+1  . BUMP COUNTER  PF
)@@G@@@E@@@[           END              III(1)    . RETURN NEW VALUE    @[@@@[PG
)@@G@@.     @[@@@[.     @#@@@[P       PROC   *3 @]@@@[BEGIN*  NAME@H@@@[ DO 1-PH
)@@G@@(G$CTR(5)=0) , G$$GFL 1,1               . REQUIRE NESTING DEPTH ZERO    PI
)@@G@@@F@@@[M         EQU       1                 . FORCE NEW NESTING DEPTH   PJ
)@@G@@@D@@@[G$CTR*(5) EQU  M                      . THEN SAVE IT  @F@@@[ DO 1-PK
)@@G@@(G$CTR(2)=0) , G$$GFL 1,2               . REQUIRE NO FLOAT  @[@@@[.     PL
)@@G@@@F@@@[K         EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SERIAL NUMBER   PM
)@@G@@@D@@@[G$CTR*(1) EQU       K                 . AND UPDATE IT @D@@@[G$TYPEPN
)@@G@@*(M) EQU      1                 . SET BLOCK TYPE@E@@@[G$SEQN*(M) EQU    PO
)@@G@@  K                 . SAVE SERIAL NUMBER  @[@@@[.     @E@@@[T         EQPP
)@@G@@U  P(1,1)+(P(1)=0)*MAINPROGRAM . GET PROG TYPE  @E@@@[G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU TPQ
)@@G@@                     . AND REMEMBER IT    @[@@@[.     @B@@@[. ALLOW 'NOSPR
)@@G@@AVE' TO DEFAULT TO SUBFIELD 2 @[@@@[.     @H@@@[NOSDEF    EQU       (T=SPS
)@@G@@UBROUTINE)**(P(1)=2)**(P(1,2)=NOSAVE) . NOSAVE DEFAULT@E@@@[ DO NOSDEF ,PT
)@@G@@P(1,3) EQU NOSAVE         . FORCE THIRD FIELD   @D@@@[ DO NOSDEF ,P(1,2)PU
)@@G@@ EQU 0              . CLEAR REGISTER@G@@@[ DO NOSDEF ,P(1)   EQU 3      PV
)@@G@@        . NOW NOTE THERE ARE 3 SUBFIELDS  @[@@@[.     @E@@@[ DO G$CTR(7)PW
)@@G@@ , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,1)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,1)    @E@@@[G$LABL*(K,1)      PX
)@@G@@              . SAVE ENTRY POINT TO BLOK  @[@@@[.     @E@@@[          REPY
)@@G@@S       G$CTR(6)          . ALLOW ZERO AS A FLAG@E@@@[G$CTR*(2) EQU     PZ
)@@G@@  -G$CTR(7)         . SET GLOBAL FLOAT    @[@@@[.     @H@@@[ DO T=CYCLICQA
)@@G@@ , END                 . SINCE CYCLICS NEVER EXIT, WE'RE DONE     @G@@@[QB
)@@G@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY , +0D               . IF CONTING, GENERATE PACKET     QC
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @G@@@[.              HANDLE EXITS WHICH SIGNAL THE EXEC (MAIQD
)@@G@@N/CONTINGENCY)    @[@@@[.     @F@@@[GI      EQU    (P(1,1)=SIGNAL)+2*(P(QE
)@@G@@2,1)=SIGNAL)+3*(P(3,1)=SIGNAL)@F@@@[. SIGNAL XREG IS FLAG, IF NONE (<0),QF
)@@G@@ THEN EXIT WILL BE 'NORMAL'   @G@@@[G$FLAG*(K,1) EQU (GI>0)*(P(1,2)+(P(1QG
)@@G@@)<2)*A0)-(GI=0) . SET SIGNAL XREG   @G@@@[G$LABL*(K,4) EQU (T=CONTINGENCQH
)@@G@@Y)*G$LABL(K,1)-(T=SUBROUTINE) . DEFAULT   @C@@@[ DO (T=EXECSUB)**(P(1)=1QI
)@@G@@) ,P*(1,2) EQU DISP     @G@@@[ DO T=EXECSUB ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU P(1,2) . JQJ
)@@G@@UMPTARGET FOR EXEC ROUTINES   @G@@@[ DO GI>0 , DO P(GI)>1 ,G$LABL*(K,4) QK
)@@G@@EQU ;  UNLESS USER PROVIDED A USPEC @G@@@[        +      (I$ 0,P(GI,4),,QL
)@@G@@P(GI,3),2*P(GI,*3)+P(GI,*2),P(GI,2) )     @[@@@[.     @C@@@[.           QM
)@@G@@   HANDLE REGISTER SAVE REQUESTS    @[@@@[.     @G@@@[ DO (T=SUBROUTINE)QN
)@@G@@**(P(1,2)=0) ,P(1,2) EQU X11 . DEFAULT LINKREG TO X11 @H@@@[SII     EQU QO
)@@G@@   ((P(1,1)=STACK)++(P(1,1)=SAVE))+; FIND REG SAVE CONTROL FIELD  @G@@@[QP
)@@G@@2*((P(2,1)=STACK)++(P(2,1)=SAVE))+3*((P(3,1)=STACK)++(P(3,1)=SAVE))     QQ
)@@G@@@H@@@[SI      EQU    SII+((SII=0)**(T=SUBROUTINE)) . IF NONE**SUBROUTINEQR
)@@G@@, SET 1     @E@@@[ DO SI=0 ,  END                       . IF NONE, WE'REQS
)@@G@@ DONE @[@@@[.     @H@@@[ST      EQU    P(SI,1)                . ELSE GETQT
)@@G@@ TYPE (SAVE/STACK/SUBROUTINE) @G@@@[NOLINK    EQU       P(1,3)=NOSAVE   QU
)@@G@@  . ON=> INHIBIT SAVE OF LINKREG    @G@@@[ DO NOLINK ,P(1,2) EQU -P(1,2)QV
)@@G@@        . IF NOT SAVING, JUST REMEMBER IT @G@@@[ DO NOLINK ,P(1) EQU +2 QW
)@@G@@              . AND FORCE THE NOSAVE SPEC AWAY  @H@@@[KLX     EQU    P(SQX
)@@G@@I)-2*(ST=STACK)     . INDEX OF LAST REG TO EXPLICITLY SAVE  @G@@@[I DO KQY
)@@G@@LX ,RSAV(P(SI,I+1)) EQU 1 . MARK ALL REGS REQUESTED EXPLICITLY    @H@@@[QZ
)@@G@@III(1)     EQU      1       . INIT INCREMENTATION CTR: 1ST SUBFIELD WILLRA
)@@G@@ BE 2 @F@@@[I DO 128 , DO RSAV(I) ,P(SI,G$$INC(1)) EQU I . SORT EXPLICITRB
)@@G@@ REGS @H@@@[ DO KLX<P(SI) , DO 1-(P(SI,KLX+1)=POINTER) , G$$EFL 3,2 . RERC
)@@G@@QUIRE REG SPEC    @F@@@[SEX     EQU    1-(ST=SUBROUTINE)      . ON IF EXRD
)@@G@@PLICIT SAVE GIVEN @H@@@[SLI     EQU    T=SUBROUTINE           . ON IF LIRE
)@@G@@NKREG IS TO BE REMEMBERED     @G@@@[ DO SEX**SLI ,P(SI,KLX+1) EQU P(1,2)RF
)@@G@@  . FORCE LINKREG INTO SAVE LIST    @G@@@[KLR     EQU    KLX+(SEX**SLI) RG
)@@G@@        . INDEX OF LAST REG TO REMEMBER   @H@@@[I DO     KLR-1 ,G$FLAG*(RH
)@@G@@K,2,I) EQU +P(SI,I+1) . REMEMBER WHATS BEING SAVED    @G@@@[KL        EQRI
)@@G@@U       KLR-NOLINK        . NUMBER TO ACTUALLY PUT IN CORE  @I@@@[I DO KRJ
)@@G@@L-1 ,FNC(I) EQU 1+5*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)<A0)+3*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)>A15) . SA, SX, SRK
)@@G@@R     @G@@@[I DO KL-1 ,AFL(I) EQU G$FLAG(K,2,I)-A0*(FNC(I)=1)-(R1-1)*(FNRL
)@@G@@C(I)=4)     @H@@@[I DO KL-1 , DO FNC(I)=1 ,FNC(I) EQU (FNC(I-1)<071)* ; RM
)@@G@@FOR SINGLE STORE A'S    @F@@@[  (070*(AFL(I+1)=(AFL(I)+1))+1) . DOUBLE SRN
)@@G@@TORE CONTIGUOUS AREGS   @G@@@[ DO ST=STACK , GO G$$B10              . IFRO
)@@G@@ STACKING, GO DO SPECIAL STUFF@G@@@[IC      EQU    &                    RP
)@@G@@  . PRESERVE USER'S LOCATION COUNTER@F@@@[$(G$LCTR(1))                  RQ
)@@G@@        . AND ESTABLISH OUR OWN     @H@@@[ DO (&=IC)**(KL>1) , I$ 074,04RR
)@@G@@,,,,$+KL        . IF SAME, LEAP AROUND THE RES  @F@@@[G$LABL*(K,3) RES KRS
)@@G@@L-1                   . SET ASIDE SAVE SPACE    @E@@@[$(IC)             RT
)@@G@@                    . RESTORE USER'S IC   @H@@@[I DO KL-1 , DO FNC(I)>0 RU
)@@G@@, I$ FNC(I),012*(FNC(I)=071),AFL(I),,,G$LABL(K,3)+I-1 @G@@@[ DO 1 , END RV
)@@G@@                          . IF NOT STACKING, WE'RE DONE     @[@@@[.     RW
)@@G@@@E@@@[G$$B10  NAME                          . HANDLE STACKING HERE@F@@@[RX
)@@G@@OI      EQU    P(SI+1,1)=OFFSET       . ON IF OFFSET SPECIFIED    @H@@@[RY
)@@G@@AI      EQU    P(SI,*KLX+2)           . ON TO AUTO-INCREMENT STACK POINTRZ
)@@G@@ER    @G@@@[OSV     EQU    + (I$ 0,OI*P(SI+1,3),0,P(SI,KLX+2),2*AI,OI*P(SA
)@@G@@SI+1,2))    @C@@@[I DO  KL-1 , S G$FLAG(K,2,I),OSV+(1-AI)*(I-1)   @F@@@[SB
)@@G@@G$LABL*(K,3) EQU 0-OSV                  . REMEMBER OFFSET FLAGS   @]@@@[SC
)@@G@@        END @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @C@@@[.               **************SD
)@@G@@***************** @C@@@[.               *                             * SE
)@@G@@@C@@@[.               *          ENDBEG             * @C@@@[.           SF
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@[.               **************SG
)@@G@@***************** @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @#@@@[P       PROC   *1 @#@@@[SH
)@@G@@ENDBEG*  NAME     @G@@@[M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET NESTSI
)@@G@@ING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @H@@@[K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . GESJ
)@@G@@T OVERALL BLOCK SEQUENCE NUMBER     @F@@@[ DO 1-(M=1) , G$$GFL 1,1      SK
)@@G@@     . BE SURE NESTING LEVEL IS OK  @D@@@[ DO 1-(G$TYPE(M)=1) , G$$GFL 1SL
)@@G@@,3 . AND BLOCK TYPE     @I@@@[G$CTR*(5) EQU       0                 . FOSM
)@@G@@RCE NESTING LEVEL FOR SUBSEQUENT CODE     @E@@@[ DO 1-(G$CTR(2)=-G$CTR(7SN
)@@G@@)) , G$$GFL 1,2 . DIAGNOSE BAD FLOAT@E@@@[G$CTR*(2) EQU       0         SO
)@@G@@        . AND FORCE IT CORRECT@E@@@[T         EQU       G$FLAG(K,3)     SP
)@@G@@  . GET BEGIN BLOCK TYPE@[@@@[.     @E@@@[          RES       -G$CTR(6) SQ
)@@G@@        . FIXUP FOR FLAGS     @E@@@[ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,2)=$) SR
)@@G@@, G$$DFL G$LABL(K,2)    @D@@@[G$LABL*(K,2)                    . MARK ENDSS
)@@G@@ OF BLOCK   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[ DO T=CYCLIC , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,1) . ST
)@@G@@IF CYCLIC, LOOP BACK    @D@@@[ DO T=CYCLIC , END                 . AND TSU
)@@G@@HAT'S ALL   @[@@@[.     @B@@@[. IF ANY REGS WERE SAVED, RESTORE THEM    SV
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @ @@@[ DO G$FLAG(K,2)=0 , GO G$$X01 @H@@@[NRR     EQU    +G$SW
)@@G@@FLAG(K,2)              . GET NO OF REGISTERS REMEMBERED     @G@@@[LINK(1SX
)@@G@@)   EQU       G$FLAG(K,2,NRR)   . LINK IS ALWAYS THE LAST ONE     @H@@@[SY
)@@G@@NR        EQU       NRR-(LINK(1)<0)   . FUDGE IN CASE WE DIDN'T SAVE LINSZ
)@@G@@K     @G@@@[ DO NRR>NR ,LINK(1) EQU -LINK(1)      . THEN GET REAL VALUE TA
)@@G@@OF LINK     @G@@@[I DO NR ,FNC(I) EQU 010+017*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)<A0)+013*(G$TB
)@@G@@FLAG(K,2,I)>A15)  @G@@@[I DO NR ,AFL(I) EQU G$FLAG(K,2,I)-A0*(FNC(I)=010TC
)@@G@@)-(R1-1)*(FNC(I)=023)   @H@@@[I DO NR , DO FNC(I)=010 ,FNC(I) EQU (FNC(ITD
)@@G@@-1)<071)* ; FOR SINGLE LOAD A'S     @F@@@[  (061*(AFL(I+1)=(AFL(I)+1))+0TE
)@@G@@10) . DOUBLE LOAD CONTIGUOUS AREGS  @F@@@[SR      EQU    0-G$LABL(K,3)  TF
)@@G@@          . GET STACKREG/SAVE FLAG  @ @@@[ DO 1-(SR>0) ,I DO NR , ;     TG
)@@G@@@G@@@[  DO FNC(I)>0 , I$ FNC(I),013*(FNC(I)=071),AFL(I),,,G$LABL(K,3)+I-TH
)@@G@@1     @F@@@[ DO 1-(SR>0) , GO G$$X01              . IF NOT STACKED, WE'RTI
)@@G@@E DONE@#@@@[. HANDLE STACKING @F@@@[INC     EQU    SR**0400000          TJ
)@@G@@  . ISOLATE AUTO-INCREMENT BIT@F@@@[XSR     EQU    (017000000**SR)*/4   TK
)@@G@@  . MOVE XREG INTO AREG FIELD @G@@@[ DO INC>0 , ANX,U 0,NR+((017000000**TL
)@@G@@SR)*/4) . BACK UP STACK POINTER     @F@@@[I DO     NR , L G$FLAG(K,2,I),TM
)@@G@@(SR**007777177777)+I-1 . AND UNSTACK@F@@@[G$$X01  NAME                  TN
)@@G@@        . END OF REG RESTORATION    @[@@@[.     @D@@@[ DO T=SUBROUTINE ,TO
)@@G@@ I$ 074,04,,LINK(1),,0 . J 0,LINK   @B@@@[ DO T=EXECSUB , I$ 074,04,,,G$TP
)@@G@@LABL(K,4)   @B@@@[ DO (T=SUBROUTINE)++(T=EXECSUB) , END     @[@@@[.     TQ
)@@G@@@B@@@[. PROCESS MAINPROGS AND CONTINGENCIES     @[@@@[.     @G@@@[XREG  TR
)@@G@@  EQU    G$FLAG(K,1)            . GET EXIT TYPE (NORMAL OR SIGNAL)@G@@@[TS
)@@G@@ DO XREG>0 , GO G$$X02                . IF EXCEPTION, GO PROCESS IT     TT
)@@G@@@G@@@[ DO T=MAINPROGRAM , ER 011            . NORMAL MAINPROGRAM EXIT ISTU
)@@G@@ EXIT$@E@@@[ DO T=CONTINGENCY , SZ,H1 G$LABL(K,4) . CLEAR PACKET UPPER  TV
)@@G@@@F@@@[ DO T=CONTINGENCY , I$ 074,04,,,1,G$LABL(K,4) . AND JUMP THRU PKT TW
)@@G@@@G@@@[ DO 1 , END                           . THAT'S ALL FOR NORMAL EXITTX
)@@G@@S     @H@@@[G$$X02  NAME                          . HERE TO HANDLE EXITSTY
)@@G@@ WITH SIGNALLING  @F@@@[ DO T=CONTINGENCY , I$ 051,H1,,,,G$LABL(K,4) . ITZ
)@@G@@S UPPER (H1) ZERO @G@@@[ DO T=CONTINGENCY , I$ 074,04,,,1,G$LABL(K,4) . UA
)@@G@@YES, EXIT THRU PACKET   @G@@@[ DO 1-(G$LABL(K,4)<0) , I$ 027,,XREG,,,G$LUB
)@@G@@ABL(K,4) . LOAD FROM SIGNALLOC@F@@@[        I$     074,04,,XREG,,$+1    UC
)@@G@@  . JUMP INTO FOLLOWING TABLE @C@@@[        ER     011                  UD
)@@G@@  . 0=EXIT$ @C@@@[        ER     040                    . 1=ERR$  @C@@@[UE
)@@G@@        ER     026                    . 2=EABT$ @C@@@[        ER     012UF
)@@G@@                    . 3=ABORT$@]@@@[        END @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     UG
)@@G@@@C@@@[.               ******************************* @C@@@[.           UH

)@@G@@CHTO            * @C@@@[.               *                             * UJ
)@@G@@@C@@@[.               ******************************* @[@@@[.     @[@@@[UK
)@@G@@.     @#@@@[P       PROC   *1 @#@@@[SWITCHTO*  NAME   @[@@@[.     @D@@@[UL
)@@G@@. NOTE: THIS FEATURE IS NO LONGER AVAILABLE BECAUSE OF@E@@@[. OPTIMIZATIUM
)@@G@@ON TECHNIQUES FOR THE OBJECT CODE. ANY BLOCK    @E@@@[. MUST BE WHOLLY GUN
)@@G@@ENERATED UNDER A SINGLE LOCATION COUNTER. @F@@@[. CONTINGENCY PROCESSINGUO
)@@G@@ IN A SEPERATE BANK MUST BE ACCOMPLISHED  @D@@@[. BY MEANS OF A SUBROUTIUP
)@@G@@NE CALL TO THE OTHER BANK.    @[@@@[.     @I@@@[          RES       1   UQ
)@@G@@              . SPACE SO DIAGNOSTIC DOESN'T CREAM OLD US    @D@@@[      UR
)@@G@@    G$$GFL    3,1               . GIVE A WARNING@H@@@[          RES     US
)@@G@@  -1                . ZAP THE IOPR SO THE PROGRAM WORKS     @G@@@[. NOTEUT
)@@G@@ THAT WE SIMPLY IGNORE THE REQUEST FOR A LOCATION COUNTER CHANGE  @]@@@[UU
)@@G@@        END @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @C@@@[.               **************UV

)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@[.               **************UY
)@@G@@***************** @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @G@@@[          PROC      *0  UZ
)@@G@@              . PROC TO DECLARE THE 'CALL' PROC @E@@@[. PREVENTS RLIB$ EVA
)@@G@@NTRY POINT CONFLICTS WITH COBOL'S 'CALL'  @[@@@[.     @B@@@[G$$CLD*   NAVB
)@@G@@ME                        .   @[@@@[.     @#@@@[P       PROC   *2 @B@@@[VC
)@@G@@CALL*** NAME                          .   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[XREG    EQU VD
)@@G@@   P(0,1)+(P(0,1)=0)*X11  . DEFAULT LINKREG TO X11    @G@@@[K DO     P(2VE
)@@G@@) , SZ P(2,K)             . CLEAR ALT EXIT SENTINALS, IF ANY@E@@@[      VF
)@@G@@  I$     074,013,XREG,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) @G@@@[K DO     P(2VG
)@@G@@) , SX XREG,P(2,K)        . SET ALT EXIT SENTINALS, IF ANY  @H@@@[      VH
)@@G@@    END                         . END OF THE ACTUAL 'CALL' PROC DEFN    VI
)@@G@@@G@@@[          END                         . END OF PROC WHICH DEFINES VJ
)@@G@@'CALL'@C@@@[/.           ******    IF   GROUP    *******    @[@@@[.     VK
)@@G@@@ @@@[. USE OF LABELS AND FLAGS --  @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @B@@@[.     VL
)@@G@@  G$FLAG(K,1) EXPLICIT NOT FLAG     @E@@@[.                2) SIDE EFFECVM
)@@G@@T AND 'IF' TEST INVERSION FLAG@B@@@[.                3) IMPLIED LINEITEMVN
)@@G@@ FLAG @D@@@[.                4) FLOAT ADJUSTMENT CAUSED BY 'ELSE' @F@@@[VO
)@@G@@.                5) FLOAT CAUSED BY OPTIMIZATION OF 'IF' TEST     @B@@@[VP
)@@G@@.                6) COMPLEX CONDITION FLAG@[@@@[.     @C@@@[.       G$LAVQ
)@@G@@BL(K,1) START ADDR OF TESTS AT 'IF' @E@@@[.                2) START ADDRVR
)@@G@@ OF USER CODE IN 'IF' BLOCK   @D@@@[.                3) END ADDR OF CODEVS

)@@G@@ BLOCK@D@@@[.                5) TARGET ADDR FOR EXIT FROM BLOCK   @[@@@[VU
)@@G@@.     @C@@@[.               ******************************* @C@@@[.     VV
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@[.               *       VW
)@@G@@     IF               * @C@@@[.               *                         VX
)@@G@@    * @C@@@[.               ******************************* @[@@@[.     VY
)@@G@@@#@@@[P       PROC   *6 @]@@@[IF*     NAME@[@@@[.     @H@@@[LOOF      EQVZ
)@@G@@U       (P(1)=1)**(P(1,1)=LOOKFOR) . CHECK FOR TABLE SEARCH FORMAT@^@@@[WA
)@@G@@ DO LOOF , GO G$$I05    @[@@@[.     @E@@@[. ANALYZE SYNTAX SO WE KNOW IFWB
)@@G@@ THIS IS LINEITEM OR A BLOCK  @[@@@[.     @#@@@[L       EQU    P-1@B@@@[WC
)@@G@@L1      EQU    (P(L)=1)**(P(L,1)=THEN)    @B@@@[L2      EQU    (P(L-1)=1WD
)@@G@@)**(P(L-1,1)=THEN)@E@@@[FLT     EQU    L1*L+L2*(L-1)  . FIELD OF 'THEN' WE
)@@G@@OR ZERO     @E@@@[THF     EQU    FLT+(FLT=0)*P  . IF NOT GIVEN, ASSUME IWF
)@@G@@T     @F@@@[IFNOT     EQU       (P(1)=1)**(P(1,1)=NOT) . SET EXPLICIT NOWG
)@@G@@T FLAG@H@@@[ DO 1-((THF=(IFNOT+2))++(THF=(IFNOT+4))) , G$$EFL 3,3 . CHECWH
)@@G@@K NO OF FIELDS    @F@@@[CXF       EQU       THF=(4+IFNOT)     . SET COMPWI
)@@G@@LEX CONDITION FLAG@C@@@[ DO P<(THF+2) , GO G$$I05 . GO DO NORMAL FORMAT WJ
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @G@@@[. LINEITEM FORMAT DOES NOT UPDATE NESTING ARRAYS- GETSWK
)@@G@@ SPECIAL HANDLING @[@@@[.     @E@@@[          G$$TST    1+IFNOT,CXF,IFNOWL
)@@G@@T . GENERATE THE TEST   @E@@@[          +P(THF+1,1)                 . THWM
)@@G@@EN THE LINEITEM   @A@@@[   DO 1 , END       . AND THEN QUIT @[@@@[.     WN
)@@G@@@B@@@[. PROCESS NORMAL (NOT LINEITEM) IF --     @[@@@[.     @#@@@[G$$I05WO
)@@G@@    NAME    @H@@@[K         EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SEQUWP
)@@G@@ENCE NO FOR THIS BLOCK  @F@@@[G$CTR*(1) EQU       K                 . ANWQ
)@@G@@D UPDATE BLOCK COUNTER  @G@@@[G$CTR*(5) EQU       G$CTR(5)+1        . BUWR
)@@G@@MP CURRENT BLOCK NESTING LEVEL@G@@@[M         EQU       G$CTR(5)        WS
)@@G@@  . GET NESTING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @G@@@[G$TYPE*(M)          EQU       WT
)@@G@@        2 . SET CURRENT BLOCKTYPE TO IF   @H@@@[G$SEQN*(M)          EQU WU
)@@G@@              K . AND REMEMBER ITS SEQUENCE NUMBER    @[@@@[.     @ @@@[WV
)@@G@@. ADJUST ALL LABELS FOR FLOAT @[@@@[.     @D@@@[G$LABL*(K,1) EQU G$LABL(WW
)@@G@@K,1)+G$CTR(2) . GLOBAL FLOAT  @E@@@[G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(WX
)@@G@@K,5) . APPLY 'IF' FLOAT @F@@@[N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,N+1) EQU G$LABL(K,N+1)+GWY
)@@G@@$CTR(2) . GLOBAL+IF     @F@@@[N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,N+3) EQU G$LABL(K,N+3)+GWZ
)@@G@@$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,4)     @[@@@[.     @E@@@[  DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(KXA
)@@G@@,1)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,1)   @G@@@[G$LABL*(K,1)                 . REMEMXB
)@@G@@BER START ADDR FOR OPTIMIZATION     @H@@@[ DO LOOF , GO G$$I10          XC
)@@G@@        . LOOKFOR TESTS GET SPECIAL HANDLING    @[@@@[.     @H@@@[NOGEN XD
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(7)*(G$LABL(K,5)=G$LABL(K,1)) . ON TO SURPRESS ALL   XE
)@@G@@@G@@@[G$CTR*(4) EQU G$CTR(4)+NOGEN           . KEEP G$$TST'S COUNTER IN XF
)@@G@@PHASE @A@@@[ DO NOGEN , END     . STOP IF NO MO @[@@@[.     @F@@@[G$FLAGXG
)@@G@@*(K,1) EQU IFNOT            . SAVE NOT FLAG FOR OPTIMIZER   @E@@@[G$FLAGXH
)@@G@@*(K,6) EQU CXF              . AND ALSO COMPLEX FLAG   @H@@@[ DO G$CTR(6)XI
)@@G@@ , G$$SVA              . PASS 1: SAVE ARGS FOR RECALL AT ENDIF    @[@@@[XJ
)@@G@@.     @F@@@[RVF       EQU       IFNOT--G$FLAG(K,2) . SET OVERALL REVERSAXK
)@@G@@L FLAG@F@@@[LIG       EQU       G$FLAG(K,3)     . SET IMPLIED LINEITEM FXL
)@@G@@LAG   @G@@@[ DO 1-LIG ,  G$$TST  1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF G$LABL(K,4)  . GENERATEXM
)@@G@@ THE TEST   @H@@@[ DO LIG  ,  G$$TST  1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF      . GENERATE LIXN
)@@G@@NE ITEM FORMAT TEST(S)  @H@@@[G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU SIDE(1)               . RXO
)@@G@@EMEMBER IF TEST HAS SIDE EFFECTS    @G@@@[G$LABL*(K,2)                  XP

)@@G@@.     @G@@@[. HANDLE 'LOOKFOR' TESTS, WHICH GENERATE 1100 SERIES SEARCH XR
)@@G@@INSTRUCTIONS@[@@@[.     @#@@@[G$$I10    NAME    @A@@@[ DO 1-(P(3,1)=VARYXS
)@@G@@) , G$$EFL 2,010 .@I@@@[VI        EQU       3                 . 'VARY' SXT
)@@G@@PECIFICATION MUST FOLLOW 'LOOKFO    @E@@@[P(3,1)    EQU       LOOKFOR   XU
)@@G@@        . FORCE THE KEYWORD   @G@@@[KW(1)     EQU       LOOKFOR         XV
)@@G@@  . IN ALL PLACES ITS EXPECTED TO BE@G@@@[G$LABL*(K,2)                  XW
)@@G@@         . GUARANTEE NON-EMPTY 'IF' CLAUSE@H@@@[          G$$LAN        XX
)@@G@@              . ANALYZE SPECS, LOAD REGS IF NECESSARY @G@@@[          G$XY
)@@G@@$LGE    3,FI(3),FI(4) G$LABL(K,4),1 . GEN CODE FOR SEARCH   @F@@@[G$CTR*XZ
)@@G@@(3) EQU G$CTR(3)+G$CTR(6)       . PRETEND WE SAVED THE ARGS @[@@@[.     YA
)@@G@@@]@@@[        END @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @C@@@[.               ********YB
)@@G@@*********************** @C@@@[.               *                         YC
)@@G@@    * @C@@@[.               *           ELSE              * @C@@@[.     YD
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@[.               ********YE
)@@G@@*********************** @[@@@[.     @#@@@[        PROC   *0 @]@@@[ELSE* YF
)@@G@@  NAME@F@@@[M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING YG
)@@G@@LEVEL @F@@@[K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . GET SEQ NUM FOR THISYH

)@@G@@        END @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @C@@@[.               **************YP

)@@G@@@C@@@[.               *           ENDIF             * @C@@@[.           YR

)@@G@@***************** @[@@@[.     @#@@@[        PROC   *0 @]@@@[ENDIF*  NAMEYT
)@@G@@@F@@@[M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING LEVEL YU
)@@G@@@G@@@[K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . GET SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLYV
)@@G@@OCK   @F@@@[ DO 1-(G$TYPE(M)=2) , G$$GFL 1,3          . CATCH NESTING ERYW
)@@G@@RORS  @[@@@[.     @E@@@[ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,5)=$) , G$$DFL G$LYX
)@@G@@ABL(K,5)    @D@@@[G$LABL*(K,5)                  . MARK END OF BLOCK     YY
)@@G@@@G@@@[G$CTR*(5) EQU       M-1               . STEP NESTING BACK ONE LEVEYZ
)@@G@@L     @[@@@[.     @G@@@[. RESTORE GLOBAL FLOAT FOR FOLLOWING BLOX (EFFECZA
)@@G@@TIVE ON PASS 2 ONLY)    @[@@@[.     @E@@@[G$CTR*(2) EQU G$CTR(7)*(G$CTR(ZB
)@@G@@2)-G$FLAG(K,5)-G$FLAG(K,4)) . @E@@@[ DO G$CTR(7) , END . ON PASS 2, WE'RZC
)@@G@@E DONE AT THIS POINT    @[@@@[.     @C@@@[.   ***** PASS 1 ONLY BEYOND TZD

)@@G@@  . ADJUST ARGSAVE STACK POINTER    @[@@@[.     @C@@@[. TABULATE FLOAT FZF
)@@G@@OR SURPRESSED ELSE, IF ANY    @[@@@[.     @G@@@[G$FLAG*(K,4) EQU -((G$LAZG
)@@G@@BL(K,3)>0)**(G$LABL(K,4)=$)) . 'ELSE' FLOAT     @G@@@[          RES     ZH
)@@G@@  G$FLAG(K,4)     . APPLY ELSFLOAT FOR SUCCEEDING CODE@[@@@[.     @G@@@[ZI
)@@G@@. CHECK FOR SURPRESSION OF EVERYTHING (NO CODE AND NO SIDE EFFECTS)     ZJ
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @H@@@[ DO ($>G$LABL(K,2))++G$FLAG(K,2) , GO G$$I20 . IF NOT,ZK
)@@G@@ GO CHECK OPTIMIZATION  @E@@@[G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU G$LABL(K,1)-G$LABL(K,2) .ZL
)@@G@@ TURN OFF 'IF'    @F@@@[          RES       G$LABL(K,1)-$   . ADJUST L.CZM
)@@G@@. APPROPRIATELY   @C@@@[  DO 1 , END        . AND TERMINATE GRACEFULLY  ZN

)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @#@@@[G$$I20    NAME    @E@@@[ DO G$LABL(K,4)=0 ,G$LABL*(K,4ZP
)@@G@@) . IF NO ELSE, PUT IT HERE   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU G$LABL(ZQ
)@@G@@K,3)=G$LABL(K,2) . NO 'IF' CLAUSE =>INVERT@D@@@[G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU ($-G$LAZR
)@@G@@BL(K,2))=1 . IMPLIED LINEITEM @F@@@[ DO 1-(G$FLAG(K,2)++G$FLAG(K,3)) , EZS
)@@G@@ND . DONE IF NO OPTIMIZATION  @[@@@[.     @G@@@[. WE'RE GOING TO OPTIMIZZT
)@@G@@E THE JUMP WHEN WE GET BACK THERE ON PASS 2     @F@@@[. TO INSURE THAT LZU
)@@G@@ABELS BELOW THIS POINT ARE OK, WE MUST PERFORCE @E@@@[. DO A TRIAL GENERZV
)@@G@@ATION OF THE MODIFIED TEST SO WE KNOW     @G@@@[. HOW MANY INSTRUCTIONS ZW
)@@G@@IT WILL TAKE WHEN WE GEN IT BACK AT THE TOP     @[@@@[.     @H@@@[KK    ZX
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(3)+1        . GET ARGSAVE INDEX OF MATCHING 'IF'    ZY
)@@G@@@F@@@[I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,J DO G$ARGS(KK,I) ,P(I,J) EQU +G$ARGS(KK,I,J)    ZZ
)@@G@@@A@@@[IFNOT     EQU       G$FLAG(K,1)     @F@@@[CXF       EQU       G$FLAA
)@@G@@AG(K,6)   . RETRIEVE COMPLEX CONDN FLAG   @F@@@[RVF       EQU       IFNOAB
)@@G@@T--G$FLAG(K,2) . SET OVERALL REVERSAL FLAG@E@@@[START                 . AC
)@@G@@REMEMBER WHERE BEGINNING OF TEST WAS@D@@@[ DO 1-G$FLAG(K,3) , G$$TST 1+IAD

)@@G@@      .     @H@@@[G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)-1        . RESTORE INTERNAF
)@@G@@AL CTR USED BY G$$TST   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[. NOW SET ADDRESS ADJUSTMENT FAG
)@@G@@LAGS SO PASS 2 WILL GEN PROPER CODE @[@@@[.     @G@@@[SIZE      EQU     AH
)@@G@@  G$LABL(K,2)-G$LABL(K,1) . SIZE OF ORIGINAL TEST     @E@@@[G$FLAG*(K,5)AI
)@@G@@ EQU $-START-SIZE       . COMPUTE PASS 2 FLOAT  @H@@@[          RES     AJ
)@@G@@  -SIZE            . COMPENSATE L.C. FOR CODE WHICH FOLLOWS @]@@@[      AK
)@@G@@  END @B@@@[/.          ******** CASE GROUP  *********@[@@@[.     @[@@@[AL
)@@G@@.     @^@@@[. ARRAY USAGE IS --     @[@@@[.     @D@@@[.       G$FLAG(K,1AM
)@@G@@) TOTAL NUMBER OF CASE VALUES GIVEN @G@@@[.         ...    2) RUNNING TAAN
)@@G@@LLY: NUMBER OF VALUES ON PREVIOUS CASE    @C@@@[.         ...    3) INHIAO
)@@G@@BIT/CALL OPTION FLAG    @E@@@[.         ...    4,X) VALUE OF X'TH SPECIFAP
)@@G@@IED CASEVALUE     @[@@@[.     @D@@@[.       G$LABL(K,1) START ADDR OF USAQ
)@@G@@ER NOFIND CODE    @C@@@[.         ...    2) END ADDR OF USER NOFIND CODEAR
)@@G@@@D@@@[.         ...    3) ULTIMATE EXIT ADDR FROM BLOCK     @E@@@[.     AS
)@@G@@    ...    4,X) JUMPTARGET ADDR FOR X'TH CASEVALUE    @E@@@[.         ..AT
)@@G@@.    5) RUNNING LABEL: LAST JUMP TO CLOSE A CASE@[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     AU
)@@G@@@C@@@[.               ******************************* @C@@@[.           AV
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@[.               *          CASAW
)@@G@@ENTRY           * @C@@@[.               *                             * AX
)@@G@@@C@@@[.               ******************************* @[@@@[.     @B@@@[AY
)@@G@@. SYNTAX--     CASENTRY <AXREG>    OR...  @D@@@[.              CASENTRY AZ
)@@G@@CALLING(,<LINK>) NAME(,<TAG>) @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @#@@@[P       PROCBA
)@@G@@   *2 @B@@@[CASENTRY*  NAME                       .   @F@@@[K         EQBB
)@@G@@U       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SEQUENCE NUM    @D@@@[G$CTR*(1) EQBC
)@@G@@U       K                 . AND UPDATE IT @G@@@[M         EQU       G$CTBD
)@@G@@R(5)+1        . NESTING LEVEL FOR THIS BLOCK    @E@@@[G$CTR*(5) EQU     BE
)@@G@@  M                 . UPDATE THAT, TOO    @G@@@[G$SEQN*(M) EQU      K   BF
)@@G@@              . REMEMBER BLOCK SEQUENCE NUMBER  @F@@@[G$TYPE*(M) EQU    BG
)@@G@@  3                 . SET BLOCK TYPE TO CASE    @[@@@[.     @F@@@[G$LABLBH
)@@G@@*(K,0) EQU    G$LABL(K,0)+G$CTR(2) . APPLY GLOBAL FLOAT     @E@@@[ DO G$BI
)@@G@@CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,0)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,0)    @G@@@[G$LABL*(K,0)BJ
)@@G@@                          . MARK START IN CASE WE'LL INHIBIT@[@@@[.     BK
)@@G@@@G@@@[CALOPT    EQU       P(1,1)=CALLING    . ON IF CALL OPTION SPECIFIEBL
)@@G@@D     @E@@@[          RES       CALOPT*G$CTR(6) . ACCOUNT FOR THE LMJ   BM
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @#@@@[G$$C10    NAME    @F@@@[ DO 1-G$CTR(7) , GO G$$C40    BN
)@@G@@       . ON PASS 1, SKIP THIS STUFF @[@@@[.     @E@@@[. ***** PASS 2 ONLBO
)@@G@@Y-- GENERATE CHECKING AND THE JUMPTABLE   @[@@@[.     @C@@@[ DO 1-CALOPTBP
)@@G@@ , ; IF NOT A SUBROUTINE CALL BLOCK @F@@@[ DO (P(1,1)<A0)++(P(1,1)>A3) ,BQ
)@@G@@ G$$EFL 3,1 . DIE IF NOT OVERLAP REG@[@@@[.     @B@@@[. COMPUTE CHARACTEBR
)@@G@@RISTICS OF THE TABLE    @[@@@[.     @F@@@[NUMCA     EQU       +G$FLAG(K,BS
)@@G@@1)      . NUMBER OF CASES GIVEN     @H@@@[CMAX(1)   EQU       0400000000BT
)@@G@@000     . INIT MAX TO SMALLEST POSSIBLE NUMBER  @H@@@[L DO NUMCA , DO G$BU
)@@G@@FLAG(K,4,L)>CMAX(1) ,CMAX(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MAX    @H@@@[CMIN(1BV
)@@G@@)   EQU       0377777777777     . INIT MIN TO LARGEST POSSIBLE NUMBER   BW
)@@G@@@H@@@[L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)<CMIN(1) ,CMIN(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,4,L) .BX
)@@G@@ GET MIN    @D@@@[OFF     EQU    1-CMIN(1)              . SET OFFSET    BY
)@@G@@@G@@@[JTSIZ   EQU    CMAX(1)+OFF            . SET TOT TABLE SIZE=RANGE OBZ
)@@G@@F VAL @E@@@[JTL       EQU       JTSIZ-CALOPT*(G$FLAG(K,4,1)=CMAX(1))    CA
)@@G@@@F@@@[ DO CALOPT , DO 1-(CMIN(1)=0) , G$$EFL 3,5 . MIN VAL NOT ZERO     CB
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @F@@@[. APPLY FLOATS TO LABELS BELONGING TO THIS BLOCK, SET CC
)@@G@@GLOBAL FLOAT@[@@@[.     @H@@@[G$LABL*(K,3) EQU    G$LABL(K,3)+G$CTR(2) .CD
)@@G@@ LAST LABEL GETS ONLY GLOBAL FLOAT  @H@@@[G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+(CE
)@@G@@1-G$FLAG(K,3))*(4*(1-CALOPT)+JTL)  . SET FLOAT  @E@@@[N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,CF
)@@G@@N) EQU G$LABL(K,N)+G$CTR(2) . APPLY IT    @G@@@[ DO G$FLAG(K,3) , END   CG
)@@G@@              . IF OPTIMIZED AWAY, QUIT HERE    @[@@@[.     @E@@@[. COMPCH
)@@G@@UTE CROSS REFERENCES NEEDED TO GENERATE THE JUMP TABLE@[@@@[.     @G@@@[CI
)@@G@@NFA(1)    EQU  G$LABL(K,3-2*(G$LABL(K,2)>G$LABL(K,1))) . NOFIND ADDR    CJ
)@@G@@@G@@@[ DO CALOPT ,NFA(1) EQU -1             . DON'T ALLOW FOR CALL OPTIOCK
)@@G@@N     @I@@@[N DO JTSIZ ,JT(N) EQU NFA(1)            . INITIALIZE ALL JUMCL
)@@G@@P TARGETS TO NOFIND     @G@@@[L DO NUMCA ,JT(G$FLAG(K,4,L)+OFF) EQU G$LACM
)@@G@@BL(K,4,L)+G$CTR(2) . SET ADDRS@F@@@[ DO CALOPT ,N DO JTSIZ , DO JT(N)<0 CN
)@@G@@, G$$EFL 3,6 . MISSING CASES  @G@@@[N DO JTSIZ , DO JT(N)=G$CTR(2) ,JT(NCO
)@@G@@) EQU G$LABL(K,3) . VACUOUS CASES   @F@@@[OTLAD     EQU       G$LABL(K,3CP
)@@G@@)+1     . FOR OPTIMIZED LAST CASE   @H@@@[N DO JTSIZ , DO JT(N)=OTLAD ,JCQ
)@@G@@T(N) EQU G$LABL(K,3) . FIX REDUNDANT CLOSURES   @[@@@[.     @E@@@[. GEN CR
)@@G@@CODE TO INSURE THAT XREG VALUE IS IN RANGE OF TABLE   @[@@@[.     @E@@@[CS

)@@G@@  I$     054,017,P(1,1)-A0,,3*(CMAX(1)<-1),CMAX(1)+1 . TLE,X@F@@@[      CU

)@@G@@. NOW GENERATE THE ACTUAL JUMP TABLE ITSELF     @[@@@[.     @#@@@[G$$C30CY
)@@G@@    NAME    @G@@@[LINK      EQU       X11+(P(1)>1)*(P(1,2)-X11) . LINK RCZ
)@@G@@EG, DEFAULT=X11   @H@@@[ DO CALOPT , I$ 074,013,LINK,P(2,2),2*P(2,*2)+P(DA
)@@G@@2,*1),P(2,1) . LMJ TO SUBRTN  @F@@@[N DO JTL , I$ 074,04,,,,JT(N)       DB

)@@G@@  . SPECS--  <VALUE-LIST>     @F@@@[M         EQU       G$CTR(5)        DP

)@@G@@,3      . DIAGNOSE BAD NESTING@F@@@[ DO G$FLAG(K,3)>0 , END             DS
)@@G@@    . DONE IF OPTIMIZED AWAY  @[@@@[.     @H@@@[JJ      EQU    +G$FLAG(KDT
)@@G@@,1)           . GET # OF CASEVALS SO FAR IN THIS GRP  @G@@@[ DO JJ=0 ,G$DU
)@@G@@LABL*(K,2)                . MARK END OF USER NOFIND CODE    @B@@@[ DO (JDV
)@@G@@J>0)++(G$FLAG(K,3)>-1) , GO G$$C60 .@[@@@[.     @C@@@[. SPECIAL STUFF FODW

)@@G@@FL 2,5 . NO NOFIND ALLOWED FOR CALL OPTION@D@@@[MAX(1)    EQU       P(1)DY
)@@G@@              . INITIALIZE MAX@F@@@[N DO P(1) , DO P(1,N)>MAX(1) ,MAX(1)DZ

)@@G@@  . INITIALIZE POSN OF MAXVAL @F@@@[N DO P(1) , DO P(1,N)=MAX(1) ,IMAX(1EB

)@@G@@  . TEMP SAVE 1ST VALUE @E@@@[P(1,1)    EQU       MAX(1)            . FOED
)@@G@@RCE IT TO MAX     @G@@@[P(1,IMAX(1)) EQU    MTEMP             . EXCHANGEEE
)@@G@@ WITH PREVIOUS VALUE    @[@@@[.     @^@@@[. CLOSE PREVIOUS CASE   @[@@@[EF
)@@G@@.     @#@@@[G$$C60    NAME    @H@@@[REDUN     EQU       $=G$LABL(K,3)   EG
)@@G@@  . ON=> CLOSURE HERE WOULD BE REDUNDANT  @G@@@[GOTSOM EQU $>G$LABL(K,4,EH
)@@G@@JJ)           . ON IF PRECEDING CASE HAD CODE   @F@@@[ DO GOTSOM**(1-REDEI
)@@G@@UN) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,3) . CLOSE LAST CASE@H@@@[ DO GOTSOM ,G$LABLEJ
)@@G@@*(K,5)              . MARK START USERCODE FOR THIS CASE     @F@@@[G$CTR*EK

)@@G@@1-GOTSOM)*G$FLAG(K,2) ,G$LABL*(K,4,JJ+1-N) EQU 0@[@@@[.     @B@@@[. TABUEM
)@@G@@LATE PARAMETERS FOR THE PRESENT CASE@[@@@[.     @E@@@[G$FLAG*(K,1) EQU JEN
)@@G@@J+P(1)              . UPDATE CASEVAL COUNT@I@@@[G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU +P(1)  EO
)@@G@@              . REMEMBER HOW MANY TBL ENTRIES WE'RE USI     @F@@@[N DO  EP

)@@G@@@G@@@[N DO     P(1) ,G$LABL*(K,4,JJ+N)      . SET OUR OWN JUMPTARGET ADDET
)@@G@@RESSES@]@@@[        END @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @C@@@[.     EU

)@@G@@P       PROC   *0 @#@@@[ENDCASE*  NAME    @G@@@[M         EQU       G$CTEZ
)@@G@@R(5)          . GET NESTING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @G@@@[K         EQU     FA
)@@G@@  G$SEQN(M)         . GET SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   @E@@@[ DO 1-(G$TYPFB
)@@G@@E(M)=3) , G$$GFL 1,3      . DIAGNOSE BAD NESTING@[@@@[.     @E@@@[. COMPFC
)@@G@@UTE TABLE SIZE SO WE KNOW HOW MUCH FLOAT TO APPLY     @[@@@[.     @H@@@[FD
)@@G@@CALOPT    EQU       G$FLAG(K,3)<0     . SET IF CASENTRY WITH CALLING OPTFE

)@@G@@ POSSIBLE NUMBER  @H@@@[L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)>CMAX(1) ,CMAX(1) EFH

)@@G@@,4,L)<CMIN(1) ,CMIN(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MIN    @G@@@[JTS(1)   EQUFK
)@@G@@    CMAX(1)-CMIN(1)+1      . SET TOT TABLE SIZE=RANGE OF VAL@E@@@[ DO G$FL
)@@G@@FLAG(K,3)<0 ,JTS(1) EQU JTS(1)-(CMAX(1)=G$FLAG(K,4,1))@[@@@[.     @F@@@[FM
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU    G$LABL(K,0)=$     . SET INHIBIT FLAG (NO CODE)@G@@@[FN
)@@G@@REDUN     EQU       G$LABL(K,5)=$ . ON => LAST CASE CLOSURE REDUNDANT   FO
)@@G@@@I@@@[FLOAT     EQU       (1-G$FLAG(K,3))*(4*(1-CALOPT)+JTS(1)-REDUN) . FP
)@@G@@FLOAT FOR TABL    @E@@@[ DO G$CTR(6) , RES FLOAT           . ON PASS 1, FQ
)@@G@@APPLY TO LC @G@@@[ DO G$CTR(7)   ,G$CTR*(2) EQU G$CTR(2)-FLOAT . ON 2, TFR
)@@G@@O GLOBAL FLOAT    @[@@@[.     @E@@@[ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,3)=$) FS
)@@G@@, G$$DFL G$LABL(K,3)    @H@@@[G$LABL*(K,3)                          . MAFT
)@@G@@RK ULTIMATE EXIT POINT FROM BLOCK   @G@@@[G$CTR*(5) EQU       M-1       FU
)@@G@@        . UPDATE GLOBAL NESTING LEVEL     @[@@@[.     @]@@@[        END FV
)@@G@@@B@@@[/.       ********* REPEAT GROUP ********* @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     FW
)@@G@@@E@@@[.    THE ARRAY G$FLAG(K,X) IS USED TO KEEP FLAGS THROUGOUT  @E@@@[FX
)@@G@@.    THE SCOPE OF THE REPEAT BLOCK. FOR EACH X, THE FLAG IS:@[@@@[.     FY
)@@G@@@F@@@[.       1      INDEX OF 'VARY' FIELD ON SOURCE 'REPEAT' IMAGE     FZ
)@@G@@@F@@@[.       2      ON IF THERE IS <LOOP CTL> CODE WHICH MUST APPEAR   GA
)@@G@@@D@@@[.              AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF THE LOOP     @E@@@[.     GB
)@@G@@  3      INDEX OF 'TO' FIELD IN SOURCE 'REPEAT' IMAGE @F@@@[.       4   GC
)@@G@@   INDEX OF 'WHILE' FIELD ON SOURCE 'REPEAT IMAGE     @B@@@[.       5   GD
)@@G@@   FLOAT FOR SURPRESSED UNTIL @C@@@[.       6      INDEX OF 'UNTIL' ON SGE
)@@G@@OURCE IMAGE @B@@@[.       7      SURPRESS EVERYTHING FLAG   @A@@@[.     GF
)@@G@@  8      ON=> 'LOOKFOR' FORMAT@C@@@[.       9      ON=> BOTTOM OF LOOP CGG
)@@G@@HECKING DONE@E@@@[.       .      FLAGS USED TO CONTROL POSITIONING AND FGH
)@@G@@LOAT: @D@@@[.      10      ON=> ENTRY CONDITION IS JUMP TO WHILE  @B@@@[GI
)@@G@@.      11      ON => SURPRESS WHILE AT TOP@B@@@[.      12      ON=> INVEGJ
)@@G@@RT ESCAPE TEST    @E@@@[.      13      ON=> CLOSE ESCAPE CLAUSE (WITH JUGK
)@@G@@MP TO EXIT) @G@@@[.      14      ON=> CLOSE OTHERWISE/UNTIL CLAUSE (WITHGL
)@@G@@ JUMP TO LOOP)    @C@@@[.      15      ON=> SURPRESS WHILE AT BOTTOM    GM
)@@G@@@C@@@[.      16      FLOAT FOR WHILE SURPRESSED AT TOP@B@@@[.      17   GN
)@@G@@   FLOAT FOR INVERTED ESCAPE  @D@@@[.      18      FLOAT FOR WHILE SURPRGO
)@@G@@ESSED AT BOTTOM   @E@@@[.      19      ON=> CODE IN LOOP WILL APPEAR BELGP
)@@G@@OW ESCAPE   @C@@@[.      20      GLOBAL FLOAT AT ENTRY TO BLOCK   @E@@@[GQ
)@@G@@.      21      1+FLOAT FOR INITIAL JUMP FALLTHRU (0=>NONE)  @[@@@[.     GR
)@@G@@@E@@@[.    THE ARRAY G$LABL(K,X) IS USED TO LABEL VARIOUS CONTROL @D@@@[GS
)@@G@@.    POINTS IN THE GENERATED CODE.  VALUES OF X ARE:  @[@@@[.     @D@@@[GT
)@@G@@.       1      LOCATION OF TOP-OF-LOOP WHILE TEST     @D@@@[.       2   GU
)@@G@@   LOCATION OF TOP-OF-LOOP <VARY> CODE    @F@@@[.       3      START USEGV
)@@G@@R-SPECIFIED REPEATED CODE (TOP OF LOOP)   @G@@@[.       4      LOCATION GW
)@@G@@OF CONDITION TEST AT ESCAPE (0=>NO ESCAPE STMNT)@D@@@[.       5      STAGX
)@@G@@RT USER-SPECIFIED ESCAPE CLAUSE     @D@@@[.       6      START USER-SPECGY
)@@G@@IFIED OTHERWISE CODE    @D@@@[.       7      LOCATION OF BOTTOM-OF-LOOP GZ
)@@G@@WHILE TEST  @D@@@[.       8      LOCATION OF BOTTOM-OF-LOOP <VARY> CODE HA
)@@G@@@C@@@[.       9      START USER-SPECIFIED ATEND CODE  @C@@@[.      10   HB
)@@G@@   ULTIMATE BLOCK EXIT TARGET ADDR  @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @G@@@[. THE HC
)@@G@@FOLLOWING ARCANE RULES ARE FOLLOWED IN POSITIONING THE VARIOUS    @ @@@[HD
)@@G@@. CODE GENERATED FOR A LOOP:  @[@@@[.     @G@@@[. 1) <UNTIL> CODE ALWAYSHE
)@@G@@ APPEARS AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF THE LOOP     @F@@@[.            SO WEHF
)@@G@@ CAN AVOID JUMPING AROUND IT AT LOOP ENTRY.     @B@@@[. 2) <VARY>  CODE HG
)@@G@@MOVES AROUND AS FOLLOWS:@G@@@[.        A)  IF THE SENSE (UP/DOWN) IS KNOHH
)@@G@@WN, THEN THE CODE IS PLACED   @G@@@[.            ACCORDING TO THE PREFERHI
)@@G@@ENCE OF THE LOOP INSTRUCTION, E.G.  @D@@@[.            JGD AT THE BOTTOMHJ
)@@G@@, SEARCHES AT THE TOP.  @G@@@[.        B)  IF THE SENSE IS UNKNOWN, THE HK
)@@G@@CODE APPEARS AT BOTH TOP AND  @F@@@[.            BOTTOM, WITH THE BRANCHHL
)@@G@@ SENSE APPROPRIATELY INVERTED.@G@@@[.            IMMEDIATELY BEFORE THE HM
)@@G@@PRIMARY CODE (BOTTOM), A SIGN TEST  @G@@@[.            IS INSERTED WHICHHN
)@@G@@ DETERMINES WHICH OF THE TWO VARIATIONS   @ @@@[.            WILL BE EXEHO
)@@G@@CUTED.@G@@@[. 3) <WHILE> CODE ALSO MOVES AROUND. WE DEFINE A <WHILE> TESHP
)@@G@@T WHICH IS  @G@@@[.            PERFORMED IN A SINGLE INSTRUCTION WHICH HHQ
)@@G@@AS AN INVERSE     @G@@@[.            (I.E. A CONDITIONAL JUMP) AS 'OPTIMHR
)@@G@@IZEABLE'. POSITIONING   @E@@@[.            THEN DEPENDS UPON OTHER CONDIHS
)@@G@@TIONS AS FOLLOWS- @G@@@[.            NORMAL POSITIONING IS AT THE BOTTOMHT
)@@G@@, WITH A (ONE TIME) JUMP@H@@@[.            TO THE WHILE TEST INSERTED ATHU
)@@G@@ THE TOP. IF THERE IS AN ESCAPE     @G@@@[.            CONDITION WHICH WHV
)@@G@@OULD OTHERWISE FALL THROUGH, HOWEVER, THE @H@@@[.            JUMP AROUNDHW
)@@G@@ THE WHILE IS AVOIDED BY PUTTING IT AT THE TOP AND    @H@@@[.           HX
)@@G@@ INVERTING THE ESCAPE TEST ACCORDINGLY. IF THERE IS NO <VARY>     @G@@@[HY
)@@G@@.            CODE AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF THE LOOP, AND THE WHILE     HZ
)@@G@@@G@@@[.            TEST IS OPTIMIZEABLE, THEN THE INITIAL JUMP TO THE WHIA
)@@G@@ILE   @G@@@[.            TEST IS REPLACED BY THE TEST ITSELF. IN THIS CAIB
)@@G@@SE, THE     @G@@@[.            TEST WILL APPEAR AT BOTH THE TOP AND BOTTIC
)@@G@@OM OF THE LOOP.   @E@@@[. 4) ESCAPE  AN ESCAPE TEST CAN BE MODIFIED BOTHID
)@@G@@ BECAUSE OF @G@@@[.            THE ABOVE, OR BECAUSE THE CLAUSE IS EMPTYIE
)@@G@@. IF THE CODE     @F@@@[.            FOLLOWING THE TEST IS NOT IN THE LOIF
)@@G@@OP (I.E. IS A NON-@F@@@[.            VACUOUS ESCAPE CLAUSE OR IS THE ENDIG
)@@G@@ OF THE LOOP),    @F@@@[.            THE ESCAPE TEST BRANCHES TO STAY INIH
)@@G@@ THE LOOP. IF     @G@@@[.            THE FOLLOWING CODE IS IN THE LOOP (II
)@@G@@I.E. VACUOUS ESCAPE     @G@@@[.            AND NON-VACUOUS OTHERWISE), TIJ
)@@G@@HEN THE SENSE IS REVERSED     @F@@@[.            SO THAT THE BRANCH CONDIK
)@@G@@ITION GOES COMPLETELY OUT OF  @^@@@[.            THE BLOCK. @[@@@[.     IL
)@@G@@@C@@@[.               ******************************* @C@@@[.           IM
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@[.               *           REIN
)@@G@@PEAT            * @C@@@[.               *                             * IO
)@@G@@@C@@@[.               ******************************* @[@@@[.     @#@@@[IP
)@@G@@P       PROC   *12@]@@@[REPEAT* NAME@[@@@[.     @E@@@[K         EQU     IQ
)@@G@@  G$CTR(1)+1        . BUMP BLOCK COUNTER  @F@@@[G$CTR*(1) EQU       K   IR

)@@G@@*(K,20) EQU   G$CTR(2)          . SAVE INITIAL FLOAT  @H@@@[ESCF      EQIZ
)@@G@@U       G$LABL(K,4)       . REMEMBER ENTRY VALUE OF ESCAPE FLAG   @H@@@[JA
)@@G@@FALLF     EQU       (G$FLAG(K,21)>0)*(1-G$FLAG(K,21)) . GET FALLTHRU FLOJB
)@@G@@AT    @H@@@[N DO 10 ,G$LABL*(K,N) EQU G$LABL(K,N)+G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,10) JC
)@@G@@. GLOBAL, JUMPENTR@I@@@[N DO 9 ,G$LABL*(K,N+1) EQU G$LABL(K,N+1)+G$FLAG(JD

)@@G@@ABL(K,N+4)+G$FLAG(K,17) . ESCAPE INVERSION@G@@@[N DO 5 ,G$LABL*(K,N+5) EJF

)@@G@@N+6) EQU G$LABL(K,N+6)+G$FLAG(K,14)+G$FLAG(K,5) . OTHER/UNTIL     @G@@@[JH

)@@G@@@E@@@[ DO ESCF=0 ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU 0 . IF NO ESCAPE, RESTORE FLAG @[@@@[JJ
)@@G@@.     @ @@@[. ***** SYNTAX ANALYSIS ***** @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @#@@@[JK
)@@G@@G$$R10    NAME    @[@@@[.     @G@@@[C(1)      EQU  1                    JL

)@@G@@              . MARK START OF WHILE TEST  @G@@@[WI      EQU    KW(1)=WHIJP

)@@G@@O G$$R59 . IF NO 'WHILE', WE'RE DONE@C@@@[WYNOT     EQU       (P(2)=1)**JS
)@@G@@(P(2,1)=NOT) .    @H@@@[WC        EQU       ((P(3+WYNOT,1)=OR)++(P(3+WYNJT
)@@G@@OT,1)=AND))**(P(3+WYNOT)=1)   @F@@@[C(1)    EQU    3+WYNOT+2*WC         JU

)@@G@@  . END PROCESSING OF 'WHILE' CONDITION   @[@@@[.     @E@@@[.       EXAMJX
)@@G@@INE <LOOP CTL> FIELD, LOADING REGS IF NECESSARY @D@@@[. NOTE: THE <LOOP JY
)@@G@@CONTROL> ANALYSIS SUBROUTINE G$$LAN @E@@@[. SETS THE FLAGS FI(X) USED BEJZ
)@@G@@LOW.  FOR THEIR DEFINITIONS,  @ @@@[. SEE THE CODE FOR G$$LAN     @[@@@[KA
)@@G@@.     @C@@@[.       SEE IF THIS IS A HARDWARE SEARCH SPEC   @[@@@[.     KB
)@@G@@@I@@@[G$$R60  NAME                          . MARK START PROCESSING OF <KC
)@@G@@LOOP CNTRL> SP    @F@@@[ DO 1-(KW(1)=LOOKFOR) , GO G$$R61 . IF NOT LOOKFKD
)@@G@@OR, GO TRY 'VARY' @I@@@[VI      EQU    C(1)+2                 . IN THIS KE
)@@G@@FMT, 'VARY' FOLLOWS LOOKFOR AND     @F@@@[ DO (P(VI,1)>VARY)++(P(VI,1)<LKF
)@@G@@OOKFOR) , G$$EFL 2,010 . CHECK IT   @G@@@[P(VI,1) EQU    LOOKFOR        KG
)@@G@@        . FORCE KEYWORD FOR USE BY G$$LAN @H@@@[G$FLAG*(K,8) EQU 1      KH
)@@G@@           . SET FLAG ALLOWING UNCONDITIONAL ESCAPE   @A@@@[ GO G$$R62 .KI
)@@G@@ THEN GO PROCESS IT     @[@@@[.     @F@@@[G$$R61  NAME                  KJ
)@@G@@        . TRY A NORMAL 'VARY' FIELD @G@@@[VI      EQU    C(1)*((KW(1)>(JKK
)@@G@@MGI-1))**(KW(1)<(VARY+1))) . FIELD INDEX  @D@@@[ DO VI=0 , GO G$$R69 . SKL
)@@G@@KIP THIS IF FIELD NOT GIVEN   @[@@@[.     @]@@@[G$$R62  NAME@E@@@[      KM
)@@G@@  G$$LAN                . ANALYZE THE LOOP CTL FIELD  @G@@@[G$FLAG*(K,2)KN
)@@G@@ EQU FI(5)              . REMEMBER IF IT HAS DEFERRED CODE  @H@@@[G$FLAGKO
)@@G@@*(K,3) EQU FI(3)              . NOTE FIELD IN WHICH 'TO' SPEC APPEARS   KP
)@@G@@@H@@@[C(1)    EQU    FI(7)+1                . SET FIELD OF NEXT (I.E. UNKQ
)@@G@@TIL) GROUP  @F@@@[KW(1)   EQU    P(C(1),1)              . AND ITS FUNCT KR
)@@G@@FLAG WORD   @]@@@[G$$R69  NAME@G@@@[G$FLAG*(K,1) EQU VI                 KS
)@@G@@. SAVE INDEX OF VARY FIELD, IF ANY  @[@@@[.     @A@@@[.              SCAKT
)@@G@@N 'UNTIL' FIELD   @[@@@[.     @H@@@[G$FLAG*(K,6) EQU    C(1)*(KW(1)=UNTIKU
)@@G@@L). EXTERNALIZE SO WE KNOW IT WAS GIVEN   @[@@@[.     @A@@@[.     ***** KV
)@@G@@CODE GENERATION *****   @[@@@[.     @]@@@[G$$R80  NAME@H@@@[ DO G$FLAG(KKW
)@@G@@,10) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,7) . ENTER WITH JUMP TO WHILE/VARY   @F@@@[KX
)@@G@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,10) . APPLY FLOAT, IF ANY   @[@@@[KY
)@@G@@.     @E@@@[G$LABL*(K,1)                 . MARK START OF WHILE TEST     KZ
)@@G@@@H@@@[ DO (WI>0)**(1-G$FLAG(K,11)) , G$$TST 2+WYNOT,WC,WYNOT G$LABL(K,9)LA
)@@G@@ . GEN IT   @D@@@[G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+((WI>0)**G$FLAG(K,11)) . LB
)@@G@@@F@@@[G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,16) . AND APPLY THE FLOAT   LC
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @A@@@[. GENERATE LOOP <VARY> CODE, IF ANY @[@@@[.     @F@@@[LD
)@@G@@G$LABL*(K,2)                  . MARK START OF 2NDARY LOOP CHECK   @C@@@[LE
)@@G@@ DO VI>0 , ; IF THERE IS LOOP VARIATION CODE    @G@@@[ DO (P(VI,1)=LOOKFLF
)@@G@@OR)++(1-(FI(5)=FI(6))) , ; AND SOME OR ALL IS HERE    @E@@@[        G$$LLG
)@@G@@GE VI,FI(3),FI(4) G$LABL(K,9),1 . GENERATE IT   @F@@@[ DO G$LABL(K,2)<$ LH
)@@G@@,G$FLAG*(K,21) EQU 0 . IF ANY, CAN'T FALL THRU  @[@@@[.     @#@@@[. FINALI
)@@G@@L CLEANUP   @[@@@[.     @E@@@[          G$$SVA                      . SALJ
)@@G@@VE ARGS FOR LATER @F@@@[G$FLAG*(K,9) EQU 0                 . CLEAR ENDCHLK
)@@G@@ECK DONE FLAG     @E@@@[ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,3)=$) , G$$DFL G$LLL
)@@G@@ABL(K,3)    @E@@@[G$LABL*(K,3)                  . MARK START OF USER'S CLM
)@@G@@ODE   @[@@@[.     @]@@@[        END @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     LN
)@@G@@@C@@@[.               ******************************* @C@@@[.           LO
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@[.               *           ESLP
)@@G@@CAPE            * @C@@@[.               *                             * LQ
)@@G@@@C@@@[.               ******************************* @[@@@[.     @[@@@[LR
)@@G@@.     @#@@@[P       PROC   *4 @#@@@[ESCAPE*  NAME     @[@@@[.     @F@@@[LS
)@@G@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@[LT
)@@G@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . AND SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   LU
)@@G@@@E@@@[ DO 1-(G$TYPE(M)=4) , G$$GFL 1,3 . CATCH NESTING ERRORS     @[@@@[LV
)@@G@@.     @E@@@[ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,4)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,4)    LW
)@@G@@@E@@@[G$LABL*(K,4)                 . MARK START OF ESCAPE TEST    @[@@@[LX
)@@G@@.     @H@@@[TBOT      EQU       G$FLAG(K,6)>0     . ON => TEST AT LOGICALY
)@@G@@L BOTTOM (UNTIL)  @H@@@[TTOP      EQU       (G$FLAG(K,1)>0)++(G$FLAG(K,4LZ
)@@G@@)>0) . ON => TESTS AT LGL TOP @H@@@[ DO TTOP**TBOT , G$$GFL 2,1         MA
)@@G@@      . CAN'T HAVE CAKE AND EAT IT TOO    @G@@@[G$FLAG*(K,8) EQU G$FLAG(MB
)@@G@@K,8)**(P(1)=0) . UNCONDITIONAL (LOOKFOR) FLAG   @G@@@[ DO G$FLAG(K,8) , MC
)@@G@@I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,10) . UNCONDITIONAL => LEAP OUT @C@@@[ DO G$FLAG(KMD
)@@G@@,8) , GO G$$E10 . THEN GO CLEAN UP  @[@@@[.     @E@@@[ DO 1-(P(1,1)=WHENME
)@@G@@) , G$$EFL 3,4 . SYNTAX ERROR IF NO 'WHEN'@F@@@[WHENOT    EQU       (P(2MF
)@@G@@)=1)**(P(2,1)=NOT) . ON FOR NOT CONDITION @H@@@[CFLG    EQU    P>(3+WHENMG
)@@G@@OT)                    . ON FOR COMPOUND CONDITION    @[@@@[.     @F@@@[MH
)@@G@@. ON PASS 1, BOTH SENSES OF THE TEST ARE GENERATED, SO WE CAN     @F@@@[MI
)@@G@@. DETERMINE THE FLOAT TO USE IF REVERSAL OCCURS. ON PASS 2, ONLY  @A@@@[MJ
)@@G@@. THE DESIRED SENSE IS GENERATED    @[@@@[.     @F@@@[ DO G$CTR(6)++G$FLMK
)@@G@@AG(K,12) , ; PASS 1 ALWAYS, PASS 2 IF REVERSED  @I@@@[    G$$TST 2+WHENOML
)@@G@@T,CFLG,WHENOT G$LABL(K,1+5*G$FLAG(K,19)) . JUMP=> KEEP LOOPIN     @F@@@[MM
)@@G@@SIZE      EQU       $-G$LABL(K,4)     . LENGTH OF REVERSED TEST   @E@@@[MN
)@@G@@          RES       -G$CTR(6)*SIZE . THEN RES TEST AWAY     @H@@@[G$CTR*MO
)@@G@@(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+G$CTR(7)+G$FLAG(K,7) . KEEP G$$TST CTR IN PHASE  MP
)@@G@@@I@@@[ DO 1-(G$FLAG(K,12)++G$FLAG(K,7)) , ; PASS1 ALWAYS, 2 IF NOT REVERMQ
)@@G@@SED/SURPRESSED    @G@@@[    G$$TST 2+WHENOT,CFLG,1-WHENOT G$LABL(K,10) .MR
)@@G@@ JUMP=> EXIT FROM LOOP  @E@@@[WIZE      EQU       $-G$LABL(K,4)     . SIMS
)@@G@@ZE OF 2ND TEST    @[@@@[.     @H@@@[ DO G$CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU    SIMT
)@@G@@DE(1)           . PASS 1: SET SIDE EFFECT @H@@@[G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTMU
)@@G@@R(2)+G$FLAG(K,17) . PASS2: APPLY FLOAT FOR ENCLOSED BL@E@@@[G$FLAG*(K,17MV
)@@G@@) EQU  SIZE-WIZE . PASS 1: GET FLOAT, 2=>NOISE  @[@@@[.     @#@@@[G$$E10MW
)@@G@@    NAME    @F@@@[G$LABL*(K,5)                    . MARK START OF USER'SMX
)@@G@@ ESCAPE CODE@]@@@[        END @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @C@@@[.           MY
)@@G@@    ******************************* @C@@@[.               *             MZ
)@@G@@                * @C@@@[.               *         OTHERWISE           * NA
)@@G@@@C@@@[.               *                             * @C@@@[.           NB
)@@G@@    *           ATEND             * @C@@@[.               *             NC
)@@G@@                * @C@@@[.               *           ENDREP            * ND
)@@G@@@C@@@[.               *                             * @C@@@[.           NE
)@@G@@    ******************************* @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @#@@@[Y     NF
)@@G@@  PROC   *1 @^@@@[OTHERWISE* NAME     0   @^@@@[ATEND*    NAME      1   NG
)@@G@@@^@@@[ENDREP*   NAME      2   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[M         EQU       G$CTNH
)@@G@@R(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@[K         EQU       G$SENI
)@@G@@QN(M)         . AND SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   @E@@@[ DO 1-(G$TYPE(M)=4NJ
)@@G@@) , G$$GFL 1,3 . CATCH NESTING ERRORS     @E@@@[ DO G$LABL(K,5)=0 ,G$LABNK
)@@G@@L*(K,5) . FIXUP FOR MISSING ESCAPE  @[@@@[.     @A@@@[. CLOSE DANGLING ENL
)@@G@@SCAPE, IF REQUIRED@[@@@[.     @F@@@[ DO G$FLAG(K,13) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LANM
)@@G@@BL(K,10) . PASS2: LEAP OUT    @F@@@[G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(NN
)@@G@@K,13) . APPLY CLOSURE FLOAT   @F@@@[G$FLAG*(K,13) EQU   0               NO
)@@G@@  . REMEMBER WE'VE DONE THIS  @[@@@[.     @C@@@[. **** OTHERWISE GETS OFNP
)@@G@@F THE TRAIN HERE ...    @[@@@[.     @G@@@[ DO Y(0,0)>0 , GO G$$Z10      NQ
)@@G@@        . IF ATEND OR ENDREP, KEEP MOVING @H@@@[ DO G$LABL(K,4)=0 , G$$GNR
)@@G@@FL 2,2            . OTHERWISE INVALID IF NO ESCAPE    @E@@@[ DO G$CTR(7)NS
)@@G@@ , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,6)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,6) 1  @F@@@[G$LABL*(K,6)      NT
)@@G@@            . MARK START OF 'OTHERWISE' CODE    @B@@@[ DO 1 , END       NU
)@@G@@  . THAT'S ALL FOLKS    @[@@@[.     @A@@@[. **** ATEND/ENDREP LUMBER ONWNV
)@@G@@ARD...@[@@@[.     @F@@@[.         CLOSE LOOP: GEN CTL CODE WHICH PREFERSNW
)@@G@@ PHYSICAL BOTTOM  @[@@@[.     @#@@@[G$$Z10    NAME    @H@@@[ DO G$FLAG(KNX
)@@G@@,9) , GO G$$Z50          . IF ITS TUESDAY, THIS MUST BE ENDREP    @F@@@[NY
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,9) EQU 1                 . REMEMBER WE'VE BEEN HERE     @E@@@[NZ
)@@G@@ DO G$LABL(K,6)=0 ,G$LABL*(K,6) . DEFAULT START OF OTHERWISE@G@@@[KK    OA
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(3)          . GET POINTER INTO ARGSAVE STACK  @H@@@[OB
)@@G@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,J DO G$ARGS(KK,I) ,P(I,J) EQU +G$ARGS(KK,I,J) . GET ARGOC
)@@G@@S     @G@@@[G$CTR*(3) EQU       KK-1              . THEN MOVE STACK POINOD
)@@G@@TER BACK    @I@@@[ DO (Y(0,0)=1)**(G$ARGS(KK)=0) , G$$GFL 2,3        . AOE
)@@G@@TEND UNREACHABLE IF NO ARG    @G@@@[LL      EQU    G$FLAG(K,2)          OF
)@@G@@. ON IF ANY <VARY> CODE WAS DEFERRED@H@@@[DFER      EQU       LL++(G$FLAOG
)@@G@@G(K,4)>0) . ON IF DEFFERED CODE OF ANY TYPE     @[@@@[.     @F@@@[. HANDOH
)@@G@@LE UNTIL CONDITIONS. THEY CAN HAVE EITHER BRANCH SENSE:     @G@@@[.   A)OI
)@@G@@ IF WHILE/VARY CODE WILL FOLLOW, UNTIL SUCCESS LEAPS TO ATEND     @E@@@[OJ
)@@G@@.   B) IF NOT (A), THEN UNTIL FAILURE LEAPS TO TOP OF LOOP  @[@@@[.     OK
)@@G@@@H@@@[UNORG                                 . MARK ORIGIN OF UNTIL TESTSOL
)@@G@@, IF ANY    @G@@@[UN        EQU       G$FLAG(K,6)     . GET INDEX INTO POM
)@@G@@ OF UNTIL SPECS   @B@@@[ DO UN=0 , GO G$$Z30                  .   @G@@@[ON
)@@G@@KILL      EQU       G$CTR(7)**G$FLAG(K,7) . ON IF SURPRESSING ALL CODE  OO
)@@G@@@G@@@[G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,5) . APPLY UNTIL SURPRESS FLOP
)@@G@@OAT   @F@@@[G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+KILL     . COUNT SURPRESSED UNTOQ
)@@G@@IL    @E@@@[ DO KILL , GO G$$Z30                   . AND FORGET THE RESTOR
)@@G@@@F@@@[UNN       EQU       (P(UN+1)=1)**(P(UN+1,1)=NOT) . SET NOT FLAG   OS
)@@G@@@I@@@[UNC       EQU       (P(UN+UNN+2)=1)**((P(UN+UNN+2,1)=OR)++(P(UN+UNOT
)@@G@@N+2,1)=AND)) .    @D@@@[  G$$TST UN+UNN+1,UNC,DFER--UNN G$LABL(K,1+9*DFEOU
)@@G@@R)    @[@@@[.     @A@@@[. CLOSE DANGLING OTHERWISE/UNTIL    @[@@@[.     OV
)@@G@@@#@@@[G$$Z30    NAME    @G@@@[G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU    UNORG-$           . GEOW
)@@G@@T FLOAT FOR SURPRESSED UNTIL  @E@@@[ DO G$FLAG(K,14) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LAOX
)@@G@@BL(K,1) . JUMP TO TOP   @F@@@[G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,14) OY
)@@G@@. FLOAT FOLLOWING CODE  @E@@@[G$FLAG*(K,14) EQU   0                 . REOZ
)@@G@@MEMBER WE DID THIS@[@@@[.     @G@@@[. HANDLE WHILE CONDITIONS.  THESE CAPA
)@@G@@N BE SURPRESSED OR CAN BRANCH TWO   @F@@@[. WAYS; FORTUNATELY, THE BRANCPB
)@@G@@H SENSE IS KNOWN ON PASS 1 (LL):    @F@@@[.  A) IF <VARY> CODE FOLLOWS, PC
)@@G@@THEN WHILE FAILURE JUMPS TO ATEND   @D@@@[.  B) IF NOT (A), WHILE SUCCESPD
)@@G@@S JUMPS TO TOP OF LOOP  @[@@@[.     @F@@@[G$LABL*(K,7)                 .PE
)@@G@@ MARK START OF BOTTOM-OF-LOOP WHILE @B@@@[. NOTE: IF WHILE EXISTS, ITS APF
)@@G@@LWAYS SPEC 1@B@@@[WYNOT     EQU       (P(2)=1)**(P(2,1)=NOT)@H@@@[WC    PG
)@@G@@    EQU       ((P(3+WYNOT,1)=OR)++(P(3+WYNOT,1)=AND))**(P(3+WYNOT)=1)   PH
)@@G@@@G@@@[ DO (G$FLAG(K,4)>0)**(1-G$FLAG(K,15)) , ; IF EXISTS AND NOT SURPREPI
)@@G@@SSED- @D@@@[        G$$TST 2+WYNOT,WC,LL=WYNOT G$LABL(K,2+7*LL)   @F@@@[PJ
)@@G@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+G$FLAG(K,15) . COUNT SURPRESSED WHILE@H@@@[PK
)@@G@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,18) . APPLY WHILE SURPRESSION FLOAPL
)@@G@@T     @[@@@[.     @^@@@[. GENERATE <VARY> CODE  @[@@@[.     @F@@@[G$LABLPM
)@@G@@*(K,8)                 . MARK START OF BOTTOM OF LOOP VARY  @H@@@[ DO G$PN
)@@G@@CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU G$FLAG(K,7)++(G$FLAG(K,1)>0) . NOTE SIDE EFFEC PO
)@@G@@@D@@@[ DO LL , G$$LGE G$FLAG(K,1),G$FLAG(K,3) G$LABL(K,3)   @[@@@[.     PP
)@@G@@@G@@@[ DO G$CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU G$FLAG(K,7)++SIDE(1) . NOTE SIDE EFPQ
)@@G@@FECTS @E@@@[ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,9)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,9) 2  PR
)@@G@@@F@@@[G$LABL*(K,9)                  . MARK START OF USER ATEND CODE     PS
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @C@@@[. END PROCESSING OF LOOP TERMINATION CONDITIONS @[@@@[PT
)@@G@@.     @D@@@[ DO Y(0,0)=1 , END  . ATEND STATEMENT FINISHES UP HERE@[@@@[PU
)@@G@@.     @ @@@[. CLEANUP FOR ENDREP STATEMENT@[@@@[.     @#@@@[G$$Z50    NAPV
)@@G@@ME    @E@@@[ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,10)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,10) 3PW
)@@G@@@D@@@[G$LABL*(K,10)                  . SET BLOCK EXIT LABEL @E@@@[G$CTR*PX
)@@G@@(2) EQU       G$FLAG(K,20)      . RESTORE GLOBAL FLOAT@G@@@[G$CTR*(5) EQPY
)@@G@@U  M-1                    . DECREMENT GLOBAL NESTING LEVEL  @C@@@[ DO G$PZ
)@@G@@CTR(7) , END . ON PASS 2, WE'RE DONE HERE @[@@@[.     @E@@@[. ***** PASSQA
)@@G@@ 1 ONLY: DETERMINE POSITIONING AND OPTIMIZATIONS@[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     QB
)@@G@@@G@@@[. SET FLAGS INDICATING WHETHER USER PUT ANY CODE IN SPECIFIC CLAUSQC
)@@G@@ES    @[@@@[.     @F@@@[ESCAPP    EQU       G$LABL(K,4)>0     . ON=>ESCAQD
)@@G@@PE STMNT APPEARED @H@@@[RVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,3)=G$LABL(K,5-ESCAPQE
)@@G@@P) . ON=> NOTHING AFTER REPEAT@H@@@[EVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,5)=G$LAQF
)@@G@@BL(K,6) . ON=> USER ESCAPE CLAUSE VACUOUS @I@@@[UOVAC     EQU       G$LAQG
)@@G@@BL(K,6)=(G$LABL(K,7)+G$FLAG(K,5)) . ON=> NO USER 'OTHER     @I@@@[OVAC  QH
)@@G@@    EQU       G$LABL(K,6)=G$LABL(K,7) . ON=> EMPTY OTHERWISE/UNTIL CLAUSQI
)@@G@@E     @H@@@[AVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,9)=G$LABL(K,10) . ON=> USER ATEQJ
)@@G@@ND CLAUSE VACUOUS @[@@@[.     @F@@@[NOKILL    EQU       G$FLAG(K,7)++(1-QK
)@@G@@(RVAC**EVAC**UOVAC**AVAC)) .  @[@@@[.     @H@@@[VATBOT    EQU       G$FLQL
)@@G@@AG(K,2)       . ON=> SOME (OR ALL) <VARY> AT BOTTOM   @H@@@[LOOBOT    EQQM
)@@G@@U       VATBOT++(1-OVAC)  . ON=> SOME LOOP CODE WILL BE AT BOTTOM @H@@@[QN
)@@G@@EFOLLO    EQU       LOOBOT++(1-AVAC)  . ON=> SOMETHING WILL FOLLOW ESCAPQO
)@@G@@E     @[@@@[.     @G@@@[. COMPUTE OPTIMUM POSITIONING OF WHILE (CAN BE TQP
)@@G@@OP, BOTTOM, OR BOTH)    @[@@@[.     @G@@@[WHSPEC    EQU       G$FLAG(K,4QQ
)@@G@@)>0     . ON IF WHILE SPECIFICATION GIVEN @H@@@[WONET     EQU       1=(GQR
)@@G@@$LABL(K,2)-G$LABL(K,1)) . ON => WHILE IS ONE INST AT T@G@@@[WONEB     EQQS
)@@G@@U       1=(G$LABL(K,8)-G$LABL(K,7)) . ON => ONE INSTR AT BOT@[@@@[.     QT
)@@G@@@I@@@[WHIBOT    EQU       (EFOLLO++(1-ESCAPP))**NOKILL . ON=> IF WHILE, QU
)@@G@@ALLOW AT BOTTO    @I@@@[WHISBO    EQU       WHSPEC**WHIBOT    . ON => WHQV
)@@G@@ILE WILL REALLY APPEAR AT BOTTOM    @I@@@[WHITOP    EQU       ((WONET**WQW
)@@G@@ONEB**(1-VATBOT))++(1-WHIBOT))**NOKILL . 0N=>ALLOW    @[@@@[.     @F@@@[QX
)@@G@@. SET GLOBAL SURPRESS FLAGS AND FLOATS FOR WHILE OPTIMIZATION     @[@@@[QY
)@@G@@.     @F@@@[G$FLAG*(K,11) EQU   WHSPEC**(1-WHITOP) . ON => SURPRESS AT TQZ
)@@G@@OP    @H@@@[G$FLAG*(K,16) EQU   (G$LABL(K,1)-G$LABL(K,2))*G$FLAG(K,11) .RA
)@@G@@ TOP SURPRESS FLOA@F@@@[G$FLAG*(K,15) EQU   WHSPEC**(1-WHIBOT) . ON=> SURB
)@@G@@RPRESS AT BOTTOM  @H@@@[G$FLAG*(K,18) EQU   (G$LABL(K,7)-G$LABL(K,8))*G$RC
)@@G@@FLAG(K,15) . BOT SURPRESS FLOA@[@@@[.     @E@@@[. COMPUTE VARIOUS FLAGS RD
)@@G@@FOR ESCAPE OPTIMIZATION AND CLOSURE @[@@@[.     @F@@@[G$FLAG*(K,19) EQU RE
)@@G@@  LOOBOT++WHISBO    . ON=>LOOP CODE FOLLOWS     @H@@@[G$FLAG*(K,12) EQU RF
)@@G@@  (1-(G$FLAG(K,19)**EVAC))**NOKILL . ON=>JUMP TO KEEP GOING @F@@@[G$FLAGRG
)@@G@@*(K,17) EQU   G$FLAG(K,17)*G$FLAG(K,12) . SET FLOAT TO USE  @F@@@[ DO 1-RH
)@@G@@NOKILL ,G$FLAG*(K,17) EQU ESCAPP*(G$LABL(K,4)-G$LABL(K,5)) .@H@@@[G$FLAGRI
)@@G@@*(K,13) EQU   NOKILL**ESCAPP**G$FLAG(K,12)**G$FLAG(K,19) . CLOSURE FLAG RJ
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @G@@@[. SET FLAG FOR GENERATION OF JUMP TO WHILE/VARY AT TOPRK
)@@G@@ (INITIAL ENTRY)  @[@@@[.     @I@@@[G$FLAG*(K,10) EQU   (VATBOT++((1-WHIRL
)@@G@@TOP)**WHSPEC))**NOKILL . ON=> GEN ENTRY JUMP    @[@@@[.     @G@@@[. FOR RM
)@@G@@IMMEDIATE JGD LOOPS WE WON'T JUMP. FOR NOW, WE WON'T CHECK FOR    @G@@@[RN
)@@G@@. PRESENCE OF WHILE AT TOP, BUT WILL TURN OFF THIS OPTIMIZATION IF THERERO
)@@G@@@G@@@[. IS ANY WHILE AT ALL. IN ADDITION, ONLY JGD'S NOW SET THE OPTIMIZRP
)@@G@@ATION @G@@@[. FLAG, SO THERE WILL BE NO FLOATING. WHEN TLEM'S AND JMGI'SRQ
)@@G@@ ARE DONE,  @G@@@[. SURPRESSION OF SOME REGISTER LOAD CODE WILL CAUSE FLRR
)@@G@@OAT WHICH WILL    @C@@@[. NEED TO BE COMPENSATED FOR AT THIS POINT.     RS
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @H@@@[CANFAL    EQU       (1-WHSPEC)**(G$FLAG(K,21)>0) . ON RT
)@@G@@=> WE CAN FALL THRU     @H@@@[ DO CANFAL ,G$FLAG*(K,10) EQU 0       . SORU
)@@G@@ FORGET ABOUT JUMPING TO BOTTOM     @G@@@[ DO 1-CANFAL ,G$FLAG*(K,21) EQRV
)@@G@@U 0     . CLEAR FLAG IF WE CAN'T FALL THRU@[@@@[.     @G@@@[. CLOSE OTHERW
)@@G@@RWISE/UNTIL WITH JUMP IF NOT FOLLOWED BY TESTS WHICH DO IT  @[@@@[.     RX
)@@G@@@H@@@[UNTOP     EQU       (G$FLAG(K,6)>0)**(1-(VATBOT++WHSPEC)) . UNTIL RY
)@@G@@JUMPS TO TOP@H@@@[G$FLAG*(K,14) EQU   (1-((OVAC**ESCAPP)++WHISBO++VATBOTRZ
)@@G@@++UNTOP))**NOKILL .     @G@@@[G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU G$FLAG(K,5)*(1-NOKILL) . SA
)@@G@@ADJUST UNTIL SURPRESSION FLOAT@[@@@[.     @G@@@[. SET LC TO REFLECT WHATSB
)@@G@@ IT WILL BE ON PASS 2 BY APPLYING FLOATS TO IT  @[@@@[.     @F@@@[G$FLAGSC
)@@G@@*(K,7) EQU    1-NOKILL          . SET FLAG TO KILL ALL CODE @H@@@[      SD
)@@G@@    RES       G$FLAG(K,5)+G$FLAG(K,10)+G$FLAG(K,16)+G$FLAG(K,17)+ ;     SE
)@@G@@@E@@@[                    G$FLAG(K,13)+G$FLAG(K,14)+G$FLAG(K,18)  @]@@@[SF
)@@G@@        END @C@@@[/.         ******** EXEC REQUEST GROUP *********@[@@@[SG
)@@G@@.     @[@@@[.     @C@@@[.               ******************************* SH
)@@G@@@C@@@[.               *                             * @C@@@[.           SI
)@@G@@    *          -READ-$            * @C@@@[.               *             SJ
)@@G@@                * @C@@@[.               ******************************* SK
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @#@@@[P       PROC   *1 @#@@@[READ$*  NAME   015SL
)@@G@@@#@@@[READA$*  NAME  042@^@@@[TREAD$*  NAME  0102     @^@@@[AREAD$*  NAMSM
)@@G@@E  0166     @^@@@[AREADA$*  NAME 0167     @^@@@[ATREAD$*  NAME 0170     SN
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @G@@@[ DO (P(0,0)=015)++(P(0,0)=0166) , GO G$$D20 . NO PKT ISO
)@@G@@F READ$,AREAD$    @G@@@[PKTOFF  EQU    (P(0,0)=0102)++(P(0,0)=0170) . OFSP
)@@G@@FSET FOR TREAD$ PACKETS @G@@@[ DO P(1)=0 , GO G$$D10                . IFSQ
)@@G@@ PKT ADDR NOT GIVEN, GO KLUDGE@[@@@[.     @F@@@[. GENERATE CODE FOR CASESR
)@@G@@ WHERE PACKET ADDR EXPLICITLY GIVEN---    @[@@@[.     @G@@@[        LA,USS
)@@G@@   A0,$+5                 . GET EOF ADDR (SKIP AFTER READ$) @H@@@[      ST
)@@G@@  I$     06,H1,A0,P(1,2),P(1,*1),P(1,1)+PKTOFF . STASH IN PACKET (FIELD SU
)@@G@@@G@@@[        I$     026,U,A0,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) . LXM PKT SV
)@@G@@ADR   @E@@@[ GO G$$D99                            . GO GENERATE THE READSW
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @E@@@[. IF PACKET ADDR CAN VARY AT XQT TIME, WE MUST FARBLE SX
)@@G@@A BIT @[@@@[.     @]@@@[G$$D10  NAME@G@@@[        LXI,U  A0,0,A1        SY
)@@G@@        . TEMP SAVE A1 LOWER IN A0 UPPER  @F@@@[        LXM,U  A1,$+7   SZ

)@@G@@,A0           . EOF ADDR TO PACKET  @G@@@[        LSSC   A0,18          TB
)@@G@@        . ALIGN OLD A1 LOWER IN A0 LOWER  @E@@@[        LXM,U  A1,0,A0  TC
)@@G@@              . RESTORE A1 LOWER    @E@@@[        SSL    A0,18          TD
)@@G@@        . REALIGN PACKET ADDR @E@@@[ GO G$$D99                          TE
)@@G@@  . THEN GO DO THE ER   @[@@@[.     @D@@@[. GENERATE CALL FOR IO FUNCTS TF
)@@G@@WHICH DO NOT USE PACKETS@[@@@[.     @]@@@[G$$D20  NAME@G@@@[        LXI,TG

)@@G@@1)>0 ,         I$     026,U,A0,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) . LXM BUFTI
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @]@@@[G$$D99  NAME@D@@@[        ER     P(0,0)               TJ

)@@G@@XIT HERE    @G@@@[        AA,U   A0,0400000             . IF EOF, SET LOTL
)@@G@@WORDER SIGN BIT   @]@@@[        END @[@@@[.     @D@@@[/.   ****** UTILITTM
)@@G@@IES FOR CONDITION TESTING *******   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[.     ************TN
)@@G@@********************************************    @F@@@[.     *           TO
)@@G@@                                           *    @F@@@[.     *       G$$CTP
)@@G@@AN : ANALYZE A SIMPLE CONDITION FIELD      *    @F@@@[.     *           TQ
)@@G@@                                           *    @F@@@[.     ************TR
)@@G@@********************************************    @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     TS
)@@G@@@H@@@[. DEFINE ARRAYS FOR OPTIMIZATION OF TYPE 1 TESTS ON REGISTERS INTOTT
)@@G@@ TYPE 3     @[@@@[.     @#@@@[          DEF     @F@@@[G$ALTT(NE)  EQU   TU
)@@G@@  NONZ              . NOT EQUAL ZERO IS NONZERO @E@@@[G$ALTT(EQ)  EQU   TV
)@@G@@  ZERO              . EQUAL ZERO IS ZERO  @ @@@[G$ALTT(DNE) EQU     DNONTW
)@@G@@Z     @ @@@[G$ALTT(DEQ) EQU     DZERO     @F@@@[G$ALTT(LT)  EQU     NEG TX
)@@G@@              . LESS THAN ZERO IS NEGATIVE@G@@@[G$ALTT(GE)  EQU     POS TY
)@@G@@              . GTR OR EQUAL ZERO IS POSITIVE   @#@@@[Z       PROC   *1 TZ
)@@G@@@#@@@[G$$CAN*  NAME     @H@@@[I       EQU    Z(1,1)                 . GEUA
)@@G@@T INDEX TO FIELD BEING ANALYZED     @F@@@[K       EQU    Z(1,2)         UB
)@@G@@        . GET ITS ORDER IN THE TEST @ @@@[. DETERMINE TYPE OF CONDITION UC
)@@G@@@ @@@[ DO P(I,2)>0  ,N(1) EQU 1     @ @@@[ DO P(I,2)=IN ,N(1) EQU 2     UD
)@@G@@@A@@@[ DO P(I,2)=IS ,N(1) EQU 3+2*(P(I)=4)@ @@@[ DO P(I)=1    ,N(1) EQU UE
)@@G@@4     @ @@@[ DO P(I,1)=CHANNEL ,N(1) EQU 6@F@@@[ DO N(1)<1 , G$$EFL 1,1 UF
)@@G@@              . E-FLAG IF UNKNOWN TYPE    @[@@@[.     @E@@@[. TRY TO CHAUG
)@@G@@NGE TEST TO A MORE OPTIMAL ONE THAN SPECIFIED   @[@@@[.     @H@@@[ DO (NUH
)@@G@@(1)=2)**G$AMPR , GO G$$A10      . REG STATUS NEEDS RELOCATION FUNC &(X) UI
)@@G@@@G@@@[ DO (N(1)>1)++(P(I,5)<016) , GO G$$A30 . VALUE TESTS NEED IMMEDIATUJ
)@@G@@ES    @[@@@[.     @D@@@[. IMMEDIATE LE OR GT CAN BE ALTERED TO LT OR GE.UK
)@@G@@..    @[@@@[.     @E@@@[FUDGE     EQU       (LT-LE)*(P(I,2)=LE)+(GE-GT)*UL
)@@G@@(P(I,2)=GT) @D@@@[P**(I,2) EQU        P(I,2)+FUDGE      . ADJUST KEYWORDUM
)@@G@@@F@@@[P**(I,3) EQU        P(I,3)+1-(FUDGE=0) . ADJUST IMMEDIATE VALUE   UN
)@@G@@@F@@@[ DO (1-((P(I,3)=0)**(P(I,4)=0)))++(G$ALTT(P(I,2))=0) , GO G$$A30 .UO
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @G@@@[. REGISTER TESTS AGAINST IMMEDIATE ZEROES CAN BECOME CUP
)@@G@@ONDITIONAL JUMPS  @[@@@[.     @C@@@[. BE CAREFUL NOT TO OVEROPTIMIZE IMMUQ
)@@G@@EDIATES     @F@@@[ DO 1-G$AMPR , GO G$$A30 . CANNOT OPTIMIZE WITHOUT & FUR
)@@G@@UNCTION     @E@@@[ DO 1-(&(P(I,3))=-2) , GO G$$A30 . ZERO MUST BE ABSOLUUS
)@@G@@TE    @F@@@[P**(I,3)  EQU       G$ALTT(P(I,2))    . GET ALTERNATE KEYWORUT
)@@G@@D     @H@@@[P**(I)    EQU       3                 . FORCE NUMBER OF ARGSUU
)@@G@@ (PRUNE AWAY ,,U) @C@@@[ GO G$$A20          . GO FINISH UP THE FARBLING UV
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @G@@@[. TYPE 2 CONDITION TESTS ON A-REGS CAN BECOME CONDITIOUW
)@@G@@NAL JUMPS, TOO.   @[@@@[.     @#@@@[G$$A10    NAME    @I@@@[REG       EQUX
)@@G@@U       P(I,3)            . GET REG FROM  <KEYWORD>,IN,<REG> FORMAT     UY
)@@G@@@G@@@[ DO (REG<A0)++(REG>A15) , GO G$$A30   . MAKE SURE ITS WITHIN AREG UZ
)@@G@@RANGE @F@@@[ DO 1-(&(REG)=-2) , GO G$$A30         . AND AN ABSOLUTE VALUVA
)@@G@@E     @H@@@[P**(I,3)  EQU       P(I,1)            . FORCE CONDITION KEYWVB
)@@G@@ORD INTO SPEC3    @F@@@[P**(I,1)  EQU       REG               . THEN MOVVC
)@@G@@E REG INTO SPEC1  @[@@@[.     @I@@@[G$$A20    NAME                      VD
)@@G@@  . FINISH FUDGING  <AREG>,IS,<KEYWORD> TEST    @E@@@[P**(I,2)  EQU     VE
)@@G@@  IS                . CRAM IN THE KEYWORD @G@@@[N(1)      EQU       3   VF
)@@G@@              . AND MARK THIS AS A TYPE 3 TEST  @[@@@[.     @#@@@[G$$A30VG
)@@G@@    NAME    @F@@@[J(1)    EQU    P(I,G$KSF(N(1)))       . GET FUNC KEYWOVH
)@@G@@RD VALUE    @H@@@[ DO DTH ,J(1) EQU G$IV(N(1),J(1))     . FLIP IF DEMORGVI
)@@G@@AN'S THEOREM IN EFFECT  @F@@@[ DO J(1)<1 , G$$EFL 1,2               . E-VJ
)@@G@@FLAG IF UNKNOWN KEYWORD @F@@@[NI$*(K) EQU    G$FJ(N(1),J(1))        . NOVK
)@@G@@ OF INSTRS GENERATED    @D@@@[WA$*(K) EQU    G$WS(N(1),J(1))        . WAVL
)@@G@@ITING STATUS@G@@@[KE$*(K) EQU    J(1)                   . EXTERNALIZE FUVM
)@@G@@NC KEYWORD VAL    @F@@@[TP$*(K) EQU    N(1)                   . EXTERNALVN
)@@G@@IZE TYPE OF TEST  @]@@@[        END @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     VO
)@@G@@@F@@@[.     ********************************************************    VP
)@@G@@@F@@@[.     *                                                      *    VQ
)@@G@@@F@@@[.     *  G$$COD : GENERATE CODE FOR A SIMPLE CONDITION TEST  *    VR
)@@G@@@F@@@[.     *                                                      *    VS
)@@G@@@F@@@[.     ********************************************************    VT
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @#@@@[Q       PROC   *2 @I@@@[G$$COD*  NAME     VU
)@@G@@                    . PF'S: FIELD-INDEX,TEST-INDEX,WAIT-VAL FA    @F@@@[VV
)@@G@@I       EQU    Q(1,1)                 . GET FIELD WE'RE SCANNING  @F@@@[VW
)@@G@@NN      EQU    Q(1,2)                 . GET DECODED DATA INDEX    @E@@@[VX
)@@G@@N       EQU    TP$(NN)                . GET CONDITION TYPE  @E@@@[. COMPVY

)@@G@@   G$FCF(N)=0             . SET FLAG IF G$FJ=FUNC CODE (ELSE ITS J-S    WA
)@@G@@@H@@@[AAA     EQU    0+(G$ASF(N)>0)*(P(I,G$ASF(N))-A0) . WATCH OUT FOR -WB
)@@G@@0!!!!!!     @ @@@[EXREG   EQU    CGISF*P(I,4)   @B@@@[HI      EQU    CGIWC
)@@G@@SF*(2*P(I,*4)+P(I,*3))  @C@@@[EWE     EQU    CGISF*P(I,3)+(1-CGISF)*Q(2,WD
)@@G@@1)    @G@@@[SIDE**(1) EQU SIDE(1)++(N=5)++(HI>0)  . ON IF TEST HAS SIDE WE
)@@G@@EFFECTS     @E@@@[. NOW GET FIELDS WHICH DEPEND UPON THE SPECIFIED CONDIWF
)@@G@@TION  @E@@@[JI(1)   EQU    KE$(NN)                . GET KEYWORD FUNCTIONWG
)@@G@@@F@@@[JI(2)   EQU    G$IV(N,JI(1))          . AND KEYWORD OF THE INVERSEWH
)@@G@@@F@@@[WOK     EQU    Q(1,3)=G$WS(N,JI(1))   . ON IF WAITING STATUS OK   WI
)@@G@@@H@@@[ DO G$FJ(N,JI(1),1)>077 , GO G$$C01   . CHECK FOR ASYMMETRIC INSTRWJ
)@@G@@UCTIONS     @[@@@[.     @G@@@[. PROCESS SYMMETRIC TESTS (FOR WHICH AN INWK
)@@G@@VERSE MACHINE INSTR EXISTS)   @[@@@[.     @G@@@[JIU     EQU    JI(2-WOK)WL
)@@G@@              . GET INDEX OF OPCODE WE'LL USE   @G@@@[NUMINS  EQU    G$FWM
)@@G@@J(N,JIU)            . GET NO OF INSTRS TO GENERATE    @H@@@[XTIM      EQWN
)@@G@@U     CGISF**(N<3)**(HI=0)**(P(I,5)>015) . IMMEDIATE EXTENSION    @E@@@[WO

)@@G@@   NUMINS ,JAY(K) EQU CGISF*P(I,5)+(1-CGISF)*G$FJ(N,JIU,K)  @I@@@[K DO  WQ
)@@G@@   NUMINS*(1-XTIM) , I$ FUN(K),JAY(K),AAA,EXREG,HI,EWE . GENERATE THE INWR
)@@G@@ST    @G@@@[K DO     NUMINS*XTIM , G$$IMU FUN(K),JAY(K),AAA,EXREG,EWE . WS
)@@G@@IMMEDIATES  @G@@@[REVER**(1) EQU (G$FJ(N,JI(1))*G$FJ(N,JI(2)))=1 . SET RWT
)@@G@@EVERSIBLE FLAG    @G@@@[ DO 1-(REVER(1)++WOK) , I$ 074,04,,,,$+2 . WATCHWU
)@@G@@OUT FOR NON-REVERSIBLES @H@@@[ DO 1 , END                           . FOWV
)@@G@@R STANDARD INSTRS, ITS ALL OVER HERE@[@@@[.     @F@@@[. PROCESS ASYMMETRWW
)@@G@@IC INSTRS (FOR WHICH NO SINGLE INVERSE EXISTS)  @[@@@[.     @]@@@[G$$C01WX

)@@G@@@D@@@[. IF NOT A DTE, THEN INSTRUCTION IS A JUMP OF SORTS   @B@@@[. (EITXA

)@@G@@00)     . FOR CHANNEL INSTRS, USE GIVEN AVALUE  @C@@@[        G$$FFJ FUNXC

)@@G@@,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUMP TO FALSE @]@@@[ GO G$$T99  @]@@@[G$$T25  NAMEAP
)@@G@@@B@@@[. HERE IF BOTH TESTS ARE MULTI-INSTRUCTION@D@@@[        G$$COD II(AQ
)@@G@@IX(1)),IX(1),2      . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@[        I$     074,04,,,,FA(1)AR

)@@G@@IP IF FALSE @[@@@[.     @]@@@[G$$T99  NAME@F@@@[ DO $=ORIG , G$$EFL 1,1 AY
