)@@G@@LBL(TTL)=$) ,  G$$DFL G$TLBL(TTL) 0,0777  @F@@@[G$TLBL**(TTL)           BA
)@@G@@        . RELEVANT ON GLOBAL PASS 1 ONLY  @]@@@[        END @E@@@[/.  **BB
)@@G@@***** UTILITIES FOR GENERATION OF LOOP CONTROLS ******@[@@@[.     @[@@@[BC
)@@G@@.     @F@@@[. SELECTION OF THE INSTRUCTION TO BE USED TO CONTROL THE LOOBD
)@@G@@P IS: @E@@@[.    1) JGD    IF LOOP TERMINATES AT 0 AND STEP IS -1, OR   BE
)@@G@@@E@@@[.              LOOP IS FOR A SPECIFIED NUMBER OF TIMES.     @E@@@[BF
)@@G@@.    2) JMGI   IF LOOP TERMINATES AT 0 AND STEP IS NOT -1.  @D@@@[.    3BG
)@@G@@) TLEM   IF LOOP TERMINATES AT OTHER THAN ZERO. @[@@@[.     @D@@@[. POSIBH
)@@G@@TIONING OF THE LOOP CONTROL INSTRUCTION IS:     @A@@@[.    1) JGD    ALWBI
)@@G@@AYS AT THE BOTTOM @F@@@[.    2) JMGI   AT BOTTOM (SO JUMP DESTINATION COBJ
)@@G@@NTINUES IN THE    @F@@@[.              LOOP), IF INCREMENT NEGATIVE (LOOBK
)@@G@@P SENSE DOWN),    @E@@@[.              I.E. VALUES OF LOOP CONTROL VARIABL
)@@G@@BLE ARE >0 .@A@@@[.              AT TOP OTHERWISE     @F@@@[.    3) TLEMBM
)@@G@@   AT BOTTOM (SO SKIP CAUSES EXIT FROM LOOP) WHEN     @E@@@[.           BN
)@@G@@   INCREMENT IS POSITIVE (LOOP SENSE UP), I.E.  @F@@@[.              TERBO
)@@G@@MINATION CONDITION IS APPROACHED FROM BELOW.    @F@@@[.              BECBP
)@@G@@AUSE OF LACK OF SIGN EXTENSION, THIS HOLDS RE-  @F@@@[.              GARBQ
)@@G@@DLESS OF THE SIGN OF THE LOOP VARIABLE ITSELF.  @[@@@[.     @G@@@[. NOTEBR
)@@G@@: IF THE SIGN OF THE INCREMENT IS UNKNOWN (JMGI/TLEM), THE CODE   @G@@@[BS
)@@G@@. TO VARY THE LOOP CONTROL VARIABLE WILL BE DUPLICATED AT BOTH TOP AND  BT
)@@G@@@F@@@[. BOTTOM, WITH AN EXECUTE-TIME TEST (SIGN JUMP) AT THE BOTTOM TO  BU
)@@G@@@A@@@[. DETERMINE WHICH IS TO BE USED.    @[@@@[.     @G@@@[. TO ENFORCEBV
)@@G@@ THE REQUIREMENT THAT THE LOOP CONTROL REGISTER CONTAIN     @F@@@[. THE BW
)@@G@@FROM/TO VALUES ON THE FIRST AND LAST TIMES THROUGH THE LOOP,@D@@@[. TLEMBX
)@@G@@ TESTS AT THE TOP ARE SURROUNDED BY AX AND ANX  @F@@@[. OF THE INCREMENTBY
)@@G@@. IN THE GENERAL CASE, THERE IS NO WAY TO AVOID @G@@@[. THIS. IN THE FUTBZ
)@@G@@URE, WE WILL ALLOW THE USER TO SURPRESS IT, AND/OR    @G@@@[. IN THE CASCA
)@@G@@E WHERE THE CONTROL FIELDS ARE IMMEDIATE, GENERATE SLIGHTLY @C@@@[. DIFFCB
)@@G@@ERENT CODE WHICH WILL MAKE IT UNNECESSARY.@[@@@[.     @F@@@[.     ******CC
)@@G@@**************************************************    @F@@@[.     *     CD
)@@G@@                                                 *    @F@@@[.     *   G$CE
)@@G@@$LAN : ANALYZE A <LOOP CONTROL> SPECIFICATION    *    @F@@@[.     *     CF
)@@G@@                                                 *    @F@@@[.     ******CG
)@@G@@**************************************************    @[@@@[.     @G@@@[CH
)@@G@@.    FLAGS SET BY THIS SUBROUTINE ARE USED BY CALLING ROUTINE (REPEAT)  CI
)@@G@@@^@@@[.    THEIR MEANINGS ARE:@D@@@[.       FI(1)  INDEX IN IMAGE OF 'FOCJ
)@@G@@R' SPECIFICATION  @C@@@[.       FI(2)  INDEX IN IMAGE OF 'FROM' SPEC    CK
)@@G@@@G@@@[.       FI(3)  INDEX OF 'TO' SPEC ('VARY'), OR 'MASKED' SPEC ('LOOCL
)@@G@@KFOR')@G@@@[.       FI(4)  INDEX OF 'BY' SPEC. NOTE THAT IF USER DIDN'T CM
)@@G@@GIVE ONE,   @C@@@[.              WE FORCE IT BY STORING IN P(X,Y) @G@@@[CN
)@@G@@.       FI(5)  ON IF ANY LOOP CONTROL CODE IS TO APPEAR AT THE PHYSICAL CO
)@@G@@@B@@@[.              BOTTOM OF THE LOOP CODE    @F@@@[.       FI(6)  ON CP
)@@G@@IF SENSE OF LOOP CTL VARIABLE (UP\DOWN) IS KNOWN@D@@@[.              ('VCQ
)@@G@@ARY'), OR OFFSET VALUE ('LOOKFOR')  @F@@@[.       FI(7)  INDEX IN P OF LCR
)@@G@@AST FIELD SCANNED BY THIS ROUTINE   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[. THE ARRAYS IM(K)CS
)@@G@@ AND IV(K) ARE USED INTERNALLY FOR THE ANALYZED @H@@@[. PARAMETERS OF THCT
)@@G@@E LOOP SPECIFICATION. IM IS ON IF THE VALUE IS IMMEDIATE,   @G@@@[. AND CU
)@@G@@IV IS THE VALUE ITSELF. K=1,2,3,4=> FORVAL, FROMVAL, TOVAL, BYVAL.@[@@@[CV
)@@G@@.     @[@@@[.     @H@@@[        PROC   *0                     . NOTE: ONCW
)@@G@@E-PASS PROC FLAG REQUIRED     @#@@@[G$$LAN*  NAME     @[@@@[.     @H@@@[CX
)@@G@@W(1)    EQU    KW(1)                  . GET KEYWORD WHICH DESCRIBES FIELCY
)@@G@@D     @[@@@[.     @E@@@[.       ***** BREAK DOWN SOURCE IMAGE, SET DEFAUCZ
)@@G@@LTS *****   @[@@@[.     @B@@@[. SCAN ALL FIELDS FOR DEFINING KEYWORDS   DA
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @E@@@[K3      EQU    MASKED*(W(1)=LOOKFOR)+TO*(1-(W(1)=LOOKFDB
)@@G@@OR))  @G@@@[FI*(1)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=FOR)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=FOR)+3*(P(VI+DC
)@@G@@3,1)=FOR)   @G@@@[FI*(2)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=FROM)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=FROM)+DD
)@@G@@3*(P(VI+3,1)=FROM)@D@@@[FI*(3)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=K3)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=K3DE
)@@G@@)+;   @B@@@[        3*(P(VI+3,1)=K3)+4*(P(VI+4,1)=K3) @F@@@[FI*(4)  EQU DF
)@@G@@   VI+(P(VI+1,1)=BY)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=BY)+3*(P(VI+3,1)=BY)@G@@@[FI*(7)  EQU DG
)@@G@@   FI(4)                  . INITIALIZE LAST FIELD POINTER   @H@@@[I DO  DH
)@@G@@   3 , DO FI(I)>FI(7) ,FI*(7) EQU FI(I) . FIND LAST FIELD USER GAVE US  DI
)@@G@@@I@@@[LF(1)   EQU    0+P                    . SET INDEX OF LAST FIELD + DJ
)@@G@@1 IN CASE OF D    @[@@@[.     @C@@@[. DEFAULT A MISSING 'TO' SPECIFICATIDK
)@@G@@ON TO ZERO  @[@@@[.     @G@@@[ DO (K3=MASKED)++(FI(3)>VI) , GO G$$L01 . DL
)@@G@@IF 'TO' EXPLICIT, SKIP THIS   @H@@@[FI*(3)  EQU    LF(1)                DM
)@@G@@  . FORCE IT INTO THE NEXT AVAIL SUBFIELD @E@@@[P*(FI(3),1) EQU TO      DN
)@@G@@              . SET ITS KEYWORD     @F@@@[P*(FI(3),4) EQU XU            DO
)@@G@@        . MAKE IT AN IMMEDIATE ZERO @G@@@[LF(1)   EQU    LF(1)+1        DP
)@@G@@        . BUMP NEXT USABLE FIELD POINTER  @G@@@[G$$L01  NAME            DQ
)@@G@@              . END OF DEFAULT FOR 'TO' FIELD   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[. 'BY'DR
)@@G@@ FIELD (IF GIVEN) IS VARIABLE LENGTH. FORCE TO FIXED FORMAT @C@@@[. BY MDS
)@@G@@OVING UP/DOWN/OFFSET TO THE FIFTH SUBFIELD@[@@@[.     @F@@@[ DO FI(4)=VIDT
)@@G@@ , GO G$$L02              . IF 'BY' OMITTED, SKIP THIS@E@@@[ DO P(FI(4),DU
)@@G@@4)=U ,P*(FI(4),4) EQU XU . FORCE SIGN EXTENSION @F@@@[NB      EQU    0+PDV
)@@G@@(FI(4))             . NO OF SPECS IN 'BY' FIELD @E@@@[ DO (P(FI(4),NB)>0DW
)@@G@@)++(NB=5) , GO G$$L02 . NOTHING TO ADJUST @G@@@[P*(FI(4),5) EQU P(FI(4),DX
)@@G@@NB)           . FORCE UP DOWN OFFSET TO FIELD 5 @F@@@[P*(FI(4),NB) EQU 0DY
)@@G@@                    . AND RESET WHEREVER IT WAS @H@@@[G$$L02  NAME      DZ
)@@G@@                    . END KEYWORD FARBLING FOR 'BY' FIELD   @[@@@[.     EA
)@@G@@@D@@@[. PUT ALL FIELDS IN STANDARD FORM TO HANDLE EQUF'S    @[@@@[.     EB
)@@G@@@E@@@[I DO     4 , DO FI(I)>VI ,UV(I) EQU ; COMBINE ALL FIELDS    @G@@@[EC
)@@G@@ +(I$ 0,P(FI(I),4),0,P(FI(I),3),2*P(FI(I),*3)+P(FI(I),*2),P(FI(I),2))   ED
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @G@@@[. NOTE:  THE CODE BELOW WILL GENERATE (USUALLY) SPURIOEE
)@@G@@US R-FLAGS IF     @F@@@[. THE FIELDS BEING EXAMINED ARE EXTERNAL (I.E. UEF
)@@G@@-FLAGGED) EVEN    @F@@@[. THOUGH WE ARE STRIPPING OFF FIELDS WHICH HAVE EG
)@@G@@NO RELOCATION (THE@E@@@[. X AND J FIELDS), AND EVEN THOUGH THE PORTION OEH
)@@G@@F UV WHICH  @F@@@[. MAY CARRY RELOCATION (THE U-FIELD) IS NOT MASKED AT EI
)@@G@@THE POINT   @A@@@[. OF ITS USE. <EXPLETIVE DELETED>   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[EJ
)@@G@@I DO     4 , DO P(FI(I),2)>0777777 ; IF THE USER EQUF'D THE SYMBOL@E@@@[EK
)@@G@@        ,IM(I) EQU (07017000000**(G$NOFO UV(I)))=07000000000@F@@@[I DO  EL
)@@G@@   4 , DO P(FI(I),2)<01000000 ; IF HE DIDN'T EQUF IT ..     @H@@@[      EM
)@@G@@  ,IM(I) EQU (P(FI(I),3)=0)**(016=(P(FI(I),4)**016)) . CHECK FOR EXPLICIEN
)@@G@@@E@@@[I DO     4 , DO IM(I)**(P(FI(I),2)<01000000) ; IF NOT EQUF'D@F@@@[EO
)@@G@@        ,IV(I) EQU P(FI(I),2)         . USE THE VALUE HE GAVE     @F@@@[EP
)@@G@@I DO     4 , DO IM(I)**(P(FI(I),2)>0777777) ; BUT IF HE EQUF'D IT @G@@@[EQ
)@@G@@        ,IV(I) EQU + (G$NOFO UV(I)**G$UMSK) . PRAY ITS NOT EXTERNAL     ER
)@@G@@@H@@@[I DO     4 , DO IV(I)>0377777 ,IV(I) EQU IV(I)++0777777000000 . SIES
)@@G@@GN EXTEND   @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @F@@@[. DEFAULT A MISSING 'BY' SPECIET
)@@G@@FICATION TO +-1, DEPENDING UPON     @F@@@[. THE SIGN OF TO-FROM, AND/OR EU
)@@G@@THE USER'S UP/DOWN/OFFSET SPEC.     @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @H@@@[ DO FIEV
)@@G@@(4)>VI , GO G$$L03              . SKIP THIS IF USER GAVE THIS FIELD     EW
)@@G@@@F@@@[FI*(4)  EQU    LF(1)                  . REMEMBER WHERE ITS GOING  EX
)@@G@@@H@@@[ DO 1-((W(1)=VARY)++(W(1)=LOOKFOR)) , GO G$$L03 . SKIP FOR SPECIFIEY
)@@G@@C LOOP TYPE @F@@@[IV(4)   EQU    1                      . INITIAL ASSUMPEZ

)@@G@@ SIGN OF DIFF     @F@@@[P*(FI(4),2) EQU     IV(4)             . SAVE FORFC

)@@G@@EDIATE@E@@@[UV(4)   EQUF   IV(4),,XU              . MARK IT AS IMMEDIATEFE
)@@G@@@G@@@[IM(4)   EQU    1                      . AND TURN ON THE IMMEDIATE FF
)@@G@@FLAG  @G@@@[G$$L03  NAME                          . END DEFAULT PROCESSIFG
)@@G@@NG OF 'BY'  @G@@@[ DO P(FI(4),5)=0 ,P*(FI(4),5) EQU P(VI,3) . SET USER'SFH
)@@G@@ SIGN, IF ANY     @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @F@@@[ DO 1-(W(1)=LOOKFOR) , GFI
)@@G@@O G$$L30      . IF NOT LOOKFOR, GO DO VARY@[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @G@@@[FJ
)@@G@@.       ***** PROCESS 'LOOKFOR' LOOP (I.E. SEARCH, MASKED SEARCH) ***** FK
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @H@@@[FI*(5)  EQU    0                      . FLAG NO CODE AFL
)@@G@@PPEARS AT THE BOTTOM    @[@@@[.     @A@@@[. LOAD MASK AND REPEAT REGISTEFM
)@@G@@RS    @[@@@[.     @G@@@[ DO (FI(3)>VI)**(P(FI(3))>1) , I$ 023,,2,,,UV(3)FN
)@@G@@ . LOAD MASK REG (R2)   @F@@@[ DO FI(1)>VI , I$ 023,,1,,,UV(1)      . ANFO
)@@G@@D REPEAT COUNT (R1)     @[@@@[.     @A@@@[. INITIALIZE REG USED AS TABLEFP
)@@G@@ INDEX@[@@@[.     @H@@@[ DO (P(FI(4),5)=OFFSET)**(1-IM(4)) , G$$EFL 2,1 FQ
)@@G@@. OFFSET NEEDS IMMEDIATE BY   @F@@@[OFV     EQU    IM(4)*(P(FI(4),5)=OFFFR
)@@G@@SET)*IV(4) . SET OFFSET VALUE @H@@@[FI*(6)  EQU    OFV                  FS
)@@G@@  . AND SAVE FOR USE BY CODE GENERATOR    @E@@@[ DO FI(2)=VI , END      FT

)@@G@@            . REQUIRE THAT A 'BY' SPEC APPEARED @H@@@[ DO IM(2)**IM(4) ,FV
)@@G@@ GO G$$L21          . IF BOTH IMMEDIATE, GO USE CONSTANT    @D@@@[      FW
)@@G@@  I$     027,,P(VI,2),,,UV(2)   . LX XN,FROM    @F@@@[ DO OFV=0 , I$ 046FX
)@@G@@,,P(VI,2),,,UV(4)   . IF NO OFFSET, LXI XN,BY   @C@@@[ DO OFV=0 , END   FY

)@@G@@OFV) . IF OVERLAPPED, ADD OFFSET IN @H@@@[ DO P(VI,2)<A0 , ANX,U P(VI,2)GA
)@@G@@,OFV    . IF NONOVERLAPPED, USE BRUTE FORCE     @B@@@[ DO P(VI,2)<A0 , LGB
)@@G@@XI,U P(VI,2),OFV    .   @D@@@[ DO 1 , END                           . THGC

)@@G@@ROM AND BY BOTH IMMEDIATE     @G@@@[        I$     027,,P(VI,2),,,(+IV(4GE
)@@G@@),IV(2)-OFV) . LOAD XREG FROM CONS  @]@@@[ DO 1 , END @[@@@[.     @F@@@[GF
)@@G@@.       ****** PROCESS 'VARY' (NORMAL LOOP) SPECIFICATION *****   @[@@@[GG
)@@G@@.     @G@@@[G$$L30  NAME                          . MARK START OF VARY CGH
)@@G@@HECKING     @[@@@[.     @E@@@[.       IF LOOP INSTR SPEC GENERIC, CHOOSEGI
)@@G@@ THE MACHINE INSTR@[@@@[.     @F@@@[ DO 1-(W(1)=VARY) , GO G$$L40 . SKIPGJ

)@@G@@              . FORCE OPCODE IF ITS NOT KNOWN   @G@@@[ DO FI(1)>VI , GO GL
)@@G@@G$$L34              . IF 'FOR', ASSUME JGD IMMEDIATELY@G@@@[ DO 1-(IM(2)GM
)@@G@@**IM(3)**IM(4)) , GO G$$L35 . NO FUDGE IF ALL NOT KNOWN     @D@@@[ DO 1-GN

)@@G@@2)                  . PUT 'FOR' IN P WHERE 'FROM' WAS @F@@@[FI*(2)  EQU GP
)@@G@@   VI                     . AND INVALIDATE THE 'FROM' @G@@@[IV(1)   EQU GQ
)@@G@@   IV(2)+1                . FORVAL IS ONE MORE THAN FROMVAL @G@@@[IM(1) GR
)@@G@@  EQU    1                      . TURN ON IMMEDIATE 'FOR' FLAG    @D@@@[GS

)@@G@@                    . THEN GO GLOBALIZE THE OPCODE    @F@@@[.           GW

)@@G@@@G@@@[ DO (FI(2)=VI)++(FI(3)=VI)++(FI(4)=VI) , G$$EFL 2,3 . REQUIRE ALL GY
)@@G@@SPECS @D@@@[W(1)    EQU    0+TLEM                 . ASSUME TLEM   @F@@@[GZ

)@@G@@.     @I@@@[G$$L39  NAME                          . END DETERMINATION OFHB

)@@G@@RCE OPCODE SPEC FIELD   @[@@@[.     @G@@@[.        SET LOOP SENSE AND FLHD

)@@G@@@F@@@[ DO 1-(W(1)=JGD) , GO G$$L41          . IF NOT JGD, WE MUST FARBLEHF
)@@G@@@F@@@[FI*(6)  EQU    1                      . ELSE MARK SENSE KNOWN     HG
)@@G@@@I@@@[FI*(5)  EQU    1                      . SET FLAG THAT CODE WILL APHH

)@@G@@  . NOT JGD, DETERMINE SENSE THE HARD WAY @H@@@[USS     EQU    (P(FI(4),HL
)@@G@@5)=UP)-(P(FI(4),5)=DOWN) . SET USER SUPPLIED SIGN     @D@@@[BYS     EQU HM
)@@G@@   IM(4)*(1-2*(IV(4)<0))  . SIGN FROM 'BY'@F@@@[FTS     EQU    (IM(2)**IHN
)@@G@@M(3))*(1-2*(IV(2)>IV(3))) . FROMTO SIGN   @G@@@[ DO (FTS*BYS)=-1 , G$$EFHO

)@@G@@+BYS                . GET MY OWN SIGN FLAG@F@@@[ DO (MYS*USS)=-1 , G$$EFHQ

)@@G@@)             . ON IF WE KNOW LOOP SENSE  @H@@@[P*(VI,3) EQU   SIGN     HT
)@@G@@              . REMEMBER FOR BOTTOM OF LOOP USAGE     @G@@@[FI*(5) EQU (HU
)@@G@@SIGN=0)++((W(1)=TLEM)**(SIGN>0))++((W(1)=JMGI)**(SIGN<0))   @[@@@[.     HV
)@@G@@@G@@@[. WATCH OUT FOR AX/ANX: TERMINATION CONDITION MAY NOT PASS THRU ZEHW

)@@G@@ AND IMMEDIATE    @F@@@[ DO (IV(2)*(IV(3)+IV(4)))<0 , G$$EFL 2,4 . LOOP HY
)@@G@@PASSES THRU ZERO  @I@@@[G$$L49  NAME                          . END OF SHZ
)@@G@@ENSE AND PREFERENCE DETERMINATIO    @[@@@[.     @C@@@[. GENERATE REGISTEIA

)@@G@@,2),,,UV(2)   . LX WITH FROMVAL     @H@@@[        I$     025,,P(VI,2),,,IO

)@@G@@                          . END OF REG INITIALIZATION @I@@@[G$$L52  NAMEIR
)@@G@@                          . IF 'BY' IMMEDIATE, LITERALS CAN BE USED-    IS
)@@G@@@F@@@[        I$     027,,P(VI,2),,,(+IV(4),0+IV(2)*IM(2)-IV(4)) . LX   IT
)@@G@@@D@@@[ DO IM(2)=0 , I$ 022,,P(VI,2),,,UV(2) . AX FROMVAL    @[@@@[.     IU
)@@G@@@]@@@[        END @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @F@@@[.     ******************IV
)@@G@@**************************************    @F@@@[.     *                 IW
)@@G@@                                     *    @F@@@[.     *   G$$LGE : GENERIX
)@@G@@ATE CODE FOR <LOOP CONTROL> FIELDS   *    @F@@@[.     *                 IY
)@@G@@                                     *    @F@@@[.     ******************IZ
)@@G@@**************************************    @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @I@@@[JA
)@@G@@Q       PROC   *2                     . PF'S: 'VARY','TO','BY'  JUMPTARGJB
)@@G@@,TOP/BOT    @#@@@[G$$LGE*  NAME     @G@@@[VI      EQU    Q(1,1)         JC
)@@G@@        . INDEX IN P OF VARY SPEC FIELD   @E@@@[TI      EQU    Q(1,2)   JD
)@@G@@              . INDEX OF 'TO' FIELD @E@@@[BI      EQU    Q(1,3)         JE
)@@G@@        . INDEX OF 'BY' FIELD @E@@@[F       EQU    P(VI,1)              JF
)@@G@@  . FUNCTION REQUESTED  @H@@@[ATTOP     EQU       Q(2,2)            . ONJG
)@@G@@ IF BEING CALLED AT TOP OF LOOP     @[@@@[.     @G@@@[ DO F=LOOKFOR , GOJH
)@@G@@ G$$L80             . SPECIAL HANDLING FOR SEARCHING  @F@@@[ DO F=JGD , JI
)@@G@@G$$FJA 070,P(VI,2),,,Q(2,1) . JUMP TO KEEP LOOPING    @G@@@[ DO F=JGD , JJ
)@@G@@END                       . FOR JGD, THAT'S ALL THERE IS    @[@@@[.     JK
)@@G@@@#@@@[. TLEM/JMGI ---   @[@@@[.     @E@@@[JMF     EQU    F=JMGI         JL
)@@G@@        . TRUE IF FUNC IS JMGI@G@@@[OLAP    EQU    P(VI,2)>X11          JM
)@@G@@  . ON IF LOOP CTL REG IS OVERLAPPED@G@@@[SENU    EQU    (P(VI,3)=0)**(AJN
)@@G@@TTOP=0) . ON AT BOTTOM AND UNKNOWN SENSE  @[@@@[.     @G@@@[ DO SENU**(1JO
)@@G@@-OLAP) , I$ 060+JMF,,,,,P(VI,2) . TP(TLEM) TN(JMGI) ON REG  @G@@@[ DO SEJP
)@@G@@NU , I$ 074,04-OLAP*(JMF+1),OLAP*P(VI,2),,,G$LABL(K,2) . J JN JP  @[@@@[JQ
)@@G@@.     @C@@@[ DO JMF , GO G$$L70 . JMGI LOOPS ARE SIMPLE     @H@@@[TUHI  JR
)@@G@@    EQU       3*(P(TI,2)<0)+2*P(TI,*3)+P(TI,*2) . T-FLAG IF ALL ARE ON  JS
)@@G@@@D@@@[TU      EQU    + (I$ 0,P(TI,4),,P(TI,3),TUHI,P(TI,2)) @H@@@[BUHI  JT
)@@G@@    EQU       3*(P(BI,2)<0)+2*P(BI,*3)+P(BI,*2) . T-FLAG IF ALL ARE ON  JU
)@@G@@@D@@@[BU      EQU    + (I$ 0,P(BI,4),,P(BI,3),BUHI,P(BI,2)) @F@@@[ DO ATJV
)@@G@@TOP , I$ 074,06,0,P(VI,2),2,0   . AT TOP AX INCR WITH A NOP @E@@@[      JW
)@@G@@    I$        047,,P(VI,2),,,TU . TLEM ON 'TO' FIELD  @B@@@[        I$  JX
)@@G@@   074,04,,,,Q(2,1) . JUMP    @G@@@[ DO ATTOP , I$ 025,,P(VI,2),,,BU    JY
)@@G@@  . UNDO FUDGE WITH ANX OF INCR     @E@@@[ DO 1 , END                   JZ
)@@G@@        . THAT'S ALL FOR TLEM @[@@@[.     @C@@@[. HANDLE JMGI LOOPS (WHIKA
)@@G@@CH TERMINATE AT ZERO)   @[@@@[.     @#@@@[G$$L70    NAME    @F@@@[ DO ATKB
)@@G@@TOP , I$ 051,017,0,P(VI,2),,0 . TNZ REG (LAST TIME CHECK)   @B@@@[ DO ATKC
)@@G@@TOP , I$ 074,04,,,,Q(2,1)       .   @C@@@[        I$     074,012,P(VI,2)KD
)@@G@@,,,Q(2,1) . JMGI  @#@@@[ DO 1 , END .     @[@@@[.     @F@@@[. HANDLE SEAKE
)@@G@@RCH/MASKED SEARCH. NOTE: SINCE THIS IS ALWAYS CALLED  @E@@@[. AT THE PHYKF
)@@G@@SICAL TOP OF THE LOOP BY REPEAT, THE VALUES OF  @B@@@[. THE ARRAY FI(N) KG
)@@G@@ARE ALWAYS AVAILABLE    @[@@@[.     @]@@@[G$$L80  NAME@H@@@[IC      EQU KH
)@@G@@   VI-1                   . INDEX IN P OF CONDITION TEST FIELD    @H@@@[KI
)@@G@@KWD     EQU    P(IC,2)                . GET KEYWORD FROM CONDITION SPEC KJ
)@@G@@FIELD @F@@@[MSF     EQU    FI(3)>VI               . ON IF SEARCH IS MASKKK
)@@G@@ED    @G@@@[FUN     EQU    G$FJ(1,KWD,1)+010*(1-MSF)-052*MSF . MODIFY TOKL
)@@G@@ A SEARCH   @G@@@[ DO   MSF , I$ 071,FUN,P(IC,1)-A0,P(VI,2),2+P(IC,*3),PKM
)@@G@@(IC,3)+FI(6) . MS-@H@@@[ DO 1-MSF , I$ FUN,P(IC,5),P(IC,1)-A0,P(VI,2),2+KN
)@@G@@P(IC,*3),P(IC,3)+FI(6) . S-   @E@@@[        I$     074,04,,,,Q(2,1)  . AKO
)@@G@@T NOFIND,  JUMP TO ATEND@[@@@[.     @]@@@[        END @ @@@[/. *** MISCEKP
)@@G@@LLANEOUS UTILITIES@[@@@[.     @H@@@[. PROCS TO CONSERVE TABLE SPACE BY SKQ
)@@G@@AVING ARGUMENTS IN RE-USABLE ARRAY SPACE  @[@@@[.     @^@@@[          PRKR
)@@G@@OC      *0  @I@@@[G$$SVA* NAME                          . SAVE ARRAY P IKS
)@@G@@N STANDARD ARGUMENT ARRAY     @F@@@[K         EQU       G$CTR(3)+1      KT
)@@G@@  . BUMP ARG PUSHDOWN LEVEL   @D@@@[G$CTR**(3) EQU K                    KU
)@@G@@  . SAVE THE LEVEL@^@@@[G$ARGS**(K) EQU +P-1    @A@@@[N DO P-1 ,G$ARGS**KV
)@@G@@(K,N) EQU +0+P(N) @C@@@[N DO P-1 ,M DO P(N) ,G$ARGS**(K,N,M) EQU +P(N,M)KW
)@@G@@@#@@@[          END     @D@@@[/. TURN ASSEMBLER MNEMONICS FOR JUMP INSTRKX
)@@G@@S INTO TRASH@[@@@[.     @#@@@[Q         PROC    @H@@@[G$JELLY* NAME     KY
)@@G@@                    . TURN THE WORLD INTO A QUIVVERING MASS @[@@@[.     KZ
)@@G@@@D@@@[. THE ROLE OF THIS PROC IS MERELY TO GET THE PROC     @D@@@[. WHICLA
)@@G@@H FOLLOWS THIS DEFINED AT THE PROGRAM LEVEL     @E@@@[. IT CANNOT HAVE ILB
)@@G@@TS OWN ENTRY POINTS OR ELSE THE ASSEMBLER @D@@@[. WOULD BE DESTROYED FORLC
)@@G@@ NON-STRUCTURED ASSEMBLIES.   @[@@@[.     @I@@@[P       PROC   *1,1     LD
)@@G@@              . A SEPERATE PROC TO AVOID NAMING CONFLICT    @[@@@[.     LE
)@@G@@@F@@@[. JGD AND JMGI ARE SPECIAL CASES, ALLOWED IF ONLY DOING ARITHMETICLF
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @#@@@[JGD***  NAME   - 1@#@@@[NEXTI   EQU    $+1@H@@@[COUNT LG

)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@H@^@@/.       ROUTINE TO CONVERT LINES CONTAINING BACKSPACEOQ
