)@@G@@  . THEN LOOP FOREVER   @#@^@]      CALL,A1 0,A1@#@]@[      CALL,A1 0,A1QU
)@@G@@@^@[@@     L,Q2    A4,0,A0    @#@@@^      CALL,A1 0,A1@^@^@]      L,Q1  QV
)@@G@@  A4,0,A0   @^@]@[      L,Q2    A4,0,A0   @^@[@@     CALL,A1     0,A1   QW
)@@G@@@^@@@^      L,Q1    A4,0,A0   @#@^@]      CALL,A1 0,A1@#@]@[      CALL,AQX
)@@G@@1 0,A1@^@[@@     L,Q3    A4,0,A0    @#@@@^      CALL,A1 0,A1@^@^@]      QY
)@@G@@L,Q2    A4,0,A0   @^@]@[      L,Q3    A4,0,A0   @^@[@@     CALL,A1     0QZ
)@@G@@,A1   @^@@@^      L,Q2    A4,0,A0   @#@^@]      CALL,A1 0,A1@#@]@[      RA
)@@G@@CALL,A1 0,A1@^@[@@     L,Q4    A4,0,*A0   @#@@@^      CALL,A1 0,A1@^@^@]RB
)@@G@@      L,Q3    A4,0,A0   @^@]@[      L,Q4    A4,0,*A0  @]@[@@   ENDREP   RC
)@@G@@@^@@@^      L,Q3    A4,0,A0   @#@^@]      CALL,A1 0,A1@]@]@[   ENDREP   RD
)@@G@@@]@[@@ ENDBEG     @#@@@^      CALL,A1 0,A1@^@^@]      L,Q4    A4,0,*A0  RE
)@@G@@@]@]@[ ENDBEG     @[@[@@ .    @^@@@^      L,Q4    A4,0,*A0  @]@^@]   ENDRF
)@@G@@REP   @[@]@[ .    @B@[@@. STASH FROM R2 USING X8,9 AS POINTERS    @]@@@^RG
)@@G@@   ENDREP   @]@^@] ENDBEG     @B@]@[ . STASH FROM R2 USING X8,9 AS POINTRH
)@@G@@ERS   @[@[@@.     @]@@@^ ENDBEG     @[@^@] .    @[@]@[ .    @[@[@@PUTR2 RI
)@@G@@@[@@@^ .    @B@^@] . STASH FROM R2 USING X8,9 AS POINTERS   @[@]@[PUTR2 RJ
)@@G@@@^@[@@ BEGIN     COROUTINE    @B@@@^ . STASH FROM R2 USING X8,9 AS POINTRK
)@@G@@ERS   @[@^@] .    @^@]@[ BEGIN     COROUTINE    @B@[@@   LXI,U   X8,1   RL
)@@G@@. INITIALIZE WORD INCR  @[@@@^ .    @[@^@]PUTR2 @E@]@[   LXI,U   X8,1   RM
)@@G@@                    . INITIALIZE WORD INCR@ @[@@   REPEAT . THEN LOOP FORN
)@@G@@REVER @^@^@] BEGIN     COROUTINE    @[@@@^PUTR2 @E@]@[   REPEAT         RO
)@@G@@                    . THEN LOOP FOREVER   @^@[@@     CALL,X9    0,X9    RP
)@@G@@@#@@@^ BEGIN CYCLIC     @E@^@]   LXI,U   X8,1                       . INRQ
)@@G@@ITIALIZE WORD INCR@#@]@[      CALL,X9 0,X9@^@[@@     S,Q1    R2,0,X8    RR
)@@G@@@E@@@^   LXI,U   X8,1                       . INITIALIZE WORD INCR@E@^@]RS
)@@G@@   REPEAT                             . THEN LOOP FOREVER   @^@]@[      RT
)@@G@@S,Q1    R2,0,X8   @^@[@@     CALL,X9    0,X9    @E@@@^   REPEAT         RU
)@@G@@                    . THEN LOOP FOREVER   @#@^@]      CALL,X9 0,X9@#@]@[RV
)@@G@@      CALL,X9 0,X9@^@[@@     S,Q2    R2,0,X8    @#@@@^      CALL,X9 0,X9RW
)@@G@@@^@^@]      S,Q1    R2,0,X8   @^@]@[      S,Q2    R2,0,X8   @^@[@@     CRX
)@@G@@ALL,X9    0,X9    @^@@@^      S,Q1    R2,0,X8   @#@^@]      CALL,X9 0,X9RY
)@@G@@@#@]@[      CALL,X9 0,X9@^@[@@     S,Q3    R2,0,X8    @#@@@^      CALL,XRZ
)@@G@@9 0,X9@^@^@]      S,Q2    R2,0,X8   @^@]@[      S,Q3    R2,0,X8   @^@[@@SA
)@@G@@     CALL,X9    0,X9    @^@@@^      S,Q2    R2,0,X8   @#@^@]      CALL,XSB
)@@G@@9 0,X9@#@]@[      CALL,X9 0,X9@^@[@@     S,Q4    R2,0,*X8   @#@@@^      SC
)@@G@@CALL,X9 0,X9@^@^@]      S,Q3    R2,0,X8   @^@]@[      S,Q4    R2,0,*X8  SD
)@@G@@@]@[@@   ENDREP   @^@@@^      S,Q3    R2,0,X8   @#@^@]      CALL,X9 0,X9SE
)@@G@@@]@]@[   ENDREP   @]@[@@ ENDBEG     @#@@@^      CALL,X9 0,X9@^@^@]      SF
)@@G@@S,Q4    R2,0,*X8  @]@]@[ ENDBEG     @[@[@@ .    @^@@@^      S,Q4    R2,0SG
)@@G@@,*X8  @]@^@]   ENDREP   @[@]@[ .    @D@[@@ . FETCH FROM OUTPUT IMAGE (NOSH
)@@G@@TE RANDOM COLS USED)    @]@@@^   ENDREP   @]@^@] ENDBEG     @D@]@[ . FETSI
)@@G@@CH FROM OUTPUT IMAGE (NOTE RANDOM COLS USED)    @[@[@@OUTGET@]@@@^ ENDBESJ
)@@G@@G     @[@^@] .    @[@]@[OUTGET@ @[@@ LA,Q1   FETCHREG,*OUTWORD    @[@@@^SK
)@@G@@ .    @D@^@] . FETCH FROM OUTPUT IMAGE (NOTE RANDOM COLS USED)    @D@@@^SL
)@@G@@ . FETCH FROM OUTPUT IMAGE (NOTE RANDOM COLS USED)    @A@]@[        LA,QSM
)@@G@@1   FETCHREG,*OUTWORD   @ @[@@ LA,Q2   FETCHREG,*OUTWORD    @[@@@]OUTGETSN
)@@G@@@A@]@[        LA,Q2   FETCHREG,*OUTWORD   @ @[@@ LA,Q3   FETCHREG,*OUTWOSO
)@@G@@RD    @A@@@]        LA,Q1   FETCHRG,*OUTWORD    @A@]@[        LA,Q3   FESP
)@@G@@TCHREG,*OUTWORD   @ @[@@ LA,Q4   FETCHREG,*OUTWORD    @A@@@]        LA,QSQ
)@@G@@2   FETCHRG,*OUTWORD    @A@]@[        LA,Q4   FETCHREG,*OUTWORD   @[@[@@SR
)@@G@@ .    @A@@@]        LA,Q3   FETCHRG,*OUTWORD    @[@]@[ .    @E@[@@ . STASS
)@@G@@SH IN OUTPUT IMAGE (RANDOM BECAUSE MIGHT BE OVERLAID) @A@@@]        LA,QST
)@@G@@4   FETCHRG,*OUTWORD    @E@]@[ . STASH IN OUTPUT IMAGE (RANDOM BECAUSE MSU
)@@G@@IGHT BE OVERLAID) @[@[@@OUTPUT@[@@@] .    @[@]@[OUTPUT@ @[@@ S,Q1    STASV
)@@G@@SHREG,*OUTWORD    @E@@@] . STASH IN OUTPUT IMAGE (RANDOM BECAUSE MIGHT BSW
)@@G@@E OVERLAID) @A@]@[        S,Q1    STASHREG,*OUTWORD   @ @[@@ S,Q2    STASX
)@@G@@SHREG,*OUTWORD    @[@@@]OUTPUT@A@]@[        S,Q2    STASHREG,*OUTWORD   SY
)@@G@@@ @[@@ S,Q3    STASHREG,*OUTWORD    @A@@@]        S,Q1    STASHRG,*OUTWOSZ
)@@G@@RD    @A@]@[        S,Q3    STASHREG,*OUTWORD   @ @[@@ S,Q4    STASHREG,TA
)@@G@@*OUTWORD    @A@@@]        S,Q2    STASHRG,*OUTWORD    @A@]@[        S,Q4TB
)@@G@@    STASHREG,*OUTWORD   @A@@@]        S,Q3    STASHRG,*OUTWORD    @A@@@]TC
)@@G@@        S,Q4    STASHRG,*OUTWORD    @[@@@@/     @[@[@@ .    @[@]@[ .    TD
)@@G@@@[@[@@ .    @[@]@[ .    @E@[@@ .       UTILITIES TO GET AND PUT IN THE VTE
)@@G@@ARIOUS BUFFERS    @[@@@] .    @E@]@[ .       UTILITIES TO GET AND PUT INTF
)@@G@@ THE VARIOUS BUFFERS    @[@[@@ .    @[@@@] .    @[@]@[ .    @[@[@@ .    TG
)@@G@@@E@@@] .       UTILITIES TO GET AND PUT IN THE VARIOUS BUFFERS    @[@]@[TH
)@@G@@ .    @#@[@@OUTCHAR  EQU     0@[@@@] .    @#@]@[OUTCHAR EQU     0 @^@[@@TI
)@@G@@SOURCECHAR       EQU 1  @[@@@] .    @B@]@[SOURCECHAR      EQU           TJ
)@@G@@        1   @#@[@@REMCHAR  EQU     2@#@@@]OUTCHAR EQU     0 @#@]@[REMCHATK
)@@G@@R EQU     2 @[@[@@ .    @#@@@]SRCCHAR EQU     1 @[@]@[ .    @#@[@@P     TL
)@@G@@   PROC     @#@@@]REMCHAR EQU     2 @]@]@[P       PROC@#@[@@STASH*   NAMTM
)@@G@@E    0@[@@@] .    @#@]@[STASH*  NAME    0 @#@[@@FETCH*   NAME    1@]@@@]TN
)@@G@@P       PROC@#@]@[FETCH*  NAME    1 @[@[@@ .    @#@@@]STASH*  NAME    0 TO
)@@G@@@[@]@[ .    @A@[@@OUTBUF   EQU     P(1,1)=OUTCHAR     @#@@@]FETCH*  NAMETP
)@@G@@    1 @ @]@[OUTBUF  EQU     P(1,1)=OUTCHAR@E@[@@ DO OUTBUF , EX OUTGET*PTQ
)@@G@@(0,0)+OUTPUT*(1-P(0,0)),OUTBREG     @[@@@] .    @G@]@[        DO      OUTR
)@@G@@TBUF , EX OUTGET*P(0,0)+OUTPUT*(1-P(0,0)),OUTBREG     @D@[@@XREG     EQUTS
)@@G@@     SRCEBREG*P(0,0)+REMBREG*(1-P(0,0))   @ @@@]OUTBUF  EQU     P(1,1)=OTT
)@@G@@UTCHAR@D@]@[XREG    EQU     SRCEBREG*P(0,0)+REMBREG*(1-P(0,0))    @A@[@@TU
)@@G@@ DO 1-OUTBUF , CALL,XREG 0,XREG     @G@@@]        DO      OUTBUF , EX OUTV
)@@G@@TGET*P(0,0)+OUTPUT*(1-P(0,0)),OUTBREG     @C@]@[        DO      1-OUTBUFTW
)@@G@@ , CALL,XREG 0,XREG     @[@[@@ END  @D@@@]XREG    EQU     SRCEBRG*P(0,0)TX
)@@G@@+REMBREG*(1-P(0,0))     @]@]@[        END @[@[@@ .    @C@@@]        DO  TY
)@@G@@    1-OUTBUF , CALL,XREG 0,XREG     @[@]@[ .    @[@[@@ .    @]@@@]      TZ
)@@G@@  END @[@]@[ .    @D@[@@ASCIBS  EQUF   010,,U              . ASCII BACKSUA
)@@G@@PACE  @[@@@] .    @E@]@[ASCIBS  EQUF    010,,U                . ASCII BAUB
)@@G@@CKSPACE     @E@[@@ASPACE  EQUF   040,,U              . ASCII SPACE (BLANUC
)@@G@@K)    @[@@@] .    @E@]@[ASPACE  EQUF    040,,U                . ASCII SPUD
)@@G@@ACE (BLANK) @[@[@@ .    @E@@@]ASCIBS  EQUF    010,,U                . ASUE
)@@G@@CII BACKSPACE     @[@]@[ .    @ @[@@$(6)     .       DATA AREAS   @E@@@]UF
)@@G@@ASPACE  EQUF    040,,U                . ASCII SPACE (BLANK) @E@]@[$(6)  UG
)@@G@@                                .       DATA AREAS    @[@[@@ .    @[@@@]UH
)@@G@@ .    @[@]@[ .    @G@[@@EOICHR   EQUF    $,,H1             . END IF INPUUI
)@@G@@T CHAR (ALSO USED AS F  @E@@@]$(6)                                  .   UJ
)@@G@@    DATA AREAS    @H@]@[EOICHR  EQUF    $,,H1                 . END IF IUK
)@@G@@NPUT CHAR (ALSO USED AS F     @F@[@@REMADR   EQUF    $,,H2             .UL
)@@G@@ BASE ADDR OF REMAINDER BUFFER@[@@@] .    @G@]@[REMADR  EQUF    $,,H2   UM
)@@G@@              . BASE ADDR OF REMAINDER BUFFER   @]@[@@ RES     1  @H@@@]UN
)@@G@@EOICHR  EQUF    $,,H1                 . END IF INPUT CHAR (ALSO USED AS UO
)@@G@@F     @#@]@[        RES     1 @F@[@@OUTADR   EQUF    $,,H2             .UP
)@@G@@ ADDRESS OF OUTPUT BUFFER     @G@@@]REMADR  EQUF    $,,H2               UQ
)@@G@@  . BASE ADDR OF REMAINDER BUFFER   @F@]@[OUTADR  EQUF    $,,H2         UR
)@@G@@        . ADDRESS OF OUTPUT BUFFER  @G@[@@OUTWORD  +OUTWREG,$-$         US
)@@G@@     . INDIRECT WD TO ACCESS OUTPUT BUFF  @#@@@]        RES     1 @H@]@[UT
)@@G@@OUTWORD +OUTWREG,$-$                   . INDIRECT WD TO ACCESS OUTPUT BUUU
)@@G@@FF    @F@[@@FUNNYF     EQUF              OUTWORD,,S1 . FUNNYMODE IMAGE FUV
)@@G@@LAG   @F@@@]OUTADR  EQUF    $,,H2                 . ADDRESS OF OUTPUT BUUW
)@@G@@FFER  @E@]@[FUNNYF  EQUF    OUTWORD,,S1           . FUNNYMODE IMAGE FLAGUX
)@@G@@@[@[@@ .    @H@@@]OUTWORD +OUTWREG,$-$                   . INDIRECT WD TUY
)@@G@@O ACCESS OUTPUT BUFF    @[@]@[ .    @[@[@@ .    @E@@@]FUNNYF  EQUF    OUUZ
)@@G@@TWORD,,S1           . FUNNYMODE IMAGE FLAG@[@]@[ .    @[@[@@ .    @[@@@]VA
)@@G@@ .    @[@]@[ .    @[@[@@$(1)  @[@@@] .    @[@]@[$(1)  @^@[@@ . ENTRY CONVB
)@@G@@DITIONS--   @[@@@] .    @^@]@[ . ENTRY CONDITIONS--   @ @[@@ .       A0=VC
)@@G@@SOURCE IMAGE ADDR @[@@@]$(1)  @ @]@[ .       A0=SOURCE IMAGE ADDR @B@[@@VD
)@@G@@ .       A1=SOURCE IMAGE LENGTH (WORDS)   @^@@@] . ENTRY CONDITIONS--   VE
)@@G@@@B@]@[ .       A1=SOURCE IMAGE LENGTH (WORDS)   @ @[@@ .       A2=OUTPUTVF
)@@G@@ IMAGE ADDR @ @@@] .       A0=SOURCE IMAGE ADDR @ @]@[ .       A2=OUTPUTVG
)@@G@@ IMAGE ADDR @F@[@@ .       A3=REMAINDER IMAGE ADDR (MAY BE SAME AS SOURCVH
)@@G@@E IMAGE)    @B@@@] .       A1=SOURCE IMAGE LENGTH (WORDS)   @F@]@[ .    VI
)@@G@@   A3=REMAINDER IMAGE ADDR (MAY BE SAME AS SOURCE IMAGE)    @E@[@@ .    VJ
)@@G@@   A4=END OF IMAGE SIGNAL CHAR (ALSO USED AS FILL)    @ @@@] .       A2=VK
)@@G@@OUTPUT IMAGE ADDR @E@]@[ .       A4=END OF IMAGE SIGNAL CHAR (ALSO USED VL
)@@G@@AS FILL)    @[@[@@ .    @F@@@] .       A3=REMAINDER IMAGE ADDR (MAY BE SVM
)@@G@@AME AS SOURCE IMAGE)    @[@]@[ .    @ @[@@ . EXIT TO 0,X11  WITH --     VN
)@@G@@@E@@@] .       A4=END OF IMAGE SIGNAL CHAR (ALSO USED AS FILL)    @ @]@[VO
)@@G@@ . EXIT TO 0,X11  WITH --     @B@[@@ .       A0=OUTPUT IMAGE LENGTH (WORVP
)@@G@@DS)   @[@@@] .    @B@]@[ .       A0=OUTPUT IMAGE LENGTH (WORDS)   @F@[@@VQ
)@@G@@ .       A1=REMAINDER IMAGE LENGTH (WORDS)-- 0 MEANS FINISHED     @ @@@]VR
)@@G@@ . EXIT TO 0,X11  WITH --     @F@]@[ .       A1=REMAINDER IMAGE LENGTH (VS
)@@G@@WORDS)-- 0 MEANS FINISHED     @[@[@@ .    @B@@@] .       A0=OUTPUT IMAGEVT
)@@G@@ LENGTH (WORDS)   @[@]@[ .    @]@[@@MULINE*     @F@@@] .       A1=REMAINVU
)@@G@@DER IMAGE LENGTH (WORDS)-- 0 MEANS FINISHED     @]@]@[MULINE*     @A@[@@VV
)@@G@@ BEGIN     SUBROUTINE SAVE,X8,X9,X10@[@@@] .    @A@]@[ BEGIN     SUBROUTVW
)@@G@@INE SAVE,X8,X9,X10@[@[@@   .  @]@@@]MULINE*     @[@]@[   .  @C@[@@   . CVX
)@@G@@ONVENTIONS INTERNAL TO THIS ROUTINE --    @A@@@] BEGIN     SUBROUTINE SAVY
)@@G@@VE,X8,X9,X10@C@]@[   . CONVENTIONS INTERNAL TO THIS ROUTINE --    @[@[@@VZ
)@@G@@   .  @[@@@]   .  @[@]@[   .  @G@[@@STASHREG    EQU  R2                .WA
)@@G@@ CHARS ARE STASHED IN OUT/REM IMAG  @C@@@]   . CONVENTIONS INTERNAL TO TWB
)@@G@@HIS ROUTINE --    @H@]@[STASHREG        EQU                   R2  . CHARWC
)@@G@@S ARE STASHED IN OUT/REM IMAG @G@[@@FETCHREG    EQU  A5                .WD
)@@G@@ CHARS FETCHED FROM SOURCE/OUT IMA  @[@@@]   .  @H@]@[FETCHREG        EQWE
)@@G@@U                   A5  . CHARS FETCHED FROM SOURCE/OUT IMA @E@[@@SOURCEWF
)@@G@@COL   EQU  A4    . COLUMN IN WHICH NEXT SOURCE CHAR   @H@@@]STASHRG EQU WG
)@@G@@    R2                    . CHARS ARE STASHED IN OUT/REM IMAG     @H@]@[WH
)@@G@@SOURCECOL       EQU                   A4  . COLUMN IN WHICH NEXT SOURCE WI
)@@G@@CHAR  @E@[@@REMCOLUMN   EQU  A3    . COL IN WHICH NEXT CHAR OF REMAIND  WJ
)@@G@@@H@@@]FETCHRG EQU     A5                    . CHARS FETCHED FROM SOURCE/WK
)@@G@@OUT IMA     @H@]@[REMCOLUMN       EQU                   A3  . COL IN WHIWL
)@@G@@CH NEXT CHAR OF REMAIND @E@[@@OUTCOLUMN   EQU  A2    . COL IN WHICH NEXTWM
)@@G@@ CHAR OF OUTPUT   @G@@@]SRCECOL EQU     A4                    . COLUMN IWN
)@@G@@N WHICH NEXT SOURCE CHAR@H@]@[OUTCOLUMN       EQU                   A2  WO
)@@G@@. COL IN WHICH NEXT CHAR OF OUTPUT  @F@[@@OUTBREG     EQU  A1           WP
)@@G@@  . A1 IS BYTE INDEX (0-3) IN OUTBUF@H@@@]REMCOL  EQU     A3            WQ
)@@G@@        . COL IN WHICH NEXT CHAR OF REMAIND     @G@]@[OUTBREG EQU     A1WR
)@@G@@                    . A1 IS BYTE INDEX (0-3) IN OUTBUF@F@[@@OUTWREG     WS
)@@G@@EQU  A0                . WORD POINTER INTO OUTBUF     @G@@@]OUTCOL  EQU WT
)@@G@@    A2                    . COL IN WHICH NEXT CHAR OF OUTPUT@F@]@[OUTWREWU
)@@G@@G EQU     A0                    . WORD POINTER INTO OUTBUF  @E@[@@SRCEBRWV
)@@G@@EG    EQU  X11            . SOURCE IMAGE BYTE LINK REG@G@@@]OUTBREG EQU WW
)@@G@@    A1                    . A1 IS BYTE INDEX (0-3) IN OUTBUF@G@]@[SRCEBRWX
)@@G@@EG        EQU                   X11  . SOURCE IMAGE BYTE LINK REG @F@[@@WY
)@@G@@SRCEWREG    EQU  X10            . SOURCE IMAGE WORD POINTER REG   @F@@@]WZ
)@@G@@OUTWREG EQU     A0                    . WORD POINTER INTO OUTBUF  @H@]@[XA
)@@G@@SRCEWREG        EQU                   X10  . SOURCE IMAGE WORD POINTER RXB
)@@G@@EG    @F@[@@SOURCEWORD  EQUF 0,SRCEWREG     . CURRENT WORD OF SOURCE IMAXC
)@@G@@GE    @F@@@]SRCEBRG EQU     X11                   . SOURCE IMAGE BYTE LIXD
)@@G@@NK REG@I@]@[SOURCEWORD      EQUF                  0,SRCEWREG  . CURRENT XE
)@@G@@WORD OF SOURCE IMAGE    @F@[@@REMBREG     EQU  X9             . REMAINDEXF
)@@G@@R IMAGE BYTE LINK REG   @G@@@]SRCEWRG EQU     X10                   . SOXG
)@@G@@URCE IMAGE WORD POINTER REG   @G@]@[REMBREG EQU     X9                  XH
)@@G@@  . REMAINDER IMAGE BYTE LINK REG   @F@[@@REMWREG     EQU  X8           XI
)@@G@@  . REMAINDER IMAGE WORD POINTER REG@G@@@]SRCEWRD EQUF    0,SRCEWRG     XJ
)@@G@@        . CURRENT WORD OF SOURCE IMAGE    @G@]@[REMWREG EQU     X8      XK
)@@G@@              . REMAINDER IMAGE WORD POINTER REG@[@[@@   .  @G@@@]REMBREXL
)@@G@@G EQU     X9                    . REMAINDER IMAGE BYTE LINK REG   @[@]@[XM
)@@G@@   .  @E@[@@   S       A2,OUTADR         . SAVE ADDR OF OUTPUT IMAGE    XN
)@@G@@@G@@@]REMWREG EQU     X8                    . REMAINDER IMAGE WORD POINTXO
)@@G@@ER REG@F@]@[   S       A2,OUTADR                  . SAVE ADDR OF OUTPUT XP
)@@G@@IMAGE @E@[@@   S       A3,REMADR         . AND ALSO REMAINDER IMAGE     XQ
)@@G@@@[@@@]   .  @F@]@[   S       A3,REMADR                  . AND ALSO REMAIXR
)@@G@@NDER IMAGE  @E@[@@   S       A4,EOICHR         . SAVE END IMAGE FLAG CHAXS
)@@G@@R     @F@@@]   S       A2,OUTADR                  . SAVE ADDR OF OUTPUT XT
)@@G@@IMAGE @F@]@[   S       A4,EOICHR                  . SAVE END IMAGE FLAG XU
)@@G@@CHAR  @[@[@@   .  @F@@@]   S       A3,REMADR                  . AND ALSOXV
)@@G@@ REMAINDER IMAGE  @[@]@[   .  @E@[@@   L       SRCEWREG,A0       . INITIXW
)@@G@@ALIZE SOURCE FETCHWORD  @F@@@]   S       A4,EOICHR                  . SAXX
)@@G@@VE END IMAGE FLAG CHAR  @G@]@[   L       SRCEWREG,A0                . INXY
)@@G@@ITIALIZE SOURCE FETCHWORD     @F@[@@   CALL,SRCEBREG    GETA5    . INITIXZ
)@@G@@ALIZE FETCHING FROM SOURCE    @[@@@]   .  @H@]@[   CALL,SRCEBREG        YA
)@@G@@              GETA5  . INITIALIZE FETCHING FROM SOURCE@F@[@@   L       RYB
)@@G@@EMWREG,A3        . INITIALIZE REMAINDER IMAGE WORDPTR @G@@@]   L       SYC
)@@G@@RCEWRG,A0                 . INITIALIZE SOURCE FETCHWORD     @H@]@[   L  YD
)@@G@@     REMWREG,A3                 . INITIALIZE REMAINDER IMAGE WORDPTR    YE
)@@G@@@F@[@@   CALL,REMBREG    PUTR2     . INITIALIZE STASHING IN REMAINDER   YF
)@@G@@@H@@@]   CALL,SRCEBRG                       GETA5  . INITIALIZE FETCHINGYG
)@@G@@ FROM SOURCE@I@]@[   CALL,REMBREG                       PUTR2  . INITIALYH
)@@G@@IZE STASHING IN REMAINDER     @[@[@@.     @H@@@]   L       REMWREG,A3   YI
)@@G@@              . INITIALIZE REMAINDER IMAGE WORDPTR    @[@]@[   .  @G@[@@YJ
)@@G@@   DSL     A2,72             . CLEAR OUTPUT AND REMAINDER IMAGE COLUMN  YK
)@@G@@@I@@@]   CALL,REMBREG                       PUTR2  . INITIALIZE STASHINGYL
)@@G@@ IN REMAINDER     @I@]@[   DSL     A2,72                      . CLEAR OUYM
)@@G@@TPUT AND REMAINDER IMAGE COLUMN     @F@[@@   SZ      SOURCECOL         .YN
)@@G@@ AND SOURCE IMAGE COLUMN COUNTER    @[@@@]   .  @G@]@[   SZ      SOURCECYO
)@@G@@OL                  . AND SOURCE IMAGE COLUMN COUNTER @E@[@@   LA,S1   AYP
)@@G@@0,SOURCEWORD     . GET 1ST CHAR OF SOURCE IMAGE @I@@@]   DSL     A2,72  YQ
)@@G@@                    . CLEAR OUTPUT AND REMAINDER IMAGE COLUMN     @G@]@[YR
)@@G@@   LA,S1   A0,SOURCEWORD              . GET 1ST CHAR OF SOURCE IMAGE    YS
)@@G@@@D@[@@   IF A0,EQ,077,,U THEN . THIS IS A FUNNYMODE IMAGE   @G@@@]   SZ YT
)@@G@@     SRCECOL                    . AND SOURCE IMAGE COLUMN COUNTER @F@]@[YU
)@@G@@   IF A0,EQ,077,,U THEN               . THIS IS A FUNNYMODE IMAGE @A@[@@YV
)@@G@@     LA,Q1   FETCHREG,SOURCEWORD    @G@@@]   LA,S1   A0,SRCEWRD         YW
)@@G@@        . GET 1ST CHAR OF SOURCE IMAGE    @A@]@[      LA,Q1   FETCHREG,SYX
)@@G@@OURCEWORD   @^@[@@     STASH   REMCHAR    @F@@@]   IF A0,EQ,077,,U THEN YY
)@@G@@              . THIS IS A FUNNYMODE IMAGE @^@]@[      STASH   REMCHAR   YZ
)@@G@@@F@[@@     L,U     REMCOLUMN,1       . SET REMAINDER IMAGE CHAR COUNT   ZA
)@@G@@@ @@@]      LA,Q1   FETCHRG,SRCEWRD @G@]@[      L,U     REMCOLUMN,1     ZB
)@@G@@        . SET REMAINDER IMAGE CHAR COUNT  @]@[@@   ENDIF    @^@@@]      ZC
)@@G@@STASH   REMCHAR   @]@]@[   ENDIF    @D@[@@   S       REMCOLUMN,FUNNYF  .ZD
)@@G@@ SET FUNNYMODE FLAG     @G@@@]      L,U     REMCOL,1                . SEZE
)@@G@@T REMAINDER IMAGE CHAR COUNT  @E@]@[   S       REMCOLUMN,FUNNYF         ZF
)@@G@@  . SET FUNNYMODE FLAG  @H@[@@   LSSL    OUTBREG,2              . CONVERZG
)@@G@@T WORDCNT TO CHARS IN SOURCE IMAGE  @]@@@]   ENDIF    @I@]@[   LSSL    OZH
)@@G@@UTBREG,2                  . CONVERT WORDCNT TO CHARS IN SOURCE IMAGE    ZI
)@@G@@@C@[@@   REPEAT VARY,R1 FOR,OUTBREG . AND LOOP ON IT  @E@@@]   S       RZJ
)@@G@@EMCOL,FUNNYF              . SET FUNNYMODE FLAG  @D@]@[   REPEAT VARY,R1 ZK
)@@G@@FOR,OUTBREG         . AND LOOP ON IT@^@[@@     FETCH   SOURCECHAR @I@@@]ZL
)@@G@@   LSSL    OUTBREG,2                  . CONVERT WORDCNT TO CHARS IN SOURZM
)@@G@@CE IMAGE    @^@]@[      FETCH   SOURCECHAR@A@[@@   ESCAPE    WHEN FETCHRZN
)@@G@@EG,EQ,EOICHR@D@@@]   REPEAT VARY,R1 FOR,OUTBREG         . AND LOOP ON ITZO
)@@G@@@A@]@[   ESCAPE    WHEN FETCHREG,EQ,EOICHR@C@[@@   OTHERWISE . THIS IS AZP
)@@G@@ CHARACTER TO BE STASHED@^@@@]      FETCH   SRCCHAR   @H@]@[   OTHERWISEZQ
)@@G@@                          . THIS IS A CHARACTER TO BE STASHED     @G@[@@ZR
)@@G@@     IF FETCHREG,EQ,ASCIBS THEN . WE CAN JUST REPOSITION THE CURSOR     ZS
)@@G@@@A@@@]   ESCAPE    WHEN FETCHRG,EQ,EOICHR @H@]@[      IF FETCHREG,EQ,ASCZT
)@@G@@IBS THEN      . WE CAN JUST REPOSITION THE CURSOR     @E@[@@       JGD  ZU
)@@G@@   SOURCECOL,$+1 . BUT NOT PAST COLUMN ZERO     @H@@@]   OTHERWISE      ZV
)@@G@@                    . THIS IS A CHARACTER TO BE STASHED     @F@]@[      ZW
)@@G@@   JGD     SOURCECOL,$+1        . BUT NOT PAST COLUMN ZERO  @C@[@@     EZX
)@@G@@LSE . WE MUST PUT THIS CHARACTER SOMEWHERE@H@@@]      IF FETCHRG,EQ,ASCIZY
)@@G@@BS THEN       . WE CAN JUST REPOSITION THE CURSOR     @H@]@[      ELSE  ZZ
)@@G@@                          . WE MUST PUT THIS CHARACTER SOMEWHERE  @D@[@@AA
)@@G@@       S       FETCHREG,STASHREG . PREPARE TO SAVE IT @F@@@]         JGDAB
)@@G@@     SRCECOL,$+1          . BUT NOT PAST COLUMN ZERO  @E@]@[         S  AC
)@@G@@     FETCHREG,STASHREG    . PREPARE TO SAVE IT  @G@[@@       L       OUTAD
)@@G@@WREG,SOURCECOL      . GET COL IT SHOULD APPEAR IN     @H@@@]      ELSE  AE
)@@G@@                          . WE MUST PUT THIS CHARACTER SOMEWHERE  @G@]@[AF
)@@G@@         L       OUTWREG,SOURCECOL    . GET COL IT SHOULD APPEAR IN     AG
)@@G@@@F@[@@       DSL     OUTWREG,2              . ISOLATE WD PART OF ADDR   AH
)@@G@@@E@@@]         S       FETCHRG,STASHRG      . PREPARE TO SAVE IT  @F@]@[AI
)@@G@@         DSL     OUTWREG,2            . ISOLATE WD PART OF ADDR   @E@[@@AJ
)@@G@@       SSL     OUTBREG,36-2           . AND ALIGN BYTE INDEX@G@@@]      AK
)@@G@@   L       OUTWREG,SRCECOL      . GET COL IT SHOULD APPEAR IN     @E@]@[AL
)@@G@@         SSL     OUTBREG,36-2         . AND ALIGN BYTE INDEX@ @[@@      AM
)@@G@@ A,U     SOURCECOL,1    @F@@@]         DSL     OUTWREG,2            . ISAN
)@@G@@OLATE WD PART OF ADDR   @ @]@[         A,U     SOURCECOL,1  @F@[@@      AO
)@@G@@ IF SOURCECOL,EQ,1,OUTCOLUMN,U THEN . WE CAN CATENATE IT    @E@@@]      AP
)@@G@@   SSL     OUTBREG,36-2         . AND ALIGN BYTE INDEX@F@]@[         IF AQ
)@@G@@SOURCECOL,EQ,1,OUTCOLUMN,U THEN . WE CAN CATENATE IT  @^@[@@         STAAR
)@@G@@SH   OUTCHAR@ @@@]         A,U     SRCECOL,1    @ @]@[            STASH AS
)@@G@@  OUTCHAR   @A@[@@         S       SOURCECOL,OUTCOLUMN@E@@@]         IF AT
)@@G@@SRCECOL,EQ,1,OUTCOL,U THEN . WE CAN CATENATE IT @B@]@[            S     AU
)@@G@@  SOURCECOL,OUTCOLUMN   @E@[@@       ELSE . CHAR MUST BE PLACED INTERIORAV
)@@G@@ TO CURRENT IMAGE @ @@@]            STASH   OUTCHAR   @I@]@[         ELSAW
)@@G@@E                         . CHAR MUST BE PLACED INTERIOR TO CURRENT     AX
)@@G@@@E@[@@         IF FETCHREG,NEQ,ASPACE THEN . WE CANNOT IGNORE IT  @A@@@]AY
)@@G@@            S       SRCECOL,OUTCOL  @F@]@[            IF FETCHREG,NEQ,ASAZ
)@@G@@PACE THEN . WE CANNOT IGNORE IT     @ @[@@           FETCH   OUTCHAR    BA
)@@G@@@I@@@]         ELSE                         . CHAR MUST BE PLACED INTERIBB
)@@G@@OR TO CURRENT     @ @]@[               FETCH   OUTCHAR@G@[@@           IBC
)@@G@@F FETCHREG,NEQ,STASHREG THEN . NOT OVERSTRUCK WITH ITSELF   @E@@@]      BD
)@@G@@      IF FETCHRG,NEQ,ASPACE THEN . WE CANNOT IGNORE IT@H@]@[            BE
)@@G@@   IF FETCHREG,NEQ,STASHREG THEN . NOT OVERSTRUCK WITH ITSELF     @F@[@@BF
)@@G@@             IF FETCHREG,EQ,ASPACE THEN . OLD CHAR CAN BE TRASHED @ @@@]BG
)@@G@@               FETCH   OUTCHAR@G@]@[                  IF FETCHREG,EQ,ASPBH
)@@G@@ACE THEN . OLD CHAR CAN BE TRASHED  @ @[@@               STASH   OUTCHARBI
)@@G@@@G@@@]               IF FETCHRG,NEQ,STASHRG THEN . NOT OVERSTRUCK WITH IBJ
)@@G@@TSELF @A@]@[                     STASH   OUTCHAR@E@[@@             ELSE BK
)@@G@@. NEW CHAR MUST BE TEMP SAVED IN REMAINDER@G@@@]                  IF FETBL
)@@G@@CHRG,EQ,ASPACE THEN . OLD CHAR CAN BE TRASHED   @I@]@[                  BM
)@@G@@ELSE                . NEW CHAR MUST BE TEMP SAVED IN REMAINDER    @B@[@@BN
)@@G@@               L,U     OUTWREG,1,REMCOLUMN@A@@@]                     STABO
)@@G@@SH   OUTCHAR@C@]@[                     L,U     OUTWREG,1,REMCOLUMN@B@[@@BP
)@@G@@               AN      OUTWREG,SOURCECOL  @I@@@]                  ELSE  BQ
)@@G@@              . NEW CHAR MUST BE TEMP SAVED IN REMAINDER    @C@]@[      BR
)@@G@@               AN      OUTWREG,SOURCECOL  @E@[@@               S       SBS
)@@G@@TASHREG,FETCHREG . PROTECT THIS CHAR@C@@@]                     L,U     OBT
)@@G@@UTWREG,1,REMCOL   @G@]@[                     S       STASHREG,FETCHREG  BU
)@@G@@. PROTECT THIS CHAR     @B@[@@               L       STASHREG,ASPACE    BV
)@@G@@@C@@@]                     AN      OUTWREG,SRCECOL    @C@]@[            BW
)@@G@@         L       STASHREG,ASPACE    @E@[@@               IF OUTWREG,IS,PBX
)@@G@@OS THEN + (L STASHREG,ASCIBS) @F@]@[                     IF OUTWREG,IS,PBY
)@@G@@OS THEN + (L STASHREG,ASCIBS) @F@@@]                     S       STASHRGBZ
)@@G@@,FETCHRG  . PROTECT THIS CHAR @C@@@]                     L       STASHRGCA
)@@G@@,ASPACE     @C@@@]                     IF OUTWREG,IS,POS THEN     @A@[@@CB
)@@G@@               SMA     OUTWREG,R3   @C@@@]                        L     CC
)@@G@@  STASHRG,ASCIBS  @B@]@[                        SMA     OUTWREG,R3@F@[@@CD
)@@G@@               REPEAT   JGD,R3            . FOR NO OF FILLS NEEDED@ @@@]CE
)@@G@@                     ENDIF    @F@]@[                        REPEAT   JGDCF
)@@G@@,R3 . FOR NO OF FILLS NEEDED  @A@[@@                 STASH   REMCHAR    CG
)@@G@@@B@@@]                     SMA     OUTWREG,R3   @B@]@[                  CH
)@@G@@         STASH   REMCHAR@^@[@@               ENDREP   @F@@@]            CI
)@@G@@         REPEAT   JGD,R3  . FOR NO OF FILLS NEEDED    @ @]@[            CJ
)@@G@@            ENDREP@E@[@@               S       FETCHREG,STASHREG . PREPACK
)@@G@@RE TO STASH @B@@@]                        STASH   REMCHAR   @G@]@[      CL
)@@G@@                  S       FETCHREG,STASHREG  . PREPARE TO STASH   @ @[@@CM
)@@G@@               STASH   REMCHAR@ @@@]                     ENDREP   @B@]@[CN
)@@G@@                        STASH   REMCHAR   @B@[@@               S       SCO
)@@G@@OURCECOL,REMCOLUMN@F@@@]                     S       FETCHRG,STASHRG  . CP
)@@G@@PREPARE TO STASH  @D@]@[                        S       SOURCECOL,REMCOLCQ
)@@G@@UMN   @#@[@@             ENDIF@A@@@]                     STASH   REMCHARCR
)@@G@@@ @]@[                     ENDIF    @#@[@@           ENDIF  @C@@@]      CS
)@@G@@               S       SRCECOL,REMCOL     @^@]@[                  ENDIF CT
)@@G@@@#@[@@         ENDIF    @^@@@]                  ENDIF @^@]@[            CU
)@@G@@   ENDIF    @]@[@@       ENDIF@^@@@]               ENDIF    @#@]@[      CV
)@@G@@      ENDIF @]@[@@     ENDIF  @#@@@]            ENDIF @#@]@[         ENDCW
)@@G@@IF    @]@[@@   ENDREP   @#@@@]         ENDIF    @]@]@[      ENDREP@E@[@@CX
)@@G@@   L       OUTWREG,OUTCOLUMN      . GET FINAL OUTCOL NUMBER @]@@@]      CY
)@@G@@ENDIF @F@]@[      L       OUTWREG,OUTCOLUMN       . GET FINAL OUTCOL NUMCZ
)@@G@@BER   @F@[@@   DSL     OUTWREG,2              . DIVIDE LAST OUTCOLUMN BYDA
)@@G@@ 4    @]@@@]   ENDREP   @F@]@[      DSL     OUTWREG,2               . DIDB
)@@G@@VIDE LAST OUTCOLUMN BY 4@D@[@@   SSL     OUTBREG,36-2           . ALIGN DC
)@@G@@BYTE INDEX  @F@@@]   L       OUTWREG,OUTCOL             . GET FINAL OUTCDD
)@@G@@OL NUMBER   @E@]@[      SSL     OUTBREG,36-2            . ALIGN BYTE INDDE
)@@G@@EX    @F@[@@   IF OUTBREG,IS,NONZ THEN   . THE LAST WORD IS NOT FILLED UDF
)@@G@@P     @F@@@]   DSL     OUTWREG,2                  . DIVIDE LAST OUTCOL BDG
)@@G@@Y 4   @G@]@[      IF OUTBREG,IS,NONZ THEN         . THE LAST WORD IS NOTDH
)@@G@@ FILLED UP  @G@[@@     ANU,U   OUTBREG,4              . COMPUTE NO OF CODI
)@@G@@LS OF FILL NEEDED @E@@@]   SSL     OUTBREG,36-2               . ALIGN BYDJ
)@@G@@TE INDEX    @H@]@[         ANU,U   OUTBREG,4            . COMPUTE NO OF DK
)@@G@@COLS OF FILL NEEDED     @C@[@@     SMA     A2,R1             . USE AS LODL
)@@G@@OP CNT@G@@@]   IF OUTBREG,IS,NONZ THEN            . THE LAST WORD IS NOTDM
)@@G@@ FILLED UP  @E@]@[         SMA     A2,R1                . USE AS LOOP CNDN
)@@G@@T     @G@[@@     L      STASHREG,ASPACE    . FILL FOR OUTPUT IMAGE ALWAYDO
)@@G@@S SPACES    @H@@@]      ANU,U   OUTBREG,4               . COMPUTE NO OF DP
)@@G@@COLS OF FILL NEEDED     @H@]@[         L       STASHREG,ASPACE      . FIDQ
)@@G@@LL FOR OUTPUT IMAGE ALWAYS SPACES   @D@[@@     REPEAT JGD,R1 . FOR NUMBEDR
)@@G@@R OF FILLS REQUIRED     @E@@@]      SMA     A2,R1                   . USDS
)@@G@@E AS LOOP CNT     @G@]@[         REPEAT JGD,R1                . FOR NUMBDT
)@@G@@ER OF FILLS REQUIRED    @^@[@@       STASH   OUTCHAR  @H@@@]      L     DU
)@@G@@  STASHRG,ASPACE          . FILL FOR OUTPUT IMAGE ALWAYS SPACES   @ @]@[DV
)@@G@@            STASH   OUTCHAR   @^@[@@       A,U     OUTBREG,1@G@@@]      DW
)@@G@@REPEAT JGD,R1                   . FOR NUMBER OF FILLS REQUIRED    @ @]@[DX
)@@G@@            A,U     OUTBREG,1 @]@[@@     ENDREP @^@@@]         STASH   ODY
)@@G@@UTCHAR@#@]@[         ENDREP   @H@[@@     A,U     OUTWREG,1              DZ
)@@G@@. MAKE OUTPUT WORD INDEX INTO WORD COUNT  @ @@@]         A,U     OUTBREGEA
)@@G@@,1    @H@]@[         A,U     OUTWREG,1            . MAKE OUTPUT WORD INDEB
)@@G@@EX INTO WORD COUNT@]@[@@   ENDIF    @]@@@]      ENDREP@]@]@[      ENDIF EC
)@@G@@@F@[@@   L       STASHREG,EOICHR   . REMAINDER IMAGE FILLED WITH EOI    ED
)@@G@@@H@@@]      A,U     OUTWREG,1               . MAKE OUTPUT WORD INDEX INTEE
)@@G@@O WORD COUNT@G@]@[      L       STASHREG,EOICHR         . REMAINDER IMAGEF
)@@G@@E FILLED WITH EOI @D@[@@   STASH   REMCHAR           . CLOSE REMAINDER IEG
)@@G@@MAGE  @]@@@]   ENDIF    @F@]@[      STASH   REMCHAR                 . CLEH
)@@G@@OSE REMAINDER IMAGE     @F@[@@   STASH   REMCHAR           . AND PAD IT EI
)@@G@@ACROSS A WORD BOUNDARY  @G@@@]   L       STASHRG,EOICHR             . REEJ
)@@G@@MAINDER IMAGE FILLED WITH EOI @H@]@[      STASH   REMCHAR               EK
)@@G@@  . AND PAD IT ACROSS A WORD BOUNDARY     @D@[@@   IF ZERO,IN,FUNNYF THEEL
)@@G@@N . IMAGE WAS NOT FUNNYMODE   @F@@@]   STASH   REMCHAR                  EM
)@@G@@  . CLOSE REMAINDER IMAGE     @F@]@[      IF ZERO,IN,FUNNYF THEN        EN
)@@G@@  . IMAGE WAS NOT FUNNYMODE   @E@[@@     STASH   REMCHAR           . ANDEO
)@@G@@ IT NEEDS ANOTHER PAD   @H@@@]   STASH   REMCHAR                    . ANEP
)@@G@@D PAD IT ACROSS A WORD BOUNDARY     @F@]@[         STASH   REMCHAR      EQ
)@@G@@        . AND IT NEEDS ANOTHER PAD  @]@[@@   ENDIF    @F@@@]   IF ZERO,IER
)@@G@@N,FUNNYF THEN             . IMAGE WAS NOT FUNNYMODE   @]@]@[      ENDIF ES
)@@G@@@D@[@@   LA,U    A1,0,REMWREG      . GET LAST WORD ADDR     @F@@@]      ET
)@@G@@STASH   REMCHAR                 . AND IT NEEDS ANOTHER PAD  @E@]@[      EU
)@@G@@LA,U    A1,0,REMWREG            . GET LAST WORD ADDR  @E@[@@   AN      AEV
)@@G@@1,REMADR         . LESS 1ST IS NUMBER OF WORDS  @]@@@]   ENDIF    @G@]@[EW
)@@G@@      AN      A1,REMADR               . LESS 1ST IS NUMBER OF WORDS     EX
)@@G@@@[@[@@   .  @E@@@]   LA,U    A1,0,REMWREG               . GET LAST WORD EY
)@@G@@ADDR  @]@]@[      .     @]@[@@ ENDBEG     @G@@@]   AN      A1,REMADR    EZ
)@@G@@              . LESS 1ST IS NUMBER OF WORDS     @]@]@[   ENDBEG   @[@@@]FA
)@@G@@   .  @]@@@] ENDBEG     @H@@@@/.       MAIN    PROGRAM TO GENERATE AN APFB
)@@G@@RINT$ FILE WITHOUT OVERSTRIKES FRO  @A@[@@ . AN ARBITRARY FILE OR ELEMENFC
)@@G@@T-    @A@]@[   . AN ARBITRARY FILE OR ELEMENT-  @[@[@@ .    @[@]@[   .  FD
)@@G@@@]@[@@$(2)     .  @A@@@] . AN ARBITRARY FILE OR ELEMENT-    @B@]@[$(2)  FE
)@@G@@                                .   @E@[@@PRINTBUF RES     40 . OUTPUT IFF
)@@G@@MAGES ARE PRINTED OUT OF HERE @[@@@] .    @I@]@[PRINTBUF        RES     FG
)@@G@@              40  . OUTPUT IMAGES ARE PRINTED OUT OF HER    @^@[@@SPACECFH
)@@G@@TL EQUF    $,,H1 .@B@@@]$(2)                                  .   @C@]@[FI
)@@G@@SPACECTL        EQUF                  $,,H1  .  @B@[@@ +0100,0 . ASSUME FJ
)@@G@@SINGLE SPACING FOR NOW  @H@@@]PRNTBUF RES     40                    . OUFK
)@@G@@TPUT IMAGES ARE PRINTED OUT OF HER  @G@]@[   +0100,0                    FL
)@@G@@        . ASSUME SINGLE SPACING FOR NOW   @F@[@@ASCICR   EQU     015   .FM
)@@G@@ USE CARRIAGE RETURN TO FLAG END OF IMAGE @B@@@]SPACCTL EQUF    $,,H1   FN
)@@G@@              .   @I@]@[ASCICR  EQU     015                   . USE CARRFO
)@@G@@IAGE RETURN TO FLAG END OF IMAGE    @[@[@@ .    @G@@@]        +0100,0   FP
)@@G@@                    . ASSUME SINGLE SPACING FOR NOW   @[@]@[   .  @ @[@@FQ
)@@G@@ . DATA AREAS USED BY SDFIO   @I@@@]ASCICR  EQU     015                 FR
)@@G@@  . USE CARRIAGE RETURN TO FLAG END OF IMAGE    @ @]@[   . DATA AREAS USFS
)@@G@@ED BY SDFIO @[@[@@ .    @[@@@] .    @[@]@[   .  @C@[@@PACKET   RES     2FT
)@@G@@              . FILE NAME     @ @@@] . DATA AREAS USED BY SDFIO   @D@]@[FU
)@@G@@PACKET  RES     2                     . FILE NAME     @]@[@@ +0      .  FV
)@@G@@@[@@@] .    @B@]@[   +0                                 .   @]@[@@ +R$,0FW
)@@G@@,0 .  @D@@@]PACKET  RES     2                     . FILE NAME     @B@]@[FX
)@@G@@   +R$,0,0                            .   @A@[@@ +SDFBSIZ,$-$          .FY
)@@G@@ ACCESS WORD@B@@@]        +0                            .   @D@]@[   +SDFZ
)@@G@@FBSIZ,$-$                        . ACCESS WORD  @ @[@@DRUMADR  +$-$    .GA
)@@G@@ DRUM ADDR  @B@@@]        +R$,0,0                       .   @D@]@[DRUMADGB
)@@G@@R +$-$                          . DRUM ADDR     @^@[@@ +SDFBUFA,SDFBUFB GC
)@@G@@     .@D@@@]        +SDFBSIZ,$-$                   . ACCESS WORD  @B@]@[GD
)@@G@@   +SDFBUFA,SDFBUFB                    .  @C@[@@ +SDFBSIZ/28,IMSIZE    .GE
)@@G@@ BIF SIZE, IMAGE SIZE   @D@@@]DRUMADR +$-$                          . DRGF
)@@G@@UM ADDR     @F@]@[   +SDFBSIZ/28,IMSIZE                  . BIF SIZE, IMAGG
)@@G@@GE SIZE     @^@[@@ +1,INIMAGE            .@B@@@]        +SDFBUFA,SDFBUFBGH
)@@G@@               .  @B@]@[   +1,INIMAGE                          .  @]@[@@GI
)@@G@@ +1,$-$  .  @F@@@]        +SDFBSIZ/28,IMSIZE             . BIF SIZE, IMAGJ
)@@G@@GE SIZE     @B@]@[   +1,$-$                             .   @A@[@@CTLWRDGK
)@@G@@   +$-$    . SDF CONTROL WORD @B@@@]        +1,INIMAGE                  GL
)@@G@@   .  @E@]@[CTLWRD  +$-$                          . SDF CONTROL WORD    GM
)@@G@@@[@[@@ .    @B@@@]        +1,$-$                        .   @[@]@[   .  GN
)@@G@@@D@[@@SDFBSIZ  EQU     224            . SIZE OF SDF BUFFERS @E@@@]CTLWRDGO
)@@G@@  +$-$                          . SDF CONTROL WORD    @E@]@[SDFBSIZ EQU GP
)@@G@@    224                   . SIZE OF SDF BUFFERS @A@[@@SDFBUFA  RES     SGQ
)@@G@@DFBSIZ        .   @[@@@] .    @B@]@[SDFBUFA RES     SDFBSIZ             GR
)@@G@@  .   @A@[@@SDFBUFB  RES     SDFBSIZ        .   @E@@@]SDFBSIZ EQU     22GS
)@@G@@4                   . SIZE OF SDF BUFFERS @B@]@[SDFBUFB RES     SDFBSIZ GT
)@@G@@              .   @[@[@@ .    @B@@@]SDFBUFA RES     SDFBSIZ             GU
)@@G@@  .   @[@]@[   .  @E@[@@SDFEOF   RES     1              . SENTINAL LOCN GV
)@@G@@FOR EOF     @B@@@]SDFBUFB RES     SDFBSIZ               .   @F@]@[SDFEOFGW
)@@G@@  RES     1                     . SENTINAL LOCN FOR EOF     @E@[@@SDFERRGX
)@@G@@   RES     1              . SENTINAL LOCN FOR ERR     @[@@@] .    @F@]@[GY
)@@G@@SDFERR  RES     1                     . SENTINAL LOCN FOR ERR     @D@[@@GZ
)@@G@@IMSIZE   EQU     40             . SIZE OF IMAGE BUFFER@F@@@]SDFEOF  RES HA
)@@G@@    1                     . SENTINAL LOCN FOR EOF     @E@]@[IMSIZE  EQU HB
)@@G@@    40                    . SIZE OF IMAGE BUFFER@D@[@@INIMAGE  RES     IHC
)@@G@@MSIZE         . INPUT IMAGE BUFFER  @F@@@]SDFERR  RES     1             HD
)@@G@@        . SENTINAL LOCN FOR ERR     @E@]@[INIMAGE RES     IMSIZE        HE
)@@G@@        . INPUT IMAGE BUFFER  @[@[@@ .    @E@@@]IMSIZE  EQU     40      HF
)@@G@@              . SIZE OF IMAGE BUFFER@[@]@[   .  @]@[@@$(1)     .  @E@@@]HG
)@@G@@INIMAGE RES     IMSIZE                . INPUT IMAGE BUFFER  @B@]@[$(1)  HH
)@@G@@                                .   @[@[@@ .    @[@@@] .    @[@]@[   .  HI
)@@G@@@]@[@@PRINTIT     @B@@@]$(1)                                  .   @]@]@[HJ
)@@G@@PRINTIT     @#@[@@ BEGIN SUBROUTINE @[@@@] .    @^@]@[   BEGIN SUBROUTINHK
)@@G@@E     @C@[@@   DS      A0,PACKET      . FILE NAME TO PACKET @]@#@]PRINTIHL
)@@G@@T     @E@]@[   DS      A0,PACKET                  . FILE NAME TO PACKET HM
)@@G@@@D@[@@   SA      A2,DRUMADR     . AND INITIAL DRUM ADDRESS  @]@@@#PRINTIHN
)@@G@@T     @#@#@] BEGIN SUBROUTINE @F@]@[   SA      A2,DRUMADR               HO
)@@G@@  . AND INITIAL DRUM ADDRESS  @^@[@@   LA,U   A0,PACKET     @#@@@# BEGINHP
)@@G@@ SUBROUTINE @E@#@]   DS      A0,PACKET                  . FILE NAME TO PHQ
)@@G@@ACKET @^@]@[   LA,U    A0,PACKET    @C@[@@   CALL        SDFIO SDFERR . HR
)@@G@@OPEN THE FILE     @E@@@#   DS      A0,PACKET                  . FILE NAMHS
)@@G@@E TO PACKET @F@#@]   SA      A2,DRUMADR                 . AND INITIAL DRHT
)@@G@@UM ADDRESS  @D@]@[   CALL    SDFIO SDFERR               . OPEN THE FILE HU
)@@G@@@A@[@@   REPEAT WHILE ZERO,IN,SDFERR .    @F@@@#   SA      A2,DRUMADR   HV
)@@G@@              . AND INITIAL DRUM ADDRESS  @^@#@]   LA,U    A0,PACKET    HW
)@@G@@@B@]@[   REPEAT WHILE ZERO,IN,SDFERR        .   @ @[@@     LA,U      A0,HX
)@@G@@PACKET .    @D@#@]   CALL    SDFIO SDFERR               . OPEN THE FILE HY
)@@G@@@^@@@#   LA,U    A0,PACKET    @D@@@#   CASENTRY CALLING SDFIO           HZ
)@@G@@  . OPEN THE FILE @D@@@#   CASE 1                             . NORMAL EIA
)@@G@@XIT   @E@@@#      SZ      SDFERR                  . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    IB
)@@G@@@D@@@#   CASE 0                             . ERROR EXIT    @E@@@#      IC
)@@G@@SX      X11,SDFERR              . RAISE ERROR FLAG    @B@]@[      LA,U  ID
)@@G@@  A0,PACKET               .   @B@[@@     CALL        SDFI SDFERR,SDFEOF IE
)@@G@@.     @]@@@#   ENDCASE  @B@#@]   REPEAT WHILE ZERO,IN,SDFERR        .   IF
)@@G@@@B@]@[      CALL    SDFI SDFERR,SDFEOF      .   @E@[@@     IF NONZ,IN,SDIG
)@@G@@FERR THEN +(SZ SDFEOF ) . NO FALSE ALARMS @E@]@[      IF NONZ,IN,SDFERR IH
)@@G@@THEN +(SZ SDFEOF ) . NO FALSE ALARMS@B@@@#   REPEAT WHILE ZERO,IN,SDFERRII
)@@G@@        .   @B@#@]      LA,U    A0,PACKET               .   @B@#@]      IJ
)@@G@@CALL    SDFI SDFERR,SDFEOF      .   @B@@@#      LA,U    A0,PACKET       IK
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@#      SZ      SDFERR                  . CLEAR ERROR FLIL
)@@G@@AG    @E@@@#      SZ      SDFEOF                  . AND END OF FILE FLAGIM
)@@G@@@ @@@#      CASENTRY CALLING SDFI   @D@@@#      CASE      2             IN
)@@G@@        . NORMAL EXIT   @D@@@#      CASE      0                     . ERIO
)@@G@@ROR EXIT    @E@@@#         SX      X11,SDFERR           . RAISE ERROR FLIP
)@@G@@AG    @E@@@#      CASE      1                     . END OF FILE EXIT    IQ
)@@G@@@D@@@#         SX      X11,SDFEOF           . RAISE EOF FLAG@#@@@#      IR
)@@G@@ENDCASE     @E@#@]      IF NONZ,IN,SDFERR THEN          . ALL FLAGS WEREIS
)@@G@@ SET  @A@[@@   ESCAPE WHEN NONZ,IN,SDFEOF .     @E@#@]         SZ      SIT
)@@G@@DFEOF               . INHIBIT FALSE ALARMS@B@]@[   ESCAPE WHEN NONZ,IN,SIU
)@@G@@DFEOF         .   @^@[@@     LA,U      A0,PACKET@]@#@]      ENDIF @^@]@[IV
)@@G@@      LA,U    A0,PACKET @C@[@@     CALL        SDFIC      . CLOSE THE FIIW
)@@G@@LE    @B@#@]   ESCAPE WHEN NONZ,IN,SDFEOF         .   @D@]@[      CALL  IX
)@@G@@  SDFIC                   . CLOSE THE FILE@C@[@@   OTHERWISE . THERE'S AIY
)@@G@@N IMAGE TO BE PROCESSED @B@@@#   ESCAPE WHEN NONZ,IN,SDFEOF         .   IZ
)@@G@@@^@#@]      LA,U    A0,PACKET @G@]@[   OTHERWISE                        JA
)@@G@@  . THERE'S AN IMAGE TO BE PROCESSED@C@[@@     IF ZERO,IN,SDFERR THEN . JB
)@@G@@ITS OK TO PROCESS @^@@@#      LA,U    A0,PACKET @D@#@]      CALL    SDFIJC
)@@G@@C                   . CLOSE THE FILE@E@]@[      IF ZERO,IN,SDFERR THEN  JD
)@@G@@        . ITS OK TO PROCESS   @C@[@@       LA      A1,CTLWRD      . GET JE
)@@G@@CONTROL WORD@D@@@#      CALL    SDFIC                   . CLOSE THE FILEJF
)@@G@@@G@#@]   OTHERWISE                          . THERE'S AN IMAGE TO BE PROJG
)@@G@@CESSED@E@]@[         LA      A1,CTLWRD            . GET CONTROL WORD    JH
)@@G@@@D@[@@       IF A1,IS,POS THEN . THIS IS REALLY AN IMAGE    @G@@@#   OTHJI
)@@G@@ERWISE                          . THERE'S AN IMAGE TO BE PROCESSED@E@#@]JJ
)@@G@@      IF ZERO,IN,SDFERR THEN          . ITS OK TO PROCESS   @F@]@[      JK
)@@G@@   IF A1,IS,POS THEN            . THIS IS REALLY AN IMAGE   @E@[@@      JL
)@@G@@   SSL     A1,36-12       . LINE UP THE WORDCOUNT     @E@@@#      IF ZERJM
)@@G@@O,IN,SDFERR THEN          . ITS OK TO PROCESS   @E@#@]         LA      AJN
)@@G@@1,CTLWRD            . GET CONTROL WORD    @F@]@[            SSL     A1,3JO
)@@G@@6-12          . LINE UP THE WORDCOUNT     @D@[@@         LA,U    A0,INIMJP
)@@G@@AGE     . GET BUFFER ADDR     @E@@@#         LA      A1,CTLWRD          JQ
)@@G@@  . GET CONTROL WORD    @F@#@]         IF A1,IS,POS THEN            . THJR
)@@G@@IS IS REALLY AN IMAGE   @E@]@[            LA,U    A0,INIMAGE        . GEJS
)@@G@@T BUFFER ADDR     @G@[@@         LA,U    A2,PRINTBUF       . CONVERT OUTJT
)@@G@@PUT IMAGE INTO PRINTBUF @F@@@#         IF A1,IS,POS THEN            . THJU
)@@G@@IS IS REALLY AN IMAGE   @F@#@]            SSL     A1,36-12          . LIJV
)@@G@@NE UP THE WORDCOUNT     @H@]@[            LA,U    A2,PRINTBUF       . COJW
)@@G@@NVERT OUTPUT IMAGE INTO PRINTBUF    @G@[@@         LA,U    A3,0,A0      JX
)@@G@@     . PUT OFLO BACK ATOP SOURCE IMAGE    @F@@@#            SSL     A1,3JY
)@@G@@6-12          . LINE UP THE WORDCOUNT     @E@#@]            LA,U    A0,IJZ
)@@G@@NIMAGE        . GET BUFFER ADDR     @G@]@[            LA,U    A3,0,A0   KA
)@@G@@        . PUT OFLO BACK ATOP SOURCE IMAGE @G@[@@         LA,U    A4,ASCIKB
)@@G@@CR         . USE CARRIAGE RETURN AS TERMINATOR  @E@@@#            LA,U  KC
)@@G@@  A0,INIMAGE        . GET BUFFER ADDR     @H@#@]            LA,U    A2,PKD
)@@G@@RNTBUF        . CONVERT OUTPUT IMAGE INTO PRNTBUF     @H@]@[            KE
)@@G@@LA,U    A4,ASCICR         . USE CARRIAGE RETURN AS TERMINATOR     @F@[@@KF
)@@G@@         CALL        MULINE        . PROCESS THE 1ST LINE OF IT   @H@@@#KG
)@@G@@            LA,U    A2,PRNTBUF        . CONVERT OUTPUT IMAGE INTO PRNTBUKH
)@@G@@F     @G@#@]            LA,U    A3,0,A0           . PUT OFLO BACK ATOP SKI
)@@G@@OURCE IMAGE @F@]@[            CALL    MULINE            . PROCESS THE 1SKJ
)@@G@@T LINE OF IT@G@[@@         AA      A0,SPACECTL       . SPACE CTL IN 2ND KK
)@@G@@SIXTH OF THIS     @G@@@#            LA,U    A3,0,A0           . PUT OFLOKL
)@@G@@ BACK ATOP SOURCE IMAGE @H@#@]            LA,U    A4,ASCICR         . USKM
)@@G@@E CARRIAGE RETURN AS TERMINATOR     @G@]@[            AA      A0,SPACECTKN
)@@G@@L       . SPACE CTL IN 2ND SIXTH OF THIS  @F@[@@         LSSL    A0,18  KO
)@@G@@           . LINE UP WORDCT, SPACE CONTROL@H@@@#            LA,U    A4,AKP
)@@G@@SCICR         . USE CARRIAGE RETURN AS TERMINATOR     @F@#@]            KQ
)@@G@@CALL    MULINE            . PROCESS THE 1ST LINE OF IT@G@]@[            KR
)@@G@@LSSL    A0,18             . LINE UP WORDCT, SPACE CONTROL   @E@[@@      KS
)@@G@@   LXM,U   A0,PRINTBUF       . AND PLUG IN BUFFER ADDR@F@@@#            KT
)@@G@@CALL    MULINE            . PROCESS THE 1ST LINE OF IT@G@#@]            KU
)@@G@@AA      A0,SPACCTL        . SPACE CTL IN 2ND SIXTH OF THIS  @F@]@[      KV
)@@G@@      LXM,U   A0,PRINTBUF       . AND PLUG IN BUFFER ADDR   @G@[@@      KW
)@@G@@   ER      APRINT$           . AND PRINT WITH STANDARD SPACING    @G@@@#KX
)@@G@@            AA      A0,SPACCTL        . SPACE CTL IN 2ND SIXTH OF THIS  KY
)@@G@@@G@#@]            LSSL    A0,18             . LINE UP WORDCT, SPACE CONTKZ
)@@G@@ROL   @G@]@[            ER      APRINT$           . AND PRINT WITH STANDLA
)@@G@@ARD SPACING @G@[@@         REPEAT WHILE A1,IS,NONZ  . WHICH MEANS THERE'LB
)@@G@@S A REMAINDER     @G@@@#            LSSL    A0,18             . LINE UP LC
)@@G@@WORDCT, SPACE CONTROL   @F@#@]            LXM,U   A0,PRNTBUF        . ANLD
)@@G@@D PLUG IN BUFFER ADDR   @G@]@[            REPEAT WHILE A1,IS,NONZ   . WHLE
)@@G@@ICH MEANS THERE'S A REMAINDER @F@[@@           LA,U    A0,INIMAGE     . LF
)@@G@@GET INPUT IMAGE ADDR BACK     @F@@@#            LXM,U   A0,PRNTBUF      LG
)@@G@@  . AND PLUG IN BUFFER ADDR   @G@#@]            ER      APRINT$         LH
)@@G@@  . AND PRINT WITH STANDARD SPACING @F@]@[               LA,U    A0,INIMLI
)@@G@@AGE     . GET INPUT IMAGE ADDR BACK @H@[@@           LA,U    A2,PRINTBUFLJ
)@@G@@       . CONVERT OUTPUT IMAGE INTO PRINTBUF     @G@@@#            ER    LK
)@@G@@  APRINT$           . AND PRINT WITH STANDARD SPACING @G@#@]            LL
)@@G@@REPEAT WHILE A1,IS,NONZ   . WHICH MEANS THERE'S A REMAINDER @H@]@[      LM
)@@G@@         LA,U    A2,PRINTBUF    . CONVERT OUTPUT IMAGE INTO PRINTBUF    LN
)@@G@@@G@[@@           LA,U    A3,0,A0           . PUT OFLO BACK ATOP SOURCE ILO
)@@G@@MAGE  @G@@@#            REPEAT WHILE A1,IS,NONZ   . WHICH MEANS THERE'S LP
)@@G@@A REMAINDER @F@#@]               LA,U    A0,INIMAGE     . GET INPUT IMAGLQ
)@@G@@E ADDR BACK @G@]@[               LA,U    A3,0,A0        . PUT OFLO BACK LR
)@@G@@ATOP SOURCE IMAGE @G@[@@           LA,U    A4,ASCICR         . USE CARRILS
)@@G@@AGE RETURN AS TERMINATOR@F@@@#               LA,U    A0,INIMAGE     . GELT
)@@G@@T INPUT IMAGE ADDR BACK @H@#@]               LA,U    A2,PRNTBUF     . COLU
)@@G@@NVERT OUTPUT IMAGE INTO PRNTBUF     @H@]@[               LA,U    A4,ASCILV
)@@G@@CR      . USE CARRIAGE RETURN AS TERMINATOR     @F@[@@           CALL   LW
)@@G@@     MULINE        . UNPACK REMAINDER IMAGE     @H@@@#               LA,LX
)@@G@@U    A2,PRNTBUF     . CONVERT OUTPUT IMAGE INTO PRNTBUF     @G@#@]      LY
)@@G@@         LA,U    A3,0,A0        . PUT OFLO BACK ATOP SOURCE IMAGE @F@]@[LZ
)@@G@@               CALL    MULINE         . UNPACK REMAINDER IMAGE    @F@[@@MA
)@@G@@           LSSL    A0,18             . LINE UP WORDCT, SPACE CTL=0@G@@@#MB
)@@G@@               LA,U    A3,0,A0        . PUT OFLO BACK ATOP SOURCE IMAGE MC
)@@G@@@H@#@]               LA,U    A4,ASCICR      . USE CARRIAGE RETURN AS TERMD
)@@G@@MINATOR     @G@]@[               LSSL    A0,18          . LINE UP WORDCTME
)@@G@@, SPACE CTL=0     @D@[@@           LXM,U   A0,PRINTBUF       . SET BUFFEMF
)@@G@@R ADDR@H@@@#               LA,U    A4,ASCICR      . USE CARRIAGE RETURN MG
)@@G@@AS TERMINATOR     @F@#@]               CALL    MULINE         . UNPACK RMH
)@@G@@EMAINDER IMAGE    @E@]@[               LXM,U   A0,PRINTBUF    . SET BUFFMI
)@@G@@ER ADDR     @C@[@@           ER      APRINT$           . PRINT IT @F@@@#MJ
)@@G@@               CALL    MULINE         . UNPACK REMAINDER IMAGE    @G@#@]MK
)@@G@@               LSSL    A0,18          . LINE UP WORDCT, SPACE CTL=0     ML
)@@G@@@C@]@[               ER      APRINT$        . PRINT IT@#@[@@         ENDMM
)@@G@@REP   @G@@@#               LSSL    A0,18          . LINE UP WORDCT, SPACMN
)@@G@@E CTL=0     @E@#@]               LXM,U   A0,PRNTBUF     . SET BUFFER ADDMO
)@@G@@R     @#@]@[            ENDREP@D@[@@       ENDIF  . END OF CONTROL IMAGEMP
)@@G@@ BYPASS CHECK     @E@@@#               LXM,U   A0,PRNTBUF     . SET BUFFMQ
)@@G@@ER ADDR     @C@#@]               ER      APRINT$        . PRINT IT@H@]@[MR
)@@G@@         ENDIF                        . END OF CONTROL IMAGE BYPASS CHECMS
)@@G@@K     @[@[@@ ENDIF@C@@@#               ER      APRINT$        . PRINT ITMT
)@@G@@@#@#@]            ENDREP@]@]@[      ENDIF @]@[@@   ENDREP   @#@@@#      MU
)@@G@@      ENDREP@H@#@]         ENDIF                        . END OF CONTROLMV
)@@G@@ IMAGE BYPASS CHECK     @]@]@[   ENDREP   @^@[@@ ENDBEG               . MW
)@@G@@@H@@@#         ENDIF                        . END OF CONTROL IMAGE BYPASMX
)@@G@@S CHECK     @]@#@]      ENDIF @B@]@[ ENDBEG                             MY
)@@G@@  .   @[@[@@ .    @]@@@#      ENDIF @]@#@]   ENDREP   @[@]@[ .    @]@@@#MZ
)@@G@@   ENDREP   @B@#@] ENDBEG                               .   @B@@@# ENDBENA
)@@G@@G                               .   @[@@@] .    @ @@@@/. DRIVER TO TEST NB
)@@G@@THE ABOVE --@[@[@@.     @[@]@[ .    @[@[@@$(1)  @[@]@[$(1)  @[@[@@START NC
)@@G@@@[@@@] .    @[@]@[START @A@[@@        LA,U   A0,0400001     .     @[@@@]ND
)@@G@@$(1)  @B@]@[        LA,U    A0,0400001            .   @E@[@@        ER  NE
)@@G@@   PSR$           . TURN ON QUARTERWORD MODE    @[@@@]START @F@]@[      NF
)@@G@@  ER      PSR$                  . TURN ON QUARTERWORD MODE  @#@[@@ BEGINNG
)@@G@@ MAINPROGRAM@B@@@]        LA,U    A0,0400001            .   @#@]@[ BEGINNH
)@@G@@ MAINPROGRAM@#@[@@ DL A0,FILENAME   @F@@@]        ER      PSR$          NI
)@@G@@        . TURN ON QUARTERWORD MODE  @^@]@[   DL      A0,FILENAME  @]@[@@NJ
)@@G@@ LA,U A2,0  @#@@@] BEGIN MAINPROGRAM@#@]@[   LA,U    A2,0   @#@[@@ CALL NK
)@@G@@    PRINTIT @^@@@]   DL      A0,FILNAME   @#@]@[   CALL    PRINTIT@]@[@@NL
)@@G@@ ENDBEG     @#@@@]   LA,U    A2,0   @]@]@[ ENDBEG     @[@[@@$(0) .@#@@@]NM
)@@G@@   CALL    PRINTIT@B@]@[$(0)                                  .   @^@[@@NN
)@@G@@FILENAME 'PRINTFILE   ' @]@@@] ENDBEG     @B@]@[FILENAME        'PRINTFINO
)@@G@@LE            '   @B@@@]$(0)                                  .   @B@^@]NP
)@@G@@FILNAME 'PRINTFILE                    '   @^@@@^FILNAME 'PRINTFILE '    NQ
)@@G@@@H@@@@/.       ROUTINE TO MERGE 2 LINE IMAGES INTO A SINGLE ONE WITH BACNR
)@@G@@KSPACES     @F@[@@ .  IMAGE 'A' MAY BE AN INPUT IMAGE (WITHOUT BACKSPACENS
)@@G@@S), OR AN   @F@]@[ .  IMAGE 'A' MAY BE AN INPUT IMAGE (WITHOUT BACKSPACENT
)@@G@@S), OR AN   @G@[@@ .  IMAGE FORMED BY A PREVIOUS APPLICATION OF THIS ROUNU
)@@G@@TINE.  IMAGE 'B'  @G@]@[ .  IMAGE FORMED BY A PREVIOUS APPLICATION OF THNV
)@@G@@IS ROUTINE.  IMAGE 'B'  @A@[@@ .  IS ALWAYS A VIRGIN INPUT IMAGE  @F@@@]NW
)@@G@@ .  IMAGE 'A' MAY BE AN INPUT IMAGE (WITHOUT BACKSPACES), OR AN   @A@]@[NX
)@@G@@ .  IS ALWAYS A VIRGIN INPUT IMAGE  @[@[@@ .    @G@@@] .  IMAGE FORMED BNY
)@@G@@Y A PREVIOUS APPLICATION OF THIS ROUTINE.  IMAGE 'B'  @[@]@[ .    @[@[@@NZ
)@@G@@.     @A@@@] .  IS ALWAYS A VIRGIN INPUT IMAGE  @[@]@[ .    @^@[@@. REGIOA
)@@G@@STER DEFINITIONS--@[@@@] .    @ @]@[ . REGISTER DEFINITIONS--     @[@[@@OB
)@@G@@.     @[@@@] .    @[@]@[ .    @H@[@@ACHAR   EQU    A4             . REG OC
)@@G@@INTO WHICH CHARS OF A-IMAGE ARE FETCHED   @ @@@] . REGISTER DEFINITIONS-OD
)@@G@@-     @I@]@[ACHAR   EQU     A4                    . REG INTO WHICH CHARSOE
)@@G@@ OF A-IMAGE ARE FETC    @E@[@@AWORDP  EQU    A0             . WORD POINTOF
)@@G@@ER INTO A-IMAGE   @[@@@] .    @F@]@[AWORDP  EQU     A0                  OG
)@@G@@  . WORD POINTER INTO A-IMAGE @E@[@@ACHARP  EQU    A1             . CHAROH
)@@G@@ POINTER INTO A-IMAGE   @I@@@]ACHAR   EQU     A4                    . REOI
)@@G@@G INTO WHICH CHARS OF A-IMAGE ARE FETC    @F@]@[ACHARP  EQU     A1      OJ
)@@G@@              . CHAR POINTER INTO A-IMAGE @H@[@@BCHAR   EQU    A5       OK
)@@G@@      . REG INTO WHICH CHARS OF B-IMAGE ARE FETCHED   @F@@@]AWORDP  EQU OL
)@@G@@    A0                    . WORD POINTER INTO A-IMAGE @I@]@[BCHAR   EQU OM
)@@G@@    A5                    . REG INTO WHICH CHARS OF B-IMAGE ARE FETC    ON
)@@G@@@E@[@@BWORDP  EQU    X10            . WORD POINTER INTO B-IMAGE   @F@@@]OO
)@@G@@ACHARP  EQU     A1                    . CHAR POINTER INTO A-IMAGE @F@]@[OP
)@@G@@BWORDP  EQU     X10                   . WORD POINTER INTO B-IMAGE @E@[@@OQ
)@@G@@BCHARP  EQU    X11            . CHAR POINTER INTO B-IMAGE   @I@@@]BCHAR OR
)@@G@@  EQU     A5                    . REG INTO WHICH CHARS OF B-IMAGE ARE FEOS
)@@G@@TC    @F@]@[BCHARP  EQU     X11                   . CHAR POINTER INTO B-OT
)@@G@@IMAGE @H@[@@CCHAR   EQU    R2             . REG FROM WHICH CHARS ARE STAOU
)@@G@@SHED INTO C-IMAGE @F@@@]BWORDP  EQU     X10                   . WORD POIOV
)@@G@@NTER INTO B-IMAGE @I@]@[CCHAR   EQU     R2                    . REG FROMOW
)@@G@@ WHICH CHARS ARE STASHED INTO C-    @F@[@@CWORDP  EQU    X8             OX
)@@G@@. WORD POINTER INTO C-IMAGE (RESULT)@F@@@]BCHARP  EQU     X11           OY
)@@G@@        . CHAR POINTER INTO B-IMAGE @H@]@[CWORDP  EQU     X8            OZ
)@@G@@        . WORD POINTER INTO C-IMAGE (RESULT)    @E@[@@CCHARP  EQU    X9 PA
)@@G@@            . CHAR POINTER INTO C-IMAGE   @I@@@]CCHAR   EQU     R2      PB
)@@G@@              . REG FROM WHICH CHARS ARE STASHED INTO C-    @F@]@[CCHARPPC
)@@G@@  EQU     X9                    . CHAR POINTER INTO C-IMAGE @[@[@@.     PD
)@@G@@@H@@@]CWORDP  EQU     X8                    . WORD POINTER INTO C-IMAGE PE
)@@G@@(RESULT)    @[@]@[ .    @ @[@@. PROCS TO GET AND PUT CHARS  @F@@@]CCHARPPF
)@@G@@  EQU     X9                    . CHAR POINTER INTO C-IMAGE @ @]@[ . PROPG
)@@G@@CS TO GET AND PUT CHARS @[@[@@.     @[@@@] .    @[@]@[ .    @#@[@@P     PH
)@@G@@  PROC   .  @ @@@] . PROCS TO GET AND PUT CHARS @B@]@[P       PROC      PI
)@@G@@                    .   @#@[@@EMIT*   NAME   .  @[@@@] .    @B@]@[EMIT* PJ
)@@G@@  NAME                          .   @F@[@@        L      CCHAR,P(1,1)   PK
)@@G@@. MOVE CHAR FROM ITS REG TO STASHREG@B@@@]P       PROC                  PL
)@@G@@        .   @H@]@[        L       CCHAR,P(1,1)          . MOVE CHAR FROMPM
)@@G@@ ITS REG TO STASHREG    @F@[@@        CALL,CWORDP 0,CWORDP  . LINK TO C-PN
)@@G@@IMAGE STASH ROUTINE     @B@@@]EMIT*   NAME                          .   PO
)@@G@@@I@]@[        CALL,CWORDP                   0,CWORDP  . LINK TO C-IMAGE PP
)@@G@@STASH ROUTINE     @#@[@@        END    .  @H@@@]        L       CCHAR,P(PQ
)@@G@@1,1)          . MOVE CHAR FROM ITS REG TO STASHRG     @B@]@[        END PR
)@@G@@                          .   @[@[@@.     @I@@@]        CALL,CWORDP     PS
)@@G@@              0,CWORDP  . LINK TO C-IMAGE STASH ROUTINE     @[@]@[ .    PT
)@@G@@@#@[@@P       PROC   .  @B@@@]        END                           .   PU
)@@G@@@B@]@[P       PROC                          .   @#@[@@GRAB*   NAME   .  PV
)@@G@@@[@@@] .    @B@]@[GRAB*   NAME                          .   @E@[@@LINK  PW
)@@G@@  EQU    AWORDP*(P(1,1)=ACHAR)+BWORDP*(P(1,1)=BCHAR) .@B@@@]P       PROCPX
)@@G@@                          .   @F@]@[LINK    EQU     AWORDP*(P(1,1)=ACHARPY
)@@G@@)+BWORDP*(P(1,1)=BCHAR)  .    @F@[@@        CALL,LINK 0,LINK      . LINKPZ
)@@G@@ TO APPROPRIATE PICKUP ROUTINE@B@@@]GRAB*   NAME                        QA
)@@G@@  .   @I@]@[        CALL,LINK                     0,LINK  . LINK TO APPRQB
)@@G@@OPRIATE PICKUP ROUTI    @#@[@@        END    .  @F@@@]LINK    EQU     AWQC
)@@G@@ORDP*(P(1,1)=ACHAR)+BWORDP*(P(1,1)=BCHAR)  .    @B@]@[        END       QD
)@@G@@                    .   @[@[@@.     @I@@@]        CALL,LINK             QE
)@@G@@        0,LINK  . LINK TO APPROPRIATE PICKUP ROUTI    @[@]@[ .    @]@[@@QF
)@@G@@$(1)    .   @B@@@]        END                           .   @B@]@[$(1)  QG
)@@G@@                                .   @[@[@@.     @[@@@] .    @[@]@[ .    QH
)@@G@@@D@[@@. ENTER WITH A0,A1,A2 = ADDR OF A, B, AND C-IMAGES    @B@@@]$(1)  QI
)@@G@@                                .   @D@]@[ . ENTER WITH A0,A1,A2 = ADDR QJ
)@@G@@OF A, B, AND C-IMAGES   @[@[@@.     @D@@@] . ENTER WITH A0,A1,A2 = ADDR QK
)@@G@@OF A, B, AND C-IMAGES   @[@]@[ .    @]@[@@MERGE*   .  @[@@@] .    @B@]@[QL
)@@G@@MERGE*                                .   @A@[@@ BEGIN SUBROUTINE SAVE,XQM
)@@G@@8,X9,X10    @B@@@]MERGE*                                .   @A@]@[ BEGINQN
)@@G@@ SUBROUTINE SAVE,X8,X9,X10    @F@[@@        L      CWORDP,A2      . SET QO
)@@G@@UP ADDR OF MERGED IMAGE BUFFER@A@@@] BEGIN SUBROUTINE SAVE,X8,X9,X10    QP
)@@G@@@H@]@[   L       CWORDP,A2                  . SET UP ADDR OF MERGED IMAGQQ
)@@G@@E BUFFER    @C@[@@        L      BWORDP,A1      . AND OF B-IMAGE  @H@@@]QR
)@@G@@   L       CWORDP,A2                  . SET UP ADDR OF MERGED IMAGE BUFFQS
)@@G@@ER    @D@]@[   L       BWORDP,A1                  . AND OF B-IMAGE@H@[@@QT
)@@G@@                              . NOTE- A-ADDR ALREADY IS IN CORRECT REGISQU
)@@G@@TER   @D@@@]   L       BWORDP,A1                  . AND OF B-IMAGE@C@]@[QV
)@@G@@   . NOTE- A-ADDR ALREADY IS IN CORRECT REGISTER@E@[@@        CALL,ACHARQW
)@@G@@P GETA4     . INITIALIZE A-IMAGE FETCH    @C@@@]   . NOTE- A-ADDR ALREADQX
)@@G@@Y IS IN CORRECT REGISTER@G@]@[   CALL,ACHARP                        GETAQY
)@@G@@4  . INITIALIZE A-IMAGE FETCH @D@[@@        CALL,BCHARP GETA5     . AND QZ
)@@G@@B-IMAGE FETCH     @G@@@]   CALL,ACHARP                        GETA4  . IRA
)@@G@@NITIALIZE A-IMAGE FETCH @F@]@[   CALL,BCHARP                        GETARB
)@@G@@5  . AND B-IMAGE FETCH  @D@[@@        CALL,CCHARP PUTR2     . AND C-IMAGRC
)@@G@@E STASH     @F@@@]   CALL,BCHARP                        GETA5  . AND B-IRD
)@@G@@MAGE FETCH  @F@]@[   CALL,CCHARP                        PUTR2  . AND C-IRE
)@@G@@MAGE STASH  @E@[@@   GRAB    ACHAR          . PRIME WITH 1ST CHAR OF 'A'RF
)@@G@@ IMAGE@F@@@]   CALL,CCHARP                        PUTR2  . AND C-IMAGE SRG
)@@G@@TASH  @G@]@[   GRAB    ACHAR                      . PRIME WITH 1ST CHAR RH
)@@G@@OF 'A' IMAGE@A@[@@   REPEAT WHILE ACHAR,NEQ,EOICHR   .@G@@@]   GRAB    ARI
)@@G@@CHAR                      . PRIME WITH 1ST CHAR OF 'A' IMAGE@B@]@[   REPRJ
)@@G@@EAT WHILE ACHAR,NEQ,EOICHR      .   @ @[@@     GRAB    BCHAR          . RK
)@@G@@@B@@@]   REPEAT WHILE ACHAR,NEQ,EOICHR      .   @B@]@[      GRAB    BCHARL
)@@G@@R                   .   @ @[@@   ESCAPE WHEN BCHAR,EQ,EOICHR@B@@@]      RM
)@@G@@GRAB    BCHAR                   .   @ @]@[   ESCAPE WHEN BCHAR,EQ,EOICHRRN
)@@G@@@A@[@@     REPEAT UNTIL ACHAR,EQ,EOICHR   @ @@@]   ESCAPE WHEN BCHAR,EQ,RO
)@@G@@EOICHR@A@]@[      REPEAT UNTIL ACHAR,EQ,EOICHR  @ @[@@       EMIT   ACHARP
)@@G@@R          .@A@@@]      REPEAT UNTIL ACHAR,EQ,EOICHR  @B@]@[         EMIRQ
)@@G@@T    ACHAR                .   @ @[@@       GRAB   ACHAR          .@B@@@]RR
)@@G@@         EMIT    ACHAR                .   @B@]@[         GRAB    ACHAR  RS
)@@G@@              .   @#@[@@     ENDREP .     @B@@@]         GRAB    ACHAR  RT
)@@G@@              .   @B@]@[      ENDREP                          .   @B@[@@RU
)@@G@@   OTHERWISE . THERE'S A B-CHAR TO PROCESS@B@@@]      ENDREP            RV
)@@G@@              .   @G@]@[   OTHERWISE                          . THERE'S RW
)@@G@@A B-CHAR TO PROCESS     @G@[@@     IF ACHAR,EQ,BCHAR OR BCHAR,EQ,ASPACE RX
)@@G@@THEN . THE B-CHAR IS TRIVIAL  @G@@@]   OTHERWISE                        RY
)@@G@@  . THERE'S A B-CHAR TO PROCESS     @G@]@[      IF ACHAR,EQ,BCHAR OR BCHRZ
)@@G@@AR,EQ,ASPACE THEN . THE B-CHAR IS TRIVIAL @A@[@@       REPEAT WHILE ACHASA
)@@G@@R,NEQ,EOICHR@G@@@]      IF ACHAR,EQ,BCHAR OR BCHAR,EQ,ASPACE THEN . THE SB
)@@G@@B-CHAR IS TRIVIAL @B@]@[         REPEAT WHILE ACHAR,NEQ,EOICHR    @^@[@@SC
)@@G@@         EMIT    ACHAR  @B@@@]         REPEAT WHILE ACHAR,NEQ,EOICHR    SD
)@@G@@@ @]@[            EMIT    ACHAR     @^@[@@         GRAB    ACHAR  @ @@@]SE
)@@G@@            EMIT    ACHAR     @ @]@[            GRAB    ACHAR     @A@[@@SF
)@@G@@       ESCAPE WHEN ACHAR,NEQ,ASCIBS @ @@@]            GRAB    ACHAR     SG
)@@G@@@B@]@[         ESCAPE WHEN ACHAR,NEQ,ASCIBS     @E@[@@       OTHERWISE .SH
)@@G@@ WE HAVE NOT YET REACHED END OF A-FIELD   @B@@@]         ESCAPE WHEN ACHSI
)@@G@@AR,NEQ,ASCIBS     @H@]@[         OTHERWISE                    . WE HAVE SJ
)@@G@@NOT YET REACHED END OF A-FIELD@E@[@@         EMIT    ACHAR             .SK
)@@G@@ OUTPUT THE BACKSPACE   @H@@@]         OTHERWISE                    . WESL
)@@G@@ HAVE NOT YET REACHED END OF A-FIELD@E@]@[            EMIT    ACHAR     SM
)@@G@@        . OUTPUT THE BACKSPACE@E@[@@         GRAB    ACHAR          . GESN
)@@G@@T THE CHAR AFTER IT     @E@@@]            EMIT    ACHAR             . OUSO
)@@G@@TPUT THE BACKSPACE@F@]@[            GRAB    ACHAR             . GET THE SP
)@@G@@CHAR AFTER IT     @#@[@@       ENDREP     @F@@@]            GRAB    ACHASQ
)@@G@@R             . GET THE CHAR AFTER IT     @#@]@[         ENDREP   @D@[@@SR
)@@G@@     ELSE   . THE CHAR IN THE B-IMAGE IS NON-TRIVIAL  @#@@@]         ENDSS
)@@G@@REP   @H@]@[      ELSE                            . THE CHAR IN THE B-IMST
)@@G@@AGE IS NON-TRIVIAL@G@[@@       IF ACHAR,EQ,ASPACE THEN . THE A-CHAR IS TSU
)@@G@@RIVIAL AND B CAN ZAP IT @H@@@]      ELSE                            . THSV
)@@G@@E CHAR IN THE B-IMAGE IS NON-TRIVIAL@H@]@[         IF ACHAR,EQ,ASPACE THSW
)@@G@@EN      . THE A-CHAR IS TRIVIAL AND B CAN ZAP IT@D@[@@         EMIT    BSX
)@@G@@CHAR          . PUT OUT THE B CHAR  @H@@@]         IF ACHAR,EQ,ASPACE THSY
)@@G@@EN      . THE A-CHAR IS TRIVIAL AND B CAN ZAP IT@E@]@[            EMIT  SZ
)@@G@@  BCHAR             . PUT OUT THE B CHAR  @F@[@@         GRAB    ACHAR  TA
)@@G@@        . AND PRIME AHEAD WITH NEXT A     @E@@@]            EMIT    BCHATB
)@@G@@R             . PUT OUT THE B CHAR  @G@]@[            GRAB    ACHAR     TC
)@@G@@        . AND PRIME AHEAD WITH NEXT A     @D@[@@       ELSE   . B MUST BTD
)@@G@@E SORTED INTO THE A-STRING    @G@@@]            GRAB    ACHAR           TE
)@@G@@  . AND PRIME AHEAD WITH NEXT A     @H@]@[         ELSE                 TF
)@@G@@        . B MUST BE SORTED INTO THE A-STRING    @H@[@@         REPEAT WHTG
)@@G@@ILE BCHAR,GT,ACHAR . I.E., B FOLLOWS A IN THE OUTPUT IMAGE  @H@@@]      TH
)@@G@@   ELSE                         . B MUST BE SORTED INTO THE A-STRING    TI
)@@G@@@I@]@[            REPEAT WHILE BCHAR,GT,ACHAR . I.E., B FOLLOWS A IN THETJ
)@@G@@ OUTPUT IMAGE     @E@[@@           EMIT    ACHAR          . PUT OUT THE TK
)@@G@@ACHARACTER  @I@@@]            REPEAT WHILE BCHAR,GT,ACHAR . I.E., B FOLLTL
)@@G@@OWS A IN THE OUTPUT IMAGE     @F@]@[               EMIT    ACHAR        TM
)@@G@@  . PUT OUT THE ACHARACTER    @D@[@@           L       ACHAR,ASCIBS   . TN
)@@G@@AND FOLLOW IT     @F@@@]               EMIT    ACHAR          . PUT OUT TO
)@@G@@THE ACHARACTER    @D@]@[               L       ACHAR,ASCIBS   . AND FOLLTP
)@@G@@OW IT @D@[@@           EMIT    ACHAR          . WITH A BACKSPACE  @D@@@]TQ
)@@G@@               L       ACHAR,ASCIBS   . AND FOLLOW IT @E@]@[            TR
)@@G@@   EMIT    ACHAR          . WITH A BACKSPACE    @H@[@@           GRAB   TS
)@@G@@ ACHAR          . THEN GET CHAR AFTER THE A-DATA IMAGE CHAR @E@@@]      TT
)@@G@@         EMIT    ACHAR          . WITH A BACKSPACE    @I@]@[            TU
)@@G@@   GRAB    ACHAR          . THEN GET CHAR AFTER THE A-DATA IMAGE CHA    TV

)@@G@@HE A-FIELD  @I@@@]               GRAB    ACHAR          . THEN GET CHAR TX
)@@G@@AFTER THE A-DATA IMAGE CHA    @I@]@[            ESCAPE WHEN ACHAR,NEQ,ASTY
)@@G@@CIBS . WHICH SIGNALS THE END OF THE A-FIELD     @G@[@@           EMIT   TZ

)@@G@@ THE A'S    @F@[@@         OTHERWISE . WE HAVE NOT REACHED THE END OF THUD
)@@G@@E AFIELD    @H@@@]               EMIT    BCHAR          . PUT OUT THE B UE

)@@G@@ HAVE NOT REACHED THE END OF THE AFIEL    @G@[@@           GRAB    ACHARUG

)@@G@@         GRAB    ACHAR          . GET 1ST A CHAR AFTER THE BACKSPACE    UL
)@@G@@@G@]@[            ATEND                     . WHEN B GOES INTERIOR TO THUM
)@@G@@E A'S @C@[@@           EMIT    BCHAR          . SPLAT IT OUT@G@@@]      UN
)@@G@@      ATEND                     . WHEN B GOES INTERIOR TO THE A'S @D@]@[UO
)@@G@@               EMIT    BCHAR          . SPLAT IT OUT  @F@[@@           IUP
)@@G@@F ACHAR,NEQ,EOICHR THEN . THERE IS MORE TO THE A-IMAGE@D@@@]            UQ
)@@G@@   EMIT    BCHAR          . SPLAT IT OUT  @G@]@[               IF ACHAR,UR
)@@G@@NEQ,EOICHR THEN . THERE IS MORE TO THE A-IMAGE  @B@[@@             L    US
)@@G@@   BCHAR,ASCIBS   .     @G@@@]               IF ACHAR,NEQ,EOICHR THEN . UT
)@@G@@THERE IS MORE TO THE A-IMAGE  @B@]@[                  L       BCHAR,ASCIUU
)@@G@@BS  . @D@[@@             REPEAT . UNTIL THE A-STRING IS EXHAUSTED @B@@@]UV
)@@G@@                  L       BCHAR,ASCIBS  . @G@]@[                  REPEATUW
)@@G@@              . UNTIL THE A-STRING IS EXHAUSTED @G@[@@               EMIUX

)@@G@@                  OTHERWISE           . THERE ARE MORE CHARS IN THIS A-SVP

)@@G@@CANT ONE    @^@[@@             ENDREP     @G@@@]                     GRAVR

)@@G@@ENDREP@#@[@@           ENDIF  @^@@@]                  ENDREP@^@]@[      VT

)@@G@@     ENDIF  @#@@@]         ENDIF    @]@]@[      ENDIF @C@[@@   ATEND  . VX

)@@G@@3MULTIBANKING CAPABILITIES    @#@@@@2BASING A BANK    @E@@@@      WITHINAH
)@@G@@ THE CONTEXT OF THE EXEC8 SYSTEM, THE PROCESS OF@F@[@@ MAKING A PROGRAM AI
)@@G@@BANK VISIBLE TO A PROGRAM IS CALLED 'BASING'.   @F@@@[ MAKING A PROGRAM AJ
)@@G@@BANK VISIBLE TO A PROGRAM IS CALLED 'BASING'.   @D@@@@ STRUC$ PROVIDES FAK
)@@G@@EATURES BY WHICH ONE MAY BASE A BANK@E@@@@ AND SIMULTANEOUSLY TRANSFER CAL
)@@G@@ONTROL TO A SUBROUTINE, OR    @E@@@@ BASE A BANK WITHOUT CONTROL TRANSFEAM
)@@G@@R.  THE FORMER METHOD   @D@@@@ IS USUALLY USED WHEN THE SUBROUTINE TO BEAN
)@@G@@ CALLED IS  @D@@@@ PHYSICALLY LOCATED IN THE NEW BANK (ALTHOUGH THIS    AO
)@@G@@@D@@@@ IS NOT ACTUALLY REQUIRED). THE LATTER METHOD IS USED @E@@@@ WHEN AP
)@@G@@ONE WISHES TO REFERENCE THE NEWLY BASED BANK AS DATA. @C@@@@     THE STAAQ
)@@G@@TEMENT FORMS FOR BASING A BANK ARE: @[@@@@0     @E@@@@0 BASE(,<X>) <TYPEAR
)@@G@@>(,<BDISPEC>) . BASE WITHOUT CONTROL XFER @F@@@@0 CALL(,<X>) <NAME> BASIAS
)@@G@@NG,<TYPE>(,<BDISPEC>) . WITH CONTROL XFER @F@[@@0   CASENTRY CALLING <NAAT
)@@G@@ME> BASING,<TYPE>(,<BDISPEC>) . WITH XFER @F@@@[0 CASENTRY   CALLING <NAAU
)@@G@@ME> BASING,<TYPE>(,<BDISPEC>) . WITH XFER @[@@@@0     @]@@@@0WHERE:     AV
)@@G@@@]@[@@COLUMN 17   @]@@@[COLUMN 17   @F@@@@     <X>        IS THE LINKAGEAW
)@@G@@ INDEX REGISTER. DEFAULT IS X11.    @B@@@@     BASING     IS A REQUIRED AX
)@@G@@KEYWORD     @D@@@@     <TYPE>     IS ONE OF THE KEYWORDS IBANK OR DBANK AY
)@@G@@@E@@@@     <BDISPEC>  IS A COMPLETE SPECIFICATION (I.E. U,X,J)    @C@@@@AZ
)@@G@@                FOR THE BDI OF THE TARGET BANK. @E@@@@                IFBA
)@@G@@ <BDISPEC> IS OMITTED, STRUC$ ASSUMES THAT@D@@@@                THE INCRBB
)@@G@@EMENT PORTION OF THE LINKAGE  @E@@@@                REGISTER HAS BEEN ALBC
)@@G@@READY INITIALIZED BY    @A@@@@                THE PROGRAMMER.     @[@@@@BD
)@@G@@0     @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @D@@@@      IN THE SUBROUTINE CALLING FORMS, ANYBE
)@@G@@ EXPRESSION @E@@@@ MAY APPEAR IN THE POSITION OF THE KEYBORD 'BASING'. IBF
)@@G@@F THIS@C@@@@ EXPRESSION EVALUATES TO ANYTHING OTHER THAN    @E@@@@ THE VBG
)@@G@@ALUE OF THE 'BASING' KEYWORD, THE BASING SPECIFICATION@E@@@@ WILL BE IGNBH
)@@G@@ORED, AND A NORMAL SUBROUTINE CALL WILL RESULT. @#@@@[2DEBASING A BANK  BI
)@@G@@@E@@@[      THE PROCESS OF REMOVING A BBANK FROM VISIBILITY TO    @C@@@[BJ
)@@G@@ THE EXECUTING PROGRAM IS DONE BY BASING A NEW  @E@@@[ BANK WHICH REPLACBK
)@@G@@ES THE OLD ONE. IT IS POSSIBLE, THEREFORE @E@@@[ TO PERFORM THIS OPERATIBL
)@@G@@ON WITH THE PREVIOUSLY DESCRIBED    @E@@@[ PROCEDURES FOR BASING A NEW BBM
)@@G@@ANK.   THERE IS, HOWEVER, A   @B@@@[ CLASS OF SUBROUTINES WHICH SHOULD EBN
)@@G@@XIT BY@F@@@[ REESTABLISHING A BANK WHICH WAS VISIBLE BEFORE THEY WERE CABO
)@@G@@LLED. @E@@@[ THESE SUBROUTINES ARE CALLED WITH THE BDI OF THE BANK TO BEBP
)@@G@@@F@@@[ RESTORED IN THE INCREMENT PORTION OF THEIR LINKAGE REGISTER.     BQ
)@@G@@@G@@@[ USUALLY THIS BDI IS DEPOSITED AUTOMATICALLY BECAUSE THE SUBROUTINBR
)@@G@@E     @D@@@[ HAS BEEN CALLED BY A 'CALL' OR 'CASENTRY' WITH BASING@D@@@[BS
)@@G@@ SPECIFIED, BUT THIS IS NOT STRICTLY NECESSARY. THE   @G@@@[ DISTINGUISHBT
)@@G@@ING FEATURE OF THESE SUBROUTINES IS THAT THEY MUST RESTORE  @^@@@[ SOME BU
)@@G@@BANK UPON EXIT.   @E@@@[      A SUBROUTINE WHICH MUST RESTORE A BANK UPOBV
)@@G@@N EXIT IS   @E@@@[ INDICATED BY USING ONE OF THE KEYWORDS 'LIJSUB' OR 'LBW
)@@G@@DJSUB'@E@@@[ IN PLACE OF THE WORD 'SUBROUTINE' ON THE BEGIN STATEMENT.  BX
)@@G@@@D@@@[ IN ALL OTHER RESPECTS, A BANK RESTORING SUBROUTINE IS@B@@@[ CODEDBY
)@@G@@ IDENTICALLY TO A NORMAL SUBROUTINE.@^@@@[3LIMITATIONS ON LOOPS   @E@@@[BZ
)@@G@@      IN THE SECTION ON LOOPING IN THE MAIN BODY OF THE     @D@@@[ STRUCCA
)@@G@@$ MANUAL, IT IS NOTED THAT LOOPS FOR WHICH THE  @E@@@[ VALUE OF THE LOOPCB
)@@G@@ CONTROL VARIABLE PASSES THROUGH ZERO ARE @D@@@[ FORBIDDEN.  IT SHOULD BCC
)@@G@@E NOTED THAT THIS CONDITION   @E@@@[ MAY OCCUR EITHER EXPLICITLY OR IMPLCD
)@@G@@ICITLY. THE IMPLICIT    @F@@@[ CASE ARISES BECAUSE STRUC$ ITSELF MAY NEECE
)@@G@@D TO MANIPULATE THE     @E@@@[ VALUE OF THE LOOP CONTROL VARIABLE INTERNCF
)@@G@@ALLY. IT MANIFESTS@F@@@[ ITSELF WHEN THE STARTING VALUE, I.E. THE 'FROM'CG
)@@G@@ SPECIFICATION    @G@@@[ IS ZERO. THIS CASE USED TO RESULT IN BAD CODE BCH
)@@G@@EING GENERATED WITHOUT  @H@@@[ ANY INDICATION OF THIS. IT NOW RESULTS INCI
)@@G@@ A DIAGNOSTIC (WHEN THE VALUE IS    @ @@@[ KNOWN, I.E. IS IMMEDIATE).   CJ

)@@G@@-2212,2314  STRUC$@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. DECODE A U-FIELD INTO MD

)@@G@@  DEF @^@@@@G$JBIT(1) EQU 1*/29     @^@@@@G$JBIT(2) EQU 1*/28     @^@@@@MI

)@@G@@@]@@@@G$$DCU* NAME@E@@@@I       EQU     Q(1,1)                . GET FIELMN

)@@G@@UBFIELD (U-SPEC)  @G@@@@N       EQU     Q(0,1)                . LEVEL OFMP
)@@G@@ P (NO OF ASTERISKS)    @D@@@@. NOTE: IF IV(1)<0, THEN IT CAN'T HAVE BEEMQ
)@@G@@N EQUF'D    @E@@@@IV(1)   EQU     +P(I,J)               . GET INITIAL VAMR
)@@G@@LUE   @F@@@@JAY(1)  EQU     0                     . ASSUME NO EQUF'D J-SMS

)@@G@@J     @D@@@@  ,K DO 4                             ; FOR ALL J-BITS@E@@@@MU

)@@G@@BIT(K)  . FOLD INTO RESULT    @G@@@@IV(1)   EQU     IV(1)-XRG(1)        ND

)@@G@@1)*/-18 . GET COMPLETE X-SPEC @F@@@@U16     EQU     (JAY(1)<016)++(XRG(1NF
)@@G@@)>0)++P(I,*J)++P(I,*J+1) .    @F@@@@HIB(1)  EQU     0                   NG

)@@G@@@E@@@@/. PROC DEFINITION, FLAG RESET FOR STRUCTURED PROC PACKAGE  @[@@@@XL
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@G$LCTR(1) EQU  2                      . DEFAULT LOCN CTR FORXM
)@@G@@ INTERNAL STORAGE @H@@@@G$DFLG  EQU    - 1                    . USE TO FXN
)@@G@@ORCE D-FLAGS FOR DIAGNOSTICS  @I@@@@G$JXMA  EQUF   0,017,016            XO
)@@G@@  . FORM FOR MASKING OFF ALL BUT JX IMMEDIAT    @H@@@@G$JMSK  EQUF   0,0XP
)@@G@@,016                . FORM FOR TESTING IMMEDIATE J-VALUES   @H@@@@G$UMSKXQ
)@@G@@  EQUF   *0177777,*0            . FORM TO MASK OFF ALL BUT IMMEDIATE U  XR
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$NOFO  FORM   36                     . FORM TO GET RID OF OTHER FXS
)@@G@@ORMS  @I@@@@G$$FJA  FORM   6,8,4,2,16             . FORM FOR INSTRS USINXT
)@@G@@G JA FIELD (E.G. JGD    @F@@@@G$$IMU    FORM    6,4,4,4,18          . FOXU
)@@G@@RM FOR IMMEDIATE U-SPECS@[@@@@.     @H@@@@STRUC$DEF* PROC     *0,0      XV
)@@G@@        . IF @ASM, DEFINE THESE BY XPLICIT CALL @B@@@@          END     XW
)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@@.     @I@@@@P       PROC   *2             XX
)@@G@@        . PF'S : DBANK-LOCNCTR,DISPLAY-OCTAL-FLAG     @E@@@@STRUC$* NAMEXY
)@@G@@                          . NORMAL ENTRY POINT  @G@@@@ DO 0=0=0 , STRUC$XZ
)@@G@@OMN                 . IF MASM, INCLUDE OMN IF NEEDED  @F@@@@ DO 0=0=1 , YA
)@@G@@STRUC$DEF                 . IF @ASM, READ IN HUGE DEF @E@@@@ DO P(1)>0 ,YB
)@@G@@G$LCTR*(1) EQU P(1,1)     . SET DATA LOCN CTR   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. USAGYC
)@@G@@E OF OVERALL COUNTER ARRAY G$CTR:   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.       1 = COUNT YD
)@@G@@OF TOTAL NO BLOX (ALL KINDS EXCEPT BEGIN) @A@@@@.       2 = GLOBAL ADDREYE
)@@G@@SS FLOAT    @A@@@@.       3 = ARG PUSHDOWN COUNTER    @C@@@@.       4 = YF
)@@G@@COUNTER OF TOTAL NO CALLS TO G$$TST @B@@@@.       5 = GLOBAL NESTING DEPYG
)@@G@@TH COUNTER  @D@@@@.       6 = LOGICAL FOR GLOBAL PASS: TRUE ON PASS 1   YH
)@@G@@@D@@@@.       7 = LOGICAL FOR GLOBAL PASS: TRUE ON PASS 2   @[@@@@.     YI
)@@G@@@D@@@@K DO     5 ,G$CTR*(K) EQU 0           . CLEAR COUNTERS@[@@@@.     YJ
)@@G@@@G@@@@. NOW DEFINE SPECIAL THINGS DEPENDENT UPON WHICH ASSEMBLER PASS THYK
)@@G@@IS IS @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$CTR*(6) EQU 1-G$CTR(6)            . SET FLAG: YL
)@@G@@ON IF ASSEMBLER PASS 1  @D@@@@G$CTR*(7) EQU      1-G$CTR(6)       . ON IYM
)@@G@@F PASS 2    @G@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , BRIEF                  . ON PASS 2, CLEYN
)@@G@@AN UP THE LISTING @D@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , END                    . THEN GETYO
)@@G@@ OUT  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. -------- PASS 1 ONLY BEYOND THIS POINT -------YP
)@@G@@-     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$MASM*   EQU       0=0=0           YQ
)@@G@@  . 0=>@ASM, 1=>@MASM   @H@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 ,G$AMPR*    EQU      &(5)=-2 YR
)@@G@@. TRUE IF RELOCATION FUNC AVAILABLE @I@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,G$AMPR*   EQU   YS
)@@G@@    1     . IF MASM, WE HAVE A RELOCATION FUNCTION    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@YT
)@@G@@          G$$CLD                      . DECLARE OUR 'CALL' PROC   @F@@@@YU
)@@G@@ DO G$MASM , $INSERT ;                . IF @MASM, FORGET ABOUT... @E@@@@YV
)@@G@@   'G$$CLD* $DELETE','STRUC$DEF* $DELETE' . SOME OLD PROCS  @E@@@@ DO G$YW
)@@G@@UOM=1 , END    . STOP HERE IF NO NEED FOR DUMMY PROCS @F@@@@ DO (G$MASM=YX
)@@G@@0)**(G$AMPR=1) , END      . IF UOM ASM, FORGET PROCS  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@YY
)@@G@@P         PROC      *0,0              . DUMMY PROCS   @#@@@@RESUME** NAMYZ
)@@G@@E     @#@@@@BRIEF**  NAME     @G@@@@         END                        ZA
)@@G@@  . END OF DUMMY INTERNAL PROC DEFN @[@@@@.     @G@@@@          END     ZB
)@@G@@                    . END DEFN OF MASTER MAGIC PROC   @ @@@@/. ***** DIAZC
)@@G@@GNOSTICS *****    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. FIELDS IN ERROR MESSAGZD
)@@G@@E FORM ARE: @C@@@@.    FIELD 1: TYPE OF CURRENTLY ACTIVE BLOCK    @E@@@@ZE
)@@G@@.             TYPES ARE 1=>BEGIN, 2=>IF, 3=>CASE, 4=>REPEAT @A@@@@.     ZF
)@@G@@     2: CURRENT NESTING DEPTH @F@@@@.          3: MESSAGE CLASS (0=LOCN ZG
)@@G@@CTR, 1=SYNTAX, 2=STRUCTURE)   @^@@@@.          4: ERROR TYPE@ @@@@.     ZH
)@@G@@     5: ERROR SUBTYPE   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. LOCATION COUNTER ERRORS (MESZI
)@@G@@SAGE CLASS=0) ARE SIGNALLED WHEN    @E@@@@. SOME CODE PREVIOUS TO THE POZJ
)@@G@@INT OF THE MESSAGE GENERATES  @F@@@@. A DIFFERENT NUMBER OF INSTRUCTIONSZK
)@@G@@ ON ASSEMBLER PASSES ONE AND  @F@@@@. TWO (ASSEMBLER D-FLAG). AT THE POIZL
)@@G@@NT OF DETECTION, STRUC$ WILL  @F@@@@. ATTEMPT TO FORESTALL SPURIOUS ERROZM
)@@G@@RS OF THIS TYPE IN THE CODE   @G@@@@. WHICH FOLLOWS BY FORCING THE LOCATZN
)@@G@@ION COUNTER TO WHAT IT BELIEVES     @F@@@@. THE CORRECT VALUE SHOULD BE.ZO
)@@G@@ THE ERROR TYPE AND SUBTYPE FIELDS  @F@@@@. ARE INTERNAL SERIAL NUMBERS,ZP
)@@G@@ AND HAVE NO SPECIAL SIGNIFICANCE.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. FOR SYNTAX ERRORZQ
)@@G@@S (MESSAGE CLASS=1), ERROR TYPES AND SUBTYPES ARE:    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@ZR
)@@G@@.    1,X => ERROR IN SPECIFICATION OF TEST@C@@@@.     ,01      UNRECOGNIZS
)@@G@@ZEABLE TYPE OF TEST     @B@@@@.     ,02      UNRECOGNIZEABLE KEYWORD    ZT
)@@G@@@B@@@@.    2,X => ERROR IN <VARY> SPECIFICATION @C@@@@.     ,01      OFFZU
)@@G@@SET REQUIRES IMMEDIATE 'BY'   @E@@@@.     ,02      LOOKFOR FORMAT REQUIRZV
)@@G@@ES 'BY' SPECIFICATION   @D@@@@.     ,03      REQUIRED FROM, TO, OR BY SPZW
)@@G@@EC MISSING  @E@@@@.     ,04      LOOP CONTROL VARIABLE PASSES THROUGH ZEZX
)@@G@@RO    @E@@@@.     ,05      SIGN OF BY CONFLICTS WITH SIGN OF TO-FROM    ZY
)@@G@@@F@@@@.     ,06      EXPLICIT SENSE (UP/DOWN) CONFLICTS WITH BY, TO-FROMZZ
)@@G@@@D@@@@.     ,07      REQUIRED 'BY' SPECIFICATION NOT GIVEN  @C@@@@.     AA
)@@G@@,010     BAD KEYWORD FOLLOWING 'LOOKFOR'  @G@@@@.     ,011     SPECIFIC AB
)@@G@@LOOP INSTR CONFLICTS WITH TO/FROM/BY/FOR SPEC   @ @@@@.    3,X => PARAMEAC
)@@G@@TER ERROR   @D@@@@.     ,01      CASEREGISTER NOT OVERLAPPED (A0-A3)    AD
)@@G@@@D@@@@.     ,02      REQUIRED REGISTER SPECIFICATION MISSING@D@@@@.     AE
)@@G@@,03      INCORRECT NUMBER OF FIELDS ON 'IF'     @D@@@@.     ,04      MISAF
)@@G@@SING 'WHEN' ON ESCAPE STATEMENT     @F@@@@.     ,05      MINIMUM SPECIFIAG
)@@G@@ED CASE NOT ZERO (CALLING OPTION)   @F@@@@.     ,06      ALL CASE VALUESAH
)@@G@@ NOT SPECIFIED (CALLING OPTION)     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. FOR STRUCTURE ERAI
)@@G@@RORS (MESSAGE CLASS=2) , TYPES AND SUBTYPES ARE:@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.    1AJ
)@@G@@,X => NESTING ERROR     @F@@@@.     ,01      TOO MANY OR TOO FEW END STAAK
)@@G@@TMENTS IN PREVIOUS BLOCK@F@@@@.     ,02      MISSING END IN PREVIOUS BLOAL
)@@G@@CK MAY CAUSE D-FLAGS    @E@@@@.     ,03      STATEMENT CANNOT APPEAR IN AM
)@@G@@CURRENT BLOCK TYPE@F@@@@.              EITHER THE END STATEMENT FOR THE AN
)@@G@@PREVIOUS BLOCK OR @G@@@@.              THE START STATEMENT FOR THE CURREAO
)@@G@@NT BLOCK IS MISSING     @D@@@@.    2,X => INCONSISTENT LOGIC (STATEMENTSAP
)@@G@@ OR FIELDS) @G@@@@.     ,01      ESCAPE INVALID IF BOTH WHILE/LOOKFOR ANAQ
)@@G@@D UNTIL ARE GIVEN @E@@@@.     ,02      OTHERWISE STMNT MEANINGLESS, NO EAR
)@@G@@SCAPE GIVEN @F@@@@.     ,03      ATEND UNREACHABLE, NO TESTS APPEARED ONAS
)@@G@@ REPEAT     @F@@@@.     ,05      NOFIND CODE ILLEGAL WITH CALLING OPTIONAT
)@@G@@ (CASE)     @C@@@@.     ,06      REMOTE CALL TO NON-REMOTE BLOCK  @ @@@@AU
)@@G@@.    3,X => MISCELLANEOUS     @E@@@@.     ,01      ATTEMPT TO CHANGE LOCAV
)@@G@@ATION COUNTERS WITHIN   @F@@@@.              A BLOCK. BLOCKS MUST BE WHOAW
)@@G@@LLY CONTAINED WITHIN    @F@@@@.              A SINGLE BANK. SWITCHING BEAX
)@@G@@TWEEN BANKS MUST BE     @D@@@@.              ACCOMPLISHED VIA A SUBROUTIAY
)@@G@@NE CALL     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@          DEF     @H@@@@G$ERFO    FORM    AZ
)@@G@@  3,6,3,12,12     . A DISTINCTIVE FORM FOR ERROR MESSAGES   @#@@@@P     BA
)@@G@@  PROC   *2 @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$$GFL*   NAME      2   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@BB
)@@G@@. FORCE DEFINITION OF PROC NEEDED TO FORCE G-FLAGS    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@BC
)@@G@@          PROC    @#@@@@G$$FRG**  NAME    @]@@@@ GO G$$DIA  @#@@@@      BD
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. NOW G-FLAG GENERATOR ACTUALLY DOES ITS TBE
)@@G@@HING  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ GO G$$FRG          . LEAP TO OTHER PROC, WHICH BF
)@@G@@LEAPS TO G$$DIA   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$IFL*  NAME       3   BG
)@@G@@              . THIS ENTRY FOR TRULY INVALID INSTRUCTION    @H@@@@      BH
)@@G@@    RES       1                 . WHICH ACTUALLY TAKES SPACE IN THE CODEBI
)@@G@@@C@@@@ GO G$$DIA          . GO DISPLAY THE MESSAGE    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@BJ
)@@G@@G$$EFL*  NAME       1                 . GENERATE AN E-FLAG  @#@@@@A     BK
)@@G@@  EQU    +) @]@@@@ GO G$$DIA  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$$DFL*  NAME       0   BL
)@@G@@@E@@@@G$DFLG****                      . GENERATE A GLOBAL D-FLAG  @B@@@@BM
)@@G@@G$DFLG****          EQU               0 . @G@@@@ DO P(1)>0 , RES P(1,1)-BN
)@@G@@$             . THEN FORCE LC BACK INTO PHASE   @]@@@@ GO G$$DIA  @[@@@@BO
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@G$$TFL*  NAME       4                 . GENERATE A T-FLAG   BP
)@@G@@@A@@@@A       EQU    + (I$ 0,0,0,0,077,0) @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. NOW WE GENBQ
)@@G@@ERATE THE MESSAGES. TO AVOID EXTRANEOUS D-FLAGS ON    @E@@@@. THE USER'SBR
)@@G@@ LISTING, NEGATIVE RES'S ARE USED TO INSURE THAT@F@@@@. THE MESSAGES DO BS
)@@G@@NOT OCCUPY ANY SPACE IN THE PROGRAM'S ADDRESS   @F@@@@. SPACE. TO INSUREBT
)@@G@@ THAT THE MESSAGE DOES NOT GO UNNOTICED, WE     @G@@@@. TRASH ON THE LASBU
)@@G@@T WORD OF GENERATED USER CODE, MAKING IT AN IOPR.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@BV
)@@G@@. TO AVOID SURPRESSION IF BRIEF MODE IS ON, THE DIAGNOSTIC  @D@@@@. MESSBW
)@@G@@AGE SENTINAL WORD IS THE 1ST ONE GENERATED.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$$DIABX
)@@G@@*   NAME                        . DIAGNOSTIC PRINTOUT STARTS HERE @H@@@@BY
)@@G@@          RES       -1                . GET RID OF USER'S LAST INSTRUCTIBZ
)@@G@@ON    @F@@@@K         EQU       1+(P(0,0)=0)      . SPEC TO FIND FLAGS ICA
)@@G@@N     @F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . CURRENT NESTING LEVECB
)@@G@@L     @D@@@@          G$ERFO    G$TYPE(M),M,P(0,0),P(K,1),P(K,2)  @#@@@@CC
)@@G@@          UNLIST  @F@@@@          G$$IFLAG                    . MARK THICD
)@@G@@S ELEMENT IN ERROR@G@@@@          RES       -2                . PURGE SECE
)@@G@@NTINAL AND IFLAG WORD   @H@@@@          +0                          . FOCF
)@@G@@RCE PROG TO IOPR IF ITS EXECUTED    @#@@@@          LIST    @E@@@@      CG
)@@G@@    END                         . OF DIAGNOSTIC PROCS @[@@@@.     @E@@@@CH
)@@G@@. THIS PROC DISPLAYS DEBUGGING INFORMATION WITHOUT AFFECTING@F@@@@. THE CI
)@@G@@GENERATED CODE. IT IS USED FOR DEBUGGING STRUC$ ITSELF.     @[@@@@.     CJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@P          PROC     *999,0    @#@@@@G$DBUG*    NAME   @B@@@@I(1)  CK
