)@@G@@     EQU      I(1)+1            .   @^@@@@ DO P(I(1))=0 , END     @ @@@@CL
)@@G@@ DO P(I(1))=1 , +P(I(1),1)    @A@@@@ DO P(I(1))=2 , +P(I(1),1),P(I(1),2)CM
)@@G@@@C@@@@ DO P(I(1))=3 , +P(I(1),1),P(I(1),2),P(I(1),3)  @E@@@@ DO P(I(1))=CN
)@@G@@4 , +P(I(1),1),P(I(1),2),P(I(1),3),P(I(1),4)    @H@@@@ DO P(I(1))>4 , +PCO
)@@G@@(I(1),1),P(I(1),2),P(I(1),3),P(I(1),4),P(I(1),5),P(I(1),6)  @^@@@@      CP
)@@G@@     RES      -1  @B@@@@ DO I(1)<P , GO G$DBUG                  . @#@@@@CQ
)@@G@@           END    @C@@@@/.    ******** PROGRAM DEFINITION GROUP ********CR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. ARRAY USAGE BY BEGIN BLOCKS:@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.    GCS
)@@G@@$LABL(K,1) ENTRY POINT TO BLOCK (=PKT ADDR IF CONTINGENCY)  @B@@@@.     CT
)@@G@@        2) EXIT POINT FROM BLOCK    @E@@@@.             3) ADDR OF GENERCU
)@@G@@ATED REG SAVE AREA (IF ANY)   @E@@@@.             4) ADDR OF SIGNAL CELLCV
)@@G@@ OR RETURN TARGET ADDR  @G@@@@.             5) ADDR OF BLOK EXIT INSTR (CW
)@@G@@AFTER REG RESTORE INSTRS)     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.    G$FLAG(K,1) XREG USCX
)@@G@@ED FOR SIGNALLING, ZERO IF NONE     @B@@@@.             2) NUMBER OF SAVCY
)@@G@@ED REGISTERS@C@@@@.             2,N) AXR$ VALUE OF N'TH SAVED REG @C@@@@CZ
)@@G@@.             3) BLOCK TYPE (MAINPROG, ETC.)    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.    GDA
)@@G@@$BSEQ(<X>) BLOK SEQ NO (I.E., K) WHERE <X> IS START ADDR    @[@@@@.     DB
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.           DC
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               *           BEDD
)@@G@@GIN             * @C@@@@.               *                             * DE
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@DF
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@           DEF    @H@@@@F          FUNC         DG
)@@G@@              . ----- UTILITY FUNC USED IN SORTING    @#@@@@G$$INC*    NDH
)@@G@@AME   @D@@@@III*(1)    EQU              III(1)+1  . BUMP COUNTER  @E@@@@DI
)@@G@@           END              III(1)    . RETURN NEW VALUE    @[@@@@.     DJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *3 @]@@@@BEGIN*  NAME@G@@@@ DO (G$CTR(5DK
)@@G@@)=0)=0 , G$$GFL 1,1             . REQUIRE NESTING DEPTH ZERO@F@@@@M     DL
)@@G@@    EQU       1                 . FORCE NEW NESTING DEPTH   @D@@@@G$CTR*DM
)@@G@@(5) EQU  M                      . THEN SAVE IT  @F@@@@ DO (G$CTR(2)=0)=0DN
)@@G@@ , G$$GFL 1,2             . REQUIRE NO FLOAT    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@K     DO
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SERIAL NUMBER   @D@@@@G$CTR*DP
)@@G@@(1) EQU       K                 . AND UPDATE IT @D@@@@G$TYPE*(M) EQU    DQ
)@@G@@  1                 . SET BLOCK TYPE@E@@@@G$SEQN*(M) EQU      K         DR
)@@G@@        . SAVE SERIAL NUMBER  @F@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 ,G$BSEQ*($) EQU      K DS
)@@G@@  . SERIAL # INDEXED BY STARTA@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,G$BSEQ*($AP($)) EQU K DT
)@@G@@  . SERIAL # INDEXED BY STARTADR    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@T         EQU  P(1DU
)@@G@@,1)+(P(1)=0)*MAINPROGRAM . GET PROG TYPE  @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU T      DV
)@@G@@               . AND REMEMBER IT    @E@@@@ISSUB      EQU      (T=SUBROUTDW
)@@G@@INE)++(T=LIJSUB)++(T=LDJSUB)  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. ALLOW 'NOSAVE' TO DEFADX
)@@G@@ULT TO SUBFIELD 2 @[@@@@.     @G@@@@NOSDEF    EQU       ISSUB**(P(1)=2)*DY
)@@G@@*(P(1,2)=NOSAVE) . NOSAVE DEFAULT   @E@@@@ DO NOSDEF ,P(1,3) EQU NOSAVE DZ
)@@G@@        . FORCE THIRD FIELD   @D@@@@ DO NOSDEF ,P(1,2) EQU 0            EA
)@@G@@  . CLEAR REGISTER@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO NOSDEF ,P(1)   EQU 3 . NOW NOTEB
)@@G@@E THERE ARE 3 SUBFIELDS @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,1)EC
)@@G@@=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,1)    @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)  EQU   $           . SAED
)@@G@@VE ENTRY POINT TO BLOK  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          RES       G$CTR(6)  EE
)@@G@@        . ALLOW ZERO AS A FLAG@E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       0-G$CTR(7)      EF
)@@G@@  . SET GLOBAL FLOAT    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO T=CYCLIC , END            EG
)@@G@@     . SINCE CYCLICS NEVER EXIT, WE'RE DONE     @G@@@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY EH
)@@G@@, +0D               . IF CONTING, GENERATE PACKET     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@EI
)@@G@@.              HANDLE EXITS WHICH SIGNAL THE EXEC (MAIN/CONTINGENCY)    EJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@GI      EQU    (P(1,1)=SIGNAL)+2*(P(2,1)=SIGNAL)+3*(P(EK
)@@G@@3,1)=SIGNAL)@F@@@@. SIGNAL XREG IS FLAG, IF NONE (<0), THEN EXIT WILL BEEL
)@@G@@ 'NORMAL'   @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,1) EQU (GI>0)*(P(1,2)+(P(1)<2)*A0)-(GI=0) . EM
)@@G@@SET SIGNAL XREG   @F@@@@ DO (T=REMOTESUB)=0                     ; IF NOTEN
)@@G@@ A REMOTE SUB     @F@@@@   ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU                  ; DEFAULT EO
)@@G@@RETURN JUMPTARGET @G@@@@      (T=CONTINGENCY)*G$LABL(K,1)-ISSUB . TO PACEP
)@@G@@KET OR -1 FLAG VALUE    @G@@@@ DO (T=EXECSUB)**(P(1)=1)             ; IFEQ
)@@G@@ EXECSUB BUT NO RETURN ADDR   @F@@@@   ,P(1,2) EQU DISP                 ER
)@@G@@  . FORCE STD RETURN ADDR     @G@@@@ DO T=EXECSUB ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU P(1,ES
)@@G@@2) . JUMPTARGET FOR EXEC ROUTINES   @G@@@@ DO GI>0 , DO P(GI)>1 ,G$LABL*ET
)@@G@@(K,4) EQU ;  UNLESS USER PROVIDED A USPEC @G@@@@        +      (I$ 0,P(GEU
)@@G@@I,4),,P(GI,3),2*P(GI,*3)+P(GI,*2),P(GI,2) )     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.     EV
)@@G@@         HANDLE REGISTER SAVE REQUESTS    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO ISSUB**(EW
)@@G@@P(1,2)=0) ,P(1,2) EQU X11 . DEFAULT LINKREG TO X11    @H@@@@SII     EQU EX
)@@G@@   ((P(1,1)=STACK)++(P(1,1)=SAVE))+; FIND REG SAVE CONTROL FIELD  @G@@@@EY
)@@G@@2*((P(2,1)=STACK)++(P(2,1)=SAVE))+3*((P(3,1)=STACK)++(P(3,1)=SAVE))     EZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@SI      EQU    SII+(SII=0)*ISSUB      . IF NONE**SUBROUTINE, SET 1FA
)@@G@@@E@@@@ DO SI=0 ,  END                       . IF NONE, WE'RE DONE @[@@@@FB
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@ST      EQU    P(SI,1)                . ELSE GET TYPE (SAVE/FC
)@@G@@STACK/SUBRTNE)    @H@@@@ DO ISSUB=0                           ; IF NOT AFD
)@@G@@ SUBROUTINE TO START WITH     @G@@@@    ,P(1,3) EQU NOSAVE              FE
)@@G@@  . OBVIOUSLY NO LINKREG TO BE SAVED@D@@@@I DO 3 ,Q(I) EQU P(I)         FF
)@@G@@        . COPY LEAVES   @G@@@@NOLINK    EQU       P(1,3)=NOSAVE     . ONFG
)@@G@@=> INHIBIT SAVE OF LINKREG    @G@@@@ DO NOLINK ,P(1,2) EQU -P(1,2)      FH
)@@G@@  . IF NOT SAVING, JUST REMEMBER IT @G@@@@ DO NOLINK ,Q(1) EQU +2       FI
)@@G@@        . AND FORCE THE NOSAVE SPEC AWAY  @H@@@@KLX     EQU    Q(SI)-2*(FJ
)@@G@@ST=STACK)     . INDEX OF LAST REG TO EXPLICITLY SAVE  @H@@@@I DO KLX ,RSFK
)@@G@@AV(P(SI,I+1)**0777777) EQU 1 . MARK ALL REGS REQUESTED EXPLICITLY @H@@@@FL
)@@G@@III(1)     EQU      1       . INIT INCREMENTATION CTR: 1ST SUBFIELD WILLFM
)@@G@@ BE 2 @F@@@@I DO 128 , DO RSAV(I) ,P(SI,G$$INC(1)) EQU I . SORT EXPLICITFN
)@@G@@ REGS @H@@@@ DO KLX<Q(SI) , DO (P(SI,KLX+1)=POINTER)=0 , G$$EFL 3,2 . REFO
)@@G@@QUIRE REG SPEC    @H@@@@SEX        EQU      (ST=SUBROUTINE)++(ST=LIJSUB)FP
)@@G@@++(ST=LDJSUB)=0 . ON IF SAVE G@H@@@@SLI        EQU      ISSUB           FQ
)@@G@@  . ON IF LINKREG SHOULD BE REMEMBERED    @G@@@@ DO SEX**SLI ,P(SI,KLX+1FR
)@@G@@) EQU P(1,2)  . FORCE LINKREG INTO SAVE LIST    @G@@@@KLR     EQU    KLXFS
)@@G@@+(SEX**SLI)         . INDEX OF LAST REG TO REMEMBER   @H@@@@I DO     KLRFT
)@@G@@-1 ,G$FLAG*(K,2,I) EQU +P(SI,I+1) . REMEMBER WHATS BEING SAVED    @I@@@@FU
)@@G@@KL        EQU       KLR-(NOLINK*(1-(T=EXECSUB))) . NUMBER TO ACTUALLY PUFV
)@@G@@T IN COR    @I@@@@I DO KL-1 ,FNC(I) EQU 1+5*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)<A0)+3*(G$FLAGFW
)@@G@@(K,2,I)>A15) . SA, SX, SR     @G@@@@I DO KL-1 ,AFL(I) EQU G$FLAG(K,2,I)-FX
)@@G@@A0*(FNC(I)=1)-(R1-1)*(FNC(I)=4)     @H@@@@I DO KL-1 , DO FNC(I)=1 ,FNC(IFY
)@@G@@) EQU (FNC(I-1)<071)* ; FOR SINGLE STORE A'S    @F@@@@  (070*(AFL(I+1)=AFZ
)@@G@@FL(I)+1)+1) . DOUBLE STORE CONTIGUOUS AREGS     @G@@@@ DO ST=STACK , GO GA
)@@G@@G$$B10              . IF STACKING, GO DO SPECIAL STUFF@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0GB
)@@G@@ ,IC      EQU    &        . PRESERVE USER'S LOCATION COUNTER@G@@@@ DO G$GC
)@@G@@MASM=1 ,IC      EQU    $LCN     . IC IS CURRENT LOCATION COUNTER  @F@@@@GD
)@@G@@$(G$LCTR(1))                          . AND ESTABLISH OUR OWN     @G@@@@GE
)@@G@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (&=IC)**(KL>1) , J $+KL    . IF =, LEAP AROUND THE RESGF
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 , DO ($LCN=IC)**(KL>1) , J $+KL . IF =, LEAP AROUND TGG
)@@G@@HE RES@G@@@@G$LABL*(K,3) EQU    $                 . START OF REG SAVE ARGH
)@@G@@EA (IF ANY) @E@@@@             RES    KL-1              . SET ASIDE SAVEGI
)@@G@@ SPACE@E@@@@$(IC)                                 . RESTORE USER'S IC   GJ
)@@G@@@H@@@@I DO KL-1 , DO FNC(I)>0 , I$ FNC(I),012*(FNC(I)=071),AFL(I),,,G$LAGK
)@@G@@BL(K,3)+I-1 @G@@@@ DO 1 , END                           . IF NOT STACKINGL
)@@G@@G, WE'RE DONE     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$$B10* NAME                        GM
)@@G@@  . HANDLE STACKING HERE@F@@@@OI      EQU    P(SI+1,1)=OFFSET       . ONGN
)@@G@@ IF OFFSET SPECIFIED    @H@@@@AI      EQU    P(SI,*KLX+2)           . ONGO
)@@G@@ TO AUTO-INCREMENT STACK POINTER    @G@@@@OSV     EQU    + (I$ 0,OI*P(SIGP
)@@G@@+1,3),0,P(SI,KLX+2),2*AI,OI*P(SI+1,2))    @C@@@@I DO  KL-1 , S G$FLAG(K,GQ
)@@G@@2,I),OSV+(1-AI)*(I-1)   @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,3) EQU 0-OSV                  . GR
)@@G@@REMEMBER OFFSET FLAGS   @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@GS
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * GT
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *          ENDBEG   GU
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@GV
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     GW
)@@G@@@#@@@@P       PROC   *1 @#@@@@ENDBEG*  NAME     @G@@@@M         EQU     GX
)@@G@@  G$CTR(5)          . GET NESTING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @H@@@@K         EQGY
)@@G@@U       G$SEQN(M)         . GET OVERALL BLOCK SEQUENCE NUMBER     @F@@@@GZ
)@@G@@ DO (M=1)=0 , G$$GFL 1,1         . BE SURE NESTING LEVEL IS OK    @D@@@@HA
)@@G@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=1)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3 . AND BLOCK TYPE     @I@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQHB
)@@G@@U       0                 . FORCE NESTING LEVEL FOR SUBSEQUENT CODE     HC
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO (G$CTR(2)=(0-G$CTR(7)))=0 , G$$GFL 1,2 . DIAGNOSE BAD FLOAT   HD
)@@G@@@E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       0                 . AND FORCE IT CORRECT@E@@@@HE
)@@G@@T         EQU       G$FLAG(K,3)       . GET BEGIN BLOCK TYPE@[@@@@.     HF
)@@G@@@E@@@@          RES       0-G$CTR(6)        . FIXUP FOR FLAGS     @E@@@@HG
)@@G@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,2)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,2)    @D@@@@G$LABLHH
)@@G@@*(K,2)  EQU   $           . MARK END OF BLOCK   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO T=HI
)@@G@@CYCLIC , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,1) . IF CYCLIC, LOOP BACK    @D@@@@ DO T=HJ
)@@G@@CYCLIC , END                 . AND THAT'S ALL   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. IF AHK
)@@G@@NY REGS WERE SAVED, RESTORE THEM    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,2)=0 HL
)@@G@@, GO G$$X01 @H@@@@NRR     EQU    +G$FLAG(K,2)              . GET NO OF RHM
)@@G@@EGISTERS REMEMBERED     @G@@@@LINK(1)   EQU       G$FLAG(K,2,NRR)   . LIHN
)@@G@@NK IS ALWAYS THE LAST ONE     @H@@@@NR        EQU       NRR-(LINK(1)<0) HO
)@@G@@  . FUDGE IN CASE WE DIDN'T SAVE LINK     @G@@@@ DO NRR>NR ,LINK(1) EQU HP
)@@G@@-LINK(1)      . THEN GET REAL VALUE OF LINK     @G@@@@I DO NR ,FNC(I) EQHQ
)@@G@@U 010+017*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)<A0)+013*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)>A15)  @G@@@@I DO NR ,AFLHR
)@@G@@(I) EQU G$FLAG(K,2,I)-A0*(FNC(I)=010)-(R1-1)*(FNC(I)=023)   @H@@@@I DO NHS
)@@G@@R , DO FNC(I)=010 ,FNC(I) EQU (FNC(I-1)<071)* ; FOR SINGLE LOAD A'S     HT
)@@G@@@F@@@@  (061*(AFL(I+1)=AFL(I)+1)+010) . DOUBLE LOAD CONTIGUOUS AREGS    HU
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 ,SR      EQU    0-G$LABL(K,3) . GET STACKREG/SAVE FLAHV
)@@G@@G     @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,SR      EQU    $AP(0-G$LABL(K,3)) . GET STACKRHW
)@@G@@EG/SAVE FLAG@ @@@@ DO (SR>0)=0 ,I DO NR , ;     @G@@@@  DO FNC(I)>0 , I$HX
)@@G@@ FNC(I),013*(FNC(I)=071),AFL(I),,,G$LABL(K,3)+I-1     @F@@@@ DO (SR>0)=0HY
)@@G@@ , GO G$$X01              . IF NOT STACKED, WE'RE DONE@#@@@@. HANDLE STAHZ
)@@G@@CKING @F@@@@INC     EQU    SR**0400000            . ISOLATE AUTO-INCREMEIA
)@@G@@NT BIT@F@@@@XSR     EQU    (017000000**SR)*/4     . MOVE XREG INTO AREG IB
)@@G@@FIELD @F@@@@ DO INC>0 , ANX,U 0,NR+(017000000**SR)*/4 . BACK UP STACK POIC
)@@G@@INTER @F@@@@I DO     NR , L G$FLAG(K,2,I),(SR**007777177777)+I-1 . AND UID
)@@G@@NSTACK@F@@@@G$$X01* NAME                          . END OF REG RESTORATIIE
)@@G@@ON    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,5)  EQU   $                 . MARK POSIF
)@@G@@N OF EXIT INSTR   @F@@@@ DO T=LIJSUB , I$ 07,013,LINK(1),LINK(1),,0 . LIIG
)@@G@@J LINK,0,LINK     @F@@@@ DO T=LDJSUB , I$ 07,012,LINK(1),LINK(1),,0 . LDIH
)@@G@@J LINK,0,LINK     @ @@@@ DO T=SUBROUTINE , J 0,LINK(1)@C@@@@ DO (T=EXECSII
)@@G@@UB)++(T=REMOTESUB) , J G$LABL(K,4)  @F@@@@ DO $>G$LABL(K,5) , END       IJ
)@@G@@        . QUIT IF ANY OF THE ABOVE  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. PROCESS MAINPROGIK
)@@G@@S AND CONTINGENCIES     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@XREG    EQU    G$FLAG(K,1)    IL
)@@G@@        . GET EXIT TYPE (NORMAL OR SIGNAL)@G@@@@ DO XREG>0 , GO G$$X02  IM
)@@G@@              . IF EXCEPTION, GO PROCESS IT     @G@@@@ DO T=MAINPROGRAM IN
)@@G@@, ER EXIT$          . NORMAL MAINPROGRAM EXIT IS EXIT$@E@@@@ DO T=CONTINIO
)@@G@@GENCY , SZ,H1 G$LABL(K,4) . CLEAR PACKET UPPER  @F@@@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY IP
)@@G@@, I$ 074,04,,,1,G$LABL(K,4) . AND JUMP THRU PKT @G@@@@ DO 1 , END       IQ
)@@G@@                    . THAT'S ALL FOR NORMAL EXITS     @H@@@@G$$X02* NAMEIR
)@@G@@                          . HERE TO HANDLE EXITS WITH SIGNALLING  @F@@@@IS
)@@G@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY , I$ 051,H1,,,,G$LABL(K,4) . IS UPPER (H1) ZERO @G@@@@IT
)@@G@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY , I$ 074,04,,,1,G$LABL(K,4) . YES, EXIT THRU PACKET   IU
)@@G@@@I@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (G$LABL(K,4)<0)=0 , LX XREG,G$LABL(K,4) . LOAD FIV
)@@G@@ROM SIGNALLOC     @I@@@@ DO G$MASM , DO $AP(G$LABL(K,4))>=0 , LX XREG,G$IW
)@@G@@LABL(K,4) . LOAD FROM SIGNALLOC     @F@@@@        I$     074,04,,XREG,,$IX
)@@G@@+1      . JUMP INTO FOLLOWING TABLE @C@@@@        ER     011            IY
)@@G@@        . 0=EXIT$ @C@@@@        ER     040                    . 1=ERR$  IZ
)@@G@@@C@@@@        ER     026                    . 2=EABT$ @C@@@@        ER  JA
)@@G@@   012                    . 3=ABORT$@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@JB
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.     JC
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               *       JD
)@@G@@  SWITCHTO            * @C@@@@.               *                         JE
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     JF
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *1 @#@@@@SWITCHTO*  NAME   @[@@@@.     JG
)@@G@@@D@@@@. NOTE: THIS FEATURE IS NO LONGER AVAILABLE BECAUSE OF@E@@@@. OPTIJH
)@@G@@MIZATION TECHNIQUES FOR THE OBJECT CODE. ANY BLOCK    @E@@@@. MUST BE WHJI
)@@G@@OLLY GENERATED UNDER A SINGLE LOCATION COUNTER. @F@@@@. CONTINGENCY PROCJJ
)@@G@@ESSING IN A SEPERATE BANK MUST BE ACCOMPLISHED  @D@@@@. BY MEANS OF A SUJK
)@@G@@BROUTINE CALL TO THE OTHER BANK.    @[@@@@.     @I@@@@          RES     JL
)@@G@@  1                 . SPACE SO DIAGNOSTIC DOESN'T CREAM OLD US    @D@@@@JM
)@@G@@          G$$GFL    3,1               . GIVE A WARNING@H@@@@          REJN
)@@G@@S       -1                . ZAP THE IOPR SO THE PROGRAM WORKS     @G@@@@JO
)@@G@@. NOTE THAT WE SIMPLY IGNORE THE REQUEST FOR A LOCATION COUNTER CHANGE  JP
)@@G@@@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               ********JQ
)@@G@@*********************** @C@@@@.               *                         JR
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               *           BASE              * @C@@@@.     JS
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               ********JT
)@@G@@*********************** @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@P          PROC   JU
)@@G@@  *1                .  SPECS:  IBANK\DBANK(,<USPEC FOR BDI>)@E@@@@BASE* JV
)@@G@@     NAME                       . MAKE A BANK VISIBLE @F@@@@XREG       EJW
)@@G@@QU      P(0,1)+X11*(P(0,1)=0) . XREG USED FOR LINKAGE @E@@@@. THE FOLLOWJX
)@@G@@ING THREE LINES ARE COURTESY OF ISAAC BORNSTEIN.@E@@@@. THEY FIX A BUG IJY
)@@G@@NVOLVING THE LOAD OF THE BDI (LXI,LDJ)    @F@@@@          DO P(1)<2 , GOJZ
)@@G@@ NOLXI . IF ONLY 1 PARAM, NO LXI IS NEEDED@H@@@@ DO P(1,4)<016 , I$ 046,KA
)@@G@@P(1,4),XREG,P(1,3),2*P(1,*3)+P(1,*2),P(1,2) . LXI BDI @G@@@@ DO P(1,4)>0KB
)@@G@@15 , G$$IMU 046,P(1,4),XREG,P(1,3),P(1,2) . LXI,U/XU BDI    @^@@@@NOLXI KC
)@@G@@    NAME      .   @F@@@@           I$       07,012+(P(1,1)=IBANK),XREG,,KD
)@@G@@,$+1 . DO LIJ/LDJ @#@@@@           END    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@KE
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * KF
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *            CALL   KG
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@KH
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     KI
)@@G@@@G@@@@          PROC      *0                . PROC TO DECLARE THE 'CALL'KJ
)@@G@@ PROC @E@@@@. PREVENTS RLIB$ ENTRY POINT CONFLICTS WITH COBOL'S 'CALL'  KK
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@G$$CLD*   NAME                        .   @[@@@@.     KL
)@@G@@@#@@@@P       PROC   *2 @B@@@@CALL*** NAME                          .   KM
)@@G@@@G@@@@RAD(1)    EQU       +(0,-1)           . ASSUME NOT CALLING RMT BLOKN
)@@G@@K     @F@@@@P11       EQU       P(1,1)            . P11 IS ADDRESS OF TAKO
)@@G@@RGET  @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,P11 EQU $AP(P11)        . IF MASM, USE ONLY ABKP
)@@G@@SOLUTE PART @E@@@@ DO P(1)=1                            ; IF ONLY ONE FIKQ
)@@G@@ELD   @E@@@@   , DO P11<0400000                   ; AND IT ISN'T EQUF'D KR
)@@G@@@E@@@@      ,RAD(1) EQU P11                 . GET ITS ACTUAL ADDR @F@@@@KS
)@@G@@K          EQU      G$BSEQ(RAD(1))    . GET SEQUENCE NO OF BLOK   @G@@@@KT
)@@G@@ DO K>0                               ; IF BLOCK HAS BEEN PROCESSED...  KU
)@@G@@@E@@@@   , DO G$FLAG(K,3)=REMOTESUB         ; AND IT'S REMOTE     @F@@@@KV
)@@G@@      , GO G$$CL1                     . GO TREAT IT SPECIALLY     @[@@@@KW
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@XREG    EQU    P(0,1)+(P(0,1)=0)*X11  . DEFAULT LINKREG TO XKX
)@@G@@11    @G@@@@BANKSW     EQU      P(2,1)=BASING     . ON IF WE SHOULD SWITKY
)@@G@@CH BANKS    @G@@@@K DO P(2)*(1-BANKSW) , SZ P(2,K) . CLEAR ALT EXIT SENTKZ
)@@G@@INALS, IF ANY     @E@@@@. THE FOLLOWING THREE LINES ARE COURTESY OF ISAALA
)@@G@@C BORNSTEIN.@E@@@@. THEY FIX A BUG INVOLVING THE LOAD OF THE BDI (LXI,LDLB
)@@G@@J)    @I@@@@          DO 1-(BANKSW**(P(2)>2)) , GO NOLXI . IF ONLY 1 PARLC
)@@G@@AM, NO LXI IS NEEDED    @H@@@@ DO P(2,5)<016 , I$ 046,P(2,5),XREG,P(2,4)LD
)@@G@@,2*P(2,*4)+P(2,*3),P(2,3) . LXI BDI @G@@@@ DO P(2,5)>015 , G$$IMU 046,P(LE
)@@G@@2,5),XREG,P(2,4),P(2,3) . LXI,U/XU BDI    @^@@@@NOLXI     NAME      .   LF
)@@G@@@D@@@@FUN        EQU      074-BANKSW*065    . LMJ OR LIJ/LDJ@H@@@@JAY   LG
)@@G@@     EQU      013-BANKSW*(P(2,2)=DBANK) . 013 UNLESS LDJ (THEN 012)     LH
)@@G@@@F@@@@           I$       FUN,JAY,XREG,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) .LI
)@@G@@@I@@@@K DO     P(2)*(1-BANKSW) , SX XREG,P(2,K)        . SET ALT EXIT SELJ
)@@G@@NTINALS, IF ANY   @]@@@@ DO 1 , END @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$$CL1***  NAME   LK
)@@G@@                    . HERE FOR CALLS TO REMOTE BLOX   @F@@@@           JLL
)@@G@@        P(1,1)            . FLYING LEAP TO THE BLOCK  @F@@@@           GLM
)@@G@@$$PRB   K,$               . PATCH ITS RETURN ADDR     @H@@@@          ENLN
)@@G@@D                         . END OF THE ACTUAL 'CALL' PROC DEFN    @G@@@@LO
)@@G@@          END                         . END OF PROC WHICH DEFINES 'CALL'LP
)@@G@@@C@@@@/.           ******    IF   GROUP    *******    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@LQ
)@@G@@. USE OF LABELS AND FLAGS --  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.       G$FLLR
)@@G@@AG(K,1) EXPLICIT NOT FLAG     @E@@@@.                2) SIDE EFFECT AND LS
)@@G@@'IF' TEST INVERSION FLAG@B@@@@.                3) IMPLIED LINEITEM FLAG LT
)@@G@@@D@@@@.                4) FLOAT ADJUSTMENT CAUSED BY 'ELSE' @F@@@@.     LU
)@@G@@           5) FLOAT CAUSED BY OPTIMIZATION OF 'IF' TEST     @B@@@@.     LV
)@@G@@           6) COMPLEX CONDITION FLAG@[@@@@.     @C@@@@.       G$LABL(K,1LW
)@@G@@) START ADDR OF TESTS AT 'IF' @E@@@@.                2) START ADDR OF USLX
)@@G@@ER CODE IN 'IF' BLOCK   @D@@@@.                3) END ADDR OF CODE IN 'ILY
)@@G@@F' BLOCK    @D@@@@.                4) START ADDR OF CODE IN 'ELSE' BLOCKLZ
)@@G@@@D@@@@.                5) TARGET ADDR FOR EXIT FROM BLOCK   @[@@@@.     MA
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.           MB
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               *            IMC
)@@G@@F               * @C@@@@.               *                             * MD
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @#@@@@ME
)@@G@@P       PROC   *6 @]@@@@IF*     NAME@[@@@@.     @H@@@@LOOF      EQU     MF
)@@G@@  (P(1)=1)**(P(1,1)=LOOKFOR) . CHECK FOR TABLE SEARCH FORMAT@^@@@@ DO LOMG
)@@G@@OF , GO G$$I05    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. ANALYZE SYNTAX SO WE KNOW IF THIS MH
)@@G@@IS LINEITEM OR A BLOCK  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@L       EQU    P-1@B@@@@L1    MI
)@@G@@  EQU    (P(L)=1)**(P(L,1)=THEN)    @B@@@@L2      EQU    (P(L-1)=1)**(P(MJ
)@@G@@L-1,1)=THEN)@E@@@@FLT     EQU    L1*L+L2*(L-1)  . FIELD OF 'THEN' OR ZERMK
)@@G@@O     @E@@@@THF     EQU    FLT+(FLT=0)*P  . IF NOT GIVEN, ASSUME IT     ML
)@@G@@@F@@@@IFNOT     EQU       (P(1)=1)**(P(1,1)=NOT) . SET EXPLICIT NOT FLAGMM
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO (THF=IFNOT+2)++(THF=IFNOT+4)=0 , G$$EFL 3,3 . CHECK NO OF FIELMN
)@@G@@DS    @F@@@@CXF       EQU       THF=IFNOT+4     . SET COMPLEX CONDITION MO
)@@G@@FLAG  @E@@@@ DO P<THF+2 , GO G$$I05               . GO DO NORMAL FORMAT MP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. LINEITEM FORMAT DOES NOT UPDATE NESTING ARRAYS- GETSMQ
)@@G@@ SPECIAL HANDLING @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          G$$TST    1+IFNOT,CXF,IFNOMR
)@@G@@T . GENERATE THE TEST   @E@@@@          +P(THF+1,1)                 . THMS
)@@G@@EN THE LINEITEM   @A@@@@   DO 1 , END       . AND THEN QUIT @[@@@@.     MT
)@@G@@@B@@@@. PROCESS NORMAL (NOT LINEITEM) IF --     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$I05MU
)@@G@@*   NAME    @H@@@@K         EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SEQUMV
)@@G@@ENCE NO FOR THIS BLOCK  @F@@@@G$CTR*(1) EQU       K                 . ANMW
)@@G@@D UPDATE BLOCK COUNTER  @G@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       G$CTR(5)+1        . BUMX
)@@G@@MP CURRENT BLOCK NESTING LEVEL@G@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)        MY
)@@G@@  . GET NESTING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @G@@@@G$TYPE*(M)          EQU       MZ
)@@G@@        2 . SET CURRENT BLOCKTYPE TO IF   @H@@@@G$SEQN*(M)          EQU NA
)@@G@@              K . AND REMEMBER ITS SEQUENCE NUMBER    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@NB
)@@G@@. ADJUST ALL LABELS FOR FLOAT @[@@@@.     @D@@@@G$LABL*(K,1) EQU G$LABL(NC
)@@G@@K,1)+G$CTR(2) . GLOBAL FLOAT  @E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(ND
)@@G@@K,5) . APPLY 'IF' FLOAT @F@@@@N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,N+1) EQU G$LABL(K,N+1)+GNE
)@@G@@$CTR(2) . GLOBAL+IF     @F@@@@N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,N+3) EQU G$LABL(K,N+3)+GNF
)@@G@@$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,4)     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@  DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,1NG
)@@G@@)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,1)   @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)  EQU   $        . REMEMNH
)@@G@@BER START ADDR FOR OPTIMIZATION     @H@@@@ DO LOOF , GO G$$I10          NI
)@@G@@        . LOOKFOR TESTS GET SPECIAL HANDLING    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@NOGEN NJ
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(7)*(G$LABL(K,5)=G$LABL(K,1)) . ON TO SURPRESS ALL   NK
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU G$CTR(4)+NOGEN           . KEEP G$$TST'S COUNTER IN NL
)@@G@@PHASE @A@@@@ DO NOGEN , END     . STOP IF NO MO @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAGNM
)@@G@@*(K,1) EQU IFNOT            . SAVE NOT FLAG FOR OPTIMIZER   @E@@@@G$FLAGNN
)@@G@@*(K,6) EQU CXF              . AND ALSO COMPLEX FLAG   @H@@@@ DO G$CTR(6)NO
)@@G@@ , G$$SVA              . PASS 1: SAVE ARGS FOR RECALL AT ENDIF    @[@@@@NP
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@RVF       EQU       IFNOT--G$FLAG(K,2) . SET OVERALL REVERSANQ
)@@G@@L FLAG@F@@@@LIG       EQU       G$FLAG(K,3)     . SET IMPLIED LINEITEM FNR
)@@G@@LAG   @G@@@@ DO 1-LIG ,  G$$TST  1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF G$LABL(K,4)  . GENERATENS
)@@G@@ THE TEST   @H@@@@ DO LIG  ,  G$$TST  1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF      . GENERATE LINT
)@@G@@NE ITEM FORMAT TEST(S)  @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU SIDE(1)               . RNU
)@@G@@EMEMBER IF TEST HAS SIDE EFFECTS    @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,2)  EQU   $         NV
)@@G@@. REMEMBER START OF USER CODE FOR OPTIMIZA@#@@@@ DO 1 , END .     @[@@@@NW
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. HANDLE 'LOOKFOR' TESTS, WHICH GENERATE 1100 SERIES SEARCH NX
)@@G@@INSTRUCTIONS@[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$I10*   NAME    @A@@@@ DO (P(3,1)=VARY)=NY
)@@G@@0 , G$$EFL 2,010 .@I@@@@VI        EQU       3                 . 'VARY' SNZ
)@@G@@PECIFICATION MUST FOLLOW 'LOOKFO    @E@@@@P(3,1)    EQU       LOOKFOR   OA
)@@G@@        . FORCE THE KEYWORD   @G@@@@KW(1)     EQU       LOOKFOR         OB
)@@G@@  . IN ALL PLACES ITS EXPECTED TO BE@G@@@@G$LABL*(K,2)  EQU   $         OC
)@@G@@         . GUARANTEE NON-EMPTY 'IF' CLAUSE@H@@@@          G$$LAN        OD
)@@G@@              . ANALYZE SPECS, LOAD REGS IF NECESSARY @G@@@@          G$OE
)@@G@@$LGE    3,FI(3),FI(4) G$LABL(K,4),1 . GEN CODE FOR SEARCH   @F@@@@G$CTR*OF
)@@G@@(3) EQU G$CTR(3)+G$CTR(6)       . PRETEND WE SAVED THE ARGS @[@@@@.     OG
)@@G@@@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               ********OH
)@@G@@*********************** @C@@@@.               *                         OI
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               *           ELSE              * @C@@@@.     OJ
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               ********OK
)@@G@@*********************** @[@@@@.     @#@@@@        PROC   *0 @]@@@@ELSE* OL
)@@G@@  NAME@F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING OM
)@@G@@LEVEL @F@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . GET SEQ NUM FOR THISON
)@@G@@ BLOCK@F@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=2)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3        . CATCH NESTING ERROOO
)@@G@@RS    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,3)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LOP
)@@G@@ABL(K,3) .  @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,3)  EQU   $                       . MARK ENDOQ
)@@G@@ OF 'IF' CLAUSE   @F@@@@ DO G$LABL(K,2)=$ , END . EMPTY 'IF' => IGNORE EOR
)@@G@@LSE COMPLETELY    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@     DO G$FLAG(K,4)=0 , I$     074,0OS
)@@G@@4,,,,G$LABL(K,5) . LEAP TO ENDI     @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(OT
)@@G@@K,4) . SET ELSE FLOAT FOR CODE BELOW@D@@@@G$LABL*(K,4)  EQU   $ . MARK SOU
)@@G@@TART OF 'ELSE' USER CODE@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@OV
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * OW
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *           ENDIF   OX
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@OY
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @#@@@@      OZ
)@@G@@  PROC   *0 @]@@@@ENDIF*  NAME@F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)        PA
)@@G@@  . GET CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)       PB
)@@G@@  . GET SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   @F@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=2)=0 , G$$GFL 1PC
)@@G@@,3          . CATCH NESTING ERRORS  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO PD
)@@G@@(G$LABL(K,5)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,5)    @D@@@@G$LABL*(K,5)  EQU   $   PE
)@@G@@      . MARK END OF BLOCK     @G@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       M-1             PF
)@@G@@  . STEP NESTING BACK ONE LEVEL     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. RESTORE GLOBAL FPG
)@@G@@LOAT FOR FOLLOWING BLOX (EFFECTIVE ON PASS 2 ONLY)    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@PH
)@@G@@G$CTR*(2) EQU G$CTR(7)*(G$CTR(2)-G$FLAG(K,5)-G$FLAG(K,4)) . @E@@@@ DO G$PI
)@@G@@CTR(7) , END . ON PASS 2, WE'RE DONE AT THIS POINT    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@PJ
)@@G@@.   ***** PASS 1 ONLY BEYOND THIS POINT *****   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$CTR*PK
)@@G@@(3) EQU G$CTR(3)-1              . ADJUST ARGSAVE STACK POINTER    @[@@@@PL
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@. TABULATE FLOAT FOR SURPRESSED ELSE, IF ANY    @[@@@@.     PM
)@@G@@@H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,4) EQU 0-((G$LABL(K,3)>0)**(G$LABL(K,4)=$)) . 'ELSE' FLOPN
)@@G@@AT (NO -0!!)@G@@@@          RES       G$FLAG(K,4)     . APPLY ELSFLOAT FPO
)@@G@@OR SUCCEEDING CODE@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. CHECK FOR SURPRESSION OF EVERYTHINPP
)@@G@@G (NO CODE AND NO SIDE EFFECTS)     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO ($>G$LABL(K,2)PQ
)@@G@@)++G$FLAG(K,2) , GO G$$I20 . IF NOT, GO CHECK OPTIMIZATION  @E@@@@G$FLAGPR
)@@G@@*(K,5) EQU G$LABL(K,1)-G$LABL(K,2) . TURN OFF 'IF'    @F@@@@          REPS
)@@G@@S       G$LABL(K,1)-$   . ADJUST L.C. APPROPRIATELY   @C@@@@  DO 1 , ENDPT
)@@G@@        . AND TERMINATE GRACEFULLY  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. CHECK FOR POSSIBPU
)@@G@@LE OPTIMIZATION OF THE INITIAL TEST @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$I20*   NAME    PV
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO G$LABL(K,4)=0 ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU $ . IF NO ELSE, PUT IT HERE   PW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU G$LABL(K,3)=G$LABL(K,2) . NO 'IF' CLAPX
)@@G@@USE =>INVERT@E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU    $-G$LABL(K,2)=1   . IMPLIED LINEITPY
)@@G@@EM    @F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,2)++G$FLAG(K,3)=0 , END . DONE IF NO OPTIMIZATIPZ
)@@G@@ON    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. WE'RE GOING TO OPTIMIZE THE JUMP WHEN WE GET BQA
)@@G@@ACK THERE ON PASS 2     @F@@@@. TO INSURE THAT LABELS BELOW THIS POINT AQB
)@@G@@RE OK, WE MUST PERFORCE @E@@@@. DO A TRIAL GENERATION OF THE MODIFIED TEQC
)@@G@@ST SO WE KNOW     @G@@@@. HOW MANY INSTRUCTIONS IT WILL TAKE WHEN WE GENQD
)@@G@@ IT BACK AT THE TOP     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@KK        EQU       G$CTR(3)+1QE
)@@G@@        . GET ARGSAVE INDEX OF MATCHING 'IF'    @F@@@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,JQF
)@@G@@ DO G$ARGS(KK,I) ,P(I,J) EQU +G$ARGS(KK,I,J)    @E@@@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,JQG
)@@G@@ DO G$ARGS(KK,I)    ; FOR ALL SUBFIELDS   @F@@@@  , DO G$ARGS(KK,I,*J) ,QH
)@@G@@P(I,J) EQU *P(I,J) . PRESERVE ASTERISKS   @A@@@@IFNOT     EQU       G$FLQI
)@@G@@AG(K,1)     @F@@@@CXF       EQU       G$FLAG(K,6)   . RETRIEVE COMPLEX CQJ
)@@G@@ONDN FLAG   @F@@@@RVF       EQU       IFNOT--G$FLAG(K,2) . SET OVERALL RQK
)@@G@@EVERSAL FLAG@E@@@@START                 . REMEMBER WHERE BEGINNING OF TEQL
)@@G@@ST WAS@D@@@@ DO 1-G$FLAG(K,3) , G$$TST 1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF $+10 .     @D@@@@QM
)@@G@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)   , G$$TST 1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF      .     @H@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQQN
)@@G@@U       G$CTR(4)-1        . RESTORE INTERNAL CTR USED BY G$$TST   @[@@@@QO
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@. NOW SET ADDRESS ADJUSTMENT FLAGS SO PASS 2 WILL GEN PROPERQP
)@@G@@ CODE @[@@@@.     @G@@@@SIZE      EQU       G$LABL(K,2)-G$LABL(K,1) . SIQQ
)@@G@@ZE OF ORIGINAL TEST     @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU $-START-SIZE       . COMPQR
)@@G@@UTE PASS 2 FLOAT  @H@@@@          RES      0-SIZE            . COMPENSATQS
)@@G@@E L.C. FOR CODE WHICH FOLLOWS @]@@@@        END @B@@@@/.          ******QT
)@@G@@** CASE GROUP  *********@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. ARRAY USAGE IS -QU
)@@G@@-     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.       G$FLAG(K,1) TOTAL NUMBER OF CASE VALUES QV
)@@G@@GIVEN @G@@@@.         ...    2) RUNNING TALLY: NUMBER OF VALUES ON PREVIQW
)@@G@@OUS CASE    @C@@@@.         ...    3) INHIBIT/CALL OPTION FLAG    @E@@@@QX
)@@G@@.         ...    4,X) VALUE OF X'TH SPECIFIED CASEVALUE     @C@@@@.     QY
)@@G@@    ...    5) # OF REMOTE CASES PROCESSED @D@@@@.         ...    6) FLAGQZ
)@@G@@ SET 1 IF NOCHECKING IS ON    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.       G$LABL(K,1) STARRA
)@@G@@T ADDR OF USER NOFIND CODE    @C@@@@.         ...    2) END ADDR OF USERRB
)@@G@@ NOFIND CODE@D@@@@.         ...    3) ULTIMATE EXIT ADDR FROM BLOCK     RC
)@@G@@@E@@@@.         ...    4,X) JUMPTARGET ADDR FOR X'TH CASEVALUE    @E@@@@RD
)@@G@@.         ...    5) RUNNING LABEL: LAST JUMP TO CLOSE A CASE@E@@@@.     RE
)@@G@@    ...    6) BASE ADDR FOR OFFSET INTO JUMP TABLE    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@RF
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.     RG
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               *       RH
)@@G@@   CASENTRY           * @C@@@@.               *                         RI
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     RJ
)@@G@@@B@@@@. SYNTAX--     CASENTRY <AXREG>    OR...  @D@@@@.              CASRK
)@@G@@ENTRY CALLING(,<LINK>) NAME(,<TAG>) @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P     RL
)@@G@@  PROC   *6 @B@@@@CASENTRY*  NAME                       .   @F@@@@K     RM
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SEQUENCE NUM    @D@@@@G$CTR*RN
)@@G@@(1) EQU       K                 . AND UPDATE IT @G@@@@M         EQU     RO
)@@G@@  G$CTR(5)+1        . NESTING LEVEL FOR THIS BLOCK    @E@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQRP
)@@G@@U       M                 . UPDATE THAT, TOO    @G@@@@G$SEQN*(M) EQU    RQ
)@@G@@  K                 . REMEMBER BLOCK SEQUENCE NUMBER  @F@@@@G$TYPE*(M) ERR
)@@G@@QU      3                 . SET BLOCK TYPE TO CASE    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@RS
)@@G@@. DO PRELIMINARY PARSING@[@@@@.     @F@@@@CALOPT     EQU      P(1,1)=CALRT
)@@G@@LING    . ON TO CALL SUBROUTINE     @G@@@@N DO (P-2)*(P>2)              RU
)@@G@@        ; SEARCH ALL BUT 0TH AND 1ST FIELD@F@@@@  , DO P(N+1)=1         RV
)@@G@@              ; IF ONLY ONE SUBFIELD...   @G@@@@    , DO P(N+1,1)=NOCHECRW
)@@G@@KING          ; AND ITS THE NOCHECKING KEYWORD  @H@@@@       ,G$FLAG*(K,RX
)@@G@@6) EQU 1            . SET GLOBAL FLAG FOR ENDCASE FLOAT     @G@@@@N DO (RY
)@@G@@P-2)*(P>2)                      ; SEARCH ALL BUT 0TH AND 1ST FIELD@G@@@@RZ
)@@G@@  , DO P(N+1,1)=NOFINDEXIT            ; AND ITS THE NOFIND EXIT SPEC    SA
)@@G@@@F@@@@     ,NFI(1) EQU N+1                  . REMEMBER WHERE IT APPEAREDSB
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO CALOPT=0 , GO G$$C05              . SKIP THIS IF NSC
)@@G@@ORMAL CASENTRY    @G@@@@BANKSW     EQU      P(3,1)=BASING     . ON IF WESD
)@@G@@ SHOULD SWITCH BANKS    @G@@@@XREG       EQU      P(1,2)+X11*(P(1,2)=0) SE
)@@G@@. LINK REG, DEFAULT => X11    @I@@@@ DO BANKSW**(P(3)>2) , I$ 046,P(3,5)SF
)@@G@@,XREG,P(3,4),3*P(3,*4)+P(3,*3),P(3,3) . LXI     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$C05SG
)@@G@@*    NAME   @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,0) EQU    G$LABL(K,0)+G$CTR(2) . APPLY GLOBASH
)@@G@@L FLOAT     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,0)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,SI
)@@G@@0)    @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,0)  EQU   $                 . MARK START IN CASE WSJ
)@@G@@E'LL INHIBIT@[@@@@.     @E@@@@          RES       CALOPT*G$CTR(6) . ACCOSK
)@@G@@UNT FOR THE LMJ   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$C10*   NAME    @F@@@@ DO G$CTR(6)SL
)@@G@@ , GO G$$C40           . ON PASS 1, SKIP THIS STUFF   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@SM
)@@G@@. ***** PASS 2 ONLY-- GENERATE CHECKING AND THE JUMPTABLE   @[@@@@.     SN
)@@G@@@C@@@@ DO 1-CALOPT , ; IF NOT A SUBROUTINE CALL BLOCK @F@@@@ DO (P(1,1)<SO
)@@G@@A0)++(P(1,1)>A3) , G$$EFL 3,1 . DIE IF NOT OVERLAP REG@[@@@@.     @B@@@@SP
)@@G@@. COMPUTE CHARACTERISTICS OF THE TABLE    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@NUMCA     EQSQ
)@@G@@U       +G$FLAG(K,1)      . NUMBER OF CASES GIVEN     @H@@@@CMAX(1)   EQSR
)@@G@@U       -34359738367      . INIT MAX TO SMALLEST POSSIBLE NUMBER  @H@@@@SS
)@@G@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)>CMAX(1) ,CMAX(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MST
)@@G@@AX    @H@@@@CMIN(1)   EQU       0377777777777     . INIT MIN TO LARGEST SU
)@@G@@POSSIBLE NUMBER   @H@@@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)<CMIN(1) ,CMIN(1) ESV
)@@G@@QU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MIN    @D@@@@OFF     EQU    1-CMIN(1)            SW
)@@G@@  . SET OFFSET    @G@@@@JTSIZ   EQU    CMAX(1)+OFF            . SET TOT SX
)@@G@@TABLE SIZE=RANGE OF VAL @F@@@@JTL       EQU       JTSIZ-(G$FLAG(K,3)=-1)SY
)@@G@@*(G$FLAG(K,4,1)=CMAX(1))@F@@@@ DO CALOPT , DO (CMIN(1)=0)=0 , G$$EFL 3,5SZ
)@@G@@ . MIN VAL NOT ZERO     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. APPLY FLOATS TO LABELS BELONTA
)@@G@@GING TO THIS BLOCK, SET GLOBAL FLOAT@[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$LABL*(K,3) EQU  TB
)@@G@@  G$LABL(K,3)+G$CTR(2) . LAST LBL GETS ONLY GLOBAL FLOAT    @G@@@@PRSIZ TC
)@@G@@    EQU       (CALOPT=0)*(4-3*G$FLAG(K,6)) . SIZE OF PREAMBLE     @G@@@@TD
)@@G@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+(G$FLAG(K,3)<1)*(PRSIZ+JTL)  . SET FLOAT   TE
)@@G@@@E@@@@N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,N) EQU G$LABL(K,N)+G$CTR(2) . APPLY IT    @G@@@@TF
)@@G@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)>0 , END                 . IF OPTIMIZED AWAY, QUIT HERE  TG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. COMPUTE CROSS REFERENCES NEEDED TO GENERATE THE JUMPTH
)@@G@@ TABLE@[@@@@.     @G@@@@ISNF      EQU       G$LABL(K,2)>G$LABL(K,1) . ONTI
)@@G@@=> USER GAVE NOFIND CODE@H@@@@ DO (NFI(1)>0)**ISNF , G$$EFL 3,07    . NOTJ
)@@G@@FIND EXIT FORBIDS NOFIND USER CODE  @G@@@@NFA(1)    EQU       G$LABL(K,3TK
)@@G@@-2*ISNF) . NOFIND ADDR <= ENDCASE/USERCODE@G@@@@ DO NFI(1)>0            TL
)@@G@@              ; IF EXPLICIT NOFIND TARGET GIVEN @E@@@@  ,NFA(1) EQU P(NFTM
)@@G@@I(1),2)             . SET JUMPTARGET TO IT@F@@@@ DO CALOPT              TN
)@@G@@              ; IF WE'RE CALLING A SUBRTNE@G@@@@  ,NFA(1) EQU -1        TO
)@@G@@              . SET MISSING CASE DETECTION FLAG @F@@@@N DO JTSIZ        TP
)@@G@@                    ; FOR ALL JUMPTABLE ENTRIES @G@@@@  ,JT(N) EQU NFA(1TQ
)@@G@@)                   . INITIALIZE TARGET ADDR TO NOFIND@F@@@@N DO NUMCA  TR
)@@G@@                          ; FOR ALL CASEVALUES GIVEN  @G@@@@  ,JT(G$FLAGTS
)@@G@@(K,4,N)+OFF)              ; SET JMPTBL ADDR FOR N'TH VALUE  @G@@@@     ETT
)@@G@@QU G$LABL(K,4,N)+G$CTR(2)       . TO FLOATED ADDR OF TARGET BLOK  @E@@@@TU
)@@G@@N DO JTSIZ                            ; FOR ALL CASE VALUES @F@@@@  , DOTV
)@@G@@ JT(N)=G$CTR(2)                 ; IF TARGET BLOCK IS EMPTY  @G@@@@     ,TW
)@@G@@JT(N) EQU G$LABL(K,3)           . JUMP DIRECTLY TO THE ENDCASE    @G@@@@TX
)@@G@@N DO CALOPT*JTSIZ                     ; FOR ALL CASEVALS OF CALL OPTION TY
)@@G@@@G@@@@  , DO JT(N)=-1                       ; IF NO ACTION GIVEN FOR N'TTZ
)@@G@@H EXIT@G@@@@     , G$$EFL 3,6                     . GIVE MISSING CASE DIUA
)@@G@@AGNOSTIC    @G@@@@. NOW FIXUP FOR LAST CASE OPTIMIZED OUT FROM UNDER EMPUB
)@@G@@TY CASES BEFORE IT@F@@@@OSADR     EQU       G$LABL(K,3)+1     . OVERSHOOUC
)@@G@@T TARGET ADDR     @F@@@@N DO JTSIZ                            ; FOR ALL UD
)@@G@@CASE VALUES GIVEN @G@@@@  , DO JT(N)=OSADR                    ; IF EMPTYUE
)@@G@@ CASE CAUSED OVERSHOOT  @H@@@@    ,JT(N) EQU G$LABL(K,3)            . PAUF
)@@G@@TCH UP EXIT TO REAL ENDBEG LOCN     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. GEN PREAMBLE TO UG
)@@G@@JUMP TABLE, I.E., CHECKING CODE AND JUMP OR CALL@[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO CAUH
)@@G@@LOPT , GO G$$C26                . CALLING OPTION GETS NO PREAMBLE @G@@@@UI
)@@G@@    DO G$FLAG(K,6)>0 , GO G$$C25      . CHECKS INHIBITED GETS ONLY JUMP UJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TLE,XU    P(1,1),CMAX(1)+1  . TEST AGAINST MAX RANGE    UK
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TLE,XU    P(1,1),CMIN(1)    . AND AGAINST THE MIN @G@@@@UL
)@@G@@          J         NFA(1)            . NOFIND EXIT IF OUT AT EITHER ENDUM
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$C25*   NAME    @E@@@@          J         $+OFF,P(1,1)      . JUUN
)@@G@@MP THRU TABLE     @#@@@@    GO G$$C29     @E@@@@G$$C26*   NAME          UO
)@@G@@              . HERE FOR CALLING    @F@@@@FUN       EQU       074-BANKSWUP
)@@G@@*065    . FUNC CODE, LMJ/LIJ/LDJ    @G@@@@JAY       EQU       013-BANKSWUQ
)@@G@@*(P(3,2)=DBANK) . J-DES IS PART OF OPCODE @B@@@@HI        EQU       2*P(UR
)@@G@@2,*2)+P(2,*1)     @D@@@@          I$        FUN,JAY,XREG,P(2,2),HI,P(2,1US
)@@G@@) .   @F@@@@G$$C29*   NAME                        . END OF PREAMBLE GENEUT
)@@G@@RATION@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. NOW ACTUALLY GENERATE THE JUMP TABLE    @[@@@@UU
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,6) EQU    $-CMIN(1)         . ESTABLISH ANCHOR ADDUV
)@@G@@R FOR JMPTBL@G@@@@N DO JTL                              ; FOR ALL ENTRIEUW
)@@G@@S IN THE TABLE    @G@@@@  , J JT(N)                           . TAKE PROUX
)@@G@@VERBIAL FLYING LEAP     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. ***** PASS 1 LEAPS DIRECTLY UY
)@@G@@HERE  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$C40*   NAME    @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU 0-CALOPUZ
)@@G@@T             . REMEMBER CALL OPTION, IF ANY    @H@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)  EQU VA
)@@G@@  $                 . MARK START OF NOFIND CODE, IF ANY     @F@@@@G$FLAGVB
)@@G@@*(K,1) EQU 0                    . NO CASE STMNTS SEEN YET   @G@@@@G$LABLVC
)@@G@@*(K,4,0) EQU  $                 . INITIALIZE LOCAL OPTIMIZATION   @I@@@@VD
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU 0                    . NO VALUES ON NON-EXISTENT PREVIOVE
)@@G@@US CASE     @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@VF
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * VG
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *           CASE    VH
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@VI
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     VJ
)@@G@@@#@@@@P       PROC   *2 @F@@@@CASE*   NAME                          . SPVK
)@@G@@ECS--  <VALUE-LIST>     @F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GEVL
)@@G@@T CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . GEVM
)@@G@@T SEQUENCE NUM OF THIS BLOCK  @E@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=3)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3    VN
)@@G@@  . DIAGNOSE BAD NESTING@F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)>0 , END                 . VO
)@@G@@DONE IF OPTIMIZED AWAY  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@JJ      EQU    +G$FLAG(K,1)   VP
)@@G@@        . GET # OF CASEVALS SO FAR IN THIS GRP  @G@@@@ DO JJ=0 ,G$LABL*(VQ
)@@G@@K,2)  EQU   $       . MARK END OF USER NOFIND CODE    @B@@@@ DO (JJ>0)++VR
)@@G@@(G$FLAG(K,3)>-1) , GO G$$C60 .@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. SPECIAL STUFF FOR 1ST VS
)@@G@@CASE WITH CALLING OPTION@G@@@@.    THE MAX VAL IS MOVED TO THE 1ST POSN VT
)@@G@@SO THAT WE CAN EASILY CHECK   @G@@@@. LATER WHETHER IT IS THE GLOBAL MAXVU
)@@G@@.  IF SO, AND IF THE 1ST BLOCK HAS  @G@@@@. CODE, THEN THE LAST JUMPTBL VV
)@@G@@ENTRY CAN BE OMITTED AND WE CAN INSTEAD   @B@@@@. SIMPLY FALL INTO THE CVW
)@@G@@ODE FOR THIS CASE.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO $>G$LABL(K,1) , G$$GFL 2,5 . NO VX
)@@G@@NOFIND ALLOWED FOR CALL OPTION@E@@@@MAX(1)    EQU       P(1,1)          VY
)@@G@@    . INITIALIZE MAX    @F@@@@N DO P(1) , DO P(1,N)>MAX(1) ,MAX(1) EQU PVZ
)@@G@@(1,N) . FIND MAX VALUE  @F@@@@IMAX(1)   EQU       1                 . INWA
)@@G@@ITIALIZE POSN OF MAXVAL @F@@@@N DO P(1) , DO P(1,N)=MAX(1) ,IMAX(1) EQU WB
)@@G@@N . FIND POSN OF MAXVAL @E@@@@MTEMP     EQU       P(1,1)            . TEWC
)@@G@@MP SAVE 1ST VALUE @E@@@@P(1,1)    EQU       MAX(1)            . FORCE ITWD
)@@G@@ TO MAX     @G@@@@P(1,IMAX(1)) EQU    MTEMP             . EXCHANGE WITH WE
)@@G@@PREVIOUS VALUE    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. CLOSE PREVIOUS CASE   @[@@@@.     WF
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$C60*   NAME    @H@@@@REDUN     EQU       $=G$LABL(K,3)     . ONWG
)@@G@@=> CLOSURE HERE WOULD BE REDUNDANT  @G@@@@GOTSOM EQU $>G$LABL(K,4,JJ)   WH
)@@G@@        . ON IF PRECEDING CASE HAD CODE   @G@@@@ DO (G$FLAG(K,3)<0)**(JJWI
)@@G@@=1)           ; IF 2ND CASE OF CALLING OPTION...@F@@@@    ,G$FLAG*(K,3) WJ
)@@G@@EQU GOTSOM-2        . SET FLAG IF 1ST CASE EMPTY@F@@@@ DO GOTSOM**1-REDUWK
)@@G@@N , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,3) . CLOSE LAST CASE  @H@@@@ DO GOTSOM ,G$LABLWL
)@@G@@*(K,5)   EQU  $     . MARK START USERCODE FOR THIS CASE     @G@@@@G$CTR*WM
)@@G@@(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)-REDUN*GOTSOM    . IF SURPRESSED, NOTE FLOAT@D@@@@WN
)@@G@@N DO (1-GOTSOM)*G$FLAG(K,2) ,G$LABL*(K,4,JJ+1-N) EQU 0@[@@@@.     @B@@@@WO
)@@G@@. TABULATE PARAMETERS FOR THE PRESENT CASE@[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,1)WP
)@@G@@ EQU JJ+P(1)              . UPDATE CASEVAL COUNT@I@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU +WQ
)@@G@@P(1)                . REMEMBER HOW MANY TBL ENTRIES WE'RE USI     @F@@@@WR
)@@G@@N DO P(1) ,G$FLAG*(K,4,JJ+N) EQU +(P(1,N)) . SAVE CASE VALUE(S)   @G@@@@WS
)@@G@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,4,JJ+1)=0)=0 , ; IF NOT OPTIMIZED AWAY ...  WT
)@@G@@@G@@@@  DO (G$LABL(K,4,JJ+1)+G$CTR(2)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,4,JJ+1)+G$CWU
)@@G@@TR(2) @H@@@@N DO     P(1) ,G$LABL*(K,4,JJ+N) EQU $ . SET OUR OWN JUMPTARWV
)@@G@@GET ADDRESSES     @G@@@@ DO (P(2,1)=REMOTESUB)=0 , END          . QUIT UWW
)@@G@@NLESS REMOTESUB CALL    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU    G$FLAG(K,5WX
)@@G@@)+G$CTR(6) . ON PASS 1,  COUNT REMOTE CALLS     @D@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) , ENDWY
)@@G@@                    . AND THAT'S ALL@F@@@@          G$$PRA    P(2,2),G$LWZ
)@@G@@ABL(K,3) . PATCH UP BLOCK EXIT INSTR@E@@@@ DO P(2,3)=VIA ,P(2,2) EQU P(2XA
)@@G@@,4)     . SET XFER TARGET ADDR@F@@@@HERE                                XB
)@@G@@  . REMEMBER WHERE WE ARE     @G@@@@N DO P(1)                           XC
)@@G@@  ; FOR ALL VALUES IN THIS CASE     @G@@@@  , G$$PJT G$LABL(K,6)+P(1,N),XD
)@@G@@P(2,2)  . MAKE JMPTBL POINT TO TARGET     @E@@@@          RES       HEREXE
)@@G@@-$            . RESTORE THE L.C.    @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @E@@@@XF
)@@G@@P         PROC      *1,0              . DO NOTHING ON PASS 1@E@@@@G$$PJTXG
)@@G@@*   NAME                        . PATCH UP JUMP TABLE @F@@@@          REXH
)@@G@@S       P(1,1)-$          . GO BACK TO JUMPTBL ENTRY  @G@@@@          J XI
)@@G@@        P(1,2)            . AND OVERLAY IT WITH NEW TARGET  @#@@@@      XJ
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               **XK
)@@G@@***************************** @C@@@@.               *                   XL
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *          ENDCASE            * @C@@@@XM
)@@G@@.               *                             * @C@@@@.               **XN
)@@G@@***************************** @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROCXO
)@@G@@   *0 @#@@@@ENDCASE*  NAME    @G@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)        XP
)@@G@@  . GET NESTING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M) XQ
)@@G@@        . GET SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   @E@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=3)=0 , G$XR
)@@G@@$GFL 1,3      . DIAGNOSE BAD NESTING@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. COMPUTE TABLE SIXS
)@@G@@ZE SO WE KNOW HOW MUCH FLOAT TO APPLY     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@CALOPT    EQXT
)@@G@@U       G$FLAG(K,3)<0     . SET IF CASENTRY WITH CALLING OPTION   @F@@@@XU
)@@G@@NUMCA     EQU       +G$FLAG(K,1)      . NUMBER OF CASES GIVEN     @H@@@@XV
)@@G@@CMAX(1)   EQU       -34359738367      . INIT MAX TO SMALLEST POSSIBLE NUXW
)@@G@@MBER  @H@@@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)>CMAX(1) ,CMAX(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,XX
)@@G@@4,L) . GET MAX    @H@@@@CMIN(1)   EQU       0377777777777     . INIT MINXY
)@@G@@ TO LARGEST POSSIBLE NUMBER   @H@@@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)<CMIN(1XZ
)@@G@@) ,CMIN(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MIN    @G@@@@JTS(1)   EQU    CMAX(1)-YA
)@@G@@CMIN(1)+1      . SET TOT TABLE SIZE=RANGE OF VAL@F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)=-1YB
)@@G@@ ,JTS(1) EQU JTS(1)-(CMAX(1)=G$FLAG(K,4,1))     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO G$YC
)@@G@@LABL(K,0)=$                     ; IF NO CODE IN ANY CASE BLOK     @G@@@@YD
)@@G@@  , DO G$FLAG(K,5)=0                  ; AND NO REMOTE BLOX EITHER...    YE
)@@G@@@F@@@@    ,G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU 1               . TURN OFF CODE GENERATION  YF
)@@G@@@G@@@@REDUN     EQU       G$LABL(K,5)=$     . ON=> LAST CASE CLOSURE REDYG
)@@G@@UNDANT@G@@@@PRSIZ     EQU       (CALOPT=0)*(4-3*G$FLAG(K,6)) . GET PREAMYH
)@@G@@BLE SIZE    @H@@@@FLOAT     EQU       (G$FLAG(K,3)<1)*(PRSIZ+JTS(1)-REDUYI
)@@G@@N) . FLOAT FOR TABL     @G@@@@          RES       FLOAT*G$CTR(6)    . ONYJ
)@@G@@ PASS 1, APPLY FLOAT TO L.C.  @H@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)-FLOAT*GYK
)@@G@@$CTR(7) . ON P2, APPLY TO GLOBAL FLOAT    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7)YL
)@@G@@ , DO (G$LABL(K,3)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,3)    @H@@@@G$LABL*(K,3)  EQU YM
)@@G@@  $                 . MARK ULTIMATE EXIT POINT FROM BLOCK   @G@@@@G$CTR*YN
)@@G@@(5) EQU       M-1               . UPDATE GLOBAL NESTING LEVEL     @[@@@@YO
)@@G@@.     @]@@@@        END @B@@@@/.       ********* REPEAT GROUP ********* YP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.    THE ARRAY G$FLAG(K,X) IS USED TO KEEPYQ
)@@G@@ FLAGS THROUGOUT  @E@@@@.    THE SCOPE OF THE REPEAT BLOCK. FOR EACH X, YR
)@@G@@THE FLAG IS:@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.       1      INDEX OF 'VARY' FIELD ON SOYS
)@@G@@URCE 'REPEAT' IMAGE     @F@@@@.       2      ON IF THERE IS <LOOP CTL> CYT
)@@G@@ODE WHICH MUST APPEAR   @D@@@@.              AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF TYU
)@@G@@HE LOOP     @E@@@@.       3      INDEX OF 'TO' FIELD IN SOURCE 'REPEAT' YV
)@@G@@IMAGE @F@@@@.       4      INDEX OF 'WHILE' FIELD ON SOURCE 'REPEAT IMAGYW
)@@G@@E     @B@@@@.       5      FLOAT FOR SURPRESSED UNTIL @C@@@@.       6   YX
)@@G@@   INDEX OF 'UNTIL' ON SOURCE IMAGE @B@@@@.       7      SURPRESS EVERYTYY
)@@G@@HING FLAG   @A@@@@.       8      ON=> 'LOOKFOR' FORMAT@C@@@@.       9   YZ
)@@G@@   ON=> BOTTOM OF LOOP CHECKING DONE@E@@@@.       .      FLAGS USED TO CZA
)@@G@@ONTROL POSITIONING AND FLOAT: @D@@@@.      10      ON=> ENTRY CONDITION ZB
)@@G@@IS JUMP TO WHILE  @B@@@@.      11      ON => SURPRESS WHILE AT TOP@B@@@@ZC
)@@G@@.      12      ON=> INVERT ESCAPE TEST    @E@@@@.      13      ON=> CLOSZD
)@@G@@E ESCAPE CLAUSE (WITH JUMP TO EXIT) @G@@@@.      14      ON=> CLOSE OTHEZE
)@@G@@RWISE/UNTIL CLAUSE (WITH JUMP TO LOOP)    @C@@@@.      15      ON=> SURPZF
)@@G@@RESS WHILE AT BOTTOM    @C@@@@.      16      FLOAT FOR WHILE SURPRESSED ZG
)@@G@@AT TOP@B@@@@.      17      FLOAT FOR INVERTED ESCAPE  @D@@@@.      18   ZH
)@@G@@   FLOAT FOR WHILE SURPRESSED AT BOTTOM   @E@@@@.      19      ON=> CODEZI
)@@G@@ IN LOOP WILL APPEAR BELOW ESCAPE   @C@@@@.      20      GLOBAL FLOAT ATZJ
)@@G@@ ENTRY TO BLOCK   @E@@@@.      21      1+FLOAT FOR INITIAL JUMP FALLTHRUZK
)@@G@@ (0=>NONE)  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.    THE ARRAY G$LABL(K,X) IS USED TO LABEZL
)@@G@@L VARIOUS CONTROL @D@@@@.    POINTS IN THE GENERATED CODE.  VALUES OF X ZM
)@@G@@ARE:  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.       1      LOCATION OF TOP-OF-LOOP WHILE TESZN
)@@G@@T     @D@@@@.       2      LOCATION OF TOP-OF-LOOP <VARY> CODE    @F@@@@ZO
)@@G@@.       3      START USER-SPECIFIED REPEATED CODE (TOP OF LOOP)   @G@@@@ZP
)@@G@@.       4      LOCATION OF CONDITION TEST AT ESCAPE (0=>NO ESCAPE STMNT)ZQ
)@@G@@@D@@@@.       5      START USER-SPECIFIED ESCAPE CLAUSE     @D@@@@.     ZR
)@@G@@  6      START USER-SPECIFIED OTHERWISE CODE    @D@@@@.       7      LOCZS
)@@G@@ATION OF BOTTOM-OF-LOOP WHILE TEST  @D@@@@.       8      LOCATION OF BOTZT
)@@G@@TOM-OF-LOOP <VARY> CODE @C@@@@.       9      START USER-SPECIFIED ATEND ZU
)@@G@@CODE  @C@@@@.      10      ULTIMATE BLOCK EXIT TARGET ADDR  @[@@@@.     ZV
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. THE FOLLOWING ARCANE RULES ARE FOLLOWED IN POSITIONIZW
)@@G@@NG THE VARIOUS    @ @@@@. CODE GENERATED FOR A LOOP:  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ZX
)@@G@@. 1) <UNTIL> CODE ALWAYS APPEARS AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF THE LOOP     ZY
)@@G@@@F@@@@.            SO WE CAN AVOID JUMPING AROUND IT AT LOOP ENTRY.     ZZ
)@@G@@@B@@@@. 2) <VARY>  CODE MOVES AROUND AS FOLLOWS:@G@@@@.        A)  IF THAA
)@@G@@E SENSE (UP/DOWN) IS KNOWN, THEN THE CODE IS PLACED   @G@@@@.           AB
)@@G@@ ACCORDING TO THE PREFERENCE OF THE LOOP INSTRUCTION, E.G.  @D@@@@.     AC
)@@G@@       JGD AT THE BOTTOM, SEARCHES AT THE TOP.  @G@@@@.        B)  IF THAD
)@@G@@E SENSE IS UNKNOWN, THE CODE APPEARS AT BOTH TOP AND  @F@@@@.           AE
)@@G@@ BOTTOM, WITH THE BRANCH SENSE APPROPRIATELY INVERTED.@G@@@@.           AF
)@@G@@ IMMEDIATELY BEFORE THE PRIMARY CODE (BOTTOM), A SIGN TEST  @G@@@@.     AG
)@@G@@       IS INSERTED WHICH DETERMINES WHICH OF THE TWO VARIATIONS   @ @@@@AH
)@@G@@.            WILL BE EXECUTED.@G@@@@. 3) <WHILE> CODE ALSO MOVES AROUND.AI
)@@G@@ WE DEFINE A <WHILE> TEST WHICH IS  @G@@@@.            PERFORMED IN A SIAJ
)@@G@@NGLE INSTRUCTION WHICH HAS AN INVERSE     @G@@@@.            (I.E. A CONAK
)@@G@@DITIONAL JUMP) AS 'OPTIMIZEABLE'. POSITIONING   @E@@@@.            THEN AL
)@@G@@DEPENDS UPON OTHER CONDITIONS AS FOLLOWS- @G@@@@.            NORMAL POSIAM
)@@G@@TIONING IS AT THE BOTTOM, WITH A (ONE TIME) JUMP@H@@@@.            TO THAN
)@@G@@E WHILE TEST INSERTED AT THE TOP. IF THERE IS AN ESCAPE     @G@@@@.     AO
)@@G@@       CONDITION WHICH WOULD OTHERWISE FALL THROUGH, HOWEVER, THE @H@@@@AP
)@@G@@.            JUMP AROUND THE WHILE IS AVOIDED BY PUTTING IT AT THE TOP AAQ
)@@G@@ND    @H@@@@.            INVERTING THE ESCAPE TEST ACCORDINGLY. IF THEREAR
)@@G@@ IS NO <VARY>     @G@@@@.            CODE AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF THE AS
)@@G@@LOOP, AND THE WHILE     @G@@@@.            TEST IS OPTIMIZEABLE, THEN THAT
)@@G@@E INITIAL JUMP TO THE WHILE   @G@@@@.            TEST IS REPLACED BY THEAU
)@@G@@ TEST ITSELF. IN THIS CASE, THE     @G@@@@.            TEST WILL APPEAR AV
)@@G@@AT BOTH THE TOP AND BOTTOM OF THE LOOP.   @E@@@@. 4) ESCAPE  AN ESCAPE TAW
)@@G@@EST CAN BE MODIFIED BOTH BECAUSE OF @G@@@@.            THE ABOVE, OR BECAX
)@@G@@AUSE THE CLAUSE IS EMPTY. IF THE CODE     @F@@@@.            FOLLOWING TAY
)@@G@@HE TEST IS NOT IN THE LOOP (I.E. IS A NON-@F@@@@.            VACUOUS ESCAZ
)@@G@@APE CLAUSE OR IS THE END OF THE LOOP),    @F@@@@.            THE ESCAPE BA
)@@G@@TEST BRANCHES TO STAY IN THE LOOP. IF     @G@@@@.            THE FOLLOWIBB
)@@G@@NG CODE IS IN THE LOOP (I.E. VACUOUS ESCAPE     @G@@@@.            AND NBC
)@@G@@ON-VACUOUS OTHERWISE), THEN THE SENSE IS REVERSED     @F@@@@.           BD
)@@G@@ SO THAT THE BRANCH CONDITION GOES COMPLETELY OUT OF  @^@@@@.           BE
)@@G@@ THE BLOCK. @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               **************************BF
)@@G@@***** @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@.     BG
)@@G@@          *           REPEAT            * @C@@@@.               *       BH
)@@G@@                      * @C@@@@.               **************************BI
)@@G@@***** @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *12@]@@@@REPEAT* NAME@[@@@@.     BJ
)@@G@@@E@@@@K         EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . BUMP BLOCK COUNTER  @F@@@@BK
)@@G@@G$CTR*(1) EQU       K                 . SAVE UPDATED BLOCK COUNT  @F@@@@BL
)@@G@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)+1        . BUMP GLOBAL NESTING LEVEL @F@@@@BM
)@@G@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       M                 . SAVE NEW NESTING LEVEL    @F@@@@BN
)@@G@@G$SEQN*(M) EQU      K                 . SAVE SEQ NO OF THIS BLOCK @F@@@@BO
)@@G@@G$TYPE*(M) EQU      4                 . SET BLOCK TYPE TO REPEAT  @[@@@@BP
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@. APPLY FLOATS TO LABELS IN THIS BLOCK    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@BQ
)@@G@@ DO G$CTR(6) , GO G$$R10           . ON PASS 1, FLOAT MEANS NOTHING     BR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,20) EQU   G$CTR(2)          . SAVE INITIAL FBS
)@@G@@LOAT  @H@@@@ESCF      EQU       G$LABL(K,4)       . REMEMBER ENTRY VALUEBT
)@@G@@ OF ESCAPE FLAG   @H@@@@FALLF     EQU       (G$FLAG(K,21)>0)*(1-G$FLAG(KBU
)@@G@@,21)) . GET FALLTHRU FLOAT    @H@@@@N DO 10 ,G$LABL*(K,N) EQU G$LABL(K,NBV
)@@G@@)+G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,10) . GLOBAL, JUMPENTR@I@@@@N DO 9 ,G$LABL*(K,N+1) EBW
)@@G@@QU G$LABL(K,N+1)+G$FLAG(K,16)+FALLF . SURPRESS TOP WHILE    @G@@@@N DO 6BX
)@@G@@ ,G$LABL*(K,N+4) EQU G$LABL(K,N+4)+G$FLAG(K,17) . ESCAPE INVERSION@G@@@@BY
)@@G@@N DO 5 ,G$LABL*(K,N+5) EQU G$LABL(K,N+5)+G$FLAG(K,13) . ESCAPE CLOSURE  BZ
)@@G@@@I@@@@N DO 4 ,G$LABL*(K,N+6) EQU G$LABL(K,N+6)+G$FLAG(K,14)+G$FLAG(K,5) CA
)@@G@@. OTHER/UNTIL     @G@@@@N DO 3 ,G$LABL*(K,N+7) EQU G$LABL(K,N+7)+G$FLAG(CB
)@@G@@K,18) . BOTTOM WHILE    @E@@@@ DO ESCF=0 ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU 0 . IF NO ESCCC
)@@G@@APE, RESTORE FLAG @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. ***** SYNTAX ANALYSIS ***** @[@@@@CD
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$R10*   NAME    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@C(1)      EQCE
)@@G@@U  1                      . INITIALIZE CURRENT FIELD COUNTER@G@@@@KW(1) CF
)@@G@@    EQU  P(1,1)                 . AND CURRENT LEADING KEYWORD     @[@@@@CG
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@.               EXAMINE 'WHILE' FIELD     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@CH
)@@G@@G$$R50* NAME                          . MARK START OF WHILE TEST  @G@@@@CI
)@@G@@WI      EQU    KW(1)=WHILE            . FIELD INDEX OF 'WHILE' OR ZERO  CJ
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,4) EQU WI                 . REMEMBER INDEX IN CASE DEFERCK
)@@G@@RED   @C@@@@ DO WI=0 , GO G$$R59 . IF NO 'WHILE', WE'RE DONE@C@@@@WYNOT CL
)@@G@@    EQU       (P(2)=1)**(P(2,1)=NOT) .    @H@@@@WC        EQU       ((P(CM
)@@G@@3+WYNOT,1)=OR)++(P(3+WYNOT,1)=AND))**(P(3+WYNOT)=1)   @F@@@@C(1)    EQU CN
)@@G@@   3+WYNOT+2*WC                 . UPDATE FIELD POINTER@F@@@@KW(1)   EQU CO
)@@G@@   P(C(1),1)              . KEYWORD FOR NEXT FIELD    @H@@@@G$$R59* NAMECP
)@@G@@                          . END PROCESSING OF 'WHILE' CONDITION   @[@@@@CQ
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@.       EXAMINE <LOOP CTL> FIELD, LOADING REGS IF NECESSARY CR
)@@G@@@D@@@@. NOTE: THE <LOOP CONTROL> ANALYSIS SUBROUTINE G$$LAN @E@@@@. SETSCS
)@@G@@ THE FLAGS FI(X) USED BELOW.  FOR THEIR DEFINITIONS,  @ @@@@. SEE THE COCT
)@@G@@DE FOR G$$LAN     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.       SEE IF THIS IS A HARDWARE SECU
)@@G@@ARCH SPEC   @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$R60* NAME                          . MACV
)@@G@@RK START PROCESSING OF <LOOP CNTRL> SP    @F@@@@ DO (KW(1)=LOOKFOR)=0 , CW
)@@G@@GO G$$R61 . IF NOT LOOKFOR, GO TRY 'VARY' @I@@@@VI      EQU    C(1)+2   CX
)@@G@@              . IN THIS FMT, 'VARY' FOLLOWS LOOKFOR AND     @F@@@@ DO (PCY
)@@G@@(VI,1)>VARY)++(P(VI,1)<LOOKFOR) , G$$EFL 2,010 . CHECK IT   @G@@@@P(VI,1CZ
)@@G@@) EQU    LOOKFOR                . FORCE KEYWORD FOR USE BY G$$LAN @H@@@@DA
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,8) EQU 1                 . SET FLAG ALLOWING UNCONDITIONAL ESCDB
)@@G@@APE   @A@@@@ GO G$$R62 . THEN GO PROCESS IT     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$$R61DC
)@@G@@* NAME                          . TRY A NORMAL 'VARY' FIELD @F@@@@VI    DD
)@@G@@  EQU    C(1)*((KW(1)>JMGI-1)**(KW(1)<VARY+1)) . FIELD INDEX@D@@@@ DO VIDE
)@@G@@=0 , GO G$$R69 . SKIP THIS IF FIELD NOT GIVEN   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$R62DF
)@@G@@* NAME@E@@@@        G$$LAN                . ANALYZE THE LOOP CTL FIELD  DG
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU FI(5)              . REMEMBER IF IT HAS DEFERRED DH
)@@G@@CODE  @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU FI(3)              . NOTE FIELD IN WHICH 'TDI
)@@G@@O' SPEC APPEARS   @H@@@@C(1)    EQU    FI(7)+1                . SET FIELDJ
)@@G@@D OF NEXT (I.E. UNTIL) GROUP  @F@@@@KW(1)   EQU    P(C(1),1)            DK
)@@G@@  . AND ITS FUNCT FLAG WORD   @]@@@@G$$R69* NAME@G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,1) EQU VDL
)@@G@@I                 . SAVE INDEX OF VARY FIELD, IF ANY  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@DM
)@@G@@.              SCAN 'UNTIL' FIELD   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,6) EQU  DN
)@@G@@  C(1)*(KW(1)=UNTIL). EXTERNALIZE SO WE KNOW IT WAS GIVEN   @[@@@@.     DO
)@@G@@@A@@@@.     ***** CODE GENERATION *****   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$R80* NAMEDP
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,10) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,7) . ENTER WITH JUMP TO WDQ
)@@G@@HILE/VARY   @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,10) . APPLY FLOADR
)@@G@@T, IF ANY   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)  EQU   $        . MARK START DS
)@@G@@OF WHILE TEST     @H@@@@ DO (WI>0)**1-G$FLAG(K,11) , G$$TST 2+WYNOT,WC,WDT
)@@G@@YNOT G$LABL(K,9) . GEN IT     @D@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+((WI>0)DU
)@@G@@**G$FLAG(K,11)) . @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,16) . AND DV
)@@G@@APPLY THE FLOAT   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. GENERATE LOOP <VARY> CODE, IF ANY DW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,2)  EQU   $         . MARK START OF 2NDARY LDX
)@@G@@OOP CHECK   @C@@@@ DO VI>0 , ; IF THERE IS LOOP VARIATION CODE    @G@@@@DY
)@@G@@ DO (P(VI,1)=LOOKFOR)++((FI(5)=FI(6))=0) , ; AND SOME OR ALL IS HERE    DZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@        G$$LGE VI,FI(3),FI(4) G$LABL(K,9),1 . GENERATE IT   @F@@@@EA
)@@G@@ DO G$LABL(K,2)<$ ,G$FLAG*(K,21) EQU 0 . IF ANY, CAN'T FALL THRU  @[@@@@EB
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@. FINAL CLEANUP   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          G$$SVA        EC
)@@G@@              . SAVE ARGS FOR LATER @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,9) EQU 0            ED
)@@G@@     . CLEAR ENDCHECK DONE FLAG     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,3)EE
)@@G@@=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,3)    @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,3)  EQU   $         . MARKEF
)@@G@@ START OF USER'S CODE   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@EG
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               ******************************* EH
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@.           EI
)@@G@@    *           ESCAPE            * @C@@@@.               *             EJ
)@@G@@                * @C@@@@.               ******************************* EK
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *4 @#@@@@ESCAPE*  NAME     EL
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NEEM
)@@G@@STING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . AND SEQUENCE NEN
)@@G@@O OF THIS BLOCK   @E@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=4)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3 . CATCH NESTINGEO
)@@G@@ ERRORS     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,4)=$)=0 , G$$DEP
)@@G@@FL G$LABL(K,4)    @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,4)  EQU   $        . MARK START OF ESCEQ
)@@G@@APE TEST    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@TBOT      EQU       G$FLAG(K,6)>0     . ONER
)@@G@@ => TEST AT LOGICAL BOTTOM (UNTIL)  @H@@@@TTOP      EQU       (G$FLAG(K,ES
)@@G@@1)>0)++(G$FLAG(K,4)>0) . ON => TESTS AT LGL TOP @H@@@@ DO TTOP**TBOT , GET
)@@G@@$$GFL 2,1               . CAN'T HAVE CAKE AND EAT IT TOO    @G@@@@G$FLAGEU
)@@G@@*(K,8) EQU G$FLAG(K,8)**(P(1)=0) . UNCONDITIONAL (LOOKFOR) FLAG   @G@@@@EV
)@@G@@ DO G$FLAG(K,8) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,10) . UNCONDITIONAL => LEAP OUT EW
)@@G@@@C@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,8) , GO G$$E10 . THEN GO CLEAN UP  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@EX
)@@G@@ DO (P(1,1)=WHEN)=0 , G$$EFL 3,4 . SYNTAX ERROR IF NO 'WHEN'@F@@@@WHENOTEY
)@@G@@    EQU       (P(2)=1)**(P(2,1)=NOT) . ON FOR NOT CONDITION @H@@@@CFLG  EZ
)@@G@@  EQU    P>3+WHENOT                      . ON FOR COMPOUND CONDITION    FA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. ON PASS 1, BOTH SENSES OF THE TEST ARE GENERATED, SOFB
)@@G@@ WE CAN     @F@@@@. DETERMINE THE FLOAT TO USE IF REVERSAL OCCURS. ON PAFC
)@@G@@SS 2, ONLY  @A@@@@. THE DESIRED SENSE IS GENERATED    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@FD
)@@G@@ DO G$CTR(6)++G$FLAG(K,12) , ; PASS 1 ALWAYS, PASS 2 IF REVERSED  @I@@@@FE
)@@G@@    G$$TST 2+WHENOT,CFLG,WHENOT G$LABL(K,1+5*G$FLAG(K,19)) . JUMP=> KEEPFF
)@@G@@ LOOPIN     @F@@@@SIZE      EQU       $-G$LABL(K,4)     . LENGTH OF REVEFG
)@@G@@RSED TEST   @E@@@@          RES      0-G$CTR(6)*SIZE . THEN RES TEST AWAFH
)@@G@@Y     @H@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+G$CTR(7)+G$FLAG(K,7) . KEEP G$$FI
)@@G@@TST CTR IN PHASE  @H@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,12)++G$FLAG(K,7)=0 , ; PASS1 ALWAYSFJ
)@@G@@, 2 IF NOT REVERSED/SURPRESSED@G@@@@    G$$TST 2+WHENOT,CFLG,1-WHENOT G$FK
)@@G@@LABL(K,10) . JUMP=> EXIT FROM LOOP  @E@@@@WIZE      EQU       $-G$LABL(KFL
)@@G@@,4)     . SIZE OF 2ND TEST    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,FM
)@@G@@7) EQU    SIDE(1)           . PASS 1: SET SIDE EFFECT @H@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQFN
)@@G@@U       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,17) . PASS2: APPLY FLOAT FOR ENCLOSED BL@E@@@@FO
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,17) EQU  SIZE-WIZE . PASS 1: GET FLOAT, 2=>NOISE  @[@@@@.     FP
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$E10*   NAME    @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,5)  EQU   $           . MARK STAFQ
)@@G@@RT OF USER'S ESCAPE CODE@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@FR
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * FS
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *         OTHERWISE FT
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@FU
)@@G@@.               *           ATEND             * @C@@@@.               * FV
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *           ENDREP  FW
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@FX
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     FY
)@@G@@@#@@@@Y       PROC   *1 @^@@@@OTHERWISE* NAME     0   @^@@@@ATEND*    NAFZ
)@@G@@ME      1   @^@@@@ENDREP*   NAME      2   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@M         EQGA
)@@G@@U       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQGB
)@@G@@U       G$SEQN(M)         . AND SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   @E@@@@ DO (GGC
)@@G@@$TYPE(M)=4)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3 . CATCH NESTING ERRORS     @F@@@@ DO G$LABL(KGD
)@@G@@,5)=0 ,G$LABL*(K,5) EQU $ . FIXUP FOR MISSING ESCAPE  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@GE
)@@G@@. CLOSE DANGLING ESCAPE, IF REQUIRED@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,13) ,GF
)@@G@@ I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,10) . PASS2: LEAP OUT    @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU     GG
)@@G@@  G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,13) . APPLY CLOSURE FLOAT   @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,13) EQU GH
)@@G@@  0                 . REMEMBER WE'VE DONE THIS  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. ****GI
)@@G@@ OTHERWISE GETS OFF THE TRAIN HERE ...    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO Y(0,0)>0GJ
)@@G@@ , GO G$$Z10              . IF ATEND OR ENDREP, KEEP MOVING @H@@@@ DO G$GK
)@@G@@LABL(K,4)=0 , G$$GFL 2,2            . OTHERWISE INVALID IF NO ESCAPE    GL
)@@G@@@E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,6)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,6) 1  @F@@@@GM
)@@G@@G$LABL*(K,6)  EQU   $         . MARK START OF 'OTHERWISE' CODE    @B@@@@GN
)@@G@@ DO 1 , END         . THAT'S ALL FOLKS    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. **** ATENDGO
)@@G@@/ENDREP LUMBER ONWARD...@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         CLOSE LOOP: GEN CTL GP
)@@G@@CODE WHICH PREFERS PHYSICAL BOTTOM  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$Z10*   NAME    GQ
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,9) , GO G$$Z50          . IF ITS TUESDAY, THIS MUST BGR
)@@G@@E ENDREP    @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,9) EQU 1                 . REMEMBER WE'VE BEGS
)@@G@@EN HERE     @F@@@@ DO G$LABL(K,6)=0 ,G$LABL*(K,6) EQU $ . DEFAULT START GT
)@@G@@OF OTHERWISE@G@@@@KK        EQU       G$CTR(3)          . GET POINTER INGU
)@@G@@TO ARGSAVE STACK  @H@@@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,J DO G$ARGS(KK,I) ,P(I,J) EQU +GV
)@@G@@G$ARGS(KK,I,J) . GET ARGS     @E@@@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,J DO G$ARGS(KK,I)  GW
)@@G@@  ; FOR ALL SUBFIELDS   @F@@@@  , DO G$ARGS(KK,I,*J) ,P(I,J) EQU *P(I,J)GX
)@@G@@ . PRESERVE ASTERISKS   @G@@@@G$CTR*(3) EQU       KK-1              . THGY
)@@G@@EN MOVE STACK POINTER BACK    @I@@@@ DO (Y(0,0)=1)**(G$ARGS(KK)=0) , G$$GZ
)@@G@@GFL 2,3        . ATEND UNREACHABLE IF NO ARG    @G@@@@LL      EQU    G$FHA
)@@G@@LAG(K,2)          . ON IF ANY <VARY> CODE WAS DEFERRED@H@@@@DFER      EQHB
)@@G@@U       LL++(G$FLAG(K,4)>0) . ON IF DEFFERED CODE OF ANY TYPE     @[@@@@HC
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@. HANDLE UNTIL CONDITIONS. THEY CAN HAVE EITHER BRANCH SENSEHD
)@@G@@:     @G@@@@.   A) IF WHILE/VARY CODE WILL FOLLOW, UNTIL SUCCESS LEAPS THE
)@@G@@O ATEND     @E@@@@.   B) IF NOT (A), THEN UNTIL FAILURE LEAPS TO TOP OF HF
)@@G@@LOOP  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@UNORG                                 . MARK ORIHG
)@@G@@GIN OF UNTIL TESTS, IF ANY    @G@@@@UN        EQU       G$FLAG(K,6)     HH
)@@G@@. GET INDEX INTO P OF UNTIL SPECS   @B@@@@ DO UN=0 , GO G$$Z30          HI
)@@G@@        .   @G@@@@KILL      EQU       G$CTR(7)**G$FLAG(K,7) . ON IF SURPHJ
)@@G@@RESSING ALL CODE  @G@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,5) . APPLYHK
)@@G@@ UNTIL SURPRESS FLOAT   @F@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+KILL     . COHL
)@@G@@UNT SURPRESSED UNTIL    @E@@@@ DO KILL , GO G$$Z30                   . AHM
)@@G@@ND FORGET THE REST@F@@@@UNN       EQU       (P(UN+1)=1)**(P(UN+1,1)=NOT)HN
)@@G@@ . SET NOT FLAG   @I@@@@UNC       EQU       (P(UN+UNN+2)=1)**((P(UN+UNN+HO
)@@G@@2,1)=OR)++(P(UN+UNN+2,1)=AND)) .    @D@@@@  G$$TST UN+UNN+1,UNC,DFER--UNHP
)@@G@@N G$LABL(K,1+9*DFER)    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. CLOSE DANGLING OTHERWISE/UNTHQ
)@@G@@IL    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$Z30*   NAME    @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU    UNORHR
)@@G@@G-$           . GET FLOAT FOR SURPRESSED UNTIL  @E@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,14) ,HS
)@@G@@ I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,1) . JUMP TO TOP   @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTHT
)@@G@@R(2)+G$FLAG(K,14) . FLOAT FOLLOWING CODE  @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,14) EQU   0   HU
)@@G@@              . REMEMBER WE DID THIS@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. HANDLE WHILE CONHV
)@@G@@DITIONS.  THESE CAN BE SURPRESSED OR CAN BRANCH TWO   @F@@@@. WAYS; FORTHW
)@@G@@UNATELY, THE BRANCH SENSE IS KNOWN ON PASS 1 (LL):    @F@@@@.  A) IF <VAHX
)@@G@@RY> CODE FOLLOWS, THEN WHILE FAILURE JUMPS TO ATEND   @D@@@@.  B) IF NOTHY
)@@G@@ (A), WHILE SUCCESS JUMPS TO TOP OF LOOP  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,7)HZ
)@@G@@  EQU   $        . MARK START OF BOTTOM-OF-LOOP WHILE @B@@@@. NOTE: IF WIA
)@@G@@HILE EXISTS, ITS ALWAYS SPEC 1@B@@@@WYNOT     EQU       (P(2)=1)**(P(2,1IB
)@@G@@)=NOT)@H@@@@WC        EQU       ((P(3+WYNOT,1)=OR)++(P(3+WYNOT,1)=AND))*IC
)@@G@@*(P(3+WYNOT)=1)   @G@@@@ DO (G$FLAG(K,4)>0)**1-G$FLAG(K,15) , ; IF EXISTID
)@@G@@S AND NOT SURPRESSED-   @D@@@@        G$$TST 2+WYNOT,WC,LL=WYNOT G$LABL(IE
)@@G@@K,2+7*LL)   @F@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+G$FLAG(K,15) . COUNT SURPIF
)@@G@@RESSED WHILE@H@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,18) . APPLY WHILIG
)@@G@@E SURPRESSION FLOAT     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. GENERATE <VARY> CODE  @[@@@@IH
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,8)  EQU   $        . MARK START OF BOTTOM OF LOOP II
)@@G@@VARY  @H@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU G$FLAG(K,7)++(G$FLAG(K,1)>0) IJ
)@@G@@. NOTE SIDE EFFEC @D@@@@ DO LL , G$$LGE G$FLAG(K,1),G$FLAG(K,3) G$LABL(KIK
)@@G@@,3)   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU G$FLAG(K,7)++SIDEIL
)@@G@@(1) . NOTE SIDE EFFECTS @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,9)=$)=0 , G$$DIM
)@@G@@FL G$LABL(K,9) 2  @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,9)  EQU   $         . MARK START OF USIN
)@@G@@ER ATEND CODE     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. END PROCESSING OF LOOP TERMINATIONIO
)@@G@@ CONDITIONS @[@@@@.     @D@@@@ DO Y(0,0)=1 , END  . ATEND STATEMENT FINIIP
)@@G@@SHES UP HERE@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. CLEANUP FOR ENDREP STATEMENT@[@@@@.     IQ
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$Z50*   NAME    @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,10)=$)=0 , G$$IR
)@@G@@DFL G$LABL(K,10) 3@D@@@@G$LABL*(K,10) EQU   $          . SET BLOCK EXIT IS
)@@G@@LABEL @E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$FLAG(K,20)      . RESTORE GLOBAL FLOATIT
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU  M-1                    . DECREMENT GLOBAL NESTING LIU
)@@G@@EVEL  @C@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , END . ON PASS 2, WE'RE DONE HERE @[@@@@.     IV
)@@G@@@E@@@@. ***** PASS 1 ONLY: DETERMINE POSITIONING AND OPTIMIZATIONS@[@@@@IW
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. SET FLAGS INDICATING WHETHER USER PUT ANY CODEIX
)@@G@@ IN SPECIFIC CLAUSES    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ESCAPP    EQU       G$LABL(K,4IY
)@@G@@)>0     . ON=>ESCAPE STMNT APPEARED @H@@@@RVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,3IZ
)@@G@@)=G$LABL(K,5-ESCAPP) . ON=> NOTHING AFTER REPEAT@H@@@@EVAC      EQU     JA
)@@G@@  G$LABL(K,5)=G$LABL(K,6) . ON=> USER ESCAPE CLAUSE VACUOUS @H@@@@UOVAC JB
)@@G@@    EQU       G$LABL(K,6)=G$LABL(K,7)+G$FLAG(K,5) . ON=> NO USER 'OTHER JC
)@@G@@@I@@@@OVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,6)=G$LABL(K,7) . ON=> EMPTY OTHERWISEJD
)@@G@@/UNTIL CLAUSE     @H@@@@AVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,9)=G$LABL(K,10) . OJE
)@@G@@N=> USER ATEND CLAUSE VACUOUS @[@@@@.     @F@@@@NOKILL    EQU       G$FLJF
)@@G@@AG(K,7)++1-(RVAC**EVAC**UOVAC**AVAC) .    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@VATBOT    EQJG
)@@G@@U       G$FLAG(K,2)       . ON=> SOME (OR ALL) <VARY> AT BOTTOM   @H@@@@JH
)@@G@@LOOBOT    EQU       VATBOT++1-OVAC  . ON=> SOME LOOP CODE WILL BE AT BOTJI
)@@G@@TOM   @G@@@@EFOLLO    EQU       LOOBOT++1-AVAC  . ON=> SOMETHING WILL FOJJ
)@@G@@LLOW ESCAPE @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. COMPUTE OPTIMUM POSITIONING OF WHILE (CAJK
)@@G@@N BE TOP, BOTTOM, OR BOTH)    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@WHSPEC    EQU       G$FLJL
)@@G@@AG(K,4)>0     . ON IF WHILE SPECIFICATION GIVEN @H@@@@WONET     EQU     JM
)@@G@@  1=G$LABL(K,2)-G$LABL(K,1) . ON => WHILE IS ONE INST AT T  @G@@@@WONEB JN
)@@G@@    EQU       1=G$LABL(K,8)-G$LABL(K,7) . ON => ONE INSTR AT BOT  @[@@@@JO
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@WHIBOT    EQU       (EFOLLO++1-ESCAPP)**NOKILL . ON=> IF WHIJP
)@@G@@LE, ALLOW AT BOTTO@I@@@@WHISBO    EQU       WHSPEC**WHIBOT    . ON => WHJQ
)@@G@@ILE WILL REALLY APPEAR AT BOTTOM    @H@@@@WHITOP    EQU       (WONET**WOJR
)@@G@@NEB**1-VATBOT++1-WHIBOT)**NOKILL . 0N=>ALLOW    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. SET JS
)@@G@@GLOBAL SURPRESS FLAGS AND FLOATS FOR WHILE OPTIMIZATION     @[@@@@.     JT
)@@G@@@E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,11) EQU   WHSPEC**1-WHITOP . ON => SURPRESS AT TOP@H@@@@JU
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,16) EQU   (G$LABL(K,1)-G$LABL(K,2))*G$FLAG(K,11) . TOP SURPRESJV
)@@G@@S FLOA@F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,15) EQU   WHSPEC**1-WHIBOT . ON=> SURPRESS AT BOTTJW
)@@G@@OM    @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,18) EQU   (G$LABL(K,7)-G$LABL(K,8))*G$FLAG(K,15) .JX
)@@G@@ BOT SURPRESS FLOA@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. COMPUTE VARIOUS FLAGS FOR ESCAPE OJY
)@@G@@PTIMIZATION AND CLOSURE @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,19) EQU   LOOBOT++WHJZ
)@@G@@ISBO    . ON=>LOOP CODE FOLLOWS     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,12) EQU   (G$FLAG(K,KA
)@@G@@19)**EVAC=0)**NOKILL . ON=>JUMP TO KEEP GOING   @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,17) EQU KB
)@@G@@  G$FLAG(K,17)*G$FLAG(K,12) . SET FLOAT TO USE  @F@@@@ DO 1-NOKILL ,G$FLKC
)@@G@@AG*(K,17) EQU ESCAPP*(G$LABL(K,4)-G$LABL(K,5)) .@I@@@@G$FLAG*(K,13) EQU KD
)@@G@@  NOKILL**ESCAPP**G$FLAG(K,12)**(EFOLLO++WHISBO) . CLOSURE FLAG   @[@@@@KE
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. SET FLAG FOR GENERATION OF JUMP TO WHILE/VARY AT TOP (INITKF
)@@G@@IAL ENTRY)  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,10) EQU   (VATBOT++1-WHITOP**WHSKG
)@@G@@PEC)**NOKILL . ON=> GEN ENTRY JUMP  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. FOR IMMEDIATE JGKH
)@@G@@D LOOPS WE WON'T JUMP. FOR NOW, WE WON'T CHECK FOR    @G@@@@. PRESENCE OKI
)@@G@@F WHILE AT TOP, BUT WILL TURN OFF THIS OPTIMIZATION IF THERE@G@@@@. IS AKJ
)@@G@@NY WHILE AT ALL. IN ADDITION, ONLY JGD'S NOW SET THE OPTIMIZATION @G@@@@KK
)@@G@@. FLAG, SO THERE WILL BE NO FLOATING. WHEN TLEM'S AND JMGI'S ARE DONE,  KL
)@@G@@@G@@@@. SURPRESSION OF SOME REGISTER LOAD CODE WILL CAUSE FLOAT WHICH WIKM
)@@G@@LL    @C@@@@. NEED TO BE COMPENSATED FOR AT THIS POINT.     @[@@@@.     KN
)@@G@@@G@@@@CANFAL    EQU       1-WHSPEC**(G$FLAG(K,21)>0) . ON => WE CAN FALLKO
)@@G@@ THRU @H@@@@ DO CANFAL ,G$FLAG*(K,10) EQU 0       . SO FORGET ABOUT JUMPKP
)@@G@@ING TO BOTTOM     @G@@@@ DO 1-CANFAL ,G$FLAG*(K,21) EQU 0     . CLEAR FLKQ
)@@G@@AG IF WE CAN'T FALL THRU@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. CLOSE OTHERWISE/UNTIL WITH JKR
)@@G@@UMP IF NOT FOLLOWED BY TESTS WHICH DO IT  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@UNTOP     EQKS
)@@G@@U       (G$FLAG(K,6)>0)**(VATBOT++WHSPEC=0) . UNTIL JUMPS TO TOP  @G@@@@KT
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,14) EQU   (OVAC**ESCAPP++WHISBO++VATBOT++UNTOP=0)**NOKILL .   KU
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU G$FLAG(K,5)*(1-NOKILL) . ADJUST UNTIL SURPRESSIONKV
)@@G@@ FLOAT@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. SET LC TO REFLECT WHAT IT WILL BE ON PASS 2 BYKW
)@@G@@ APPLYING FLOATS TO IT  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU    1-NOKILL  KX
)@@G@@        . SET FLAG TO KILL ALL CODE @H@@@@          RES       G$FLAG(K,5KY
)@@G@@)+G$FLAG(K,10)+G$FLAG(K,16)+G$FLAG(K,17)+ ;     @E@@@@                  KZ
)@@G@@  G$FLAG(K,13)+G$FLAG(K,14)+G$FLAG(K,18)  @]@@@@        END @C@@@@/.    LA
)@@G@@     ******** EXEC REQUEST GROUP *********@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@LB
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * LC
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *          -READ-$  LD
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@LE
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     LF
)@@G@@@#@@@@P       PROC   *1 @#@@@@READ$*  NAME   015@#@@@@READA$*  NAME  042LG
)@@G@@@^@@@@TREAD$*  NAME  0102     @^@@@@AREAD$*  NAME  0166     @^@@@@AREADALH
)@@G@@$*  NAME 0167     @^@@@@ATREAD$*  NAME 0170     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO (PLI
)@@G@@(0,0)=015)++(P(0,0)=0166) , GO G$$D20 . NO PKT IF READ$,AREAD$    @G@@@@LJ
)@@G@@PKTOFF  EQU    (P(0,0)=0102)++(P(0,0)=0170) . OFFSET FOR TREAD$ PACKETS LK
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO P(1)=0 , GO G$$D10                . IF PKT ADDR NOT GIVEN, GO LL
)@@G@@KLUDGE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. GENERATE CODE FOR CASE WHERE PACKET ADDR EXPLILM
)@@G@@CITLY GIVEN---    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@        LA,U   A0,$+5               LN
)@@G@@  . GET EOF ADDR (SKIP AFTER READ$) @H@@@@        I$     06,H1,A0,P(1,2)LO
)@@G@@,P(1,*1),P(1,1)+PKTOFF . STASH IN PACKET (FIELD @G@@@@        I$     026LP
)@@G@@,U,A0,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) . LXM PKT ADR   @E@@@@ GO G$$D99  LQ
)@@G@@                          . GO GENERATE THE READ@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. IF PLR
)@@G@@ACKET ADDR CAN VARY AT XQT TIME, WE MUST FARBLE A BIT @[@@@@.     @]@@@@LS
)@@G@@G$$D10* NAME@G@@@@        LXI,U  A0,0,A1                . TEMP SAVE A1 LLT
)@@G@@OWER IN A0 UPPER  @F@@@@        LXM,U  A1,$+7                 . GET ADDRLU
)@@G@@ OF EOF RETURN    @E@@@@        SA,H1  A1,PKTOFF,A0           . EOF ADDRLV
)@@G@@ TO PACKET  @G@@@@        LSSC   A0,18                  . ALIGN OLD A1 LLW
)@@G@@OWER IN A0 LOWER  @E@@@@        LXM,U  A1,0,A0                . RESTORE LX
)@@G@@A1 LOWER    @E@@@@        SSL    A0,18                  . REALIGN PACKETLY
)@@G@@ ADDR @E@@@@ GO G$$D99                            . THEN GO DO THE ER   LZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. GENERATE CALL FOR IO FUNCTS WHICH DO NOT USE PACKETSMA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$D20* NAME@G@@@@        LXI,U  A0,$+(P(1)>0)+3      MB
)@@G@@  . SET EOF TO SKIP AFTER READ$     @H@@@@ DO P(1)>0 ,         I$     02MC
)@@G@@6,U,A0,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) . LXM BUF@[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$D99MD
)@@G@@* NAME@D@@@@        ER     P(0,0)                 . DO THE FUNC   @E@@@@ME
)@@G@@        I$     074,04,,,,$+2          . NORMAL EXIT HERE    @G@@@@      MF
)@@G@@  AA,U   A0,0400000             . IF EOF, SET LOWORDER SIGN BIT   @]@@@@MG
)@@G@@        END @[@@@@.     @D@@@@/.   ****** UTILITIES FOR CONDITION TESTINMH
)@@G@@G *******   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************************************MI
)@@G@@********************    @F@@@@.     *                                   MJ
)@@G@@                   *    @F@@@@.     *       G$$CAN : ANALYZE A SIMPLE COMK
)@@G@@NDITION FIELD      *    @F@@@@.     *                                   ML
)@@G@@                   *    @F@@@@.     ************************************MM
)@@G@@********************    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. DEFINE ARRAYS FOMN
)@@G@@R OPTIMIZATION OF TYPE 1 TESTS ON REGISTERS INTO TYPE 3     @[@@@@.     MO
)@@G@@@#@@@@          DEF     @F@@@@G$ALTT(NE)  EQU     NONZ              . NOMP
)@@G@@T EQUAL ZERO IS NONZERO @E@@@@G$ALTT(EQ)  EQU     ZERO              . EQMQ
)@@G@@UAL ZERO IS ZERO  @ @@@@G$ALTT(DNE) EQU     DNONZ     @ @@@@G$ALTT(DEQ) MR
)@@G@@EQU     DZERO     @F@@@@G$ALTT(LT)  EQU     NEG               . LESS THAMS
)@@G@@N ZERO IS NEGATIVE@G@@@@G$ALTT(GE)  EQU     POS               . GTR OR EMT
)@@G@@QUAL ZERO IS POSITIVE   @#@@@@Z       PROC   *1 @#@@@@G$$CAN*  NAME     MU
)@@G@@@H@@@@I       EQU    Z(1,1)                 . GET INDEX TO FIELD BEING AMV
)@@G@@NALYZED     @F@@@@K       EQU    Z(1,2)                 . GET ITS ORDER MW
)@@G@@IN THE TEST @ @@@@. DETERMINE TYPE OF CONDITION @ @@@@ DO P(I,2)>0  ,N(1MX
)@@G@@) EQU 1     @ @@@@ DO P(I,2)=IN ,N(1) EQU 2     @A@@@@ DO P(I,2)=IS ,N(1MY
)@@G@@) EQU 3+2*(P(I)=4)@ @@@@ DO P(I)=1    ,N(1) EQU 4     @ @@@@ DO P(I,1)=CMZ
)@@G@@HANNEL ,N(1) EQU 6@F@@@@ DO N(1)<1 , G$$EFL 1,1               . E-FLAG INA
)@@G@@F UNKNOWN TYPE    @F@@@@ DO N(1)<3 , G$$DCU,2 I,3             . DECODE ENB
)@@G@@QUF'D U-SPECS     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. TRY TO CHANGE TEST TO A MORE OPTIMNC
)@@G@@AL ONE THAN SPECIFIED   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO (N(1)=2)**G$AMPR , GO G$$AND
)@@G@@10      . REG STATUS NEEDS RELOCATION FUNC &(X) @E@@@@U16     EQU     (PNE
)@@G@@(I,5)<016)++(P(I,4)>0)++P(I,*3)++P(I,*4)  @E@@@@ DO (N(1)>1)++U16 , GO GNF
)@@G@@$$A30 . VALUE TESTS NEED IMMEDIATES @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. IMMEDIATE LE OR NG
)@@G@@GT CAN BE ALTERED TO LT OR GE...    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@PI3       EQU     NH
)@@G@@  P(I,3)            . PI3 IS UFIELD @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,PI3 EQU $AP(PI3)NI
)@@G@@        . IF MASM, REMOVE RELOCATABLE PART@C@@@@NEGEQU    EQU       (P(INJ
)@@G@@,5)=017)**(PI3>0377777) @E@@@@OFVAL     EQU       0377777+0400000*((P(I,NK
)@@G@@5)=016)++NEGEQU)  @F@@@@FUDGE     EQU       ((LT-LE)*(P(I,2)=LE)+(GE-GT)NL
)@@G@@*(P(I,2)=GT))* ;  @F@@@@                    (PI3<OFVAL) . DON'T OVERFLOWNM
)@@G@@ OR CHANGE SIGN   @D@@@@P**(I,2) EQU        P(I,2)+FUDGE      . ADJUST KNN
)@@G@@EYWORD@F@@@@P**(I,3) EQU        P(I,3)+1-(FUDGE=0) . ADJUST IMMEDIATE VANO
)@@G@@LUE   @F@@@@ DO ((P(I,3)=0)**(P(I,4)=0)=0)++(G$ALTT(P(I,2))=0) , GO G$$ANP
)@@G@@30 .  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. REGISTER TESTS AGAINST IMMEDIATE ZEROES CAN BENQ
)@@G@@COME CONDITIONAL JUMPS  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. BE CAREFUL NOT TO OVEROPTIMINR
)@@G@@ZE IMMEDIATES     @F@@@@ DO 1-G$AMPR , GO G$$A30 . CANNOT OPTIMIZE WITHONS
)@@G@@UT & FUNCTION     @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (&(P(I,3))=-2)=0 , GO G$$A30 .NT
)@@G@@ ZERO MUST BE ABSOLUTE  @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 , DO ($BA(P(I,3))=0)=0 , GO GNU
)@@G@@$$A30 . ZERO MUST BE ABSOLUTE @F@@@@P**(I,3)  EQU       G$ALTT(P(I,2))  NV
)@@G@@  . GET ALTERNATE KEYWORD     @I@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 ,P**(I) EQU 3          NW
)@@G@@    . FORCE NUMBER OF ARGS (PRUNE AWAY ,,U)     @I@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,P**(NX
