)@@G@@I,4) $DELETE          . FORCE NUMBER OF ARGS (PRUNE AWAY ,,U)     @I@@@@NY
)@@G@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,P**(I,5) $DELETE          . FORCE NUMBER OF ARGS (PRUNE AWNZ
)@@G@@AY ,,U)     @C@@@@ GO G$$A20          . GO FINISH UP THE FARBLING @[@@@@OA
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. TYPE 2 CONDITION TESTS ON A-REGS CAN BECOME CONDITIONAL JUOB
)@@G@@MPS, TOO.   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$A10*   NAME    @G@@@@ DO P(I)>3 , GO G$OC
)@@G@@$A30                . DON'T OPTIMIZE EQUF'D CORE LOCNS@I@@@@REG       EQOD
)@@G@@U       P(I,3)            . GET REG FROM  <KEYWORD>,IN,<REG> FORMAT     OE
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 , DO ($BA(REG)=0)=0 , GO G$$A30 . MUST BE AN ABSOLUTEOF
)@@G@@ VALUE@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (&(REG)=-2)=0 , GO G$$A30  . MUST BE AN ABOG
)@@G@@SOLUTE VALUE@G@@@@ DO (REG<A0)++(REG>A15) , GO G$$A30   . MAKE SURE ITS OH
)@@G@@WITHIN AREG RANGE @H@@@@P**(I,3)  EQU       P(I,1)            . FORCE COOI
)@@G@@NDITION KEYWORD INTO SPEC3    @F@@@@P**(I,1)  EQU       REG             OJ
)@@G@@  . THEN MOVE REG INTO SPEC1  @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$A20*   NAME          OK
)@@G@@              . FINISH FUDGING  <AREG>,IS,<KEYWORD> TEST    @E@@@@P**(I,OL
)@@G@@2)  EQU       IS                . CRAM IN THE KEYWORD @G@@@@N(1)      EQOM
)@@G@@U       3                 . AND MARK THIS AS A TYPE 3 TEST  @[@@@@.     ON
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$A30*   NAME    @F@@@@J(1)    EQU    P(I,G$KSF(N(1)))       . GEOO
)@@G@@T FUNC KEYWORD VALUE    @H@@@@ DO DTH ,J(1) EQU G$IV(N(1),J(1))     . FLOP
)@@G@@IP IF DEMORGAN'S THEOREM IN EFFECT  @F@@@@ DO J(1)<1 , G$$EFL 1,2       OQ
)@@G@@        . E-FLAG IF UNKNOWN KEYWORD @F@@@@NI$*(K) EQU    G$FJ(N(1),J(1))OR
)@@G@@        . NO OF INSTRS GENERATED    @D@@@@WA$*(K) EQU    G$WS(N(1),J(1))OS
)@@G@@        . WAITING STATUS@G@@@@KE$*(K) EQU    J(1)                   . EXOT
)@@G@@TERNALIZE FUNC KEYWORD VAL    @F@@@@TP$*(K) EQU    N(1)                 OU
)@@G@@  . EXTERNALIZE TYPE OF TEST  @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     OV
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************************************************OW
)@@G@@********    @F@@@@.     *                                               OX
)@@G@@       *    @F@@@@.     *  G$$COD : GENERATE CODE FOR A SIMPLE CONDITIONOY
)@@G@@ TEST  *    @F@@@@.     *                                               OZ
)@@G@@       *    @F@@@@.     ************************************************PA
)@@G@@********    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@Q       PROC   *2 @I@@@@G$$CODPB
)@@G@@*  NAME                         . PF'S: FIELD-INDEX,TEST-INDEX,WAIT-VAL PC
)@@G@@FA    @F@@@@I       EQU    Q(1,1)                 . GET FIELD WE'RE SCANPD
)@@G@@NING  @F@@@@NN      EQU    Q(1,2)                 . GET DECODED DATA INDPE
)@@G@@EX    @E@@@@N       EQU    TP$(NN)                . GET CONDITION TYPE  PF
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@CGISF   EQU    G$FCF(N)=0             . TRUE IF G$FJ=FPG
)@@G@@UNC CODE (ELSE J-S@E@@@@JI(1)   EQU    KE$(NN)                . GET KEYWPH
)@@G@@ORD FUNCTION@F@@@@JI(2)   EQU    G$IV(N,JI(1))          . AND KEYWORD OFPI
)@@G@@ THE INVERSE@F@@@@WOK     EQU    Q(1,3)=G$WS(N,JI(1))   . ON IF WAITING PJ
)@@G@@STATUS OK   @A@@@@.     ---- DECODE OPERAND FIELDS    @G@@@@AAA     EQU PK
)@@G@@   0+(G$ASF(N)>0)*(P(I,G$ASF(N))-A0) . WATCH OUT FOR -0!!!!!@D@@@@JJJ   PL
)@@G@@  EQU     CGISF*P(I,5)          . J DESIGNATOR  @ @@@@XXX     EQU     CGPM
)@@G@@ISF*P(I,4)  @C@@@@HI      EQU     CGISF*(2*P(I,*4)+P(I,*3)) .     @G@@@@PN
)@@G@@U18     EQU     (JJJ>015)**(XXX=0)**(N<3)**(HI=0) . ON=>18 BIT U-FIELD  PO
)@@G@@@C@@@@UUU     EQU    CGISF*P(I,3)+(1-CGISF)*Q(2,1)    @G@@@@SIDE**(1) EQPP
)@@G@@U SIDE(1)++(N=5)++(HI>0)  . ON IF TEST HAS SIDE EFFECTS     @G@@@@ DO G$PQ
)@@G@@FJ(N,JI(1),1)>077 , GO G$$G10   . CHECK FOR ASYMMETRIC INSTRUCTION@[@@@@PR
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. PROCESS SYMMETRIC TESTS (FOR WHICH AN INVERSE MACHINE INSTPS
)@@G@@R EXISTS)   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@JIU     EQU    JI(2-WOK)              . GEPT
)@@G@@T INDEX OF OPCODE WE'LL USE   @G@@@@NUMINS  EQU    G$FJ(N,JIU)          PU
)@@G@@  . GET NO OF INSTRS TO GENERATE    @E@@@@K DO     NUMINS ,FUN(K) EQU G$PV
)@@G@@FCF(N)+CGISF*G$FJ(N,JIU,K)    @E@@@@K DO     NUMINS ,JAY(K) EQU JJJ+(1-CPW
)@@G@@GISF)*G$FJ(N,JIU,K)     @G@@@@K DO     NUMINS*(1-U18) , I$ FUN(K),JAY(K)PX
)@@G@@,AAA,XXX,HI,UUU . GENERATE    @F@@@@K DO     NUMINS*U18 , G$$IMU FUN(K),PY
)@@G@@JAY(K),AAA,XXX,UUU . IMMEDIAT @F@@@@REVER**(1) EQU G$FJ(N,JI(1))*G$FJ(N,PZ
)@@G@@JI(2))=1 . SET REVERSIBLE FLAG@G@@@@ DO REVER(1)++WOK=0 , I$ 074,04,,,,$QA
)@@G@@+2 . WATCHOUT FOR NON-REVERSIBLES   @H@@@@ DO 1 , END                   QB
)@@G@@        . FOR STANDARD INSTRS, ITS ALL OVER HERE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. PROCQC
)@@G@@ESS ASYMMETRIC INSTRS (FOR WHICH NO SINGLE INVERSE EXISTS)  @[@@@@.     QD
)@@G@@@]@@@@G$$G10* NAME@F@@@@FUN     EQU    G$FJ(N,JI(1),1)        . GET FUNCQE
)@@G@@T-JDESIG VALUE    @E@@@@ DO FUN=01637 , GO G$$G20             . TEST FORQF
)@@G@@ DTE INSTR  @D@@@@. IF NOT A DTE, THEN INSTRUCTION IS A JUMP OF SORTS   QG
)@@G@@@B@@@@. (EITHER DJZ OR AN I/O CHANNEL TEST)     @H@@@@AREG    EQU    AAAQH
)@@G@@+A0*(FUN>01700)     . FOR CHANNEL INSTRS, USE GIVEN AVALUE  @G@@@@      QI
)@@G@@     I$       FUN*/-4,FUN**017,AREG,,,WOK*UUU+(WOK=0)*($+2) .     @ @@@@QJ
)@@G@@ DO WOK=0 , I$ 074,04,,,,UUU  @]@@@@ DO 1 , END @B@@@@. HERE WE HANDLE TQK
)@@G@@HE DOUBLE TEST EQUAL -  @]@@@@G$$G20* NAME@D@@@@           I$       FUN*QL
)@@G@@/-4,FUN**017,AAA,XXX,HI,UUU . @ @@@@ DO WOK=0 , I$ 074,04,,,,$+2  @]@@@@QM
)@@G@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************************QN
)@@G@@********************************    @F@@@@.     *                       QO
)@@G@@                               *    @F@@@@.     *  G$$TST : DRIVER FOR SQP
)@@G@@IMPLE AND COMPOUND COND TESTS  *    @F@@@@.     *                       QQ
)@@G@@                               *    @F@@@@.     ************************QR
)@@G@@********************************    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@R     QS
)@@G@@  PROC   *2 @H@@@@G$$TST*  NAME                         . PF'S: FIELD-INQT
)@@G@@-P,COMPOUND-FLAG,INVERT @I@@@@                              . IF NO JUMPQU
)@@G@@-EXIT GIVEN, G$TLBL(TTL)+1 IS USED (LINE I@H@@@@TTL     EQU    G$CTR(4)+QV
)@@G@@1             . COUNT THIS REFERENCE TO THIS PROCEDURE@F@@@@ORIG        QW
)@@G@@                          . REMEMBER WHERE WE STARTED @G@@@@G$CTR**(4) EQX
)@@G@@QU  TTL                   . BUMP NO OF CALLS TO THIS PROC   @D@@@@G$TLBLQY
)@@G@@**(TTL) EQU G$TLBL(TTL)+G$CTR(2) . FOLD IN FLOAT@F@@@@LIF     EQU    R(2QZ
)@@G@@)=0                 . ON IF LINEITEM FORMAT     @E@@@@FA(1)   EQU    R(2RA
)@@G@@,1)+LIF*(G$TLBL(TTL)+1) . SET FALSE EXIT  @G@@@@DTH     EQU    R(1,3)   RB
)@@G@@              . ON => USE DEMORGAN'S THEOREM FOR@I@@@@                  RC
)@@G@@                    . WHICH CAUSES G$$CAN TO INVERT THE SENSE     @[@@@@RD
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@ DO R(1,2) , GO G$$T10                . GO DO COMPOUND CONDIRE
)@@G@@TION  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. CODE GENERATION FOR SIMPLE CONDITIONS   @[@@@@RF
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@        G$$CAN R(1,1),1               . ANALYZE THE (SINGLE)RG
)@@G@@ FIELD@H@@@@ DO WA$(1)>1 , GO G$$T01              . CHECK FOR TEST INSTRRH
)@@G@@ TO GE GENN'D     @D@@@@        G$$COD R(1,1),1,0 FA(1)       . JUMP TO RI
)@@G@@FALSE @C@@@@ GO G$$T99                            . AND QUIT@[@@@@.     RJ
)@@G@@@H@@@@G$$T01* NAME                          . HERE IF SIMPLE CONDITION IRK
)@@G@@S A TEST    @I@@@@        G$$COD R(1,1),1,2+LIF         . SKIP IF: TRUE RL
)@@G@@(IF-ELSE) FALSE (LINEITEM)    @F@@@@ DO 1-LIF , I$ 074,04,,,,FA(1)      RM
)@@G@@  . JUMP TO FALSE (IF-ELSE)   @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     RN
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$$T10* NAME                          . COMPOUND CONDITIONS COME HRO
)@@G@@ERE   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@K DO     2 ,II(K) EQU R(1,1)+2*(K=2)  . SET FIELRP
)@@G@@D INDICES FOR SIMPLE CONDS    @E@@@@K DO     2 , G$$CAN II(K),K         RQ
)@@G@@  . ANALYZE BOTH FIELDS @H@@@@K DO     2 ,IX(K) EQU K+(WA$(2)<WA$(1))*(3RR
)@@G@@-2*K) . ORDER SO 2ND IS HIGHER WAIT @H@@@@.  DO WA$(1)=WA$(2) ,K DO 2 ,IRS
)@@G@@X(K) EQU K+(NI$(2)>NI$(1))*(3-2*K) . NOT NOW    @G@@@@WOVR    EQU    (WART
)@@G@@$(1)>1)+(WA$(2)>1)  . DETERMINE OVERALL WAIT TYPE     @G@@@@ DO (P(R(1,1RU
)@@G@@)+1,1)=AND)=1-DTH , GO G$$T20 . IF AND-CONDITION, GO DO IT  @[@@@@.     RV
)@@G@@@C@@@@. GENERATE OPTIMIZED CODE FOR OR-CONDITIONS     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@RW
)@@G@@ DO WOVR>0 , GO G$$T11  @ @@@@. COME HERE FOR JUMP-JUMP     @E@@@@      RX
)@@G@@  G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),1 G$TLBL(TTL) . JUMP IF TRUE @D@@@@        G$$CRY
)@@G@@OD II(IX(2)),IX(2),0 FA(1) . JUMP IF FALSE@]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @]@@@@G$$T11RZ
)@@G@@* NAME@^@@@@ DO WOVR>1 , GO G$$T13  @ @@@@. COME HERE FOR TEST-JUMP     SA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. NOTE THAT THIS IS THE ONLY CASE IN WHICH WE GENERATESB
)@@G@@ A TEST     @E@@@@. OVER A JUMP, AND IS THUS THE ONLY PLACE WE NEED TO CSC
)@@G@@HECK  @F@@@@. WHETHER THE JUMP INSTRUCTION HAS A SINGLE-INSTRUCTION INVESD
)@@G@@RSE   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO (WA$(IX(1))=0)++(G$FJ(TP$(IX(1)),KE$(IX(1)),SE
)@@G@@1)<0100) , GO G$$T12    @ @@@@. OOPS, WE'RE IN HOT WATER--  @E@@@@      SF
)@@G@@  G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),1 G$TLBL(TTL) . JUMP IF TRUE @I@@@@        G$$CSG
)@@G@@OD II(IX(2)),IX(2),2+LIF  . SKIP IF: TRUE (IF-ELSE) FALSE (LINEITEM     SH
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO 1-LIF , I$ 074,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUMP TO FALSE (IF-ELSE)   SI
)@@G@@@]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @ @@@@. TEST OVER JUMP IS LEGAL --  @]@@@@G$$T12* NAMESJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),2      . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@@      SK
)@@G@@  G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),0 FA(1) . JUMP IF FALSE@]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @]@@@@SL
)@@G@@G$$T13* NAME@ @@@@. COME HERE TO DO TEST-TEST   @H@@@@ DO LIF , GO G$$T1SM
)@@G@@4                   . DIFFERENT STUFF IF LINE ITEM FORMAT   @D@@@@      SN
)@@G@@  G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),3      . SKIP IF FALSE @D@@@@        I$     074SO
)@@G@@,04,,,,G$TLBL(TTL)  . JUMP TO TRUE  @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2)SP
)@@G@@,2      . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUSQ
)@@G@@MP TO FALSE @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$$T14* NAME            SR
)@@G@@              . THIS IS TEST-TEST IN LINE ITEM FORMAT @ @@@@ DO NI$(IX(1SS
)@@G@@))>1 , GO G$$T15  @ @@@@. HERE IF TEST 1 IS 1 INSTR   @D@@@@        G$$CST
)@@G@@OD II(IX(2)),IX(2),2      . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1))SU
)@@G@@,IX(1),3      . SKIP IF FALSE @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$T15SV
)@@G@@* NAME@ @@@@ DO NI$(IX(2))>1 , GO G$$T16  @C@@@@. HERE IF 1ST TEST IS MOSW
)@@G@@RE THAN ONE INSTRUCTION @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),2      . SKSX
)@@G@@IP IF TRUE  @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),3      . SKIP IF FALSE SY
)@@G@@@]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @]@@@@G$$T16* NAME@B@@@@. HERE IF BOTH TESTS ARE MULTISZ
)@@G@@-INSTRUCTION@D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),3      . SKIP IF FALSE TA
)@@G@@@D@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,G$TLBL(TTL)  . JUMP TO TRUE  @D@@@@      TB
)@@G@@  G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),3      . SKIP IF FALSE @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @[@@@@TC
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. GENERATE TESTS FOR AND-CONDITIONS @[@@@@.     TD
)@@G@@@]@@@@G$$T20* NAME@[@@@@.     @^@@@@ DO WOVR>0 , GO G$$T21  @ @@@@. GENETE
)@@G@@RATE CODE FOR JUMP-JUMP @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),0 FA(1) . JTF

)@@G@@$T23  @ @@@@. COME HERE FOR TEST-JUMP     @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1))TI
)@@G@@,IX(1),0 FA(1) . JUMP IF FALSE@I@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),2+LIFTJ
)@@G@@  . SKIP IF: TRUE (IF-ELSE) FALSE (LINEITEM     @F@@@@ DO 1-LIF , I$ 074TK
)@@G@@,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUMP TO FALSE (IF-ELSE)   @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @[@@@@TL
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@G$$T23* NAME                          . THIS PLACE FOR TEST-TM
)@@G@@TEST  @I@@@@ DO LIF , GO G$$T26                   . SPECIAL EASIER STUFFTN
)@@G@@ IN LINEITEM FORMAT     @ @@@@ DO NI$(IX(1))>1 , GO G$$T24  @ @@@@. HERETO
)@@G@@ IF TEST 1 IS 1 INSTR   @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),3      . SKTP
)@@G@@IP IF FALSE @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),2      . SKIP IF TRUE  TQ
)@@G@@@D@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUMP TO FALSE @]@@@@ GO G$TR
)@@G@@$T99  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$T24* NAME@ @@@@ DO NI$(IX(2))>1 , GO G$$T25  TS
)@@G@@@C@@@@. HERE IF 1ST TEST IS MORE THAN ONE INSTRUCTION @D@@@@        G$$CTT
)@@G@@OD II(IX(1)),IX(1),3      . SKIP IF FALSE @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2))TU
)@@G@@,IX(2),2      . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,FA(1)      TV
)@@G@@  . JUMP TO FALSE @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @]@@@@G$$T25* NAME@B@@@@. HERE IF BOTW
)@@G@@TH TESTS ARE MULTI-INSTRUCTION@D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),2    TX
)@@G@@  . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUMP TO TY
)@@G@@FALSE @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),2      . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@@TZ
)@@G@@        I$     074,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUMP TO FALSE @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  UA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$T26* NAME                          . TEST-TEST IN LUB
)@@G@@INE ITEM FORMAT (MUCH SIMP    @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),2    UC

)@@G@@FALSE @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),3      . SKIP IF FALSE @[@@@@UE
)@@G@@.     @]@@@@G$$T99* NAME@F@@@@ DO $=ORIG , G$$EFL 1,1               . BOUF
)@@G@@MBOUT IF NOTHING DONE   @F@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$TLBL(TTL)=$)=0 ,  G$$UG
)@@G@@DFL G$TLBL(TTL) 0,0777  @F@@@@G$TLBL**(TTL) EQU   $           . RELEVANTUH
)@@G@@ ON GLOBAL PASS 1 ONLY  @]@@@@        END @E@@@@/.  ******* UTILITIES FOUI
)@@G@@R GENERATION OF LOOP CONTROLS ******@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. SELEUJ
)@@G@@CTION OF THE INSTRUCTION TO BE USED TO CONTROL THE LOOP IS: @E@@@@.    1UK
)@@G@@) JGD    IF LOOP TERMINATES AT 0 AND STEP IS -1, OR   @E@@@@.           UL
)@@G@@   LOOP IS FOR A SPECIFIED NUMBER OF TIMES.     @E@@@@.    2) JMGI   IF UM
)@@G@@LOOP TERMINATES AT 0 AND STEP IS NOT -1.  @D@@@@.    3) TLEM   IF LOOP TUN
)@@G@@ERMINATES AT OTHER THAN ZERO. @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. POSITIONING OF THE LOOUO
)@@G@@P CONTROL INSTRUCTION IS:     @A@@@@.    1) JGD    ALWAYS AT THE BOTTOM UP
)@@G@@@F@@@@.    2) JMGI   AT BOTTOM (SO JUMP DESTINATION CONTINUES IN THE    UQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@.              LOOP), IF INCREMENT NEGATIVE (LOOP SENSE DOWN),    UR
)@@G@@@E@@@@.              I.E. VALUES OF LOOP CONTROL VARIABLE ARE >0 .@A@@@@US
)@@G@@.              AT TOP OTHERWISE     @F@@@@.    3) TLEM   AT BOTTOM (SO SUT
)@@G@@KIP CAUSES EXIT FROM LOOP) WHEN     @E@@@@.              INCREMENT IS POUU
)@@G@@SITIVE (LOOP SENSE UP), I.E.  @F@@@@.              TERMINATION CONDITIONUV
)@@G@@ IS APPROACHED FROM BELOW.    @F@@@@.              BECAUSE OF LACK OF SIUW
)@@G@@GN EXTENSION, THIS HOLDS RE-  @F@@@@.              GARDLESS OF THE SIGN UX
)@@G@@OF THE LOOP VARIABLE ITSELF.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NOTE: IF THE SIGN OF TUY
)@@G@@HE INCREMENT IS UNKNOWN (JMGI/TLEM), THE CODE   @G@@@@. TO VARY THE LOOPUZ
)@@G@@ CONTROL VARIABLE WILL BE DUPLICATED AT BOTH TOP AND  @F@@@@. BOTTOM, WIVA
)@@G@@TH AN EXECUTE-TIME TEST (SIGN JUMP) AT THE BOTTOM TO  @A@@@@. DETERMINE VB
)@@G@@WHICH IS TO BE USED.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. TO ENFORCE THE REQUIREMENT TVC
)@@G@@HAT THE LOOP CONTROL REGISTER CONTAIN     @F@@@@. THE FROM/TO VALUES ON VD
)@@G@@THE FIRST AND LAST TIMES THROUGH THE LOOP,@D@@@@. TLEM TESTS AT THE TOP VE
)@@G@@ARE SURROUNDED BY AX AND ANX  @F@@@@. OF THE INCREMENT. IN THE GENERAL CVF
)@@G@@ASE, THERE IS NO WAY TO AVOID @G@@@@. THIS. IN THE FUTURE, WE WILL ALLOWVG
)@@G@@ THE USER TO SURPRESS IT, AND/OR    @G@@@@. IN THE CASE WHERE THE CONTROVH
)@@G@@L FIELDS ARE IMMEDIATE, GENERATE SLIGHTLY @C@@@@. DIFFERENT CODE WHICH WVI
)@@G@@ILL MAKE IT UNNECESSARY.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************************VJ
)@@G@@********************************    @F@@@@.     *                       VK
)@@G@@                               *    @F@@@@.     *   G$$LAN : ANALYZE A <VL
)@@G@@LOOP CONTROL> SPECIFICATION    *    @F@@@@.     *                       VM
)@@G@@                               *    @F@@@@.     ************************VN
)@@G@@********************************    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.    FLAGS SET BY VO
)@@G@@THIS SUBROUTINE ARE USED BY CALLING ROUTINE (REPEAT)  @^@@@@.    THEIR MVP
)@@G@@EANINGS ARE:@D@@@@.       FI(1)  INDEX IN IMAGE OF 'FOR' SPECIFICATION  VQ
)@@G@@@C@@@@.       FI(2)  INDEX IN IMAGE OF 'FROM' SPEC    @G@@@@.       FI(3VR
)@@G@@)  INDEX OF 'TO' SPEC ('VARY'), OR 'MASKED' SPEC ('LOOKFOR')@G@@@@.     VS
)@@G@@  FI(4)  INDEX OF 'BY' SPEC. NOTE THAT IF USER DIDN'T GIVE ONE,   @C@@@@VT
)@@G@@.              WE FORCE IT BY STORING IN P(X,Y) @G@@@@.       FI(5)  ON VU
)@@G@@IF ANY LOOP CONTROL CODE IS TO APPEAR AT THE PHYSICAL @B@@@@.           VV
)@@G@@   BOTTOM OF THE LOOP CODE    @F@@@@.       FI(6)  ON IF SENSE OF LOOP CVW
)@@G@@TL VARIABLE (UP\DOWN) IS KNOWN@D@@@@.              ('VARY'), OR OFFSET VVX
)@@G@@ALUE ('LOOKFOR')  @F@@@@.       FI(7)  INDEX IN P OF LAST FIELD SCANNED VY
)@@G@@BY THIS ROUTINE   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE ARRAYS IM(K) AND IV(K) ARE USEVZ
)@@G@@D INTERNALLY FOR THE ANALYZED @H@@@@. PARAMETERS OF THE LOOP SPECIFICATIWA
)@@G@@ON. IM IS ON IF THE VALUE IS IMMEDIATE,   @G@@@@. AND IV IS THE VALUE ITWB
)@@G@@SELF. K=1,2,3,4=> FORVAL, FROMVAL, TOVAL, BYVAL.@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     WC
)@@G@@@H@@@@        PROC   *0                     . NOTE: ONE-PASS PROC FLAG RWD
)@@G@@EQUIRED     @#@@@@G$$LAN*  NAME     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@W(1)    EQU    KW(WE
)@@G@@1)                  . GET KEYWORD WHICH DESCRIBES FIELD     @[@@@@.     WF
)@@G@@@E@@@@.       ***** BREAK DOWN SOURCE IMAGE, SET DEFAULTS *****   @[@@@@WG
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@. SCAN ALL FIELDS FOR DEFINING KEYWORDS   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@WH
)@@G@@K3      EQU    MASKED*(W(1)=LOOKFOR)+TO*((W(1)=LOOKFOR)=0)  @G@@@@FI*(1)WI
)@@G@@  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=FOR)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=FOR)+3*(P(VI+3,1)=FOR)   @G@@@@WJ
)@@G@@FI*(2)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=FROM)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=FROM)+3*(P(VI+3,1)=FROM)WK
)@@G@@@D@@@@FI*(3)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=K3)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=K3)+;   @B@@@@      WL
)@@G@@  3*(P(VI+3,1)=K3)+4*(P(VI+4,1)=K3) @F@@@@FI*(4)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=BWM
)@@G@@Y)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=BY)+3*(P(VI+3,1)=BY)@G@@@@FI*(7)  EQU    FI(4)          WN
)@@G@@        . INITIALIZE LAST FIELD POINTER   @H@@@@I DO     3 , DO FI(I)>FIWO
)@@G@@(7) ,FI*(7) EQU FI(I) . FIND LAST FIELD USER GAVE US  @I@@@@LF(1)   EQU WP
)@@G@@   0+P                    . SET INDEX OF LAST FIELD + 1 IN CASE OF D    WQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. DEFAULT A MISSING 'TO' SPECIFICATION TO ZERO  @[@@@@WR
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@ DO (K3=MASKED)++(FI(3)>VI) , GO G$$L01 . IF 'TO' EXPLICIT, WS
)@@G@@SKIP THIS   @H@@@@FI*(3)  EQU    LF(1)                  . FORCE IT INTO WT
)@@G@@THE NEXT AVAIL SUBFIELD @E@@@@P*(FI(3),1) EQU TO                    . SEWU
)@@G@@T ITS KEYWORD     @F@@@@P*(FI(3),4) EQU XU                    . MAKE IT WV
)@@G@@AN IMMEDIATE ZERO @G@@@@LF(1)   EQU    LF(1)+1                . BUMP NEXWW
)@@G@@T USABLE FIELD POINTER  @G@@@@G$$L01* NAME                          . ENWX
)@@G@@D OF DEFAULT FOR 'TO' FIELD   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. 'BY' FIELD (IF GIVEN) WY
)@@G@@IS VARIABLE LENGTH. FORCE TO FIXED FORMAT @C@@@@. BY MOVING UP/DOWN/OFFSWZ
)@@G@@ET TO THE FIFTH SUBFIELD@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO FI(4)=VI , GO G$$L02      XA
)@@G@@        . IF 'BY' OMITTED, SKIP THIS@E@@@@ DO P(FI(4),4)=U ,P*(FI(4),4) XB
)@@G@@EQU XU . FORCE SIGN EXTENSION @F@@@@NB      EQU    0+P(FI(4))           XC
)@@G@@  . NO OF SPECS IN 'BY' FIELD @H@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (P(FI(4),NB)>0)++(XD
)@@G@@NB=5) , GO G$$L02 . NOTHING TO ADJUST     @H@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 , DO ($AP(PXE
)@@G@@(FI(4),NB))>0)++(NB=5) , GO G$$L02 . NOTHING TO ADJUST@G@@@@P*(FI(4),5) XF
)@@G@@EQU P(FI(4),NB)           . FORCE UP DOWN OFFSET TO FIELD 5 @F@@@@P*(FI(XG
)@@G@@4),NB) EQU 0                    . AND RESET WHEREVER IT WAS @H@@@@G$$L02XH
)@@G@@* NAME                          . END KEYWORD FARBLING FOR 'BY' FIELD   XI
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NOTE:  THE CODE BELOW WILL GENERATE (USUALLY) SPURIOXJ
)@@G@@US R-FLAGS IF     @F@@@@. THE FIELDS BEING EXAMINED ARE EXTERNAL (I.E. UXK
)@@G@@-FLAGGED) EVEN    @F@@@@. THOUGH WE ARE STRIPPING OFF FIELDS WHICH HAVE XL
)@@G@@NO RELOCATION (THE@E@@@@. X AND J FIELDS), AND EVEN THOUGH THE PORTION OXM
)@@G@@F UV WHICH  @F@@@@. MAY CARRY RELOCATION (THE U-FIELD) IS NOT MASKED AT XN
)@@G@@THE POINT   @A@@@@. OF ITS USE. <EXPLETIVE DELETED>   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@XO
)@@G@@          ON        G$MASM=0          . BEGIN ASM CODE@[@@@@.     @D@@@@XP
)@@G@@. PUT ALL FIELDS IN STANDARD FORM TO HANDLE EQUF'S    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@XQ
)@@G@@I DO     4 , DO FI(I)>VI ,UV(I) EQU ; COMBINE ALL FIELDS    @G@@@@ +(I$ XR
)@@G@@0,P(FI(I),4),0,P(FI(I),3),2*P(FI(I),*3)+P(FI(I),*2),P(FI(I),2))   @[@@@@XS
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@I DO     4 , DO P(FI(I),2)>0777777 ; IF THE USER EQUF'D THE XT
)@@G@@SYMBOL@E@@@@        ,IM(I) EQU 07017000000**(G$NOFO UV(I))=07000000000  XU
)@@G@@@F@@@@I DO     4 , DO P(FI(I),2)<01000000 ; IF HE DIDN'T EQUF IT ..     XV
)@@G@@@H@@@@        ,IM(I) EQU (P(FI(I),3)=0)**(016=P(FI(I),4)**016) . CHECK FXW
)@@G@@OR EXPLICI  @E@@@@I DO     4 , DO IM(I)**(P(FI(I),2)<01000000) ; IF NOT XX
)@@G@@EQUF'D@F@@@@        ,IV(I) EQU P(FI(I),2)         . USE THE VALUE HE GAVXY
)@@G@@E     @F@@@@I DO     4 , DO IM(I)**(P(FI(I),2)>0777777) ; BUT IF HE EQUFXZ
)@@G@@'D IT @G@@@@        ,IV(I) EQU + (G$NOFO UV(I)**G$UMSK) . PRAY ITS NOT EYA
)@@G@@XTERNAL     @H@@@@I DO     4 , DO IV(I)>0377777 ,IV(I) EQU IV(I)++077777YB
)@@G@@7000000 . SIGN EXTEND   @I@@@@I DO 2 ,APIV(I+1) EQU IV(I+1)         . FUYC
)@@G@@DGE ABSOLUTE PART FOR LATER MASM TESTS    @E@@@@          OFF           YD
)@@G@@              . END OF ASM CODE     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          ON      YE
)@@G@@  G$MASM=1          . BEGIN MASM CODE     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@I         $RYF
)@@G@@EPEAT   4                 . DO ALL THIS FOR I=1,2,3,4 @G@@@@APU       EQYG
)@@G@@U       $AP(P(FI(I),2))   . STRIP U-FIELD OF RELOCATION     @[@@@@.     YH
)@@G@@@D@@@@. PUT ALL FIELDS IN STANDARD FORM TO HANDLE EQUF'S    @[@@@@.     YI
)@@G@@@C@@@@ DO FI(I)>VI ,UV(I) EQU ; COMBINE ALL FIELDS    @G@@@@ +(I$ 0,P(FIYJ
)@@G@@(I),4),0,P(FI(I),3),2*P(FI(I),*3)+P(FI(I),*2),P(FI(I),2))   @G@@@@APUV  YK
)@@G@@    EQU       $AP(UV(I))        . APUV IS ABSOLUTE PART OF UV(I)  @[@@@@YL
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@IM(I) EQU APU>0777777-> ; . IF THE USER EQUF'D THE SYMBOL   YM
)@@G@@@H@@@@ 07017000000**(G$NOFO APUV)=07000000000! ; THEN SET TRUE IF 'U' ANYN
)@@G@@D NO XDESIG @I@@@@ (P(FI(I),3)=0)**(016=P(FI(I),4)**016) . ELSE SET TRUEYO
)@@G@@ IF EXPLICIT 'U', NO XREG     @D@@@@IV(I) EQU IM(I)**(APU<01000000)-> ; YP
)@@G@@  . IF NOT EQUF'D @F@@@@       P(FI(I),2)! ;      . USE THE VALUE HE GAVYQ
)@@G@@E IN SUBFIELD 2   @F@@@@    + (G$NOFO APUV**G$UMSK)           . ELSE PRAYR
)@@G@@Y ITS NOT EXTERNAL@H@@@@ DO $AP(IV(I))>0377777 ,IV(I) EQU -(0777777-IV(IYS
)@@G@@)) . SIGN EXTEND (IF NEEDED)  @G@@@@APIV(I)   EQU       $AP(IV(I))      YT
)@@G@@  . NO RELOCATION FOR LATER TESTS.  @F@@@@          $ENDR               YU
)@@G@@        . END OF $REPEAT STRUCTURE  @E@@@@          OFF                 YV
)@@G@@        . END OF MASM CODE    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. APIV(2) AND APIV(3) ARYW
)@@G@@E NON-RELOCATABLE EQUIVALENTS OF    @D@@@@. IV(2...3) FOR USE BY MASM INYX
)@@G@@ COMPARISONS OF THE FORM@C@@@@. IV(2)>IV(3). WHEN USING @ASM, APIV(I)=IVYY
)@@G@@(I).  @E@@@@. ***NOTE*** WE ASSUME THAT IV(I) WILL NOT BE UPDATED PRIOR YZ
)@@G@@@A@@@@. TO THE USE OF APIV(I), FOR I=2,3  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ZA
)@@G@@. DEFAULT A MISSING 'BY' SPECIFICATION TO +-1, DEPENDING UPON     @F@@@@ZB
)@@G@@. THE SIGN OF TO-FROM, AND/OR THE USER'S UP/DOWN/OFFSET SPEC.     @[@@@@ZC
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO FI(4)>VI , GO G$$L03              . SKIP THIZD
)@@G@@S IF USER GAVE THIS FIELD     @F@@@@FI*(4)  EQU    LF(1)                ZE
)@@G@@  . REMEMBER WHERE ITS GOING  @H@@@@ DO (W(1)=VARY)++(W(1)=LOOKFOR)=0 , ZF
)@@G@@GO G$$L03 . SKIP FOR SPECIFIC LOOP TYPE   @F@@@@IV(4)   EQU    1        ZG
)@@G@@              . INITIAL ASSUMPTION IS +1  @G@@@@ DO ((W(1)=LOOKFOR)=0)**ZH
)@@G@@IM(2)**IM(3)  ; UNLESS WE KNOW TO-FROM VALUES   @F@@@@        ,IV(4) EQUZI
)@@G@@ 1-2*(APIV(2)>APIV(3))  . THEN USE SIGN OF DIFF @G@@@@ DO (IV(4)=1)**(P(ZJ
)@@G@@FI(4),5)=DOWN) ,IV(4) EQU -1 . MAKE IMPLICIT EXPLICIT @F@@@@P*(FI(4),2) ZK
)@@G@@EQU     IV(4)             . SAVE FOR USE BY GENERATOR @D@@@@P*(FI(4),4) ZL
)@@G@@EQU XU  . MAKE SURE HE KNOWS ITS IMMEDIATE@E@@@@UV(4)   EQUF   IV(4),,XUZM
)@@G@@              . MARK IT AS IMMEDIATE@G@@@@IM(4)   EQU    1              ZN
)@@G@@        . AND TURN ON THE IMMEDIATE FLAG  @G@@@@G$$L03* NAME            ZO
)@@G@@              . END DEFAULT PROCESSING OF 'BY'  @G@@@@ DO P(FI(4),5)=0 ,ZP
)@@G@@P*(FI(4),5) EQU P(VI,3) . SET USER'S SIGN, IF ANY     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@ZQ
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@ DO (W(1)=LOOKFOR)=0 , GO G$$L30      . IF NOT LOOKFOR, GO DZR
)@@G@@O VARY@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.       ***** PROCESS 'LOOKFOR' LOOPZS
)@@G@@ (I.E. SEARCH, MASKED SEARCH) ***** @[@@@@.     @H@@@@FI*(5)  EQU    0  ZT
)@@G@@                    . FLAG NO CODE APPEARS AT THE BOTTOM    @[@@@@.     ZU
)@@G@@@A@@@@. LOAD MASK AND REPEAT REGISTERS    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO (FI(3)>VZV
)@@G@@I)**(P(FI(3))>1) , I$ 023,,2,,,UV(3) . LOAD MASK REG (R2)   @F@@@@ DO FIZW
)@@G@@(1)>VI , I$ 023,,1,,,UV(1)      . AND REPEAT COUNT (R1)     @[@@@@.     ZX
)@@G@@@A@@@@. INITIALIZE REG USED AS TABLE INDEX@[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO (P(FI(4)ZY
)@@G@@,5)=OFFSET)**1-IM(4) , G$$EFL 2,1 . OFFSET NEEDS IMMEDIATE BY     @F@@@@ZZ
)@@G@@OFV     EQU    IM(4)*(P(FI(4),5)=OFFSET)*IV(4) . SET OFFSET VALUE @H@@@@AA
)@@G@@FI*(6)  EQU    OFV                    . AND SAVE FOR USE BY CODE GENERATAB
)@@G@@OR    @E@@@@ DO FI(2)=VI , END                    . IF NO 'FROM', QUIT  AC
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO FI(4)=VI , G$$EFL 2,2                 . REQUIRE THAT A 'BY' SPAD
)@@G@@EC APPEARED @H@@@@ DO IM(2)**IM(4) , GO G$$L21          . IF BOTH IMMEDIAE
)@@G@@ATE, GO USE CONSTANT    @D@@@@        I$     027,,P(VI,2),,,UV(2)   . LXAF
)@@G@@ XN,FROM    @F@@@@ DO OFV=0 , I$ 046,,P(VI,2),,,UV(4)   . IF NO OFFSET, AG
)@@G@@LXI XN,BY   @C@@@@ DO OFV=0 , END                       . AND QUIT@G@@@@AH
)@@G@@ DO P(VI,2)>X11 , AH P(VI,2),(+OFV,-OFV) . IF OVERLAPPED, ADD OFFSET IN AI
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO P(VI,2)<A0 , ANX,U P(VI,2),OFV    . IF NONOVERLAPPED, USE BRUTAJ
)@@G@@E FORCE     @B@@@@ DO P(VI,2)<A0 , LXI,U P(VI,2),OFV    .   @D@@@@ DO 1 AK
)@@G@@, END                           . THEN GET OUT  @I@@@@G$$L21* NAME      AL
)@@G@@                    . COME HERE IF FROM AND BY BOTH IMMEDIATE     @G@@@@AM
)@@G@@        I$     027,,P(VI,2),,,(+IV(4),IV(2)-OFV) . LOAD XREG FROM CONS  AN
)@@G@@@]@@@@ DO 1 , END @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.       ****** PROCESS 'VARY' (NORMAAO
)@@G@@L LOOP) SPECIFICATION *****   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$$L30* NAME            AP
)@@G@@              . MARK START OF VARY CHECKING     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ORIGOPAQ
)@@G@@     EQU      +W(1)             . REMEMBER ORIGINAL OPCODE  @[@@@@.     AR
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO FI(1)>VI , GO G$$L34              . IF 'FOR', ASSUME JGD IMMEDAS
)@@G@@IATELY@F@@@@ DO IM(2)**IM(3)**IM(4)=0 , GO G$$L35 . NO FUDGE IF ALL NOT AT
)@@G@@KNOWN @D@@@@ DO (APIV(2)>0)**(IV(3)=0)**(IV(4)=-1)=0 , GO G$$L35  @G@@@@AU
)@@G@@FI*(1)  EQU    FI(2)                  . PUT 'FOR' IN P WHERE 'FROM' WAS AV
)@@G@@@F@@@@FI*(2)  EQU    VI                     . AND INVALIDATE THE 'FROM' AW
)@@G@@@G@@@@IV(1)   EQU    IV(2)+1                . FORVAL IS ONE MORE THAN FRAX
)@@G@@OMVAL @G@@@@IM(1)   EQU    1                      . TURN ON IMMEDIATE 'FAY
)@@G@@OR' FLAG    @D@@@@UV(1)   EQUF   IV(1),,XU              . AND SET U-SPECAZ
)@@G@@@D@@@@G$$L34* NAME                          . SET OPCODE JGD@G@@@@W(1)  BA
)@@G@@  EQU    0+JGD                  . ADD ZERO TO OVERRIDE OPCODE EQU @G@@@@BB
)@@G@@ GO G$$L39                            . THEN GO GLOBALIZE THE OPCODE    BC
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                             OP CAN'T BE JGD, MUST BE TLEM\JMGI  BD
)@@G@@@]@@@@G$$L35* NAME@G@@@@ DO (VARY=ORIGOP)=0 , GO G$$L40       . SKIP IF BE
)@@G@@OPCODE EXPLICITLY GIVEN @G@@@@ DO (FI(2)=VI)++(FI(3)=VI)++(FI(4)=VI) , GBF
)@@G@@$$EFL 2,3 . REQUIRE ALL SPECS @D@@@@W(1)    EQU    0+TLEM               BG
)@@G@@  . ASSUME TLEM   @F@@@@ DO IM(3)**(IV(3)=0) ,W(1) EQU 0+JMGI . UNLESS TBH
)@@G@@O IMMEDIATE ZERO  @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$L39* NAME                        BI
)@@G@@  . END DETERMINATION OF INSTR SPECIFICATION    @F@@@@P*(VI,1) EQU   W(1BJ
)@@G@@)                   . FORCE OPCODE SPEC FIELD   @G@@@@ DO (VARY=ORIGOP)+BK
)@@G@@+(W(1)=ORIGOP)=0 , G$$EFL 2,011 . OPCODE MISMATCH     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@BL
)@@G@@.        SET LOOP SENSE AND FLAG IF CODE AT BOTTOM OF LOOP REQUIRED     BM
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$L40* NAME@F@@@@ DO (W(1)=JGD)=0 , GO G$$L41        BN
)@@G@@  . IF NOT JGD, WE MUST FARBLE@F@@@@FI*(6)  EQU    1                    BO
)@@G@@  . ELSE MARK SENSE KNOWN     @I@@@@FI*(5)  EQU    1                    BP
)@@G@@  . SET FLAG THAT CODE WILL APPEAR AT BOTTOM    @D@@@@ GO G$$L49        BQ
)@@G@@                    . AND WE'RE DONE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. COMPUTE SIGN/SENBR
)@@G@@SE FOR JMGI, TLEM LOOPS, AND CHECK TERMINATION  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$$L41BS
)@@G@@* NAME                          . NOT JGD, DETERMINE SENSE THE HARD WAY BT
)@@G@@@H@@@@USS     EQU    (P(FI(4),5)=UP)-(P(FI(4),5)=DOWN) . SET USER SUPPLIBU
)@@G@@ED SIGN     @D@@@@BYS     EQU    IM(4)*(1-2*(IV(4)<0))  . SIGN FROM 'BY'BV
)@@G@@@G@@@@FTS     EQU    (IM(2)**IM(3))*(1-2*(APIV(2)>APIV(3))) . FROMTO SIGBW
)@@G@@N     @G@@@@ DO FTS*BYS=-1 , G$$EFL 2,5               . N.G. IF SIGNS DOBX
)@@G@@N'T AGREE   @E@@@@MYS     EQU    FTS+BYS                . GET MY OWN SIGBY
)@@G@@N FLAG@F@@@@ DO MYS*USS=-1 , G$$EFL 2,6               . BETTER AGREE WITBZ
)@@G@@H HIS @F@@@@SIGN    EQU    MYS+USS                . GET THE SIGN WE'LL UCA
)@@G@@SE    @F@@@@FI*(6)  EQU    (SIGN=0)=0             . ON IF WE KNOW LOOP SCB
)@@G@@ENSE  @H@@@@P*(VI,3) EQU   SIGN                   . REMEMBER FOR BOTTOM CC
)@@G@@OF LOOP USAGE     @F@@@@FI*(5) EQU (SIGN=0)++(W(1)=TLEM)**(SIGN>0)++(W(1CD
)@@G@@)=JMGI)**(SIGN<0) @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. WATCH OUT FOR AX/ANX: TERMINATION CE
)@@G@@CONDITION MAY NOT PASS THRU ZERO    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO 1-((W(1)=TLEM)CF
)@@G@@**IM(2)**IM(3)**IM(4)) ; UNLESS TLEM AND IMMEDIATE... @E@@@@    , GO G$$CG
)@@G@@L49                       . DON'T DO THIS TEST  @E@@@@VV(1)      EQU    CH
)@@G@@  IV(2)             . SET UP START VAL    @E@@@@VV(2)      EQU      IV(3CI
)@@G@@)+IV(4)       . AND TERMINATION VAL @D@@@@          ON        G$MASM=0  CJ
)@@G@@        . BEGIN ASM CODE@G@@@@  DO G$AMPR                           ; IFCK
)@@G@@ RELOCATION CAN BE DETERMINED @F@@@@    ,VK DO 2                        CL
)@@G@@  ; THEN FOR BOTH FROM AND TO @F@@@@      , DO 1-(&(VV(VK))=-2)         CM
)@@G@@  ; IF VALUE NOT ABSOLUTE     @F@@@@        ,VV(VK) EQU VV(VK)+01000    CN
)@@G@@  . FUDGE FOR ITS RELOCATION  @E@@@@VK DO 2                             CO
)@@G@@  ; FOR BOTH LIMITS...  @G@@@@  ,VV(VK) EQU (1-(VV(VK)=0))*(1-2*(VV(VK)<CP
)@@G@@0)) . SIGN FLAG => -1, 0, +1  @F@@@@ DO VV(1)*VV(2)<1 , G$$EFL 2,4      CQ
)@@G@@  . LOOP PASSES TO/THRU ZERO  @E@@@@          OFF                       CR
)@@G@@  . END OF ASM CODE     @E@@@@          ON        G$MASM=1          . BECS
)@@G@@GIN MASM CODE     @G@@@@  DO G$AMPR                           ; IF RELOCCT
)@@G@@ATION CAN BE DETERMINED @F@@@@    ,VK DO 2                          ; THCU
)@@G@@EN FOR BOTH FROM AND TO @F@@@@      , DO 1-($BA(VV(VK))=0)          ; IFCV
)@@G@@ VALUE NOT ABSOLUTE     @F@@@@        ,VV(VK) EQU VV(VK)+01000      . FUCW
)@@G@@DGE FOR ITS RELOCATION  @E@@@@VK DO 2                               ; FOCX
)@@G@@R BOTH LIMITS...  @H@@@@  ,VV(VK) EQU (1-(VV(VK)=0))*(1-2*($AP(VV(VK))<0CY
)@@G@@)) . SIGN FLAG => -1, 0, +1   @G@@@@ DO $AP(VV(1))*$AP(VV(2))<1 , G$$EFLCZ
)@@G@@ 2,4 . LOOP PASSES TO/THRU ZERO     @E@@@@          OFF                 DA
)@@G@@        . END OF MASM CODE    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$$L49*    NAME         DB
)@@G@@              . END SENSE/PREFERENCE DETERMINATION    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@DC
)@@G@@. SIGN EXTEND NEGATIVE EQUFS TO GET 18-BIT NEGATIVE IMMEDIATES.   @[@@@@DD
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@I DO 3 , DO (IM(I+1)=1)**(IV(I+1)<0) ; . FOR 2,3,4    @G@@@@DE
)@@G@@ ,UV(I+1)   EQUF      *IV(I+1),*0,XU  . IF NEG IMMED, SET HI BITS=1     DF
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. GENERATE REGISTER INITIAL LOAD CODE, IF ANY   @[@@@@DG
)@@G@@.     @I@@@@IMOP      EQU       G$FLAG(K,21)>0    . IMMEDIATE OPTIMIZE FDH
)@@G@@LAG (ZERO ON PASS 1)    @H@@@@ DO FI(1)=VI , GO G$$L51              . IFDI
)@@G@@ 'FOR' NOT GIVEN, GO DO FROM/BY     @G@@@@RR      EQU    027*(P(VI,2)<A4DJ
)@@G@@)+023*(P(VI,2)>R1-1) . OPCODE IF X/R REG  @B@@@@RA      EQU    077**(0+PDK
)@@G@@(VI,2)-(RR=0)*A0) @G@@@@        I$     RR+010*(RR=0),,RA,,,UV(1)-IMOP . DL
)@@G@@LOAD COUNT REGISTER     @G@@@@G$FLAG**(K,21) EQU IM(1)              . SEDM
)@@G@@T IMMEDIATE OPTIMIZATION FLAG @F@@@@ DO 1 , END                         DN
)@@G@@  . END OF REG LOAD GENERATION@[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$$L51* NAME            DO
)@@G@@              . HERE TO LOAD REG USING FROM/BY SPECS  @G@@@@ DO FI(2)=VIDP
)@@G@@ , END                    . NO LOAD IF 'FROM' FIELD ABSENT  @G@@@@ DO FIDQ
)@@G@@(4)=VI , G$$EFL 2,7                 . ERROR IF 'FROM' BUT NO 'BY' @[@@@@DR
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@. IF 'BY' NOT IMMEDIATE, GEN 3 INSTRUCTIONS:    @C@@@@.   LXDS
)@@G@@ XR,FROM  ;  ANX XR,(BY)  ;  LXI XR,(BY)  @E@@@@. IF 'BY' AND 'FROM' AREDT
)@@G@@ IMMED, GEN:  LX XR,(BY,FROM-BY)    @D@@@@. IF 'BY' AND LOOP CNTRL REG IDU
)@@G@@S OVERLAPPED AREG, GEN: @F@@@@.   LX AR,(BY,BY)  ;  AH AR,(FROM)    . IFDV
)@@G@@ 'FROM' NOT IMMEDIATE   @H@@@@. NOTE: IF LOOP REG IS NON-OVERLAPPED REG DW
)@@G@@WE MUST GEN BRUTE FORCE (3 INSTRS)  @G@@@@. WE CANNOT GEN (AX XR,(FROM) DX
)@@G@@) BECAUSE OF OVERFLOW INTO INCREMENT,     @E@@@@. E.G. (1,-1) + (2) = (2DY
)@@G@@,0) , NOT (1,1). SURPRISE, CHIEF!   @[@@@@.     @I@@@@ DO IM(4)=0 , GO GDZ
)@@G@@$$L52               . IF 'BY' NOT IMMEDIATE, CANT USE LITERAL     @H@@@@EA
)@@G@@ DO (W(1)=JMGI)**IM(2)**1-G$FLAG(K,4) ; IF IMMEDIATE JMGI WITHOUT 'WHILEEB
)@@G@@'     @G@@@@ , DO IV(4)<0 , GO G$$L53             . AND DECREASING, GO OEC
)@@G@@PTIMIZE     @G@@@@ DO IM(2) , LX P(VI,2),(+IV(4),0+IV(2)-IV(4)) . LX XR,ED
)@@G@@(STEP,FROM-STEP)  @H@@@@ DO IM(2) , END                       . IF 'FROMEE
)@@G@@' AND 'BY' ARE IMMED, DONE    @G@@@@ DO P(VI,2)<A0 , GO G$$L52          EF
)@@G@@  . IF NOT OVERLAP, BRUTE FORCE     @F@@@@        LX     P(VI,2),(+IV(4)EG
)@@G@@,0-IV(4)) . LX XR,(STEP,FROM-STEP)  @G@@@@        AH     P(VI,2),UV(2)  EH
)@@G@@        . AH FROMVAL (OVERLAP ONLY!!!)    @]@@@@ DO 1 , END @D@@@@G$$L52EI
)@@G@@*   NAME                        . BRUTE FORCE.  @E@@@@        LX     P(VEJ
)@@G@@I,2),UV(2)          . LX WITH FROMVAL     @H@@@@        ANX    P(VI,2),UEK
)@@G@@V(4)          . ANX STEP TO COMPENSATE FOR INCR AT TOP@G@@@@        LXI EL
)@@G@@   P(VI,2),UV(4)          . LXI STEP TO SET UP INCREMENT    @F@@@@ DO 1 EM
)@@G@@, END                           . END OF REG INITIALIZATION @[@@@@.     EN
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$$L53* NAME                          . OPTIMIZE IMMEDIATE JMGI LOEO
)@@G@@OPS   @E@@@@        LX      P(VI,2),(+IV(4),IV(2)) . LOAD (+BY,FROM)    EP
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$FLAG**(K,21) EQU  1                   . TURN ON OPTIMIZATION FLAEQ
)@@G@@G     @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************ER
)@@G@@********************************************    @F@@@@.     *           ES
)@@G@@                                           *    @F@@@@.     *   G$$LGE :ET
)@@G@@ GENERATE CODE FOR <LOOP CONTROL> FIELDS   *    @F@@@@.     *           EU
)@@G@@                                           *    @F@@@@.     ************EV
)@@G@@********************************************    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     EW
)@@G@@@I@@@@Q       PROC   *2                     . PF'S: 'VARY','TO','BY'  JUEX
)@@G@@MPTARG,TOP/BOT    @#@@@@G$$LGE*  NAME     @G@@@@VI      EQU    Q(1,1)   EY
)@@G@@              . INDEX IN P OF VARY SPEC FIELD   @E@@@@TI      EQU    Q(1EZ
)@@G@@,2)                 . INDEX OF 'TO' FIELD @E@@@@BI      EQU    Q(1,3)   FA
)@@G@@              . INDEX OF 'BY' FIELD @E@@@@F       EQU    P(VI,1)        FB
)@@G@@        . FUNCTION REQUESTED  @H@@@@ATTOP     EQU       Q(2,2)          FC
)@@G@@  . ON IF BEING CALLED AT TOP OF LOOP     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO F=LOOKFOFD
)@@G@@R , GO G$$L80             . SPECIAL HANDLING FOR SEARCHING  @F@@@@ DO F=FE
)@@G@@JGD , G$$FJA 070,P(VI,2),,,Q(2,1) . JUMP TO KEEP LOOPING    @G@@@@ DO F=FF
)@@G@@JGD , END                       . FOR JGD, THAT'S ALL THERE IS    @[@@@@FG
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@. TLEM/JMGI ---   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@JMF     EQU    F=JMGI   FH
)@@G@@              . TRUE IF FUNC IS JMGI@G@@@@OLAP    EQU    P(VI,2)>X11    FI
)@@G@@        . ON IF LOOP CTL REG IS OVERLAPPED@G@@@@SENU    EQU    (P(VI,3)=FJ
)@@G@@0)**(ATTOP=0) . ON AT BOTTOM AND UNKNOWN SENSE  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO SEFK
)@@G@@NU**1-OLAP , I$ 060+JMF,,,,,P(VI,2) . TP(TLEM) TN(JMGI) ON REG    @H@@@@FL
)@@G@@ DO SENU , I$ 074,04-OLAP*(JMF+1),0+OLAP*(P(VI,2)-A0),,,G$LABL(K,2) . J FM
)@@G@@JN JP @[@@@@.     @C@@@@ DO JMF , GO G$$L70 . JMGI LOOPS ARE SIMPLE     FN
)@@G@@@E@@@@PTI2      EQU       P(TI,2)           . 'TO' FIELD UFIELD   @E@@@@FO
)@@G@@PBI2      EQU       P(BI,2)           . 'BY' FIELD UFIELD   @F@@@@ DO G$FP
)@@G@@MASM=1 ,PTI2 EQU $AP(PTI2)      . JUST THE ABSOLUTE PART    @F@@@@ DO G$FQ
)@@G@@MASM=1 ,PBI2 EQU $AP(PBI2)      . JUST THE ABSOLUTE PART    @G@@@@TUHI  FR
)@@G@@  EQU    3*(PTI2<0)+2*P(TI,*3)+P(TI,*2) . T-FLAG IF ALL ARE ON    @D@@@@FS
)@@G@@TU      EQU    + (I$ 0,P(TI,4),,P(TI,3),TUHI,P(TI,2)) @G@@@@BUHI    EQU FT
)@@G@@   3*(PBI2<0)+2*P(BI,*3)+P(BI,*2) . T-FLAG IF ALL ARE ON    @D@@@@BU    FU
)@@G@@  EQU    + (I$ 0,P(BI,4),,P(BI,3),BUHI,P(BI,2)) @F@@@@ DO ATTOP , I$ 074FV
)@@G@@,06,0,P(VI,2),2,0   . AT TOP AX INCR WITH A NOP @E@@@@          I$      FW
)@@G@@  047,,P(VI,2),,,TU . TLEM ON 'TO' FIELD  @B@@@@        I$     074,04,,,FX
)@@G@@,Q(2,1) . JUMP    @G@@@@ DO ATTOP , I$ 025,,P(VI,2),,,BU      . UNDO FUDFY
)@@G@@GE WITH ANX OF INCR     @E@@@@ DO 1 , END                           . THFZ
)@@G@@AT'S ALL FOR TLEM @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. HANDLE JMGI LOOPS (WHICH TERMINATEGA
)@@G@@ AT ZERO)   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$L70*   NAME    @F@@@@ DO ATTOP , I$ 051GB
)@@G@@,017,0,P(VI,2),,0 . TNZ REG (LAST TIME CHECK)   @B@@@@ DO ATTOP , I$ 074GC
)@@G@@,04,,,,Q(2,1)       .   @C@@@@        I$     074,012,P(VI,2),,,Q(2,1) . GD
)@@G@@JMGI  @#@@@@ DO 1 , END .     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. HANDLE SEARCH/MASKED SGE
)@@G@@EARCH. NOTE: SINCE THIS IS ALWAYS CALLED  @E@@@@. AT THE PHYSICAL TOP OFGF
)@@G@@ THE LOOP BY REPEAT, THE VALUES OF  @B@@@@. THE ARRAY FI(N) ARE ALWAYS AGG
)@@G@@VAILABLE    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$L80* NAME@H@@@@IC      EQU    VI-1     GH
)@@G@@              . INDEX IN P OF CONDITION TEST FIELD    @H@@@@KWD     EQU GI
)@@G@@   P(IC,2)                . GET KEYWORD FROM CONDITION SPEC FIELD @F@@@@GJ
)@@G@@MSF     EQU    FI(3)>VI               . ON IF SEARCH IS MASKED    @G@@@@GK
)@@G@@FUN     EQU    G$FJ(1,KWD,1)+010*(1-MSF)-052*MSF . MODIFY TO A SEARCH   GL
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO   MSF , I$ 071,FUN,P(IC,1)-A0,P(VI,2),2+P(IC,*3),P(IC,3)+FI(6)GM
)@@G@@ . MS-@H@@@@ DO 1-MSF , I$ FUN,P(IC,5),P(IC,1)-A0,P(VI,2),2+P(IC,*3),P(IGN
)@@G@@C,3)+FI(6) . S-   @E@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,Q(2,1)  . AT NOFIND,  JGO
)@@G@@UMP TO ATEND@[@@@@.     @]@@@@        END @ @@@@/. *** MISCELLANEOUS UTIGP
)@@G@@LITIES@[@@@@.     @H@@@@. PROCS TO CONSERVE TABLE SPACE BY SAVING ARGUMEGQ
)@@G@@NTS IN RE-USABLE ARRAY SPACE  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          PROC      *0  GR
)@@G@@@I@@@@G$$SVA* NAME                          . SAVE ARRAY P IN STANDARD AGS
)@@G@@RGUMENT ARRAY     @F@@@@K         EQU       G$CTR(3)+1        . BUMP ARGGT
)@@G@@ PUSHDOWN LEVEL   @D@@@@G$CTR**(3) EQU K                      . SAVE THEGU
)@@G@@ LEVEL@^@@@@G$ARGS**(K) EQU +P-1    @A@@@@N DO P-1 ,G$ARGS**(K,N) EQU +0GV
)@@G@@+P(N) @C@@@@N DO P-1 ,M DO P(N) ,G$ARGS**(K,N,M) EQU +P(N,M)@F@@@@N DO PGW
)@@G@@-1 ,M DO P(N) , DO P(N,*M) ,G$ARGS**(K,N,M) EQU *0+P(N,M) . @#@@@@      GX
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. DECODE A U-FIELD INTO ITS COGY
)@@G@@NSTITUENT ELEMENTS. THIS PROC USES  @G@@@@. SUBTRACTION TO AVOID SPURIOUGZ
)@@G@@S R-FLAGS WHICH MIGHT OTHERWISE ARISE.    @F@@@@. IN ADDITION, IT DOES NHA
)@@G@@OT ALTER THE FORM OF THE ORIGINAL U-FIELD,@F@@@@. SINCE IT IS UNKNOWN WHHB
)@@G@@ETHER THE U FIELD ALREADY HAS FORM OR NOT.@[@@@@.     @]@@@@        DEF HC
)@@G@@@^@@@@G$JBIT(1) EQU 1*/29     @^@@@@G$JBIT(2) EQU 1*/28     @^@@@@G$JBITHD
)@@G@@(3) EQU 1*/27     @^@@@@G$JBIT(4) EQU 1*/26     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$XBITHE
)@@G@@(1) EQU 1*/21     @^@@@@G$XBIT(2) EQU 1*/20     @^@@@@G$XBIT(3) EQU 1*/1HF
)@@G@@9     @^@@@@G$XBIT(4) EQU 1*/18     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$HIBI(1) EQU 1*/1HG
)@@G@@7     @^@@@@G$HIBI(2) EQU 1*/16     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@G$JBITS EQU +(I$ 0HH
)@@G@@,017,,,,0)       . MASK FOR J-DESEG @D@@@@G$XBITS EQU +(I$ 0,,,017,,0)  HI
)@@G@@     . MASK FOR X-DESEG @D@@@@G$HBITS EQU +(I$ 0,,,,2,0)         . MASK HJ
)@@G@@FOR H-DESEG @[@@@@.     @B@@@@Q       PROC        *2                .   HK
)@@G@@@B@@@@G$$DCU* NAME                          .   @E@@@@I       EQU     Q(HL
)@@G@@1,1)                . GET FIELD TO SCAN   @G@@@@J       EQU     Q(1,2)  HM
)@@G@@              . AND STARTING SUBFIELD (U-SPEC)  @G@@@@N       EQU     Q(HN
)@@G@@0,1)                . LEVEL OF P (NO OF ASTERISKS)    @C@@@@. OBTAIN MANHO
)@@G@@IPULATABLE UFIELD FROM MASM OR ASM  @D@@@@. NOTE: IF IV(1)<0, THEN IT CAHP
)@@G@@N'T HAVE BEEN EQUF'D    @G@@@@ DO G$MASM , $GO G$$DCU1              . IFHQ
)@@G@@ @MASM, SKIP ASM FUMBLING     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. BEGIN ASM PROCESSING  HR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@JAY(1)  EQU     0   . ASSUME NO EQUF'D J-SPEC   @C@@@@HS
)@@G@@XRG(1)  EQU     0   . ASSUME NO EQUF'D X-SPEC   @C@@@@HIB(1)  EQU     0 HT
)@@G@@  . ASSUME NO EQUF'D HISPEC   @E@@@@IV(1)   EQU     +P(I,J)             HU
)@@G@@  . GET INITIAL VALUE   @F@@@@ DO IV(1)>0377777777                  ; IFHV
)@@G@@ VALUE HAS EQUF'D J     @D@@@@  ,K DO 4                             ; FOHW
)@@G@@R ALL J-BITS@E@@@@    , DO (IV(1)-JAY(1))>(G$JBIT(K)-1) ; IF CURRENT BITHX
)@@G@@ ON   @E@@@@       ,JAY(1) EQU JAY(1)++G$JBIT(K)  . FOLD INTO RESULT    HY
)@@G@@@G@@@@IV(1)   EQU     IV(1)-JAY(1)          . STRIP EQUF'D J FROM OPERANHZ
)@@G@@D     @E@@@@JAY(1)  EQU     P(I,J+2)++JAY(1)*/-26 . GET COMPLETE J-SPEC IA
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO IV(1)>0777777                     ; IF VALUE HAS EQUF'D X     IB
)@@G@@@D@@@@  ,K DO 4                             ; FOR ALL X-BITS@E@@@@    , IC
)@@G@@DO (IV(1)-XRG(1))>(G$XBIT(K)-1) ; IF CURRENT BIT ON   @E@@@@       ,XRG(ID
)@@G@@1) EQU XRG(1)++G$XBIT(K)  . FOLD INTO RESULT    @G@@@@IV(1)   EQU     IVIE
)@@G@@(1)-XRG(1)          . STRIP EQUF'D X FROM OPERAND     @E@@@@XRG(1)  EQU IF
)@@G@@    P(I,J+1)++XRG(1)*/-18 . GET COMPLETE X-SPEC @F@@@@U16     EQU     (JIG
)@@G@@AY(1)<016)++(XRG(1)>0)++P(I,*J)++P(I,*J+1) .    @F@@@@ DO IV(1)>0177777 IH
)@@G@@                    ; IF VALUE HAS EQUF'D H OR I@G@@@@  ,K DO 2*U16     II
)@@G@@                    ; FOR BOTH BITS (OF I$ FORM INSTR)@E@@@@    , DO (IVIJ
)@@G@@(1)-HIB(1))>(G$HIBI(K)-1) ; IF CURRENT BIT ON   @E@@@@       ,HIB(1) EQUIK
)@@G@@ HIB(1)++G$HIBI(K)  . FOLD INTO RESULT    @E@@@@IV(1)   EQU     IV(1)-HIIL
)@@G@@B(1)          . STRIP H AND I BITS  @E@@@@HIB(1)  EQU     HIB(1)*/-16   IM
)@@G@@        . ALIGN H AND I BITS  @E@@@@HBIT    EQU     P(I,*J+1)++(HIB(1)*/IN
)@@G@@-1) . SET TRUE H-BIT    @D@@@@IBIT    EQU     P(I,*J)++(HIB(1)**1) . SETIO
)@@G@@ TRUE I-BIT @^@@@@. GLOBALIZE RESULTS     @F@@@@ DO N=2 , GO G$$DC1     IP
)@@G@@              . CHECK FOR 2 *'S NEEDED    @G@@@@P**(I)   EQU     J+2    IQ
)@@G@@               . FORCE NUMBER OF SPECFIELDS     @A@@@@  DO 1-IBIT ,P**(IIR
)@@G@@,J) EQU IV(1)     @A@@@@  DO  IBIT  ,P**(I,J) EQU *IV(1)    @A@@@@  DO 1IS
)@@G@@-HBIT ,P**(I,J+1) EQU XRG(1)  @A@@@@  DO  HBIT  ,P**(I,J+1) EQU *XRG(1) IT
)@@G@@@^@@@@P**(I,J+2) EQU   JAY(1) @]@@@@ DO 1 , END @F@@@@G$$DC1* NAME      IU
)@@G@@                     . HERE IF P IS 2 LEVELS OUT@F@@@@P***(I)  EQU     JIV
)@@G@@+2                  . FORCE NUMBER OF SPECFIELDS@A@@@@  DO 1-IBIT ,P***(IW
)@@G@@I,J) EQU IV(1)    @A@@@@  DO  IBIT  ,P***(I,J) EQU *IV(1)   @A@@@@  DO 1IX
)@@G@@-HBIT ,P***(I,J+1) EQU XRG(1) @A@@@@  DO  HBIT  ,P***(I,J+1) EQU *XRG(1)IY
)@@G@@@^@@@@P***(I,J+2) EQU   JAY(1)@]@@@@ DO 1 , END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     IZ
)@@G@@@^@@@@. BEGIN MASM PROCESSING @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$$DCU1* $NAME          JA
)@@G@@              . BEGIN @MASM CODE    @G@@@@IV      EQU     $AP(P(I,J))   JB
)@@G@@        . GET INITIAL VALUE W/O RELOCATION@E@@@@JAY2    EQU     (IV>0)*(JC
)@@G@@IV**G$JBITS)  . STRIP OFF J-DESEG   @E@@@@JAY1    EQU     P(I,J+2)++JAY2JD
)@@G@@*/-26   . GET COMPLETE J-SPEC @E@@@@XRG2    EQU     (IV>0)*(IV**G$XBITS)JE
)@@G@@  . STRIP OFF X-DESEG   @E@@@@XRG1    EQU     P(I,J+1)++XRG2*/-18   . GEJF
)@@G@@T COMPLETE X-SPEC @E@@@@U16     EQU     (JAY1<016)++(XRG1>0)++P(I,*J)++PJG
)@@G@@(I,*J+1) .  @D@@@@HIB1    EQU     U16*(IV**G$HBITS)  . STRIP OFF HIDESEGJH
)@@G@@@E@@@@HBIT    EQU     P(I,*J+1)++(HIB1*/-17) . SET TRUE H-BIT     @E@@@@JI
)@@G@@IBIT    EQU     P(I,*J)++((HIB1*/-16)**1) . SET TRUE I-BIT  @^@@@@. GLOBJJ
)@@G@@ALIZE RESULTS     @F@@@@          $LEVEL    0,N+1,0           . ADD N+1 JK
)@@G@@STARS TO LABELS   @D@@@@P(I,J)   EQU   [IBIT->'*'!'']P(I,J)-JAY2-XRG2-HIJL
)@@G@@B1  . @A@@@@P(I,J+1) EQU   [HBIT->'*'!'']XRG1 . @^@@@@P(I,J+2) EQU   JAYJM
)@@G@@1     @E@@@@          $LEVEL    0,1,0             . RESET PROPER LEVEL  JN
)@@G@@@D@@@@          END                         . END OF G$$DCU @[@@@@.     JO
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. ----- PATCH UP RETURN ADDR (EXIT INSTR) OF A REMOTE JP
)@@G@@BLOCK @B@@@@.       INVOKED BY 'CALL' AND REMOTE CASES@D@@@@.       SPECJQ
)@@G@@S ARE: <BLOCKID>,<BLOK EXIT TARGET ADDR>  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@P          PJR
)@@G@@ROC     *1,0              . DO NOTHING ON PASS 1@G@@@@G$$PRA*    NAME   JS
)@@G@@                    . HERE IF P(1,1) IS ADDR OF BLOK  @H@@@@ DO G$MASM=0JT
)@@G@@ ,P(1,1)   EQU      G$BSEQ(P(1,1)) . USE ITS SERIAL NUMBER INSTEAD@I@@@@JU
)@@G@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,P(1,1)   EQU    G$BSEQ($AP(P(1,1))) . USE ITS SERIAL NUMBEJV
)@@G@@R INSTEA    @#@@@@G$$PRB*    NAME   @F@@@@K          EQU      P(1,1)    JW
)@@G@@        . SERIAL NO OF TARGET BLOCK @G@@@@ISRB       EQU      (K>0)**(G$JX
)@@G@@FLAG(K,3)=REMOTESUB) . ON IF BLK IS REMOTE@G@@@@ DO ISRB=0 , G$$GFL 2,6 JY
)@@G@@              . ERROR IF BLOK NOT REALLY RMT    @F@@@@ DO ISRB=0 , END  JZ
)@@G@@                    . DON'T CLOBBER SPURIOUSLY  @G@@@@G$LABL**(K,4) EQU KA
)@@G@@  P(1,2)            . ESTABLISH JUMPTARG FOR BLK EXIT @G@@@@ DO G$LABL(KKB
)@@G@@,1)>$                     ; IF BLOCK APPEARS AFTER THIS...  @F@@@@  , ENKC
)@@G@@D                               . THEN NO NEED TO PATCH IT  @G@@@@. WHENKD
)@@G@@ BLOCK PRECEDED US, THE RETURN ADDR IT NEEDED WAS NOT DEFINED     @F@@@@KE
)@@G@@. AT THE TIME THE ENDBEG WAS ASSEMBLED, SO WE MUST PATCH IT UP.   @^@@@@KF
)@@G@@HERE       EQU      $   @F@@@@           RES      G$LABL(K,5)-$     . GOKG
)@@G@@ BACK TO THE ENDBEG     @F@@@@           J        P(1,2)            . FIKH
)@@G@@X UP ITS EXIT INSTR     @E@@@@           RES      HERE-$            . THKI
)@@G@@EN RESTORE IC     @#@@@@           END    @D@@@@/. THINGS TO ADD IN THE KJ
)@@G@@FUTURE-- (NOTES TO MYSELF)-   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.      ENDBEKK
)@@G@@G    SPAWNING AT,<LABEL> WITH IOXI$ (AND MAKE IOXI N.G.)    @G@@@@.     KL
)@@G@@              SINCE IOXI IS ANOTHER WAY OF TERMINATING AN ACTIVITY@[@@@@KM
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@.      SPAWN AT,<LABEL> NAME,<NAME-STASH> @G@@@@.           KN
)@@G@@           FORK$ TO AN ACTIVITY AND ACQUIRE A NAME FOR IT   @G@@@@.     KO
)@@G@@                 NOTE THAT NAME IS OWNED BY SPAWNNER, NOT SPAWNEE @[@@@@KP
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.      DEFINITIONS OF 'CRITICAL' BLOCKS, BOUNDED BY TS, CTS KQ
)@@G@@ON DATA     @E@@@@.      AND/OR IMPLEMENTATION OF P/V OR TS QUEUEING USAKR
)@@G@@GE    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. FINISH FALLTHRU OPTIMIZATION FOR JKS
)@@G@@MGI/TLEM LOOPS    @C@@@@. FLAG AND SURPRESS CODE FOR 0 EXECUTION LOOPS  KT
)@@G@@@C@@@@. FLAG AND SURPRESS CODE FOR IMPOSSIBLE TESTS   @F@@@@. DO DOUBLE KU
)@@G@@LINEITEM IF-ELSE: TEST/INST1/NOTEST/INST2, IF AND     @E@@@@.   ONLY IF KV
)@@G@@NO SIDE EFFECTS AND INST1 DOES NOT ALTER CONTEXT@F@@@@. CASENTRY CALLINGKW
)@@G@@: NORMAL 1,X11 AND 1 INSTR 0,X11 SHOULD SKIP    @D@@@@. DO SPARSE CASES KX
)@@G@@WITH TESTS INSTEAD OF JUMPTABLES    @B@@@@. OPTIMIZE JUMPS ACROSS BLOCK KY
)@@G@@BOUNDARIES  @F@@@@          PROC                        . THIS IS A CHARKZ
)@@G@@LIE MCCARTHY@E@@@@          END                         . AND A MORTIMERLA
)@@G@@ SNERD@D@@@@.         END                         . *****MASM*****___OTELB

)@@G@@[@]DP,@@@K@BK@D@@@[@AC?^D@@D^RG$$D10#@#@]9@^W@]9K @@@@[@^D@S#@@@@@SPANS LN

)@@G@@G$$L39#@#@#D@^"@#LK @@@@[@^C1X#@@@@@DNEQ  K @@@G[@^DD/#@@C?WOFLO  K @@@[MD
)@@G@@C)E@@@[@]DD/@@@K@BK@D@@@[@AD@7D@@C1XG$$C29#@#@]R@#U@]WK @@@@C)E@@@[@]D@7ME

)@@G@@[@AC(7D@@D@7G$$L01#@#@#D@#'@#EK @@@@[@ C29#)@@@@CONTINGENCY MH@__*[@^C7%MG
)@@G@@#@@C(7INBUSYK @@@[C)E@@@[@]C7%@@@K@BK@D@@@[@AC2UD@@C29G$$TFL#@#@[6@#$@[6MH
